| **Sanskrit** | **English Translation** |
|-------------|-------------------------|
| `Line 1:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2: ||१ महाभारते आदिपर्वम् ||` | "The First Book [Ādi Parva] of the Mahābhārata" |
| `Line 3:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5: अनुक्रमणीपर्व` | "The Chapter of Contents [Index section]" |
| `Line 6: १` | "1" |
| `Line 7:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 8:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 9: नारायणं नमस्कृत्य नरं चैव नरोत्तमम् |` | "Having bowed to Nārāyaṇa [Supreme deity] and also to Nara [divine sage], the best among men," |
| `Line 10: देवीं सरस्वतीं चैव ततो जयमुदीरयेत् ||०||` | "And to the goddess Sarasvatī [learning deity], then one should recite the Jaya [Victory epic]." |
| `Line 11:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 12: लोमहर्षणपुत्र उग्रश्रवाः सूतः पौराणिको नैमिषारण्ये शौनकस्य कुलपतेर्द्वादशवार्षिके सत्रे | ००१ |` | "Ugraśravās [fierce-eared], the son of Lomaharṣaṇa, a sūta [bard-chronicler], a reciter of ancient tales, came to the twelve-year sacrificial session of Śaunaka, the family head, in the Naimiṣa forest." |
| `Line 13:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 14: समासीनानभ्यगच्छद्ब्रह्मर्षीन्संशितव्रतान् |` | "He approached the Brahmarṣis [Brahmin sages] of strict vows who were seated together," |
| `Line 15: विनयावनतो भूत्वा कदाचित्सूतनन्दनः ||२||` | "The son of the sūta [bard], having bowed with humility, at one time." |
| `Line 16:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 17: तमाश्रममनुप्राप्तं नैमिषारण्यवासिनः |` | "The dwellers of the Naimiṣa forest [sacred grove], upon his arrival at the hermitage," |
| `Line 18: चित्राः श्रोतुं कथास्तत्र परिवव्रुस्तपस्विनः ||३||` | "The ascetics surrounded him there to hear wonderful stories." |
| `Line 19:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 20: अभिवाद्य मुनींस्तांस्तु सर्वानेव कृताञ्जलिः |` | "Having saluted all those sages with folded hands," |
| `Line 21: अपृच्छत्स तपोवृद्धिं सद्भिश्चैवाभिनन्दितः ||४||` | "He inquired about the progress of their austerities, and was welcomed by the virtuous ones." |
| `Line 22:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 23: अथ तेषूपविष्टेषु सर्वेष्वेव तपस्विषु |` | "Then, when all those ascetics were seated," |
| `Line 24: निर्दिष्टमासनं भेजे विनयाल्लोमहर्षणिः ||५||` | "The son of Lomaharṣaṇa [sūta] humbly took the seat assigned to him." |
| `Line 25:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 26: सुखासीनं ततस्तं तु विश्रान्तमुपलक्ष्य च |` | "Then, observing him seated comfortably and rested," |
| `Line 27: अथापृच्छदृषिस्तत्र कश्चित्प्रस्तावयन्कथाः ||६||` | "A certain sage there asked him, initiating conversations. ||6||" |
| `Line 28: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 29: कुत आगम्यते सौते क्व चायं विहृतस्त्वया |` | "From where do you come, O Sūta [bard/narrator], and where have you spent your time," |
| `Line 30: कालः कमलपत्राक्ष शंसैतत्पृच्छतो मम ||७||` | "O lotus-eyed one, tell this to me who asks. ||7||" |
| `Line 31: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 32: सूत उवाच||` | "Sūta [bard/narrator] said:" |
| `Line 33: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 34: जनमेजयस्य राजर्षेः सर्पसत्रे महात्मनः |` | "At the snake sacrifice of Janamejaya, the royal sage [rājarṣi] of great soul," |
| `Line 35: समीपे पार्थिवेन्द्रस्य सम्यक्पारिक्षितस्य च ||८||` | "In the presence of that lord of the earth, the worthy son of Parikshit. ||8||" |
| `Line 36: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 37: कृष्णद्वैपायनप्रोक्ताः सुपुण्या विविधाः कथाः |` | "Various most sacred stories narrated by Krishna Dvaipāyana [Vyāsa]," |
| `Line 38: कथिताश्चापि विधिवद्या वैशम्पायनेन वै ||९||` | "Were properly recited by Vaiśampāyana indeed. ||9||" |
| `Line 39: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 40: श्रुत्वाहं ता विचित्रार्था महाभारतसंश्रिताः |` | "Having heard those stories of wonderful meanings contained in the Mahābhārata," |
| `Line 41: बहूनि सम्परिक्रम्य तीर्थान्यायतनानि च ||१०||` | "And having visited many holy places [tīrthas] and temples, ||10||" |
| `Line 42: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 43: समन्तपञ्चकं नाम पुण्यं द्विजनिषेवितम् |` | "I went to that sacred place called Samantapañcaka [five lakes region], frequented by the twice-born [Brahmins]," |
| `Line 44: गतवानस्मि तं देशं युद्धं यत्राभवत्पुरा ||११||` | "That region where the battle took place long ago, ||11||" |
| `Line 45: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 46: पाण्डवानां कुरूणां च सर्वेषां च महीक्षिताम् ||११||` | "Between the Pāṇḍavas, the Kurus, and all the rulers of the earth. ||11||" |
| `Line 47: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 48: दिदृक्षुरागतस्तस्मात्समीपं भवतामिह |` | "Desiring to see you, I have come here from that place to your presence," |
| `Line 49: आयुष्मन्तः सर्व एव ब्रह्मभूता हि मे मताः ||१२||` | "Long-lived ones, all of you are indeed regarded by me as embodiments of Brahman [divine knowledge]. ||12||" |
| `Line 50: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 51: अस्मिन्यज्ञे महाभागाः सूर्यपावकवर्चसः |` | "In this sacrifice, the fortunate ones, with radiance like the sun and fire," |
| `Line 52: कृताभिषेकाः शुचयः कृतजप्या हुताग्नयः ||१३||` | "Having performed ablutions, pure, having completed prayers, having offered oblations to fire. ||13||" |
| `Line 53: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 54: भवन्त आसते स्वस्था ब्रवीमि किमहं द्विजाः ||१३||` | "You all are seated comfortably; what shall I speak, O twice-born [Brahmins]? ||13||" |
| `Line 55: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 56: पुराणसंश्रिताः पुण्याः कथा वा धर्मसंश्रिताः |` | "Stories based on the Puranas [ancient texts], virtuous tales based on dharma [righteousness]," |
| `Line 57: इतिवृत्तं नरेन्द्राणामृषीणां च महात्मनाम् ||१४||` | "Or the histories of kings and great-souled sages? ||14||" |
| `Line 58: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 59: ऋषय ऊचुः||` | "The sages said:" |
| `Line 60: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 61: द्वैपायनेन यत्प्रोक्तं पुराणं परमर्षिणा |` | "That which was narrated by Dvaipayana [Vyasa], the great sage," |
| `Line 62: सुरैर्ब्रह्मर्षिभिश्चैव श्रुत्वा यदभिपूजितम् ||१५||` | "Which, having heard, was revered by gods and brahmarshis [sage-seers]. ||15||" |
| `Line 63: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 64: तस्याख्यानवरिष्ठस्य विचित्रपदपर्वणः |` | "Of that most excellent narrative with its wonderful chapters and sections," |
| `Line 65: सूक्ष्मार्थन्याययुक्तस्य वेदार्थैर्भूषितस्य च ||१६||` | "Endowed with subtle meanings and logic, adorned with Vedic meanings. ||16||" |
| `Line 66: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 67: भारतस्येतिहासस्य पुण्यां ग्रन्थार्थसंयुताम् |` | "Of the Bharata [Mahabharata], the sacred history, complete with textual meaning," |
| `Line 68: संस्कारोपगतां ब्राह्मीं नानाशास्त्रोपबृंहिताम् ||१७||` | "Refined, divine, enriched with various scriptures. ||17||" |
| `Line 69: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 70: जनमेजयस्य यां राज्ञो वैशम्पायन उक्तवान् |` | "Which Vaishampayana narrated to King Janamejaya," |
| `Line 71: यथावत्स ऋषिस्तुष्ट्या सत्रे द्वैपायनाज्ञया ||१८||` | "That sage, properly, with joy, during the sacrifice, by the command of Dvaipayana [Vyasa]. ||18||" |
| `Line 72: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 73: वेदैश्चतुर्भिः समितां व्यासस्याद्भुतकर्मणः |` | "Harmonized with the four Vedas, of Vyasa of wonderful deeds," |
| `Line 74: संहितां श्रोतुमिच्छामो धर्म्यां पापभयापहाम् ||१९||` | "We wish to hear that compilation, righteous and removing the fear of sin. ||19||" |
| `Line 75: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 76: सूत उवाच||` | "Sūta [bard-narrator] said:" |
| `Line 77: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 78: आद्यं पुरुषमीशानं पुरुहूतं पुरुष्टुतम् |` | "The primeval Person [Purusha], the Lord, the much-invoked, the much-praised," |
| `Line 79: ऋतमेकाक्षरं ब्रह्म व्यक्ताव्यक्तं सनातनम् ||२०||` | "The Truth, the one-syllabled Brahman [Absolute], the manifest and unmanifest, the eternal. ||20||" |
| `Line 80: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 81: असच्च सच्चैव च यद्विश्वं सदसतः परम् |` | "He who is both non-existence and existence, the universe, beyond both being and non-being," |
| `Line 82: परावराणां स्रष्टारं पुराणं परमव्ययम् ||२१||` | "The creator of the high and low, the ancient, the supreme and imperishable. ||21||" |
| `Line 83: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 84: मङ्गल्यं मङ्गलं विष्णुं वरेण्यमनघं शुचिम् |` | "The auspicious, the blessed Vishnu [all-pervading deity], the most excellent, the sinless, the pure," |
| `Line 85: नमस्कृत्य हृषीकेशं चराचरगुरुं हरिम् ||२२||` | "Having bowed to Hrishikesha [lord of senses], the teacher of the moving and unmoving, Hari [remover of obstacles]. ||22||" |
| `Line 86: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 87: महर्षेः पूजितस्येह सर्वलोके महात्मनः |` | "Of the great sage who is worshipped in this world, the great-souled one," |
| `Line 88: प्रवक्ष्यामि मतं कृत्स्नं व्यासस्यामिततेजसः ||२३||` | "I shall declare the complete doctrine of Vyāsa [compiler of Vedas] of immeasurable splendor. ||23||" |
| `Line 89: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 90: आचख्युः कवयः केचित्सम्प्रत्याचक्षते परे |` | "Some poets have narrated it, others are narrating it now," |
| `Line 91: आख्यास्यन्ति तथैवान्ये इतिहासमिमं भुवि ||२४||` | "And others will likewise narrate this history [itihāsa] on earth. ||24||" |
| `Line 92: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 93: इदं तु त्रिषु लोकेषु महज्ज्ञानं प्रतिष्ठितम् |` | "This great knowledge is established in the three worlds [triloka]," |
| `Line 94: विस्तरैश्च समासैश्च धार्यते यद्द्विजातिभिः ||२५||` | "Which is preserved by the twice-born [Brahmins] in detailed and condensed forms. ||25||" |
| `Line 95: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 96: अलङ्कृतं शुभैः शब्दैः समयैर्दिव्यमानुषैः |` | "Adorned with auspicious words, with divine and human conventions," |
| `Line 97: छन्दोवृत्तैश्च विविधैरन्वितं विदुषां प्रियम् ||२६||` | "Composed in various meters [chandas], dear to the learned. ||26||" |
| `Line 98: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 99: निष्प्रभेऽस्मिन्निरालोके सर्वतस्तमसावृते |` | "When this (universe) was without light, without illumination, covered with darkness on all sides," |
| `Line 100: बृहदण्डमभूदेकं प्रजानां बीजमक्षयम् ||२७||` | "There was one great cosmic egg [Brahmanda], the imperishable seed of all creatures. ||27||" |
| `Line 101: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 102: युगस्यादौ निमित्तं तन्महद्दिव्यं प्रचक्षते |` | "At the beginning of a yuga [cosmic age], they declare that great divine cause," |
| `Line 103: यस्मिंस्तच्छ्रूयते सत्यं ज्योतिर्ब्रह्म सनातनम् ||२८||` | "In which is heard that truth, the luminous eternal Brahman [absolute reality]. ||28||" |
| `Line 104: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 105: अद्भुतं चाप्यचिन्त्यं च सर्वत्र समतां गतम् |` | "Wondrous and inconceivable, having reached equality everywhere," |
| `Line 106: अव्यक्तं कारणं सूक्ष्मं यत्तत्सदसदात्मकम् ||२९||` | "The unmanifest, subtle cause, which is the essence of both being and non-being. ||29||" |
| `Line 107: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 108: यस्मात्पितामहो जज्ञे प्रभुरेकः प्रजापतिः |` | "From which was born the grandfather [Brahma], the one lord, Prajapati [lord of creatures]," |
| `Line 109: ब्रह्मा सुरगुरुः स्थाणुर्मनुः कः परमेष्ठ्यथ ||३०||` | "Brahma, the preceptor of gods, Sthanu [Shiva], Manu, Ka [Prajapati], and Paramesthi [supreme one]. ||30||" |
| `Line 110: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 111: प्राचेतसस्तथा दक्षो दक्षपुत्राश्च सप्त ये |` | "Then Prachetasa Daksha and his seven sons," |
| `Line 112: ततः प्रजानां पतयः प्राभवन्नेकविंशतिः ||३१||` | "From them arose twenty-one lords of creatures [Prajapatis]. ||31||" |
| `Line 113: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 114: पुरुषश्चाप्रमेयात्मा यं सर्वमृषयो विदुः |` | "And the Purusha [cosmic being] of immeasurable nature, whom all sages know," |
| `Line 115: विश्वेदेवास्तथादित्या वसवोऽथाश्विनावपि ||३२||` | "The Vishvedevas [universal gods], the Adityas [solar deities], the Vasus [elemental gods], and also the two Ashvins [divine physicians]. ||32||" |
| `Line 116: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 117: यक्षाः साध्याः पिशाचाश्च गुह्यकाः पितरस्तथा |` | "The Yakshas [wealth spirits], Sadhyas [celestial beings], Pisachas [fiends], Guhyakas [hidden beings], and also the Pitris [ancestors]," |
| `Line 118: ततः प्रसूता विद्वांसः शिष्टा ब्रह्मर्षयोऽमलाः ||३३||` | "Then were born the learned ones, the distinguished, pure Brahmarshis [sage-seers]. ||33||" |
| `Line 119: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 120: राजर्षयश्च बहवः सर्वैः समुदिता गुणैः |` | "And many Rajarshis [royal sages] endowed with all excellent qualities," |
| `Line 121: आपो द्यौः पृथिवी वायुरन्तरिक्षं दिशस्तथा ||३४||` | "Water, heaven, earth, wind, sky, and the directions as well. ||34||" |
| `Line 122: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 123: संवत्सरर्तवो मासाः पक्षाहोरात्रयः क्रमात् |` | "The year, seasons, months, fortnights, days and nights in sequence," |
| `Line 124: यच्चान्यदपि तत्सर्वं सम्भूतं लोकसाक्षिकम् ||३५||` | "And whatever else exists, all that has come into being, witnessed by the world. ||35||" |
| `Line 125: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 126: यदिदं दृश्यते किञ्चिद्भूतं स्थावरजङ्गमम् |` | "Whatever is seen here, any being, immovable or movable," |
| `Line 127: पुनः सङ्क्षिप्यते सर्वं जगत्प्राप्ते युगक्षये ||३६||` | "All is dissolved again, the entire world, when the end of the yuga [cosmic age] arrives. ||36||" |
| `Line 128: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 129: यथर्तावृतुलिङ्गानि नानारूपाणि पर्यये |` | "Just as the characteristics of seasons, of various forms, in their cycle," |
| `Line 130: दृश्यन्ते तानि तान्येव तथा भावा युगादिषु ||३७||` | "Are seen as the very same ones repeatedly, so are the states of existence at the beginning of each yuga [cosmic age]. ||37||" |
| `Line 131: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 132: एवमेतदनाद्यन्तं भूतसंहारकारकम् |` | "Thus this, without beginning or end, causing the dissolution of beings," |
| `Line 133: अनादिनिधनं लोके चक्रं सम्परिवर्तते ||३८||` | "The wheel [of time] without beginning or end revolves in the world. ||38||" |
| `Line 134: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 135: त्रयस्त्रिंशत्सहस्राणि त्रयस्त्रिंशच्छतानि च |` | "Thirty-three thousand, thirty-three hundred, and" |
| `Line 136: त्रयस्त्रिंशच्च देवानां सृष्टिः सङ्क्षेपलक्षणा ||३९||` | "Thirty-three gods - this is the creation in brief description. ||39||" |
| `Line 137: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 138: दिवस्पुत्रो बृहद्भानुश्चक्षुरात्मा विभावसुः |` | "The son of heaven, Brihadbhānu, Chakshuratma, Vibhāvasu [sun deity]," |
| `Line 139: सविता च ऋचीकोऽर्को भानुराशावहो रविः ||४०||` | "Savitā, Ṛchīka, Arka, Bhānu, Āśāvaha, Ravi [all solar deities]. ||40||" |
| `Line 140: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 141: पुत्रा विवस्वतः सर्वे मह्यस्तेषां तथावरः |` | "All are sons of Vivasvat [sun god], and Mahya is the youngest among them," |
| `Line 142: देवभ्राट्तनयस्तस्य तस्मात्सुभ्राडिति स्मृतः ||४१||` | "Devabhrāṭ's son was his, therefore he is known as Subhrāḍ. ||41||" |
| `Line 143: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 144: सुभ्राजस्तु त्रयः पुत्राः प्रजावन्तो बहुश्रुताः |` | "Subhrāja had three sons, prolific and highly learned," |
| `Line 145: दशज्योतिः शतज्योतिः सहस्रज्योतिरात्मवान् ||४२||` | "Daśajyoti, Śatajyoti, and the noble Sahasrajyoti. ||42||" |
| `Line 146: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 147: दश पुत्रसहस्राणि दशज्योतेर्महात्मनः |` | "Ten thousand sons were born to the great-souled Daśajyoti," |
| `Line 148: ततो दशगुणाश्चान्ये शतज्योतेरिहात्मजाः ||४३||` | "And ten times that number were the sons of Śatajyoti here. ||43||" |
| `Line 149: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 150: भूयस्ततो दशगुणाः सहस्रज्योतिषः सुताः |` | "And ten times more than that were the sons of Sahasrajyoti," |
| `Line 151: तेभ्योऽयं कुरुवंशश्च यदूनां भरतस्य च ||४४||` | "From them arose this lineage of the Kurus, of the Yadus [Krishna's clan], and of Bharata [ancient king]. ||44||" |
| `Line 152: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 153: ययातीक्ष्वाकुवंशश्च राजर्षीणां च सर्वशः |` | "And the lineages of Yayāti [legendary king] and Ikṣvāku [solar dynasty founder], and of all the royal sages [rājarṣis] completely," |
| `Line 154: सम्भूता बहवो वंशा भूतसर्गाः सविस्तराः ||४५||` | "Many lineages arose, and the detailed creation of beings. ||45||" |
| `Line 155: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 156: भूतस्थानानि सर्वाणि रहस्यं त्रिविधं च यत् |` | "All the abodes of beings, and the threefold mysteries [esoteric knowledge]," |
| `Line 157: वेदयोगं सविज्ञानं धर्मोऽर्थः काम एव च ||४६||` | "The application of Vedas with special knowledge, and dharma [righteousness], artha [wealth], and kāma [pleasure] as well. ||46||" |
| `Line 158: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 159: धर्मकामार्थशास्त्राणि शास्त्राणि विविधानि च |` | "The treatises on dharma, kāma, and artha, and various other treatises," |
| `Line 160: लोकयात्राविधानं च सम्भूतं दृष्टवानृषिः ||४७||` | "And the rules for worldly conduct, the sage saw all these manifested. ||47||" |
| `Line 161: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 162: इतिहासाः सवैयाख्या विविधाः श्रुतयोऽपि च |` | "Histories with their explanations, various sacred texts [śrutis] as well," |
| `Line 163: इह सर्वमनुक्रान्तमुक्तं ग्रन्थस्य लक्षणम् ||४८||` | "Here everything is enumerated, thus the characteristics of this work are described. ||48||" |
| `Line 164: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 165: विस्तीर्यैतन्महज्ज्ञानमृषिः सङ्क्षेपमब्रवीत् |` | "Having expanded this great knowledge, the sage spoke it in condensed form," |
| `Line 166: इष्टं हि विदुषां लोके समासव्यासधारणम् ||४९||` | "For in the world of the learned, the grasp of both concise and elaborate forms is desired. ||49||" |
| `Line 167: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 168: मन्वादि भारतं केचिदास्तीकादि तथापरे |` | "Some study the Bharata beginning with Manu [first man], others beginning with Āstīka [serpent sacrifice story]," |
| `Line 169: तथोपरिचराद्यन्ये विप्राः सम्यगधीयते ||५०||` | "And other Brahmins study it properly beginning with Uparicara [King Vasu]. ||50||" |
| `Line 170: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 171: विविधं संहिताज्ञानं दीपयन्ति मनीषिणः |` | "The wise illuminate the diverse knowledge of the Saṃhitās [collections]," |
| `Line 172: व्याख्यातुं कुशलाः केचिद्ग्रन्थं धारयितुं परे ||५१||` | "Some are skilled in explaining, others in memorizing the text. ||51||" |
| `Line 173: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 174: तपसा ब्रह्मचर्येण व्यस्य वेदं सनातनम् |` | "Having divided the eternal Veda through austerity and celibacy," |
| `Line 175: इतिहासमिमं चक्रे पुण्यं सत्यवतीसुतः ||५२||` | "The son of Satyavatī [Vyāsa] created this sacred history. ||52||" |
| `Line 176: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 177: पराशरात्मजो विद्वान्ब्रह्मर्षिः संशितव्रतः |` | "The learned son of Parāśara, a brahmarṣi [sage of highest order], of firm vows," |
| `Line 178: मातुर्नियोगाद्धर्मात्मा गाङ्गेयस्य च धीमतः ||५३||` | "By the command of his mother and of the wise Gāṅgeya [son of Gaṅgā], that righteous soul. ||53||" |
| `Line 179: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 180: क्षेत्रे विचित्रवीर्यस्य कृष्णद्वैपायनः पुरा |` | "In the field [wife] of Vicitravīrya, Kṛṣṇa Dvaipāyana [Vyāsa] formerly," |
| `Line 181: त्रीनग्नीनिव कौरव्याञ्जनयामास वीर्यवान् ||५४||` | "Like three sacred fires, begot the Kauravya princes, that powerful sage. ||54||" |
| `Line 182: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 183: उत्पाद्य धृतराष्ट्रं च पाण्डुं विदुरमेव च |` | "Having begotten Dhṛtarāṣṭra, Pāṇḍu, and Vidura," |
| `Line 184: जगाम तपसे धीमान्पुनरेवाश्रमं प्रति ||५५||` | "The wise one went again to his hermitage for performing austerities. ||55||" |
| `Line 185: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 186: तेषु जातेषु वृद्धेषु गतेषु परमां गतिम् |` | "When they were born, had grown up, and had attained the supreme state [death]," |
| `Line 187: अब्रवीद्भारतं लोके मानुषेऽस्मिन्महानृषिः ||५६||` | "The great sage narrated the Bhārata in this world of humans. ||56||" |
| `Line 188: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 189: जनमेजयेन पृष्टः सन्ब्राह्मणैश्च सहस्रशः |` | "Being asked by Janamejaya and by thousands of Brāhmaṇas [priests]," |
| `Line 190: शशास शिष्यमासीनं वैशम्पायनमन्तिके ||५७||` | "He instructed his disciple Vaiśampāyana who was seated nearby. ||57||" |
| `Line 191: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 192: स सदस्यैः सहासीनः श्रावयामास भारतम् |` | "He, seated with the assembly members, recited the Bhārata," |
| `Line 193: कर्मान्तरेषु यज्ञस्य चोद्यमानः पुनः पुनः ||५८||` | "Being repeatedly requested during the intervals of the sacrifice. ||58||" |
| `Line 194: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 195: विस्तरं कुरुवंशस्य गान्धार्या धर्मशीलताम् |` | "The detailed account of the Kuru lineage, the righteousness of Gāndhārī [Dhritarashtra's wife]," |
| `Line 196: क्षत्तुः प्रज्ञां धृतिं कुन्त्याः सम्यग्द्वैपायनोऽब्रवीत् ||५९||` | "The wisdom of Kṣattṛ [Vidura] and the steadfastness of Kuntī—Dvaipāyana narrated all this properly. ||59||" |
| `Line 197: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 198: वासुदेवस्य माहात्म्यं पाण्डवानां च सत्यताम् |` | "The greatness of Vāsudeva [Krishna] and the truthfulness of the Pāṇḍavas," |
| `Line 199: दुर्वृत्तं धार्तराष्ट्राणामुक्तवान्भगवानृषिः ||६०||` | "The evil conduct of the sons of Dhṛtarāṣṭra—the venerable sage narrated. ||60||" |
| `Line 200: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 201: चतुर्विंशतिसाहस्रीं चक्रे भारतसंहिताम् |` | "He composed the Bhārata Saṃhitā [epic compilation] of twenty-four thousand verses," |
| `Line 202: उपाख्यानैर्विना तावद्भारतं प्रोच्यते बुधैः ||६१||` | "Without the sub-narratives, that much is called Bhārata by the wise. ||61||" |
| `Line 203: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 204: ततोऽध्यर्धशतं भूयः सङ्क्षेपं कृतवानृषिः |` | "Then the sage further composed a summary of one hundred and fifty," |
| `Line 205: अनुक्रमणिमध्यायं वृत्तान्तानां सपर्वणाम् ||६२||` | "An index chapter of the contents along with the Parvas [sections]. ||62||" |
| `Line 206: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 207: इदं द्वैपायनः पूर्वं पुत्रमध्यापयच्छुकम् |` | "This was first taught by Dvaipāyana [Vyāsa] to his son Śuka," |
| `Line 208: ततोऽन्येभ्योऽनुरूपेभ्यः शिष्येभ्यः प्रददौ प्रभुः ||६३||` | "Then the master gave it to other suitable disciples. ||63||" |
| `Line 209: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 210: नारदोऽश्रावयद्देवानसितो देवलः पितृन् |` | "Nārada recited it to the gods, Asita Devala to the ancestors," |
| `Line 211: गन्धर्वयक्षरक्षांसि श्रावयामास वै शुकः ||६४||` | "And Śuka indeed recited it to the Gandharvas [celestial musicians], Yakṣas [wealth spirits], and Rākṣasas [demons]. ||64||" |
| `Line 212: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 213: दुर्योधनो मन्युमयो महाद्रुमः; स्कन्धः कर्णः शकुनिस्तस्य शाखाः |` | "Duryodhana is a great tree made of anger; Karṇa is its trunk, Śakuni its branches," |
| `Line 214: दुःशासनः पुष्पफले समृद्धे; मूलं राजा धृतराष्ट्रोऽमनीषी ||६५||` | "Duḥśāsana its abundant flowers and fruits; the unwise king Dhṛtarāṣṭra is its root. ||65||" |
| `Line 215: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 216: युधिष्ठिरो धर्ममयो महाद्रुमः; स्कन्धोऽर्जुनो भीमसेनोऽस्य शाखाः |` | "Yudhiṣṭhira is a great tree made of dharma [righteousness]; Arjuna is its trunk, Bhīmasena its branches," |
| `Line 217: माद्रीसुतौ पुष्पफले समृद्धे; मूलं कृष्णो ब्रह्म च ब्राह्मणाश्च ||६६||` | "The sons of Mādrī [Nakula and Sahadeva] are its abundant flowers and fruits; Kṛṣṇa, Brahman, and the Brāhmaṇas are its roots. ||66||" |
| `Line 218: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 219: पाण्डुर्जित्वा बहून्देशान्युधा विक्रमणेन च |` | "Pāṇḍu, having conquered many lands through battle and valor," |
| `Line 220: अरण्ये मृगयाशीलो न्यवसत्सजनस्तदा ||६७||` | "Then lived in the forest with his people, devoted to hunting. ||67||" |
| `Line 221: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 222: मृगव्यवायनिधने कृच्छ्रां प्राप स आपदम् |` | "He met with a terrible calamity due to intercourse while in the form of a deer [during hunting]," |
| `Line 223: जन्मप्रभृति पार्थानां तत्राचारविधिक्रमः ||६८||` | "From the birth of the Pārthas [sons of Pṛthā/Kuntī], there is the sequence of their conduct and rules. ||68||" |
| `Line 224: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 225: मात्रोरभ्युपपत्तिश्च धर्मोपनिषदं प्रति |` | "And the approach of their mothers regarding the secret doctrine of dharma [divine conception]," |
| `Line 226: धर्मस्य वायोः शक्रस्य देवयोश्च तथाश्विनोः ||६९||` | "Of Dharma [righteousness deity], Vayu [wind god], Shakra [Indra], and also of the two Ashvins [divine twins]. ||69||" |
| `Line 227: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 228: तापसैः सह संवृद्धा मातृभ्यां परिरक्षिताः |` | "They grew up with ascetics, protected by their mothers," |
| `Line 229: मेध्यारण्येषु पुण्येषु महतामाश्रमेषु च ||७०||` | "In sacred forests and in the great hermitages of sages. ||70||" |
| `Line 230: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 231: ऋषिभिश्च तदानीता धार्तराष्ट्रान्प्रति स्वयम् |` | "And then the sages themselves brought them to the sons of Dhritarashtra," |
| `Line 232: शिशवश्चाभिरूपाश्च जटिला ब्रह्मचारिणः ||७१||` | "The children, handsome, with matted hair, practicing celibacy [brahmacharya]. ||71||" |
| `Line 233: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 234: पुत्राश्च भ्रातरश्चेमे शिष्याश्च सुहृदश्च वः |` | "These are your sons, brothers, disciples, and friends," |
| `Line 235: पाण्डवा एत इत्युक्त्वा मुनयोऽन्तर्हितास्ततः ||७२||` | "These are the Pandavas," saying thus, the sages disappeared from there. ||72||" |
| `Line 236: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 237: तांस्तैर्निवेदितान्दृष्ट्वा पाण्डवान्कौरवास्तदा |` | "Seeing those Pandavas thus introduced, the Kauravas then," |
| `Line 238: शिष्टाश्च वर्णाः पौरा ये ते हर्षाच्चुक्रुशुर्भृशम् ||७३||` | "And the noble classes and citizens who were there, cried out loudly with joy. ||73||" |
| `Line 239: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 240: आहुः केचिन्न तस्यैते तस्यैत इति चापरे |` | "Some said, 'These are not his,' while others said, 'These are indeed his,'" |
| `Line 241: यदा चिरमृतः पाण्डुः कथं तस्येति चापरे ||७४||` | "And others said, 'Since Pandu died long ago, how can they be his?' ||74||" |
| `Line 242: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 243: स्वागतं सर्वथा दिष्ट्या पाण्डोः पश्याम सन्ततिम् |` | "'Welcome in every way! By good fortune we see the progeny of Pandu!'" |
| `Line 244: उच्यतां स्वागतमिति वाचोऽश्रूयन्त सर्वशः ||७५||` | "Voices saying 'Welcome!' were heard from all sides. ||75||" |
| `Line 245: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 246: तस्मिन्नुपरते शब्दे दिशः सर्वा विनादयन् |` | "When that sound subsided, resounding in all directions," |
| `Line 247: अन्तर्हितानां भूतानां निस्वनस्तुमुलोऽभवत् ||७६||` | "There arose a tumultuous sound of invisible beings. ||76||" |
| `Line 248: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 249: पुष्पवृष्टिः शुभा गन्धाः शङ्खदुन्दुभिनिस्वनाः |` | "A shower of flowers, auspicious fragrances, sounds of conches and drums," |
| `Line 250: आसन्प्रवेशे पार्थानां तदद्भुतमिवाभवत् ||७७||` | "Occurred at the entrance of the Parthas [sons of Pritha], and it was like a miracle. ||77||" |
| `Line 251: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 252: तत्प्रीत्या चैव सर्वेषां पौराणां हर्षसम्भवः |` | "And from that affection arose the joy of all the citizens," |
| `Line 253: शब्द आसीन्महांस्तत्र दिवस्पृक्कीर्तिवर्धनः ||७८||` | "There was a great sound there, reaching the heavens, enhancing their fame. ||78||" |
| `Line 254: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 255: तेऽप्यधीत्याखिलान्वेदाञ्शास्त्राणि विविधानि च |` | "Having studied all the Vedas and various śāstras [sacred texts]," |
| `Line 256: न्यवसन्पाण्डवास्तत्र पूजिता अकुतोभयाः ||७९||` | "The Pāṇḍavas lived there, honored and fearless. ||79||" |
| `Line 257: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 258: युधिष्ठिरस्य शौचेन प्रीताः प्रकृतयोऽभवन् |` | "The subjects were pleased with Yudhiṣṭhira's purity," |
| `Line 259: धृत्या च भीमसेनस्य विक्रमेणार्जुनस्य च ||८०||` | "With Bhīmasena's steadfastness and Arjuna's valor. ||80||" |
| `Line 260: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 261: गुरुशुश्रूषया कुन्त्या यमयोर्विनयेन च |` | "With Kuntī's service to elders and the twins' [Nakula-Sahadeva] humility," |
| `Line 262: तुतोष लोकः सकलस्तेषां शौर्यगुणेन च ||८१||` | "The entire world was satisfied with their heroic qualities. ||81||" |
| `Line 263: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 264: समवाये ततो राज्ञां कन्यां भर्तृस्वयंवराम् |` | "Then, in an assembly of kings, at a bride's self-choice ceremony [svayaṃvara]," |
| `Line 265: प्राप्तवानर्जुनः कृष्णां कृत्वा कर्म सुदुष्करम् ||८२||` | "Arjuna won Kṛṣṇā [Draupadī], having performed an extremely difficult feat. ||82||" |
| `Line 266: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 267: ततः प्रभृति लोकेऽस्मिन्पूज्यः सर्वधनुष्मताम् |` | "From then on, in this world, he was revered among all archers," |
| `Line 268: आदित्य इव दुष्प्रेक्ष्यः समरेष्वपि चाभवत् ||८३||` | "And became difficult to look at in battles, like the sun [Āditya]. ||83||" |
| `Line 269: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 270: स सर्वान्पार्थिवाञ्जित्वा सर्वांश्च महतो गणान् |` | "Having conquered all the kings and all the great hosts," |
| `Line 271: आजहारार्जुनो राज्ञे राजसूयं महाक्रतुम् ||८४||` | "Arjuna brought for the king the Rājasūya, the great sacrifice [royal consecration]. ||84||" |
| `Line 272: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 273: अन्नवान्दक्षिणावांश्च सर्वैः समुदितो गुणैः |` | "Abundant with food and gifts, endowed with all excellent qualities," |
| `Line 274: युधिष्ठिरेण सम्प्राप्तो राजसूयो महाक्रतुः ||८५||` | "The great Rājasūya sacrifice was performed by Yudhiṣṭhira. ||85||" |
| `Line 275: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 276: सुनयाद्वासुदेवस्य भीमार्जुनबलेन च |` | "Through the wise policy of Vāsudeva [Krishna] and by the strength of Bhīma and Arjuna," |
| `Line 277: घातयित्वा जरासन्धं चैद्यं च बलगर्वितम् ||८६||` | "Having caused the slaying of Jarāsandha and Chaidya [Shishupala] who was proud of his strength. ||86||" |
| `Line 278: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 279: दुर्योधनमुपागच्छन्नर्हणानि ततस्ततः |` | "Tributes came to Duryodhana from here and there," |
| `Line 280: मणिकाञ्चनरत्नानि गोहस्त्यश्वधनानि च ||८७||` | "Jewels, gold, gems, and wealth in the form of cows, elephants, and horses. ||87||" |
| `Line 281: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 282: समृद्धां तां तथा दृष्ट्वा पाण्डवानां तदा श्रियम् |` | "Seeing thus the abundant prosperity of the Pāṇḍavas at that time," |
| `Line 283: ईर्ष्यासमुत्थः सुमहांस्तस्य मन्युरजायत ||८८||` | "Great anger born of envy arose in him. ||88||" |
| `Line 284: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 285: विमानप्रतिमां चापि मयेन सुकृतां सभाम् |` | "And seeing the assembly hall resembling a celestial palace, beautifully constructed by Maya [demon architect]," |
| `Line 286: पाण्डवानामुपहृतां स दृष्ट्वा पर्यतप्यत ||८९||` | "Presented to the Pāṇḍavas, he was consumed with grief. ||89||" |
| `Line 287: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 288: यत्रावहसितश्चासीत्प्रस्कन्दन्निव सम्भ्रमात् |` | "Where he had been laughed at when he fell in confusion," |
| `Line 289: प्रत्यक्षं वासुदेवस्य भीमेनानभिजातवत् ||९०||` | "In the presence of Vāsudeva [Krishna], by Bhīma, as if he were of low birth. ||90||" |
| `Line 290: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 291: स भोगान्विविधान्भुञ्जन्रत्नानि विविधानि च |` | "He, though enjoying various pleasures and diverse jewels," |
| `Line 292: कथितो धृतराष्ट्रस्य विवर्णो हरिणः कृशः ||९१||` | "Was described to Dhṛtarāṣṭra as pale, agitated, and emaciated. ||91||" |
| `Line 293: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 294: अन्वजानात्ततो द्यूतं धृतराष्ट्रः सुतप्रियः |` | "Then Dhṛtarāṣṭra, loving his son, approved of the gambling match," |
| `Line 295: तच्छ्रुत्वा वासुदेवस्य कोपः समभवन्महान् ||९२||` | "Hearing of this, great was the anger of Vāsudeva [Krishna]. ||92||" |
| `Line 296: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 297: नातिप्रीतमनाश्चासीद्विवादांश्चान्वमोदत |` | "He [Dhritarashtra] was not very pleased at heart, yet he approved of the disputes," |
| `Line 298: द्यूतादीननयान्घोरान्प्रवृद्धांश्चाप्युपैक्षत ||९३||` | "And overlooked the terrible injustices beginning with the gambling match that had grown out of control. ||93||" |
| `Line 299: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 300: निरस्य विदुरं द्रोणं भीष्मं शारद्वतं कृपम् |` | "Rejecting Vidura, Droṇa, Bhīṣma, Śāradvata [Kripa's father], and Kṛpa," |
| `Line 301: विग्रहे तुमुले तस्मिन्नहन्क्षत्रं परस्परम् ||९४||` | "In that tumultuous battle, the warriors [kṣatriyas] slew one another. ||94||" |
| `Line 302: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 303: जयत्सु पाण्डुपुत्रेषु श्रुत्वा सुमहदप्रियम् |` | "When the sons of Pandu were victorious, having heard this greatly unpleasant news," |
| `Line 304: दुर्योधनमतं ज्ञात्वा कर्णस्य शकुनेस्तथा ||९५||` | "And knowing the intentions of Duryodhana, Karna, and Shakuni as well, ||95||" |
| `Line 305: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 306: धृतराष्ट्रश्चिरं ध्यात्वा सञ्जयं वाक्यमब्रवीत् ||९५||` | "Dhritarashtra, after reflecting for a long time, spoke these words to Sanjaya. ||95||" |
| `Line 307: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 308: शृणु सञ्जय मे सर्वं न मेऽसूयितुमर्हसि |` | "Listen, Sanjaya, to all I say, and you should not find fault with me," |
| `Line 309: श्रुतवानसि मेधावी बुद्धिमान्प्राज्ञसंमतः ||९६||` | "You are learned, intelligent, and esteemed by the wise. ||96||" |
| `Line 310: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 311: न विग्रहे मम मतिर्न च प्रीये कुरुक्षये |` | "My mind is not inclined toward conflict, nor do I delight in the destruction of the Kurus," |
| `Line 312: न मे विशेषः पुत्रेषु स्वेषु पाण्डुसुतेषु च ||९७||` | "I have no preference between my own sons and the sons of Pandu. ||97||" |
| `Line 313: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 314: वृद्धं मामभ्यसूयन्ति पुत्रा मन्युपरायणाः |` | "My sons, devoted to anger, find fault with me, an old man," |
| `Line 315: अहं त्वचक्षुः कार्पण्यात्पुत्रप्रीत्या सहामि तत् ||९८||` | "But being blind, out of weakness and love for my sons, I endure it. ||98||" |
| `Line 316: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 317: मुह्यन्तं चानुमुह्यामि दुर्योधनमचेतनम् ||९८||` | "And I follow in delusion my deluded and senseless Duryodhana. ||98||" |
| `Line 318: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 319: राजसूये श्रियं दृष्ट्वा पाण्डवस्य महौजसः |` | "Having seen the prosperity of the mighty Pandava at the Rajasuya [royal sacrifice]," |
| `Line 320: तच्चावहसनं प्राप्य सभारोहणदर्शने ||९९||` | "And having experienced humiliation at the sight of the assembly hall, ||99||" |
| `Line 321: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 322: अमर्षितः स्वयं जेतुमशक्तः पाण्डवान्रणे |` | "Filled with intolerance, yet himself unable to defeat the Pandavas in battle," |
| `Line 323: निरुत्साहश्च सम्प्राप्तुं श्रियमक्षत्रियो यथा ||१००||` | "And lacking the energy to attain prosperity, like one who is not a kshatriya [warrior], ||100||" |
| `Line 324: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 325: गान्धारराजसहितश्छद्मद्यूतममन्त्रयत् ||१००||` | "Together with the king of Gandhara [Shakuni], he plotted the fraudulent game of dice. ||100||" |
| `Line 326: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 327: तत्र यद्यद्यथा ज्ञातं मया सञ्जय तच्छृणु |` | "Listen, Sanjaya, to what I have known there, in whatever way I have known it." |
| `Line 328: श्रुत्वा हि मम वाक्यानि बुद्ध्या युक्तानि तत्त्वतः ||१०१||` | "For having heard my words, which are endowed with wisdom and truth. ||101||" |
| `Line 329: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 330: ततो ज्ञास्यसि मां सौते प्रज्ञाचक्षुषमित्युत ||१०१||` | "Then you will know me, O charioteer's son [Sanjaya], as one who sees with the eye of wisdom. ||101||" |
| `Line 331: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 332: यदाश्रौषं धनुरायम्य चित्रं; विद्धं लक्ष्यं पातितं वै पृथिव्याम् |` | "When I heard that, drawing the marvelous bow, the target was pierced and made to fall on the earth," |
| `Line 333: कृष्णां हृतां पश्यतां सर्वराज्ञां; तदा नाशंसे विजयाय सञ्जय ||१०२||` | "And Krishnā [Draupadi] was dragged away in the sight of all kings; then, Sanjaya, I did not hope for victory. ||102||" |
| `Line 334: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 335: यदाश्रौषं द्वारकायां सुभद्रां; प्रसह्योढां माधवीमर्जुनेन |` | "When I heard that Subhadrā, the daughter of Mādhava [Krishna's family], was forcibly carried away from Dvārakā by Arjuna," |
| `Line 336: इन्द्रप्रस्थं वृष्णिवीरौ च यातौ; तदा नाशंसे विजयाय सञ्जय ||१०३||` | "And that the two Vrishni heroes [Krishna and Balarama] went to Indraprastha; then, Sanjaya, I did not hope for victory. ||103||" |
| `Line 337: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 338: यदाश्रौषं देवराजं प्रवृष्टं; शरैर्दिव्यैर्वारितं चार्जुनेन |` | "When I heard that the king of gods [Indra] showering (arrows) was repelled by Arjuna with divine arrows," |
| `Line 339: अग्निं तथा तर्पितं खाण्डवे च; तदा नाशंसे विजयाय सञ्जय ||१०४||` | "And that the fire god was satisfied in the Khāṇḍava forest; then, Sanjaya, I did not hope for victory. ||104||" |
| `Line 340: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 341: यदाश्रौषं हृतराज्यं युधिष्ठिरं; पराजितं सौबलेनाक्षवत्याम् |` | "When I heard that Yudhishthira was deprived of his kingdom, defeated by Soubala [Shakuni] in the game of dice," |
| `Line 342: अन्वागतं भ्रातृभिरप्रमेयै; स्तदा नाशंसे विजयाय सञ्जय ||१०५||` | "And was followed by his immeasurable brothers; then, Sanjaya, I did not hope for victory. ||105||" |
| `Line 343: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 344: यदाश्रौषं द्रौपदीमश्रुकण्ठीं; सभां नीतां दुःखितामेकवस्त्राम् |` | "When I heard that Draupadi, with tears in her throat, was brought to the assembly hall, distressed, wearing only a single garment," |
| `Line 345: रजस्वलां नाथवतीमनाथव; त्तदा नाशंसे विजयाय सञ्जय ||१०६||` | "In her monthly period, though having protectors, yet treated as if without protection; then, Sanjaya, I did not hope for victory. ||106||" |
| `Line 346: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 347: यदाश्रौषं विविधास्तात चेष्टा; धर्मात्मनां प्रस्थितानां वनाय |` | "When I heard, O dear one, of the various efforts of those righteous souls departing for the forest," |
| `Line 348: ज्येष्ठप्रीत्या क्लिश्यतां पाण्डवानां; तदा नाशंसे विजयाय सञ्जय ||१०७||` | "Of the Pāṇḍavas suffering out of devotion to their eldest brother; then, Sanjaya, I did not hope for victory. ||107||" |
| `Line 349: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 350: यदाश्रौषं स्नातकानां सहस्रै; रन्वागतं धर्मराजं वनस्थम् |` | "When I heard that Dharmarāja [Yudhishthira], dwelling in the forest, was followed by thousands of graduate students [Snātakas]," |
| `Line 351: भिक्षाभुजां ब्राह्मणानां महात्मनां; तदा नाशंसे विजयाय सञ्जय ||१०८||` | "Of the alms-eating Brahmins, the great souls; then, O Sanjaya, I had no hope for victory. ||108||" |
| `Line 352: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 353: यदाश्रौषमर्जुनो देवदेवं; किरातरूपं त्र्यम्बकं तोष्य युद्धे |` | "When I heard that Arjuna had pleased the God of gods, Tryambaka [three-eyed Shiva] in the form of a Kirata [hunter], in battle," |
| `Line 354: अवाप तत्पाशुपतं महास्त्रं; तदा नाशंसे विजयाय सञ्जय ||१०९||` | "And obtained that mighty Pashupata [Shiva's weapon] weapon; then, O Sanjaya, I had no hope for victory. ||109||" |
| `Line 355: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 356: यदाश्रौषं त्रिदिवस्थं धनञ्जयं; शक्रात्साक्षाद्दिव्यमस्त्रं यथावत् |` | "When I heard that Dhananjaya [Arjuna] was in heaven [Tridiva], properly learning divine weapons directly from Shakra [Indra]," |
| `Line 357: अधीयानं शंसितं सत्यसन्धं; तदा नाशंसे विजयाय सञ्जय ||११०||` | "He who is praised, truthful and steadfast in his vows; then, O Sanjaya, I had no hope for victory. ||110||" |
| `Line 358: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 359: यदाश्रौषं वैश्रवणेन सार्धं; समागतं भीममन्यांश्च पार्थान् |` | "When I heard that Bhima and the other Parthas [Pandavas] had met with Vaishravana [Kubera]," |
| `Line 360: तस्मिन्देशे मानुषाणामगम्ये; तदा नाशंसे विजयाय सञ्जय ||१११||` | "In that region inaccessible to humans; then, O Sanjaya, I had no hope for victory. ||111||" |
| `Line 361: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 362: यदाश्रौषं घोषयात्रागतानां; बन्धं गन्धर्वैर्मोक्षणं चार्जुनेन |` | "When I heard of the capture of those who had gone on the Ghoshayatra [cattle expedition], by the Gandharvas, and their release by Arjuna," |
| `Line 363: स्वेषां सुतानां कर्णबुद्धौ रतानां; तदा नाशंसे विजयाय सञ्जय ||११२||` | "Of my sons who relied on Karna's wisdom; then, O Sanjaya, I had no hope for victory. ||112||" |
| `Line 364: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 365: यदाश्रौषं यक्षरूपेण धर्मं; समागतं धर्मराजेन सूत |` | "When I heard that Dharma [Yama] in the form of a Yaksha [supernatural being] had met with Dharmaraja [Yudhishthira], O charioteer," |
| `Line 366: प्रश्नानुक्तान्विब्रुवन्तं च सम्य; क्तदा नाशंसे विजयाय सञ्जय ||११३||` | "And that he correctly answered all the questions asked; then, O Sanjaya, I had no hope for victory. ||113||" |
| `Line 367: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 368: यदाश्रौषं मामकानां वरिष्ठा; न्धनञ्जयेनैकरथेन भग्नान् |` | "When I heard that the best of my warriors were defeated by Dhananjaya [Arjuna] alone in his chariot," |
| `Line 369: विराटराष्ट्रे वसता महात्मना; तदा नाशंसे विजयाय सञ्जय ||११४||` | "By that great soul residing in the kingdom of Virata; then, O Sanjaya, I had no hope for victory. ||114||" |
| `Line 370: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 371: यदाश्रौषं सत्कृतां मत्स्यराज्ञा; सुतां दत्तामुत्तरामर्जुनाय |` | "When I heard that the honored daughter of the Matsya king, Uttara, was given to Arjuna," |
| `Line 372: तां चार्जुनः प्रत्यगृह्णात्सुतार्थे; तदा नाशंसे विजयाय सञ्जय ||११५||` | "And that Arjuna accepted her for his son's sake; then, O Sanjaya, I had no hope for victory. ||115||" |
| `Line 373: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 374: यदाश्रौषं निर्जितस्याधनस्य; प्रव्राजितस्य स्वजनात्प्रच्युतस्य |` | "When I heard that Yudhishthira, who was defeated, made penniless, exiled, and separated from his kinsmen," |
| `Line 375: अक्षौहिणीः सप्त युधिष्ठिरस्य; तदा नाशंसे विजयाय सञ्जय ||११६||` | "Had seven akshauhinis [large army divisions] at his command; then, O Sanjaya, I had no hope for victory. ||116||" |
| `Line 376: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 377: यदाश्रौषं नरनारायणौ तौ; कृष्णार्जुनौ वदतो नारदस्य |` | "When I heard from Narada's words that those two, Nara-Narayana [ancient sages], were Krishna and Arjuna," |
| `Line 378: अहं द्रष्टा ब्रह्मलोके सदेति; तदा नाशंसे विजयाय सञ्जय ||११७||` | "That I would always see them in Brahmaloka [celestial realm], then, O Sanjaya, I had no hope for victory. ||117||" |
| `Line 379: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 380: यदाश्रौषं माधवं वासुदेवं; सर्वात्मना पाण्डवार्थे निविष्टम् |` | "When I heard that Madhava [Krishna], Vasudeva, was wholly devoted to the Pandavas' cause," |
| `Line 381: यस्येमां गां विक्रममेकमाहु; स्तदा नाशंसे विजयाय सञ्जय ||११८||` | "He whose single stride is said to cover this earth, then, O Sanjaya, I had no hope for victory. ||118||" |
| `Line 382: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 383: यदाश्रौषं कर्णदुर्योधनाभ्यां; बुद्धिं कृतां निग्रहे केशवस्य |` | "When I heard that Karna and Duryodhana had formed a plan to capture Keshava [Krishna]," |
| `Line 384: तं चात्मानं बहुधा दर्शयानं; तदा नाशंसे विजयाय सञ्जय ||११९||` | "And that he revealed himself in multiple forms, then, O Sanjaya, I had no hope for victory. ||119||" |
| `Line 385: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 386: यदाश्रौषं वासुदेवे प्रयाते; रथस्यैकामग्रतस्तिष्ठमानाम् |` | "When I heard that as Vasudeva [Krishna] departed, Pritha [Kunti] stood alone before his chariot," |
| `Line 387: आर्तां पृथां सान्त्वितां केशवेन; तदा नाशंसे विजयाय सञ्जय ||१२०||` | "Distressed Pritha was consoled by Keshava, then, O Sanjaya, I had no hope for victory. ||120||" |
| `Line 388: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 389: यदाश्रौषं मन्त्रिणं वासुदेवं; तथा भीष्मं शान्तनवं च तेषाम् |` | "When I heard that Vasudeva was their counselor, and that Bhishma, son of Shantanu, was with them," |
| `Line 390: भारद्वाजं चाशिषोऽनुब्रुवाणं; तदा नाशंसे विजयाय सञ्जय ||१२१||` | "And that Bharadvaja [Drona] pronounced blessings upon them, then, O Sanjaya, I had no hope for victory. ||121||" |
| `Line 391: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 392: यदाश्रौषं कर्ण उवाच भीष्मं; नाहं योत्स्ये युध्यमाने त्वयीति |` | "When I heard that Karna said to Bhishma, 'I will not fight while you are fighting,'" |
| `Line 393: हित्वा सेनामपचक्राम चैव; तदा नाशंसे विजयाय सञ्जय ||१२२||` | "And that he left the army and departed, then, O Sanjaya, I had no hope for victory. ||122||" |
| `Line 394: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 395: यदाश्रौषं वासुदेवार्जुनौ तौ; तथा धनुर्गाण्डिवमप्रमेयम् |` | "When I heard that those two, Vasudeva and Arjuna, along with the immeasurable Gandiva bow [divine weapon]," |
| `Line 396: त्रीण्युग्रवीर्याणि समागतानि; तदा नाशंसे विजयाय सञ्जय ||१२३||` | "These three of terrible prowess had come together, then, O Sanjaya, I had no hope for victory. ||123||" |
| `Line 397: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 398: यदाश्रौषं कश्मलेनाभिपन्ने; रथोपस्थे सीदमानेऽर्जुने वै |` | "When I heard that Arjuna, overcome with dejection, was sinking down in his chariot," |
| `Line 399: कृष्णं लोकान्दर्शयानं शरीरे; तदा नाशंसे विजयाय सञ्जय ||१२४||` | "And Krishna revealed all the worlds within his body, then, O Sanjaya, I had no hope for victory. ||124||" |
| `Line 400: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 401: यदाश्रौषं भीष्मममित्रकर्शनं; निघ्नन्तमाजावयुतं रथानाम् |` | "When I heard that Bhishma, the tormentor of foes, was destroying ten thousand chariots in battle," |
| `Line 402: नैषां कश्चिद्वध्यते दृश्यरूप; स्तदा नाशंसे विजयाय सञ्जय ||१२५||` | "Yet none of our visible warriors was being slain, then, O Sanjaya, I had no hope for victory. ||125||" |
| `Line 403: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 404: यदाश्रौषं भीष्ममत्यन्तशूरं; हतं पार्थेनाहवेष्वप्रधृष्यम् |` | "When I heard that Bhishma, the extremely valiant one, unconquerable in battles, was slain by Partha [Arjuna]," |
| `Line 405: शिखण्डिनं पुरतः स्थापयित्वा; तदा नाशंसे विजयाय सञ्जय ||१२६||` | "After placing Shikhandi in front, then, O Sanjaya, I had no hope for victory. ||126||" |
| `Line 406: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 407: यदाश्रौषं शरतल्पे शयानं; वृद्धं वीरं सादितं चित्रपुङ्खैः |` | "When I heard that the aged hero was lying on a bed of arrows, brought down by variegated-feathered shafts," |
| `Line 408: भीष्मं कृत्वा सोमकानल्पशेषां; स्तदा नाशंसे विजयाय सञ्जय ||१२७||` | "And that Bhishma had reduced the Somakas [Pandava allies] to a small remnant, then, O Sanjaya, I had no hope for victory. ||127||" |
| `Line 409: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 410: यदाश्रौषं शान्तनवे शयाने; पानीयार्थे चोदितेनार्जुनेन |` | "When I heard that while the son of Shantanu [Bhishma] was lying wounded, Arjuna, being urged for water," |
| `Line 411: भूमिं भित्त्वा तर्पितं तत्र भीष्मं; तदा नाशंसे विजयाय सञ्जय ||१२८||` | "Pierced the earth and satisfied Bhishma's thirst there, then, O Sanjaya, I had no hope for victory. ||128||" |
| `Line 412: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 413: यदाश्रौषं शुक्रसूर्यौ च युक्तौ; कौन्तेयानामनुलोमौ जयाय |` | "When I heard that Venus and the Sun were favorably positioned for the victory of the sons of Kunti [Pandavas]," |
| `Line 414: नित्यं चास्माञ्श्वापदा व्याभषन्त; स्तदा नाशंसे विजयाय सञ्जय ||१२९||` | "And that wild beasts were constantly frightening us, then, O Sanjaya, I had no hope for victory. ||129||" |
| `Line 415: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 416: यदा द्रोणो विविधानस्त्रमार्गा; न्विदर्शयन्समरे चित्रयोधी |` | "When Drona, displaying various paths of weapons in battle, fighting wonderfully," |
| `Line 417: न पाण्डवाञ्श्रेष्ठतमान्निहन्ति; तदा नाशंसे विजयाय सञ्जय ||१३०||` | "Could not slay the foremost of the Pandavas, then, O Sanjaya, I had no hope for victory. ||130||" |
| `Line 418: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 419: यदाश्रौषं चास्मदीयान्महारथा; न्व्यवस्थितानर्जुनस्यान्तकाय |` | "When I heard that our great warriors, who had positioned themselves to kill Arjuna," |
| `Line 420: संशप्तकान्निहतानर्जुनेन; तदा नाशंसे विजयाय सञ्जय ||१३१||` | "The Samsaptakas [oath-bound warriors], were slain by Arjuna, then, O Sanjaya, I had no hope for victory. ||131||" |
| `Line 421: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 422: यदाश्रौषं व्यूहमभेद्यमन्यै; र्भारद्वाजेनात्तशस्त्रेण गुप्तम् |` | "When I heard that the formation, impenetrable to others, protected by the armed son of Bharadvaja [Drona]," |
| `Line 423: भित्त्वा सौभद्रं वीरमेकं प्रविष्टं; तदा नाशंसे विजयाय सञ्जय ||१३२||` | "Was penetrated by the heroic son of Subhadra [Abhimanyu] who entered alone, then, O Sanjaya, I had no hope for victory. ||132||" |
| `Line 424: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 425: यदाभिमन्युं परिवार्य बालं; सर्वे हत्वा हृष्टरूपा बभूवुः |` | "When all our warriors, having surrounded the young Abhimanyu, slew him and became joyful," |
| `Line 426: महारथाः पार्थमशक्नुवन्त; स्तदा नाशंसे विजयाय सञ्जय ||१३३||` | "When the great warriors were unable to defeat Pārtha [Arjuna], then, O Sañjaya, I had no hope for victory. ||133||" |
| `Line 427: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 428: यदाश्रौषमभिमन्युं निहत्य; हर्षान्मूढान्क्रोशतो धार्तराष्ट्रान् |` | "When I heard the Dhārtarāṣṭras [Duryodhana's forces] shouting foolishly with joy after slaying Abhimanyu," |
| `Line 429: क्रोधं मुक्तं सैन्धवे चार्जुनेन; तदा नाशंसे विजयाय सञ्जय ||१३४||` | "And Arjuna's unleashed anger against Saindhava [Jayadratha], then, O Sañjaya, I had no hope for victory. ||134||" |
| `Line 430: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 431: यदाश्रौषं सैन्धवार्थे प्रतिज्ञां; प्रतिज्ञातां तद्वधायार्जुनेन |` | "When I heard the vow regarding Saindhava [Jayadratha], the pledge made by Arjuna for his slaying," |
| `Line 432: सत्यां निस्तीर्णां शत्रुमध्ये च तेन; तदा नाशंसे विजयाय सञ्जय ||१३५||` | "And that he fulfilled it truthfully in the midst of enemies, then, O Sañjaya, I had no hope for victory. ||135||" |
| `Line 433: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 434: यदाश्रौषं श्रान्तहये धनञ्जये; मुक्त्वा हयान्पाययित्वोपवृत्तान् |` | "When I heard that Dhanañjaya [Arjuna], whose horses were tired, released them, gave them water, and returned," |
| `Line 435: पुनर्युक्त्वा वासुदेवं प्रयातं; तदा नाशंसे विजयाय सञ्जय ||१३६||` | "And then, yoking them again, proceeded with Vāsudeva [Krishna], then, O Sañjaya, I had no hope for victory. ||136||" |
| `Line 436: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 437: यदाश्रौषं वाहनेष्वाश्वसत्सु; रथोपस्थे तिष्ठता गाण्डिवेन |` | "When I heard that while the horses were resting, standing in his chariot with Gāṇḍīva [Arjuna's bow]," |
| `Line 438: सर्वान्योधान्वारितानर्जुनेन; तदा नाशंसे विजयाय सञ्जय ||१३७||` | "Arjuna warded off all the warriors, then, O Sañjaya, I had no hope for victory. ||137||" |
| `Line 439: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 440: यदाश्रौषं नागबलैर्दुरुत्सहं; द्रोणानीकं युयुधानं प्रमथ्य |` | "When I heard that Yuyudhāna [Sātyaki], having crushed Droṇa's formation that was formidable with elephant forces," |
| `Line 441: यातं वार्ष्णेयं यत्र तौ कृष्णपार्थौ; तदा नाशंसे विजयाय सञ्जय ||१३८||` | "That Vārṣṇeya [Sātyaki] went to where Krishna and Pārtha [Arjuna] were, then, O Sañjaya, I had no hope for victory. ||138||" |
| `Line 442: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 443: यदाश्रौषं कर्णमासाद्य मुक्तं; वधाद्भीमं कुत्सयित्वा वचोभिः |` | "When I heard that Bhīma, having encountered Karṇa, was released from death after being insulted with words," |
| `Line 444: धनुष्कोट्या तुद्य कर्णेन वीरं; तदा नाशंसे विजयाय सञ्जय ||१३९||` | "And that Karṇa struck the hero with the end of his bow, then, O Sañjaya, I had no hope for victory. ||139||" |
| `Line 445: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 446: यदा द्रोणः कृतवर्मा कृपश्च; कर्णो द्रौणिर्मद्रराजश्च शूरः |` | "When Droṇa, Kṛtavarman, Kṛpa, Karṇa, Droṇi [Ashvatthāma], and the heroic king of Madra [Shalya]," |
| `Line 447: अमर्षयन्सैन्धवं वध्यमानं; तदा नाशंसे विजयाय सञ्जय ||१४०||` | "Could not prevent Saindhava [Jayadratha] from being slain, then, O Sañjaya, I had no hope for victory. ||140||" |
| `Line 448: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 449: यदाश्रौषं देवराजेन दत्तां; दिव्यां शक्तिं व्यंसितां माधवेन |` | "When I heard that the divine spear given by the king of gods [Indra] was thwarted by Mādhava [Krishna]," |
| `Line 450: घटोत्कचे राक्षसे घोररूपे; तदा नाशंसे विजयाय सञ्जय ||१४१||` | "When aimed at the terrifying rākṣasa [demon] Ghaṭotkaca, then, O Sañjaya, I had no hope for victory. ||141||" |
| `Line 451: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 452: यदाश्रौषं कर्णघटोत्कचाभ्यां; युद्धे मुक्तां सूतपुत्रेण शक्तिम् |` | "When I heard about the spear released by the son of a charioteer [Karna] in the battle between Karna and Ghatotkaca," |
| `Line 453: यया वध्यः समरे सव्यसाची; तदा नाशंसे विजयाय सञ्जय ||१४२||` | "By which the left-handed archer [Arjuna] was to be slain in battle, then, O Sanjaya, I despaired of victory. ||142||" |
| `Line 454: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 455: यदाश्रौषं द्रोणमाचार्यमेकं; धृष्टद्युम्नेनाभ्यतिक्रम्य धर्मम् |` | "When I heard that Drona, the teacher, alone was killed by Dhrishtadyumna, transgressing dharma [righteousness]," |
| `Line 456: रथोपस्थे प्रायगतं विशस्तं; तदा नाशंसे विजयाय सञ्जय ||१४३||` | "Slain while seated in his chariot, having nearly given up his life, then, O Sanjaya, I despaired of victory. ||143||" |
| `Line 457: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 458: यदाश्रौषं द्रौणिना द्वैरथस्थं; माद्रीपुत्रं नकुलं लोकमध्ये |` | "When I heard that Nakula, son of Madri, standing in a chariot duel with Drona's son [Ashvatthama] before the world," |
| `Line 459: समं युद्धे पाण्डवं युध्यमानं; तदा नाशंसे विजयाय सञ्जय ||१४४||` | "The Pandava fighting equally in battle, then, O Sanjaya, I despaired of victory. ||144||" |
| `Line 460: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 461: यदा द्रोणे निहते द्रोणपुत्रो; नारायणं दिव्यमस्त्रं विकुर्वन् |` | "When, after Drona was slain, his son [Ashvatthama] deployed the divine Narayana weapon [celestial missile]," |
| `Line 462: नैषामन्तं गतवान्पाण्डवानां; तदा नाशंसे विजयाय सञ्जय ||१४५||` | "Yet could not bring about the end of the Pandavas, then, O Sanjaya, I despaired of victory. ||145||" |
| `Line 463: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 464: यदाश्रौषं कर्णमत्यन्तशूरं; हतं पार्थेनाहवेष्वप्रधृष्यम् |` | "When I heard that Karna, the extremely valiant, unconquerable in battles, was slain by Partha [Arjuna]," |
| `Line 465: तस्मिन्भ्रातृणां विग्रहे देवगुह्ये; तदा नाशंसे विजयाय सञ्जय ||१४६||` | "In that mysterious conflict of brothers ordained by gods, then, O Sanjaya, I despaired of victory. ||146||" |
| `Line 466: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 467: यदाश्रौषं द्रोणपुत्रं कृपं च; दुःशासनं कृतवर्माणमुग्रम् |` | "When I heard that Drona's son [Ashvatthama], Kripa, Duhshasana, and the fierce Kritavarman," |
| `Line 468: युधिष्ठिरं शून्यमधर्षयन्तं; तदा नाशंसे विजयाय सञ्जय ||१४७||` | "Were unable to overcome Yudhishthira when he was alone, then, O Sanjaya, I despaired of victory. ||147||" |
| `Line 469: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 470: यदाश्रौषं निहतं मद्रराजं; रणे शूरं धर्मराजेन सूत |` | "When I heard that the king of Madra [Shalya], valiant in battle, was slain by Dharmaraja [Yudhishthira], O charioteer," |
| `Line 471: सदा सङ्ग्रामे स्पर्धते यः स कृष्णं; तदा नाशंसे विजयाय सञ्जय ||१४८||` | "He who always rivaled Krishna in combat, then, O Sanjaya, I despaired of victory. ||148||" |
| `Line 472: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 473: यदाश्रौषं कलहद्यूतमूलं; मायाबलं सौबलं पाण्डवेन |` | "When I heard that Soubala [Shakuni], the root cause of the gambling dispute, powerful in illusion," |
| `Line 474: हतं सङ्ग्रामे सहदेवेन पापं; तदा नाशंसे विजयाय सञ्जय ||१४९||` | "The sinful one, was slain in battle by Sahadeva, then, O Sanjaya, I despaired of victory. ||149||" |
| `Line 475: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 476: यदाश्रौषं श्रान्तमेकं शयानं; ह्रदं गत्वा स्तम्भयित्वा तदम्भः |` | "When I heard that the exhausted one was lying alone, having gone to the lake and frozen its waters," |
| `Line 477: दुर्योधनं विरथं भग्नदर्पं; तदा नाशंसे विजयाय सञ्जय ||१५०||` | "Duryodhana, chariotless and with broken pride - then, Sanjaya, I had no hope for victory. ||150||" |
| `Line 478: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 479: यदाश्रौषं पाण्डवांस्तिष्ठमाना; न्गङ्गाह्रदे वासुदेवेन सार्धम् |` | "When I heard that the Pandavas were standing at the Ganga lake [sacred river pool] together with Vasudeva [Krishna]," |
| `Line 480: अमर्षणं धर्षयतः सुतं मे; तदा नाशंसे विजयाय सञ्जय ||१५१||` | "Provoking my impatient son - then, Sanjaya, I had no hope for victory. ||151||" |
| `Line 481: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 482: यदाश्रौषं विविधांस्तात मार्गा; न्गदायुद्धे मण्डलं सञ्चरन्तम् |` | "When I heard, dear one, about the various paths he was moving in circular patterns during the mace duel," |
| `Line 483: मिथ्या हतं वासुदेवस्य बुद्ध्या; तदा नाशंसे विजयाय सञ्जय ||१५२||` | "And was falsely defeated by Vasudeva's [Krishna's] strategy - then, Sanjaya, I had no hope for victory. ||152||" |
| `Line 484: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 485: यदाश्रौषं द्रोणपुत्रादिभिस्तै; र्हतान्पाञ्चालान्द्रौपदेयांश्च सुप्तान् |` | "When I heard that by Drona's son [Ashvatthama] and others, the sleeping Panchalas and Draupadi's sons were slain," |
| `Line 486: कृतं बीभत्समयशस्यं च कर्म; तदा नाशंसे विजयाय सञ्जय ||१५३||` | "A horrible and inglorious deed was done - then, Sanjaya, I had no hope for victory. ||153||" |
| `Line 487: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 488: यदाश्रौषं भीमसेनानुयातेन; अश्वत्थाम्ना परमास्त्रं प्रयुक्तम् |` | "When I heard that Ashvatthama, pursued by Bhimasena, discharged the supreme weapon," |
| `Line 489: क्रुद्धेनैषीकमवधीद्येन गर्भं; तदा नाशंसे विजयाय सञ्जय ||१५४||` | "And in anger destroyed the fetus with his reed-weapon [Brahmastra] - then, Sanjaya, I had no hope for victory. ||154||" |
| `Line 490: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 491: यदाश्रौषं ब्रह्मशिरोऽर्जुनेन; मुक्तं स्वस्तीत्यस्त्रमस्त्रेण शान्तम् |` | "When I heard that the Brahma-weapon [divine missile] released by Arjuna neutralized the other weapon with a 'svasti' [blessing]," |
| `Line 492: अश्वत्थाम्ना मणिरत्नं च दत्तं; तदा नाशंसे विजयाय सञ्जय ||१५५||` | "And that Ashvatthama surrendered his jewel [head gem] - then, Sanjaya, I had no hope for victory. ||155||" |
| `Line 493: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 494: यदाश्रौषं द्रोणपुत्रेण गर्भे; वैराट्या वै पात्यमाने महास्त्रे |` | "When I heard that when Drona's son [Ashvatthama] directed the great weapon at the womb of Virata's daughter [Uttara]," |
| `Line 495: द्वैपायनः केशवो द्रोणपुत्रं; परस्परेणाभिशापैः शशाप ||१५६||` | "Dvaipayana [Vyasa] and Keshava [Krishna] cursed Drona's son with mutual curses - ||156||" |
| `Line 496: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 497: शोच्या गान्धारी पुत्रपौत्रैर्विहीना; तथा वध्वः पितृभिर्भ्रातृभिश्च |` | "Pitiable is Gandhari, bereft of sons and grandsons; likewise the daughters-in-law, of their fathers and brothers," |
| `Line 498: कृतं कार्यं दुष्करं पाण्डवेयैः; प्राप्तं राज्यमसपत्नं पुनस्तैः ||१५७||` | "The Pandavas have accomplished a difficult task; they have regained the kingdom without rivals. ||157||" |
| `Line 499: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 500: कष्टं युद्धे दश शेषाः श्रुता मे; त्रयोऽस्माकं पाण्डवानां च सप्त |` | "Alas! I have heard that only ten survived the war - three of ours and seven of the Pandavas," |
| `Line 501: द्व्यूना विंशतिराहताक्षौहिणीनां; तस्मिन्सङ्ग्रामे विग्रहे क्षत्रियाणाम् ॥१५८॥` | "Eighteen akshauhinis [army units] were destroyed in that battle, in that conflict of the kshatriyas [warrior class]. ||158||" |
| `Line 502: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 503: तमसा त्वभ्यवस्तीर्णो मोह आविशतीव माम् |` | "I am overcome by darkness, and delusion seems to enter me," |
| `Line 504: सञ्ज्ञां नोपलभे सूत मनो विह्वलतीव मे ॥१५९॥` | "I cannot maintain consciousness, O Suta [charioteer/bard], my mind seems to be bewildered. ||159||" |
| `Line 505: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 506: इत्युक्त्वा धृतराष्ट्रोऽथ विलप्य बहुदुःखितः |` | "Having spoken thus, Dhritarashtra then lamented, greatly distressed," |
| `Line 507: मूर्च्छितः पुनराश्वस्तः सञ्जयं वाक्यमब्रवीत् ॥१६०॥` | "Having fainted and regained consciousness, he spoke these words to Sanjaya. ||160||" |
| `Line 508: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 509: सञ्जयैवङ्गते प्राणांस्त्यक्तुमिच्छामि माचिरम् |` | "Sanjaya, in this situation, I wish to abandon my life without delay," |
| `Line 510: स्तोकं ह्यपि न पश्यामि फलं जीवितधारणे ॥१६१॥` | "For I see not even the slightest benefit in continuing to live. ||161||" |
| `Line 511: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 512: तं तथावादिनं दीनं विलपन्तं महीपतिम् |` | "To him who was speaking thus, miserable and lamenting, the ruler of the earth," |
| `Line 513: गावल्गणिरिदं धीमान्महार्थं वाक्यमब्रवीत् ॥१६२॥` | "Gavalgani [Sanjaya's patronymic] the wise one spoke these profound words. ||162||" |
| `Line 514: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 515: श्रुतवानसि वै राज्ञो महोत्साहान्महाबलान् |` | "You have indeed heard of kings of great enthusiasm and great strength," |
| `Line 516: द्वैपायनस्य वदतो नारदस्य च धीमतः ॥१६३॥` | "From the narrations of Dvaipayana [Vyasa] and the wise Narada. ||163||" |
| `Line 517: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 518: महत्सु राजवंशेषु गुणैः समुदितेषु च |` | "Born in great royal dynasties, endowed with excellent qualities," |
| `Line 519: जातान्दिव्यास्त्रविदुषः शक्रप्रतिमतेजसः ॥१६४॥` | "Born knowers of divine weapons, with splendor equal to Shakra [Indra]. ||164||" |
| `Line 520: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 521: धर्मेण पृथिवीं जित्वा यज्ञैरिष्ट्वाप्तदक्षिणैः |` | "Having conquered the earth righteously, having performed sacrifices with ample gifts," |
| `Line 522: अस्मिँल्लोके यशः प्राप्य ततः कालवशं गताः ॥१६५॥` | "Having attained fame in this world, they then succumbed to the power of time. ||165||" |
| `Line 523: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 524: वैन्यं महारथं वीरं सृञ्जयं जयतां वरम् |` | "Vainya [King Prithu] the great chariot-warrior, the heroic Srinjaya, foremost among conquerors," |
| `Line 525: सुहोत्रं रन्तिदेवं च कक्षीवन्तं तथौशिजम् ॥१६६॥` | "Suhotra, Rantideva, Kakshivanta, and also Aushija [Kakshivan's son]. ||166||" |
| `Line 526: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 527: बाह्लीकं दमनं शैब्यं शर्यातिमजितं जितम् |` | "Bāhlīka, Damana, Śaibya, Śaryāti, Ajita, Jita," |
| `Line 528: विश्वामित्रममित्रघ्नमम्बरीषं महाबलम् ||१६७||` | "Viśvāmitra the destroyer of enemies, Ambarīṣa of great strength. ||167||" |
| `Line 529: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 530: मरुत्तं मनुमिक्ष्वाकुं गयं भरतमेव च |` | "Marutta, Manu, Ikṣvāku, Gaya, and Bharata too," |
| `Line 531: रामं दाशरथिं चैव शशबिन्दुं भगीरथम् ||१६८||` | "And Rāma the son of Daśaratha, Śaśabindu, and Bhagīratha. ||168||" |
| `Line 532: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 533: ययातिं शुभकर्माणं देवैर्यो याजितः स्वयम् |` | "Yayāti of virtuous deeds, who was himself worshipped by the gods," |
| `Line 534: चैत्ययूपाङ्किता भूमिर्यस्येयं सवनाकरा ||१६९||` | "Whose land was marked with sacrificial posts [yūpa] and filled with sacred groves. ||169||" |
| `Line 535: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 536: इति राज्ञां चतुर्विंशन्नारदेन सुरर्षिणा |` | "Thus these twenty-four kings were by Nārada, the divine sage," |
| `Line 537: पुत्रशोकाभितप्ताय पुरा शैब्याय कीर्तिताः ||१७०||` | "Recounted in the past to Śaibya who was afflicted with grief for his son. ||170||" |
| `Line 538: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 539: तेभ्यश्चान्ये गताः पूर्वं राजानो बलवत्तराः |` | "And before them went other kings who were even mightier," |
| `Line 540: महारथा महात्मानो सर्वैः समुदिता गुणैः ||१७१||` | "Great chariot-warriors [maharathas], great souls, endowed with all excellent qualities. ||171||" |
| `Line 541: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 542: पूरुः कुरुर्यदुः शूरो विष्वगश्वो महाधृतिः |` | "Pūru, Kuru, Yadu, Śūra, Viṣvagaśva of great resolve," |
| `Line 543: अनेना युवनाश्वश्च ककुत्स्थो विक्रमी रघुः ||१७२||` | "Anena, Yuvanāśva, Kakutstha, and the valiant Raghu. ||172||" |
| `Line 544: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 545: विजिती वीतिहोत्रश्च भवः श्वेतो बृहद्गुरुः |` | "Vijitī, Vītihotra, Bhava, Śveta, Bṛhadguru," |
| `Line 546: उशीनरः शतरथः कङ्को दुलिदुहो द्रुमः ||१७३||` | "Uśīnara, Śataratha, Kaṅka, Duliduha, Druma. ||173||" |
| `Line 547: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 548: दम्भोद्भवः परो वेनः सगरः सङ्कृतिर्निमिः |` | "Dambhodbhava, Para, Vena, Sagara, Saṅkṛti, Nimi," |
| `Line 549: अजेयः परशुः पुण्ड्रः शम्भुर्देवावृधोऽनघः ||१७४||` | "Ajeya, Paraśu, Puṇḍra, Śambhu, Devāvṛdha the sinless one. ||174||" |
| `Line 550: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 551: देवाह्वयः सुप्रतिमः सुप्रतीको बृहद्रथः |` | "Devāhvaya, Supratima, Supratīka, Brihadratha," |
| `Line 552: महोत्साहो विनीतात्मा सुक्रतुर्नैषधो नलः ||१७५||` | "Mahotsāha, Vinītātmā, Sukratu, and Nala of Nishadha [famous king]. ||175||" |
| `Line 553: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 554: सत्यव्रतः शान्तभयः सुमित्रः सुबलः प्रभुः |` | "Satyavrata, Śāntabhaya, Sumitra, Subala, Prabhu," |
| `Line 555: जानुजङ्घोऽनरण्योऽर्कः प्रियभृत्यः शुभव्रतः ||१७६||` | "Jānujaṅgha, Anaraṇya, Arka, Priyabhṛtya, Śubhavrata. ||176||" |
| `Line 556: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 557: बलबन्धुर्निरामर्दः केतुशृङ्गो बृहद्बलः |` | "Balabandhu, Nirāmarda, Ketuśṛṅga, Brihadbala," |
| `Line 558: धृष्टकेतुर्बृहत्केतुर्दीप्तकेतुर्निरामयः ||१७७||` | "Dhṛṣṭaketu, Bṛhatketu, Dīptaketu, Nirāmaya. ||177||" |
| `Line 559: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 560: अविक्षित्प्रबलो धूर्तः कृतबन्धुर्दृढेषुधिः |` | "Avikṣit, Prabala, Dhūrta, Kṛtabandhu, Dṛḍheṣudhi," |
| `Line 561: महापुराणः सम्भाव्यः प्रत्यङ्गः परहा श्रुतिः ||१७८||` | "Mahāpurāṇa, Sambhāvya, Pratyaṅga, Parahā, Śruti. ||178||" |
| `Line 562: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 563: एते चान्ये च बहवः शतशोऽथ सहस्रशः |` | "These and many others, by hundreds and thousands," |
| `Line 564: श्रूयन्तेऽयुतशश्चान्ये सङ्ख्याताश्चापि पद्मशः ||१७९||` | "Are heard of in tens of thousands, and others counted by millions [padmas]. ||179||" |
| `Line 565: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 566: हित्वा सुविपुलान्भोगान्बुद्धिमन्तो महाबलाः |` | "Having abandoned vast enjoyments, these intelligent and mighty," |
| `Line 567: राजानो निधनं प्राप्तास्तव पुत्रैर्महत्तमाः ||१८०||` | "Greatest of kings have met their death at the hands of your sons. ||180||" |
| `Line 568: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 569: येषां दिव्यानि कर्माणि विक्रमस्त्याग एव च |` | "Whose divine deeds, valor, and generosity," |
| `Line 570: माहात्म्यमपि चास्तिक्यं सत्यता शौचमार्जवम् ||१८१||` | "As well as greatness, faith, truthfulness, purity, and straightforwardness, ||181||" |
| `Line 571: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 572: विद्वद्भिः कथ्यते लोके पुराणैः कविसत्तमैः |` | "Are spoken of in the world by the learned, by ancient [purāṇas] and excellent poets," |
| `Line 573: सर्वर्द्धिगुणसम्पन्नास्ते चापि निधनं गताः ||१८२||` | "They too, endowed with all prosperous qualities, have met their end. ||182||" |
| `Line 574: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 575: तव पुत्रा दुरात्मानः प्रतप्ताश्चैव मन्युना |` | "Your sons, evil-souled and consumed by anger," |
| `Line 576: लुब्धा दुर्वृत्तभूयिष्ठा न ताञ्शोचितुमर्हसि ||१८३||` | "They were greedy and mostly of bad conduct; you should not grieve for them. ||183||" |
| `Line 577: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 578: श्रुतवानसि मेधावी बुद्धिमान्प्राज्ञसंमतः |` | "You are learned, intelligent, wise, and respected by the wise." |
| `Line 579: येषां शास्त्रानुगा बुद्धिर्न ते मुह्यन्ति भारत ||१८४||` | "Those whose intellect follows the scriptures [śāstras] do not become deluded, O Bhārata [Dhritarashtra]. ||184||" |
| `Line 580: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 581: निग्रहानुग्रहौ चापि विदितौ ते नराधिप |` | "Punishment and favor are both known to you, O ruler of men." |
| `Line 582: नात्यन्तमेवानुवृत्तिः श्रूयते पुत्ररक्षणे ||१८५||` | "Excessive attachment is not prescribed in the protection of sons. ||185||" |
| `Line 583: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 584: भवितव्यं तथा तच्च नातः शोचितुमर्हसि |` | "What is destined to happen will happen thus; therefore you should not grieve." |
| `Line 585: दैवं प्रज्ञाविशेषेण को निवर्तितुमर्हति ||१८६||` | "Who can avert fate [divine will] even with exceptional wisdom? ||186||" |
| `Line 586: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 587: विधातृविहितं मार्गं न कश्चिदतिवर्तते |` | "No one can transgress the path ordained by the Creator [Vidhātṛ]." |
| `Line 588: कालमूलमिदं सर्वं भावाभावौ सुखासुखे ||१८७||` | "All this—existence and non-existence, happiness and sorrow—is rooted in Time [Kāla]. ||187||" |
| `Line 589: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 590: कालः पचति भूतानि कालः संहरति प्रजाः |` | "Time ripens all beings; Time destroys all creatures." |
| `Line 591: निर्दहन्तं प्रजाः कालं कालः शमयते पुनः ||१८८||` | "Time, which consumes all creatures, is itself pacified by Time again. ||188||" |
| `Line 592: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 593: कालो विकुरुते भावान्सर्वाँल्लोके शुभाशुभान् |` | "Time transforms all states in the world, both auspicious and inauspicious." |
| `Line 594: कालः सङ्क्षिपते सर्वाः प्रजा विसृजते पुनः ||१८९||` | "Time contracts all beings and creates them again. ||189||" |
| `Line 595: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 596: कालः सर्वेषु भूतेषु चरत्यविधृतः समः ||१८९||` | "Time moves among all beings, unrestrained and impartial. ||189||" |
| `Line 597: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 598: अतीतानागता भावा ये च वर्तन्ति साम्प्रतम् |` | "All conditions—past, future, and those existing at present—" |
| `Line 599: तान्कालनिर्मितान्बुद्ध्वा न सञ्ज्ञां हातुमर्हसि ||१९०||` | "Understanding them to be created by Time, you should not lose your composure. ||190||" |
| `Line 600: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 601: सूत उवाच||` | "Sūta [bard-narrator] said:" |
| `Line 602: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 603: अत्रोपनिषदं पुण्यां कृष्णद्वैपायनोऽब्रवीत् |` | "Here, Krishna Dvaipāyana [Vyāsa] spoke this sacred Upanishad [esoteric teaching]," |
| `Line 604: भारताध्ययनात्पुण्यादपि पादमधीयतः ||१९१||` | "Even for one who studies just a quarter of the holy Bhārata [Mahābhārata]. ||191||" |
| `Line 605: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 606: श्रद्दधानस्य पूयन्ते सर्वपापान्यशेषतः ||१९१||` | "For the one who has faith, all sins are purified completely. ||191||" |
| `Line 607: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 608: देवर्षयो ह्यत्र पुण्या ब्रह्मराजर्षयस्तथा |` | "Indeed, here the divine sages, the brahmarṣis [Brahmin sages] and rājarṣis [royal sages]," |
| `Line 609: कीर्त्यन्ते शुभकर्माणस्तथा यक्षमहोरगाः ||१९२||` | "Are glorified for their auspicious deeds, as well as the Yakṣas [demigods] and Mahoragas [great serpents]. ||192||" |
| `Line 610: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 611: भगवान्वासुदेवश्च कीर्त्यतेऽत्र सनातनः |` | "And Lord Vāsudeva [Krishna], the eternal one, is glorified here," |
| `Line 612: स हि सत्यमृतं चैव पवित्रं पुण्यमेव च ||१९३||` | "For he is truth, immortality, purity, and virtue indeed. ||193||" |
| `Line 613: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 614: शाश्वतं ब्रह्म परमं ध्रुवं ज्योतिः सनातनम् |` | "The eternal Brahman [Absolute], supreme, immutable, the eternal light," |
| `Line 615: यस्य दिव्यानि कर्माणि कथयन्ति मनीषिणः ||१९४||` | "Whose divine deeds the wise ones narrate. ||194||" |
| `Line 616: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 617: असत्सत्सदसच्चैव यस्माद्देवात्प्रवर्तते |` | "From which deity proceeds the unmanifest, the manifest, and that which is both manifest and unmanifest," |
| `Line 618: सन्ततिश्च प्रवृत्तिश्च जन्म मृत्युः पुनर्भवः ||१९५||` | "And continuity, activity, birth, death, and rebirth. ||195||" |
| `Line 619: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 620: अध्यात्मं श्रूयते यच्च पञ्चभूतगुणात्मकम् |` | "And what is heard as spiritual knowledge, composed of the qualities of the five elements," |
| `Line 621: अव्यक्तादि परं यच्च स एव परिगीयते ||१९६||` | "And that which is beyond the unmanifest beginning—He alone is celebrated. ||196||" |
| `Line 622: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 623: यत्तद्यतिवरा युक्ता ध्यानयोगबलान्विताः |` | "That which the best of ascetics [yatis], concentrated and endowed with the power of meditation yoga," |
| `Line 624: प्रतिबिम्बमिवादर्शे पश्यन्त्यात्मन्यवस्थितम् ||१९७||` | "See established in their own self, like a reflection in a mirror. ||197||" |
| `Line 625: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 626: श्रद्दधानः सदोद्युक्तः सत्यधर्मपरायणः |` | "One who is faithful, always diligent, and devoted to truth and righteousness," |
| `Line 627: आसेवन्निममध्यायं नरः पापात्प्रमुच्यते ||१९८||` | "A person who regularly studies this chapter is freed from sins. ||198||" |
| `Line 628: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 629: अनुक्रमणिमध्यायं भारतस्येममादितः |` | "This index chapter [anukramaṇi] of the Bharata from the beginning," |
| `Line 630: आस्तिकः सततं शृण्वन्न कृच्छ्रेष्ववसीदति ||१९९||` | "A believer [āstika] who constantly listens to it does not sink in difficulties. ||199||" |
| `Line 631: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 632: उभे सन्ध्ये जपन्किञ्चित्सद्यो मुच्येत किल्बिषात् |` | "One who recites even a little of it at both twilights [dawn and dusk] is immediately freed from sin," |
| `Line 633: अनुक्रमण्या यावत्स्यादह्ना रात्र्या च सञ्चितम् ||२००||` | "Whatever sins are accumulated during day and night, through the index [anukramaṇī]. ||200||" |
| `Line 634: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 635: भारतस्य वपुर्ह्येतत्सत्यं चामृतमेव च |` | "This is indeed the body of the Bharata, both truth and immortality," |
| `Line 636: नवनीतं यथा दध्नो द्विपदां ब्राह्मणो यथा ||२०१||` | "As butter is from curd, as the Brahmin is among bipeds [humans]. ||201||" |
| `Line 637: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 638: ह्रदानामुदधिः श्रेष्ठो गौर्वरिष्ठा चतुष्पदाम् |` | "As the ocean is the best among lakes, as the cow is the foremost among quadrupeds," |
| `Line 639: यथैतानि वरिष्ठानि तथा भारतमुच्यते ||२०२||` | "Just as these are the best, so is the Bharata declared to be. ||202||" |
| `Line 640: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 641: यश्चैनं श्रावयेच्छ्राद्धे ब्राह्मणान्पादमन्ततः |` | "Whoever recites this to Brahmins during a śrāddha [ancestral rite], even just a portion," |
| `Line 642: अक्षय्यमन्नपानं तत्पितृंस्तस्योपतिष्ठति ||२०३||` | "Inexhaustible food and drink reach his ancestors. ||203||" |
| `Line 643: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 644: इतिहासपुराणाभ्यां वेदं समुपबृंहयेत् |` | "One should supplement the Veda with Itihāsas [histories] and Purāṇas [ancient texts]," |
| `Line 645: बिभेत्यल्पश्रुताद्वेदो मामयं प्रतरिष्यति ||२०४||` | "The Veda fears one of little learning, thinking 'he will misinterpret me'. ||204||" |
| `Line 646: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 647: कार्ष्णं वेदमिमं विद्वाञ्श्रावयित्वार्थमश्नुते |` | "The learned one, having recited this Veda of Kṛṣṇa [Vyāsa's text], obtains wealth," |
| `Line 648: भ्रूणहत्याकृतं चापि पापं जह्यान्न संशयः ||२०५||` | "And even the sin of killing a fetus [brūṇahatyā] is abandoned, without doubt. ||205||" |
| `Line 649: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 650: य इमं शुचिरध्यायं पठेत्पर्वणि पर्वणि |` | "Whoever, being pure, recites this chapter at each parvan [sacred occasion]," |
| `Line 651: अधीतं भारतं तेन कृत्स्नं स्यादिति मे मतिः ||२०६||` | "The entire Bharata would be studied by him - this is my belief. ||206||" |
| `Line 652: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 653: यश्चेमं शृणुयान्नित्यमार्षं श्रद्धासमन्वितः |` | "And whoever listens to this sage-composed [ārṣa] text regularly with faith," |
| `Line 654: स दीर्घमायुः कीर्तिं च स्वर्गतिं चाप्नुयान्नरः ||२०७||` | "That person attains long life, fame, and the path to heaven [svargati]. ||207||" |
| `Line 655: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 656: चत्वार एकतो वेदा भारतं चैकमेकतः |` | "The four Vedas on one side and the Bharata alone on the other side," |
| `Line 657: समागतैः सुरर्षिभिस्तुलामारोपितं पुरा ||२०८||` | "Were placed on a scale by the assembled divine sages [surarṣi] in ancient times. ||208||" |
| `Line 658: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 659: महत्त्वे च गुरुत्वे च ध्रियमाणं ततोऽधिकम् ||२०८||` | "And in greatness and weight, it was held to be superior. ||208||" |
| `Line 660: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 661: महत्त्वाद्भारवत्त्वाच्च महाभारतमुच्यते |` | "Due to its greatness [mahattva] and weightiness [bhāravattva], it is called the Mahābhārata," |
| `Line 662: निरुक्तमस्य यो वेद सर्वपापैः प्रमुच्यते ||२०९||` | "One who knows this etymology [nirukta] is freed from all sins. ||209||" |
| `Line 663: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 664: तपो न कल्कोऽध्ययनं न कल्कः; स्वाभाविको वेदविधिर्न कल्कः |` | "Austerity is not impurity [kalka], study is not impurity; the natural Vedic procedure is not impurity;" |
| `Line 665: प्रसह्य वित्ताहरणं न कल्क; स्तान्येव भावोपहतानि कल्कः ||२१०||` | "Forcible taking of wealth is not impurity; these very things when corrupted by evil intent become impurity. ||210||" |
| `Line 666: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 667: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 668: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 669: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 670: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 671: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 672: पर्वसंग्रहपर्व` | "Parvasaṃgraha Parva [Chapter summarizing sections]" |
| `Line 673: २` | "2" |
| `Line 674: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 675: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 676: ऋषय ऊचुः॥` | "The sages said:" |
| `Line 677: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 678: समन्तपञ्चकमिति यदुक्तं सूतनन्दन |` | "O Sūta-nandana [son of Sūta], what has been mentioned as Samantapañcaka [five lakes region]," |
| `Line 679: एतत्सर्वं यथान्यायं श्रोतुमिच्छामहे वयम् ॥१॥` | "All this we wish to hear properly in detail. ||1||" |
| `Line 680: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 681: सूत उवाच॥` | "Sūta said:" |
| `Line 682: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 683: शुश्रूषा यदि वो विप्रा ब्रुवतश्च कथाः शुभाः |` | "If you, O Vipras [learned Brahmins], wish to listen to auspicious stories from me," |
| `Line 684: समन्तपञ्चकाख्यं च श्रोतुमर्हथ सत्तमाः ॥२॥` | "Then you deserve to hear about the place called Samantapañcaka, O excellent ones. ||2||" |
| `Line 685: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 686: त्रेताद्वापरयोः सन्धौ रामः शस्त्रभृतां वरः |` | "At the junction of Tretā and Dvāpara [yugas/ages], Rāma [Paraśurāma], the best among weapon-bearers," |
| `Line 687: असकृत्पार्थिवं क्षत्रं जघानामर्षचोदितः ॥३॥` | "Repeatedly slaughtered the Kṣatriya [warrior] class, impelled by anger. ||3||" |
| `Line 688: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 689: स सर्वं क्षत्रमुत्साद्य स्ववीर्येणानलद्युतिः |` | "Having exterminated the entire Kṣatriya class by his own prowess, he who had the brilliance of fire," |
| `Line 690: समन्तपञ्चके पञ्च चकार रुधिरह्रदान् ॥४॥` | "Created five lakes of blood at Samantapañcaka. ||4||" |
| `Line 691: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 692: स तेषु रुधिराम्भस्सु ह्रदेषु क्रोधमूर्च्छितः |` | "In those lakes filled with bloody waters, overcome with rage," |
| `Line 693: पितृन्सन्तर्पयामास रुधिरेणेति नः श्रुतम् ॥५॥` | "He satisfied his ancestors with blood offerings - thus we have heard. ||5||" |
| `Line 694: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 695: अथर्चीकादयोऽभ्येत्य पितरो ब्राह्मणर्षभम् |` | "Then, approaching the bull among Brahmins [Paraśurāma], his ancestors led by Ṛcīka," |
| `Line 696: तं क्षमस्वेति सिषिधुस्ततः स विरराम ह ॥६॥` | "Restrained him saying, 'Desist from this,' and then he stopped. ||6||" |
| `Line 697: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 698: तेषां समीपे यो देशो ह्रदानां रुधिराम्भसाम् |` | "That region which is near those lakes of bloody waters," |
| `Line 699: समन्तपञ्चकमिति पुण्यं तत्परिकीर्तितम् ॥७॥` | "Is celebrated as the sacred Samantapañcaka. ||7||" |
| `Line 700: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 701: येन लिङ्गेन यो देशो युक्तः समुपलक्ष्यते |` | "By which characteristic a region is observed to be distinguished," |
| `Line 702: तेनैव नाम्ना तं देशं वाच्यमाहुर्मनीषिणः ||८||` | "By that very name that region should be called, say the wise ones. ||8||" |
| `Line 703: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 704: अन्तरे चैव सम्प्राप्ते कलिद्वापरयोरभूत् |` | "And when the interval between Kali [dark age] and Dvapara [third age] arrived," |
| `Line 705: समन्तपञ्चके युद्धं कुरुपाण्डवसेनयोः ||९||` | "At Samantapanchaka [five lakes region] occurred the war between the armies of the Kurus and Pandavas. ||9||" |
| `Line 706: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 707: तस्मिन्परमधर्मिष्ठे देशे भूदोषवर्जिते |` | "In that most righteous region, free from defects of the earth," |
| `Line 708: अष्टादश समाजग्मुरक्षौहिण्यो युयुत्सया ||१०||` | "Eighteen akshauhinis [army divisions] assembled with the desire to fight. ||10||" |
| `Line 709: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 710: एवं नामाभिनिर्वृत्तं तस्य देशस्य वै द्विजाः |` | "Thus the derivation of the name of that region, O twice-born [Brahmins]," |
| `Line 711: पुण्यश्च रमणीयश्च स देशो वः प्रकीर्तितः ||११||` | "That sacred and delightful region has been described to you. ||11||" |
| `Line 712: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 713: तदेतत्कथितं सर्वं मया वो मुनिसत्तमाः |` | "All this has been told by me to you, O best of sages," |
| `Line 714: यथा देशः स विख्यातस्त्रिषु लोकेषु विश्रुतः ||१२||` | "How that region became renowned, celebrated in the three worlds [heaven, earth, netherworld]. ||12||" |
| `Line 715: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 716: ऋषय ऊचुः||` | "The sages said:" |
| `Line 717: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 718: अक्षौहिण्य इति प्रोक्तं यत्त्वया सूतनन्दन |` | "What you have mentioned as 'akshauhinis', O son of Suta [bard/charioteer]," |
| `Line 719: एतदिच्छामहे श्रोतुं सर्वमेव यथातथम् ||१३||` | "We wish to hear all about this exactly as it is. ||13||" |
| `Line 720: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 721: अक्षौहिण्याः परीमाणं रथाश्वनरदन्तिनाम् |` | "The measure of an akshauhini in terms of chariots, horses, men, and elephants," |
| `Line 722: यथावच्चैव नो ब्रूहि सर्वं हि विदितं तव ||१४||` | "Tell us properly, for everything is known to you. ||14||" |
| `Line 723: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 724: सूत उवाच||` | "Suta [bard/narrator] said:" |
| `Line 725: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 726: एको रथो गजश्चैको नराः पञ्च पदातयः |` | "One chariot, one elephant, five men as foot-soldiers," |
| `Line 727: त्रयश्च तुरगास्तज्ज्ञैः पत्तिरित्यभिधीयते ||१५||` | "And three horses - by those who know, this is called a patti [basic military unit]. ||15||" |
| `Line 728: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 729: पत्तिं तु त्रिगुणामेतामाहुः सेनामुखं बुधाः |` | "The wise call three such pattis a senāmukha [battalion head]," |
| `Line 730: त्रीणि सेनामुखान्येको गुल्म इत्यभिधीयते ||१६||` | "Three senāmukhas are called one gulma [troop division]. ||16||" |
| `Line 731: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 732: त्रयो गुल्मा गणो नाम वाहिनी तु गणास्त्रयः |` | "Three gulmas are named a gaṇa [brigade], and three gaṇas are a vāhinī [division]," |
| `Line 733: स्मृतास्तिस्रस्तु वाहिन्यः पृतनेति विचक्षणैः ||१७||` | "Three vāhinīs are remembered by the discerning as a pṛtanā [army corps]. ||17||" |
| `Line 734: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 735: चमूस्तु पृतनास्तिस्रस्तिस्रश्चम्वस्त्वनीकिनी |` | "Three pṛtanās make a camū [army], and three camūs make an anīkinī [large army]," |
| `Line 736: अनीकिनीं दशगुणां प्राहुरक्षौहिणीं बुधाः ||१८||` | "The wise declare ten anīkinīs to be an akṣauhiṇī [complete army]. ||18||" |
| `Line 737: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 738: अक्षौहिण्याः प्रसङ्ख्यानं रथानां द्विजसत्तमाः |` | "The enumeration of chariots in an akṣauhiṇī, O best of twice-born [Brahmins]," |
| `Line 739: सङ्ख्यागणिततत्त्वज्ञैः सहस्राण्येकविंशतिः ||१९||` | "According to those who know the principles of numerical calculation, is twenty-one thousand. ||19||" |
| `Line 740: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 741: शतान्युपरि चैवाष्टौ तथा भूयश्च सप्ततिः |` | "And eight hundred, and furthermore seventy," |
| `Line 742: गजानां तु परीमाणमेतदेवात्र निर्दिशेत् ||२०||` | "The measure of elephants should be indicated as exactly the same here. ||20||" |
| `Line 743: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 744: ज्ञेयं शतसहस्रं तु सहस्राणि तथा नव |` | "It should be known that one hundred thousand and nine thousand," |
| `Line 745: नराणामपि पञ्चाशच्छतानि त्रीणि चानघाः ||२१||` | "And fifty and three hundred men, O sinless ones [sages]. ||21||" |
| `Line 746: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 747: पञ्चषष्टिसहस्राणि तथाश्वानां शतानि च |` | "Sixty-five thousand, and hundreds of horses," |
| `Line 748: दशोत्तराणि षट्प्राहुर्यथावदिह सङ्ख्यया ||२२||` | "Six hundred and ten more, they declare here according to the proper count. ||22||" |
| `Line 749: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 750: एतामक्षौहिणीं प्राहुः सङ्ख्यातत्त्वविदो जनाः |` | "This is what those who know the principles of enumeration declare to be an akṣauhiṇī [complete army]." |
| `Line 751: यां वः कथितवानस्मि विस्तरेण द्विजोत्तमाः ||२३||` | "Which I have narrated to you in detail, O best of the twice-born [Brahmins]. ||23||" |
| `Line 752: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 753: एतया सङ्ख्यया ह्यासन्कुरुपाण्डवसेनयोः |` | "According to this enumeration, the armies of the Kurus and Pandavas" |
| `Line 754: अक्षौहिण्यो द्विजश्रेष्ठाः पिण्डेनाष्टादशैव ताः ||२४||` | "Consisted of exactly eighteen akshauhinis [complete armies] in total, O foremost of the twice-born. ||24||" |
| `Line 755: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 756: समेतास्तत्र वै देशे तत्रैव निधनं गताः |` | "Assembled in that place, they met their destruction in that very place," |
| `Line 757: कौरवान्कारणं कृत्वा कालेनाद्भुतकर्मणा ||२५||` | "With the Kauravas as the cause, by Time [destiny] of wonderful deeds. ||25||" |
| `Line 758: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 759: अहानि युयुधे भीष्मो दशैव परमास्त्रवित् |` | "Bhishma, the supreme weapon-knower, fought for exactly ten days," |
| `Line 760: अहानि पञ्च द्रोणस्तु ररक्ष कुरुवाहिनीम् ||२६||` | "While Drona protected the Kuru army for five days. ||26||" |
| `Line 761: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 762: अहनी युयुधे द्वे तु कर्णः परबलार्दनः |` | "Karna, the tormentor of enemy forces, fought for two days," |
| `Line 763: शल्योऽर्धदिवसं त्वासीद्गदायुद्धमतः परम् ||२७||` | "Shalya was (commander) for half a day, and after that was the mace duel. ||27||" |
| `Line 764: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 765: तस्यैव तु दिनस्यान्ते हार्दिक्यद्रौणिगौतमाः |` | "At the end of that very day, Hardikya [Kritavarma], Drauni [Ashvatthama], and Gautama [Kripa]" |
| `Line 766: प्रसुप्तं निशि विश्वस्तं जघ्नुर्यौधिष्ठिरं बलम् ||२८||` | "Slew the sleeping, unsuspecting Pandava army at night. ||28||" |
| `Line 767: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 768: यत्तु शौनकसत्रे ते भारताख्यानविस्तरम् |` | "But in Shaunaka's sacrificial session, the detailed narration of the Bharata story" |
| `Line 769: आख्यास्ये तत्र पौलोममाख्यानं चादितः परम् ||२९||` | "I shall narrate there, beginning with the excellent Pauloma tale. ||29||" |
| `Line 770: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 771: विचित्रार्थपदाख्यानमनेकसमयान्वितम् |` | "A narrative with diverse meanings and words, containing many contexts," |
| `Line 772: अभिपन्नं नरैः प्राज्ञैर्वैराग्यमिव मोक्षिभिः ||३०||` | "Sought after by wise men, like detachment is by those seeking liberation. ||30||" |
| `Line 773: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 774: आत्मेव वेदितव्येषु प्रियेष्विव च जीवितम् |` | "Like the Self among things to be known, like life among things dear," |
| `Line 775: इतिहासः प्रधानार्थः श्रेष्ठः सर्वागमेष्वयम् ||३१||` | "This history [Mahabharata] with its principal meaning is the best among all scriptures. ||31||" |
| `Line 776: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 777: इतिहासोत्तमे ह्यस्मिन्नर्पिता बुद्धिरुत्तमा |` | "In this supreme historical narrative [itihāsa], the finest intellect has been invested," |
| `Line 778: स्वरव्यञ्जनयोः कृत्स्ना लोकवेदाश्रयेव वाक् ||३२||` | "Complete in vowels and consonants, like speech founded on worldly knowledge and Vedas. ||32||" |
| `Line 779: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 780: अस्य प्रज्ञाभिपन्नस्य विचित्रपदपर्वणः |` | "Of this wisdom-filled narrative with its diverse chapters and sections," |
| `Line 781: भारतस्येतिहासस्य श्रूयतां पर्वसङ्ग्रहः ||३३||` | "Listen to the summary of sections of the historical narrative [itihāsa] of Bharata. ||33||" |
| `Line 782: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 783: पर्वानुक्रमणी पूर्वं द्वितीयं पर्वसङ्ग्रहः |` | "First is the table of contents [Parvānukramaṇī], second is the summary of sections [Parvasaṅgraha]," |
| `Line 784: पौष्यं पौलोममास्तीकमादिवंशावतारणम् ||३४||` | "The Paushya, Pauloma, Āstīka, and the Descent of the First Dynasty [Ādivaṃśāvataraṇa]. ||34||" |
| `Line 785: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 786: ततः सम्भवपर्वोक्तमद्भुतं देवनिर्मितम् |` | "Then comes the marvelous divine-created section called Sambhava [Origin]," |
| `Line 787: दाहो जतुगृहस्यात्र हैडिम्बं पर्व चोच्यते ||३५||` | "The burning of the lac house is here, and the section called Hiḍimba is mentioned. ||35||" |
| `Line 788: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 789: ततो बकवधः पर्व पर्व चैत्ररथं ततः |` | "Then comes the section on the slaying of Baka, and then the Chaitraratha section," |
| `Line 790: ततः स्वयंवरं देव्याः पाञ्चाल्याः पर्व चोच्यते ||३६||` | "Then is mentioned the section on the self-choice [svayaṃvara] of the Panchala princess [Draupadi]. ||36||" |
| `Line 791: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 792: क्षत्रधर्मेण निर्जित्य ततो वैवाहिकं स्मृतम् |` | "Having conquered according to Kshatriya duty, then comes the section on marriage [Vaivāhika]," |
| `Line 793: विदुरागमनं पर्व राज्यलम्भस्तथैव च ||३७||` | "The section on Vidura's arrival, and likewise the obtaining of the kingdom. ||37||" |
| `Line 794: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 795: अर्जुनस्य वने वासः सुभद्राहरणं ततः |` | "Arjuna's dwelling in the forest, then the abduction of Subhadra," |
| `Line 796: सुभद्राहरणादूर्ध्वं ज्ञेयं हरणहारिकम् ||३८||` | "After the abduction of Subhadra, know the section called Haraṇahārika [Gifts after abduction]. ||38||" |
| `Line 797: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 798: ततः खाण्डवदाहाख्यं तत्रैव मयदर्शनम् |` | "Then the section called the burning of Khandava forest, and therein the appearance of Maya [architect]," |
| `Line 799: सभापर्व ततः प्रोक्तं मन्त्रपर्व ततः परम् ||३९||` | "Then is declared the Assembly Hall section [Sabhāparva], and after that the Council section [Mantraparva]. ||39||" |
| `Line 800: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 801: जरासन्धवधः पर्व पर्व दिग्विजयस्तथा |` | "The chapter of Jarāsandha's slaying, and likewise the chapter of world conquest [digvijaya]," |
| `Line 802: पर्व दिग्विजयादूर्ध्वं राजसूयिकमुच्यते ||४०||` | "After the chapter of world conquest, the chapter concerning the Rājasūya [royal consecration] is described. ||40||" |
| `Line 803: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 804: ततश्चार्घाभिहरणं शिशुपालवधस्ततः |` | "Then the offering of honors [arghya], and after that the slaying of Śiśupāla," |
| `Line 805: द्यूतपर्व ततः प्रोक्तमनुद्यूतमतः परम् ||४१||` | "Then is described the Gambling chapter, and after that the Consequent Gambling chapter. ||41||" |
| `Line 806: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 807: तत आरण्यकं पर्व किर्मीरवध एव च |` | "Then the Forest chapter, and also the slaying of Kirmīra," |
| `Line 808: ईश्वरार्जुनयोर्युद्धं पर्व कैरातसञ्ज्ञितम् ||४२||` | "The battle between Īśvara [Śiva] and Arjuna, the chapter known as Kirāta [hunter form of Śiva]. ||42||" |
| `Line 809: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 810: इन्द्रलोकाभिगमनं पर्व ज्ञेयमतः परम् |` | "After that should be known the chapter of the journey to Indra's world [heaven]," |
| `Line 811: तीर्थयात्रा ततः पर्व कुरुराजस्य धीमतः ||४३||` | "Then the chapter of the pilgrimage of the wise Kuru king [Yudhiṣṭhira]. ||43||" |
| `Line 812: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 813: जटासुरवधः पर्व यक्षयुद्धमतः परम् |` | "The chapter of Jaṭāsura's slaying, and after that the battle with the Yakṣa [supernatural being]," |
| `Line 814: तथैवाजगरं पर्व विज्ञेयं तदनन्तरम् ||४४||` | "And likewise the Ajagara [python] chapter should be known thereafter. ||44||" |
| `Line 815: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 816: मार्कण्डेयसमस्या च पर्वोक्तं तदनन्तरम् |` | "And the chapter of Mārkaṇḍeya's discourse is described thereafter," |
| `Line 817: संवादश्च ततः पर्व द्रौपदीसत्यभामयोः ||४५||` | "And then the chapter of the conversation between Draupadī and Satyabhāmā. ||45||" |
| `Line 818: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 819: घोषयात्रा ततः पर्व मृगस्वप्नभयं ततः |` | "Then the chapter of the journey to Ghoṣa, then the fear from the deer dream," |
| `Line 820: व्रीहिद्रौणिकमाख्यानं ततोऽनन्तरमुच्यते ||४६||` | "The story of the measure of rice [vrīhidroṇika] is described immediately after that. ||46||" |
| `Line 821: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 822: द्रौपदीहरणं पर्व सैन्धवेन वनात्ततः |` | "The chapter of Draupadī's abduction from the forest by Saindhava [Jayadratha]," |
| `Line 823: कुण्डलाहरणं पर्व ततः परमिहोच्यते ||४७||` | "The chapter of the taking of the earrings is described here after that. ||47||" |
| `Line 824: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 825: आरणेयं ततः पर्व वैराटं तदनन्तरम् |` | "Then the Āraṇeya chapter, and after that the Virāṭa chapter," |
| `Line 826: कीचकानां वधः पर्व पर्व गोग्रहणं ततः ||४८||` | "The section on the slaying of the Kīcakas [Matsya generals], and then the section on the cattle-raid [Go-grahaṇa]. ||48||" |
| `Line 827: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 828: अभिमन्युना च वैराट्याः पर्व वैवाहिकं स्मृतम् |` | "The section on the marriage of Abhimanyu with the princess of Virāṭa [Uttarā] is remembered as the wedding section." |
| `Line 829: उद्योगपर्व विज्ञेयमत ऊर्ध्वं महाद्भुतम् ||४९||` | "After this, the highly wonderful Udyoga Parva [Effort section] should be known. ||49||" |
| `Line 830: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 831: ततः सञ्जययानाख्यं पर्व ज्ञेयमतः परम् |` | "Then after this, the section known as Sañjaya-yāna [Sanjaya's journey] should be known." |
| `Line 832: प्रजागरं ततः पर्व धृतराष्ट्रस्य चिन्तया ||५०||` | "Then the section called Prajāgara [Sleepless night], with Dhritarashtra's anxieties. ||50||" |
| `Line 833: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 834: पर्व सानत्सुजातं च गुह्यमध्यात्मदर्शनम् |` | "And the Sanat-sujāta section, containing secret spiritual knowledge [metaphysical teachings]." |
| `Line 835: यानसन्धिस्ततः पर्व भगवद्यानमेव च ||५१||` | "Then the section on Yāna-sandhi [Preparation for march], and also the section on Bhagavad-yāna [Lord's journey]. ||51||" |
| `Line 836: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 837: ज्ञेयं विवादपर्वात्र कर्णस्यापि महात्मनः |` | "Here should be known the section on the dispute of the noble-souled Karṇa." |
| `Line 838: निर्याणं पर्व च ततः कुरुपाण्डवसेनयोः ||५२||` | "And then the section on the marching forth of the armies of the Kurus and Pāṇḍavas. ||52||" |
| `Line 839: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 840: रथातिरथसङ्ख्या च पर्वोक्तं तदनन्तरम् |` | "And after that is described the section on the enumeration of charioteers and great charioteers [military rankings]." |
| `Line 841: उलूकदूतागमनं पर्वामर्षविवर्धनम् ||५३||` | "The section on the arrival of Ulūka as messenger, which increases anger [provocation]. ||53||" |
| `Line 842: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 843: अम्बोपाख्यानमपि च पर्व ज्ञेयमतः परम् |` | "And after this should be known the section containing the story of Ambā [Bhishma's nemesis]." |
| `Line 844: भीष्माभिषेचनं पर्व ज्ञेयमद्भुतकारणम् ||५४||` | "The section on the installation of Bhīṣma [as commander], which should be known as causing wonder. ||54||" |
| `Line 845: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 846: जम्बूखण्डविनिर्माणं पर्वोक्तं तदनन्तरम् |` | "After that is described the section on the formation of Jambū-khaṇḍa [geography of India]." |
| `Line 847: भूमिपर्व ततो ज्ञेयं द्वीपविस्तरकीर्तनम् ||५५||` | "Then should be known the Bhūmi Parva [Earth section], describing the extent of the continents [world geography]. ||55||" |
| `Line 848: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 849: पर्वोक्तं भगवद्गीता पर्व भीष्मवधस्ततः |` | "Then is described the section on the Bhagavad Gītā [divine song], and after that the section on the slaying of Bhīṣma." |
| `Line 850: द्रोणाभिषेकः पर्वोक्तं संशप्तकवधस्ततः ||५६||` | "The section on the installation of Droṇa [as commander] is described, and then the slaying of the Saṃśaptakas [oath-bound warriors]. ||56||" |
| `Line 851: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 852: अभिमन्युवधः पर्व प्रतिज्ञापर्व चोच्यते |` | "The Abhimanyu-vadha Parva [Abhimanyu's death section] and the Pratijñā Parva [vow section] are described." |
| `Line 853: जयद्रथवधः पर्व घटोत्कचवधस्ततः ||५७||` | "Then the Jayadratha-vadha Parva [Jayadratha's death section] and after that the Ghatotkaca-vadha [Ghatotkaca's death section]. ||57||" |
| `Line 854: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 855: ततो द्रोणवधः पर्व विज्ञेयं लोमहर्षणम् |` | "Then comes the Drona-vadha Parva [Drona's death section], which should be known as hair-raising [terrifying]." |
| `Line 856: मोक्षो नारायणास्त्रस्य पर्वानन्तरमुच्यते ||५८||` | "The release of the Nārāyaṇāstra [divine weapon] is described in the section immediately following. ||58||" |
| `Line 857: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 858: कर्णपर्व ततो ज्ञेयं शल्यपर्व ततः परम् |` | "Then should be known the Karna Parva [Karna section], and after that the Shalya Parva [Shalya section]." |
| `Line 859: ह्रदप्रवेशनं पर्व गदायुद्धमतः परम् ||५९||` | "The Hrada-praveshana Parva [lake-entering section] and after that the Gadāyuddha [mace battle section]. ||59||" |
| `Line 860: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 861: सारस्वतं ततः पर्व तीर्थवंशगुणान्वितम् |` | "Then the Sarasvata Parva [Sarasvati river section], endowed with the qualities of pilgrimage places and lineages." |
| `Line 862: अत ऊर्ध्वं तु बीभत्सं पर्व सौप्तिकमुच्यते ||६०||` | "After this comes the dreadful Sauptika Parva [sleeping warriors section]. ||60||" |
| `Line 863: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 864: ऐषीकं पर्व निर्दिष्टमत ऊर्ध्वं सुदारुणम् |` | "The Aishika Parva [arrow section] is designated next, which is extremely terrible." |
| `Line 865: जलप्रदानिकं पर्व स्त्रीपर्व च ततः परम् ||६१||` | "The Jala-pradānika Parva [water-offering section] and after that the Stri Parva [women's section]. ||61||" |
| `Line 866: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 867: श्राद्धपर्व ततो ज्ञेयं कुरूणामौर्ध्वदेहिकम् |` | "Then should be known the Shraddha Parva [funeral rites section], concerning the post-death ceremonies of the Kurus." |
| `Line 868: आभिषेचनिकं पर्व धर्मराजस्य धीमतः ||६२||` | "The Abhishechanika Parva [coronation section] of the wise Dharmaraja [Yudhishthira]. ||62||" |
| `Line 869: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 870: चार्वाकनिग्रहः पर्व रक्षसो ब्रह्मरूपिणः |` | "The Charvaka-nigraha Parva [Charvaka's punishment section], about the demon in Brahmin form." |
| `Line 871: प्रविभागो गृहाणां च पर्वोक्तं तदनन्तरम् ||६३||` | "And the distribution of households section is described immediately after that. ||63||" |
| `Line 872: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 873: शान्तिपर्व ततो यत्र राजधर्मानुकीर्तनम् |` | "Then the Shanti Parva [peace section], wherein is the exposition of Raja-dharma [royal duties]." |
| `Line 874: आपद्धर्मश्च पर्वोक्तं मोक्षधर्मस्ततः परम् ||६४||` | "And the Apad-dharma [emergency duties] section is described, followed by the Moksha-dharma [liberation principles]. ||64||" |
| `Line 875: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 876: ततः पर्व परिज्ञेयमानुशासनिकं परम् |` | "Then should be known the supreme Anuśāsanika Parva [Instruction section]," |
| `Line 877: स्वर्गारोहणिकं पर्व ततो भीष्मस्य धीमतः ||६५||` | "And then the Svargārohaṇika Parva [Ascent to Heaven section] of the wise Bhīṣhma. ||65||" |
| `Line 878: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 879: ततोऽश्वमेधिकं पर्व सर्वपापप्रणाशनम् |` | "Then the Aśvamedhika Parva [Horse Sacrifice section], which destroys all sins," |
| `Line 880: अनुगीता ततः पर्व ज्ञेयमध्यात्मवाचकम् ||६६||` | "Then should be known the Anugītā Parva [Subsequent Song section], which speaks of spiritual knowledge. ||66||" |
| `Line 881: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 882: पर्व चाश्रमवासाख्यं पुत्रदर्शनमेव च |` | "And the section called Āśramavāsa [Forest Dwelling] and also the seeing of sons," |
| `Line 883: नारदागमनं पर्व ततः परमिहोच्यते ||६७||` | "Then the section called Nāradāgamana [Nārada's Arrival] is described here next. ||67||" |
| `Line 884: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 885: मौसलं पर्व च ततो घोरं समनुवर्ण्यते |` | "Then the terrible Mausala Parva [Club section] is described," |
| `Line 886: महाप्रस्थानिकं पर्व स्वर्गारोहणिकं ततः ||६८||` | "The Mahāprasthānika Parva [Great Departure section], and then the Svargārohaṇika [Ascent to Heaven section]. ||68||" |
| `Line 887: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 888: हरिवंशस्ततः पर्व पुराणं खिलसञ्ज्ञितम् |` | "Then the Harivaṃśa Parva [Hari's Lineage section], a Purāṇa [ancient text] known as a supplement," |
| `Line 889: भविष्यत्पर्व चाप्युक्तं खिलेष्वेवाद्भुतं महत् ||६९||` | "And also the Bhaviṣyat Parva [Future section] is mentioned, a great and wonderful supplement. ||69||" |
| `Line 890: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 891: एतत्पर्वशतं पूर्णं व्यासेनोक्तं महात्मना |` | "This complete hundred of sections was narrated by the great-souled Vyāsa," |
| `Line 892: यथावत्सूतपुत्रेण लोमहर्षणिना पुनः ||७०||` | "And then properly retold by the son of a sūta [bard], Lomaharṣaṇa. ||70||" |
| `Line 893: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 894: कथितं नैमिषारण्ये पर्वाण्यष्टादशैव तु |` | "Narrated in the Naimiṣāraṇya [Naimiṣa forest], these eighteen sections," |
| `Line 895: समासो भारतस्यायं तत्रोक्तः पर्वसङ्ग्रहः ||७१||` | "This is the summary of the Bhārata, the collection of sections described therein. ||71||" |
| `Line 896: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 897: पौष्ये पर्वणि माहात्म्यमुत्तङ्कस्योपवर्णितम् |` | "In the Pauṣya Parva [Pauṣya section], the greatness of Uttaṅka is described," |
| `Line 898: पौलोमे भृगुवंशस्य विस्तारः परिकीर्तितः ||७२||` | "In the Pauloma [Pauloma section], the expansion of Bhṛgu's lineage is celebrated. ||72||" |
| `Line 899: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 900: आस्तीके सर्वनागानां गरुडस्य च सम्भवः |` | "In the Āstīka [Āstīka section], the origin of all serpents and of Garuḍa [divine eagle]," |
| `Line 901: क्षीरोदमथनं चैव जन्मोच्छैःश्रवसस्तथा ||७३||` | "And the churning of the milk ocean [Kshīroda], as well as the birth of Uchchaihshravas [divine horse]. ||73||" |
| `Line 902: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 903: यजतः सर्पसत्रेण राज्ञः पारिक्षितस्य च |` | "And of King Parikshit performing the snake sacrifice [Sarpa-satra]," |
| `Line 904: कथेयमभिनिर्वृत्ता भारतानां महात्मनाम् ||७४||` | "This story is completed about the great-souled Bharatas [Kuru dynasty]. ||74||" |
| `Line 905: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 906: विविधाः सम्भवा राज्ञामुक्ताः सम्भवपर्वणि |` | "Various origins of kings are narrated in the Sambhava Parva [Book of Origins]," |
| `Line 907: अन्येषां चैव विप्राणामृषेर्द्वैपायनस्य च ||७५||` | "And of other Brahmins, and of the sage Dvaipāyana [Vyāsa] as well. ||75||" |
| `Line 908: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 909: अंशावतरणं चात्र देवानां परिकीर्तितम् |` | "The descent of portions [incarnations] of the gods is described here," |
| `Line 910: दैत्यानां दानवानां च यक्षाणां च महौजसाम् ||७६||` | "Of the Daityas [demon class], Dānavas [demon class], and of the mighty Yakshas [wealth spirits]. ||76||" |
| `Line 911: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 912: नागानामथ सर्पाणां गन्धर्वाणां पतत्रिणाम् |` | "Of Nāgas [divine serpents] and serpents, of Gandharvas [celestial musicians] and of winged beings," |
| `Line 913: अन्येषां चैव भूतानां विविधानां समुद्भवः ||७७||` | "And the origin of various other beings as well. ||77||" |
| `Line 914: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 915: वसूनां पुनरुत्पत्तिर्भागीरथ्यां महात्मनाम् |` | "The rebirth of the great-souled Vasus [celestial deities] from Bhāgīrathī [Gangā]," |
| `Line 916: शन्तनोर्वेश्मनि पुनस्तेषां चारोहणं दिवि ||७८||` | "In the house of Shantanu, and their ascension again to heaven. ||78||" |
| `Line 917: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 918: तेजोंशानां च सङ्घाताद्भीष्मस्याप्यत्र सम्भवः |` | "From the collection of portions of splendor, the birth of Bhīshma here," |
| `Line 919: राज्यान्निवर्तनं चैव ब्रह्मचर्यव्रते स्थितिः ||७९||` | "And his renunciation of the kingdom, and establishment in the vow of celibacy [Brahmacharya]. ||79||" |
| `Line 920: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 921: प्रतिज्ञापालनं चैव रक्षा चित्राङ्गदस्य च |` | "And the keeping of his promise, and the protection of Chitrāngada," |
| `Line 922: हते चित्राङ्गदे चैव रक्षा भ्रातुर्यवीयसः ||८०||` | "And when Chitrāngada was slain, the protection of his younger brother. ||80||" |
| `Line 923: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 924: विचित्रवीर्यस्य तथा राज्ये सम्प्रतिपादनम् |` | "The establishment of Vichitravirya in the kingdom," |
| `Line 925: धर्मस्य नृषु सम्भूतिरणीमाण्डव्यशापजा ||८१||` | "The birth of Dharma [Yudhishthira] among men due to the curse of sage Māṇḍavya to Aṇi [Yama]. ||81||" |
| `Line 926: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 927: कृष्णद्वैपायनाच्चैव प्रसूतिर्वरदानजा |` | "And from Krishna Dvaipāyana [Vyāsa], births resulting from the boon," |
| `Line 928: धृतराष्ट्रस्य पाण्डोश्च पाण्डवानां च सम्भवः ||८२||` | "The birth of Dhritarāshtra and Pāndu, and the origin of the Pāndavas. ||82||" |
| `Line 929: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 930: वारणावतयात्रा च मन्त्रो दुर्योधनस्य च |` | "The journey to Vāranāvata [city name] and the conspiracy of Duryodhana," |
| `Line 931: विदुरस्य च वाक्येन सुरुङ्गोपक्रमक्रिया ||८३||` | "And by Vidura's words, the construction of the underground passage. ||83||" |
| `Line 932: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 933: पाण्डवानां वने घोरे हिडिम्बायाश्च दर्शनम् |` | "The Pāndavas' encounter with Hidimbā [rākshasi] in the terrible forest," |
| `Line 934: घटोत्कचस्य चोत्पत्तिरत्रैव परिकीर्तिता ||८४||` | "And the birth of Ghatotkaca is also narrated here. ||84||" |
| `Line 935: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 936: अज्ञातचर्या पाण्डूनां वासो ब्राह्मणवेश्मनि |` | "The Pāndavas' living incognito in the house of a Brahmin [priest]," |
| `Line 937: बकस्य निधनं चैव नागराणां च विस्मयः ||८५||` | "And the killing of Baka [demon], and the amazement of the townspeople. ||85||" |
| `Line 938: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 939: अङ्गारपर्णं निर्जित्य गङ्गाकूलेऽर्जुनस्तदा |` | "Having defeated Aṅgāraparna [king], Arjuna then, on the banks of the Ganges [sacred river]," |
| `Line 940: भ्रातृभिः सहितः सर्वैः पाञ्चालानभितो ययौ ||८६||` | "Together with all his brothers, proceeded toward the Pāñcālas [kingdom]. ||86||" |
| `Line 941: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 942: तापत्यमथ वासिष्ठमौर्वं चाख्यानमुत्तमम् |` | "The tale of Tāpatya [sun's descendant], Vāsiṣṭha [sage], and Aurva [sage], the excellent narrative," |
| `Line 943: पञ्चेन्द्राणामुपाख्यानमत्रैवाद्भुतमुच्यते ||८७||` | "The wondrous story of the five Indras [deities] is told here. ||87||" |
| `Line 944: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 945: पञ्चानामेकपत्नीत्वे विमर्शो द्रुपदस्य च |` | "The deliberation on the five (brothers) having one wife, and of Drupada [king]," |
| `Line 946: द्रौपद्या देवविहितो विवाहश्चाप्यमानुषः ||८८||` | "And Draupadī's divinely ordained marriage, which was superhuman. ||88||" |
| `Line 947: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 948: विदुरस्य च सम्प्राप्तिर्दर्शनं केशवस्य च |` | "The arrival of Vidura and the meeting with Keshava [Krishna]," |
| `Line 949: खाण्डवप्रस्थवासश्च तथा राज्यार्धशासनम् ||८९||` | "The dwelling at Khāṇḍavaprastha [city] and the ruling of half the kingdom. ||89||" |
| `Line 950: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 951: नारदस्याज्ञया चैव द्रौपद्याः समयक्रिया |` | "By Nārada's [divine sage] command, the agreement regarding Draupadī [Pāṇḍavas' wife]," |
| `Line 952: सुन्दोपसुन्दयोस्तत्र उपाख्यानं प्रकीर्तितम् ||९०||` | "And there the tale of Sunda and Upasunda was narrated. ||90||" |
| `Line 953: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 954: पार्थस्य वनवासश्च उलूप्या पथि सङ्गमः |` | "Pārtha's [Arjuna's] forest dwelling and his meeting with Ulūpī [Nāga princess] on the way," |
| `Line 955: पुण्यतीर्थानुसंयानं बभ्रुवाहनजन्म च ||९१||` | "His pilgrimage to sacred places and the birth of Babhruvāhana [Arjuna's son]. ||91||" |
| `Line 956: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 957: द्वारकायां सुभद्रा च कामयानेन कामिनी |` | "And in Dvārakā, Subhadrā [Krishna's sister], the passionate one, by the desiring one," |
| `Line 958: वासुदेवस्यानुमते प्राप्ता चैव किरीटिना ||९२||` | "Was obtained by the diadem-wearer [Arjuna] with Vāsudeva's [Krishna's] consent. ||92||" |
| `Line 959: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 960: हरणं गृह्य सम्प्राप्ते कृष्णे देवकिनन्दने |` | "The abduction being accomplished, when Krishna, son of Devakī, arrived," |
| `Line 961: सम्प्राप्तिश्चक्रधनुषोः खाण्डवस्य च दाहनम् ||९३||` | "The acquisition of the discus and bow, and the burning of the Khāṇḍava forest. ||93||" |
| `Line 962: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 963: अभिमन्योः सुभद्रायां जन्म चोत्तमतेजसः |` | "The birth of the supremely radiant Abhimanyu to Subhadrā," |
| `Line 964: मयस्य मोक्षो ज्वलनाद्भुजङ्गस्य च मोक्षणम् ||९४||` | "The release of Maya [asura architect] from the fire, and the liberation of the serpent. ||94||" |
| `Line 965: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 966: महर्षेर्मन्दपालस्य शार्ङ्ग्यं तनयसम्भवः ||९४||` | "The birth of the son of the great sage Mandapāla in the Śārṅgya [bird] form. ||94||" |
| `Line 967: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 968: इत्येतदाधिपर्वोक्तं प्रथमं बहुविस्तरम् |` | "Thus this first extensive Ādi Parva [beginning book] has been narrated," |
| `Line 969: अध्यायानां शते द्वे तु सङ्ख्याते परमर्षिणा ||९५||` | "Comprising two hundred chapters as counted by the supreme sage. ||95||" |
| `Line 970: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 971: अष्टादशैव चाध्याया व्यासेनोत्तमतेजसा ||९५||` | "And eighteen chapters by the supremely radiant Vyāsa. ||95||" |
| `Line 972: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 973: सप्त श्लोकसहस्राणि तथा नव शतानि च |` | "Seven thousand and nine hundred verses," |
| `Line 974: श्लोकाश्च चतुराशीतिर्दृष्टो ग्रन्थो महात्मना ||९६||` | "And eighty-four verses - this text was composed by the great soul. ||96||" |
| `Line 975: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 976: द्वितीयं तु सभापर्व बहुवृत्तान्तमुच्यते |` | "The second, the Sabha Parva [Assembly Book], is said to contain many episodes." |
| `Line 977: सभाक्रिया पाण्डवानां किङ्कराणां च दर्शनम् ||९७||` | "The construction of the assembly hall by the Pandavas and the appearance of the servants. ||97||" |
| `Line 978: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 979: लोकपालसभाख्यानं नारदाद्देवदर्शनात् |` | "The description of the assemblies of the Lokapalas [world guardians] as seen by Narada among the gods." |
| `Line 980: राजसूयस्य चारम्भो जरासन्धवधस्तथा ||९८||` | "The commencement of the Rajasuya [royal sacrifice] and the slaying of Jarasandha. ||98||" |
| `Line 981: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 982: गिरिव्रजे निरुद्धानां राज्ञां कृष्णेन मोक्षणम् |` | "The liberation by Krishna of the kings imprisoned in Girivraja [mountain fortress]." |
| `Line 983: राजसूयेऽर्घसंवादे शिशुपालवधस्तथा ||९९||` | "The slaying of Shishupala during the dispute about the offering at the Rajasuya sacrifice. ||99||" |
| `Line 984: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 985: यज्ञे विभूतिं तां दृष्ट्वा दुःखामर्षान्वितस्य च |` | "Having seen that splendor at the sacrifice, and filled with sorrow and envy," |
| `Line 986: दुर्योधनस्यावहासो भीमेन च सभातले ||१००||` | "Duryodhana was mocked by Bhima on the floor of the assembly hall. ||100||" |
| `Line 987: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 988: यत्रास्य मन्युरुद्भूतो येन द्यूतमकारयत् |` | "Where his anger arose, because of which he arranged the gambling match." |
| `Line 989: यत्र धर्मसुतं द्यूते शकुनिः कितवोऽजयत् ||१०१||` | "Where Shakuni, the deceitful gambler, defeated Dharma's son [Yudhishthira] in the game. ||101||" |
| `Line 990: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 991: यत्र द्यूतार्णवे मग्नान्द्रौपदी नौरिवार्णवात् |` | "Where Draupadi, like a boat in the ocean, rescued those who were drowning in the ocean of gambling." |
| `Line 992: तारयामास तांस्तीर्णाञ्ज्ञात्वा दुर्योधनो नृपः ||१०२||` | "King Duryodhana, knowing they had been saved, ||102||" |
| `Line 993: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 994: पुनरेव ततो द्यूते समाह्वयत पाण्डवान् ||१०२||` | "Again challenged the Pandavas to another game of dice. ||102||" |
| `Line 995: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 996: एतत्सर्वं सभापर्व समाख्यातं महात्मना |` | "All this is narrated in the Sabha Parva by the great-souled one [Vyasa]." |
| `Line 997: अध्यायाः सप्ततिर्ज्ञेयास्तथा द्वौ चात्र सङ्ख्यया ||१०३||` | "Seventy-two chapters are to be known here by count. ||103||" |
| `Line 998: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 999: श्लोकानां द्वे सहस्रे तु पञ्च श्लोकशतानि च |` | "Two thousand and five hundred verses," |
| `Line 1000: श्लोकाश्चैकादश ज्ञेयाः पर्वण्यस्मिन्प्रकीर्तिताः ||१०४||` | "And eleven verses are to be known as proclaimed in this Parva [book section]. ||104||" |
| `Line 1001: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1002: अतः परं तृतीयं तु ज्ञेयमारण्यकं महत् |` | "Next after this, the third great section to be known is the Āraṇyaka [Forest Book]," |
| `Line 1003: पौरानुगमनं चैव धर्मपुत्रस्य धीमतः ||१०५||` | "And the following of the wise Dharmaputra [Yudhiṣṭhira] by the citizens. ||105||" |
| `Line 1004: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1005: वृष्णीनामागमो यत्र पाञ्चालानां च सर्वशः |` | "Where the arrival of the Vṛṣṇis [Krishna's clan] and all the Pāñcālas [Draupadi's people] is described," |
| `Line 1006: यत्र सौभवधाख्यानं किर्मीरवध एव च ||१०६||` | "Where the narrative of Saubha's destruction and the killing of Kirmīra [demon] are also told. ||106||" |
| `Line 1007: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1008: अस्त्रहेतोर्विवासश्च पार्थस्यामिततेजसः ||१०६||` | "And the departure of Pārtha [Arjuna] of immeasurable splendor for the sake of weapons. ||106||" |
| `Line 1009: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1010: महादेवेन युद्धं च किरातवपुषा सह |` | "And the battle with Mahādeva [Shiva] in the form of a Kirāta [mountain hunter]," |
| `Line 1011: दर्शनं लोकपालानां स्वर्गारोहणमेव च ||१०७||` | "The vision of the Lokapālas [world guardians] and the ascent to heaven as well. ||107||" |
| `Line 1012: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1013: दर्शनं बृहदश्वस्य महर्षेर्भावितात्मनः |` | "The meeting with Bṛhadaśva, the great sage of purified soul," |
| `Line 1014: युधिष्ठिरस्य चार्तस्य व्यसने परिदेवनम् ||१०८||` | "And the lamentation of the distressed Yudhiṣṭhira in his misfortune. ||108||" |
| `Line 1015: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1016: नलोपाख्यानमत्रैव धर्मिष्ठं करुणोदयम् |` | "The story of Nala is also here, righteous and arousing compassion," |
| `Line 1017: दमयन्त्याः स्थितिर्यत्र नलस्य व्यसनागमे ||१०९||` | "Where is described Damayantī's steadfastness during Nala's misfortune. ||109||" |
| `Line 1018: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1019: वनवासगतानां च पाण्डवानां महात्मनाम् |` | "And of the noble-souled Pāṇḍavas dwelling in the forest," |
| `Line 1020: स्वर्गे प्रवृत्तिराख्याता लोमशेनार्जुनस्य वै ||११०||` | "The account of Arjuna in heaven is narrated by Lomaśa [sage]. ||110||" |
| `Line 1021: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1022: तीर्थयात्रा तथैवात्र पाण्डवानां महात्मनाम् |` | "The pilgrimage to sacred places of the noble-souled Pāṇḍavas is likewise here," |
| `Line 1023: जटासुरस्य तत्रैव वधः समुपवर्ण्यते ||१११||` | "The killing of Jaṭāsura [demon] is also described there. ||111||" |
| `Line 1024: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1025: नियुक्तो भीमसेनश्च द्रौपद्या गन्धमादने |` | "And Bhīmasena was sent by Draupadī to Gandhamādana [mountain]," |
| `Line 1026: यत्र मन्दारपुष्पार्थं नलिनीं तामधर्षयत् ||११२||` | "Where he violated that Nalinī for the sake of Mandāra flowers [celestial blooms]. ||112||" |
| `Line 1027: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1028: यत्रास्य सुमहद्युद्धमभवत्सह राक्षसैः |` | "Where his great battle occurred with the Rākṣasas [demons]," |
| `Line 1029: यक्षैश्चापि महावीर्यैर्मणिमत्प्रमुखैस्तथा ||११३||` | "And also with the mighty Yakṣas [wealth guardians], led by Maṇimat. ||113||" |
| `Line 1030: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1031: आगस्त्यमपि चाख्यानं यत्र वातापिभक्षणम् |` | "Also the tale of Agastya, where the devouring of Vātāpi [demon brother] occurred," |
| `Line 1032: लोपामुद्राभिगमनमपत्यार्थमृषेरपि ||११४||` | "And the sage's union with Lopāmudrā for the sake of offspring. ||114||" |
| `Line 1033: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1034: ततः श्येनकपोतीयमुपाख्यानमनन्तरम् |` | "Then immediately follows the story of the hawk and the dove," |
| `Line 1035: इन्द्रोऽग्निर्यत्र धर्मश्च अजिज्ञासञ्शिबिं नृपम् ||११५||` | "Where Indra [king of gods], Agni [fire god], and Dharma [righteousness] tested King Śibi. ||115||" |
| `Line 1036: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1037: ऋश्यशृङ्गस्य चरितं कौमारब्रह्मचारिणः |` | "The story of Ṛśyaśṛṅga [deer-horned sage], who practiced celibacy from childhood," |
| `Line 1038: जामदग्न्यस्य रामस्य चरितं भूरितेजसः ||११६||` | "And the story of Rāma Jāmadagnya [Paraśurāma], of immense splendor. ||116||" |
| `Line 1039: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1040: कार्तवीर्यवधो यत्र हैहयानां च वर्ण्यते |` | "Where the slaying of Kārtavīrya [thousand-armed king] and the Haihayas is described," |
| `Line 1041: सौकन्यमपि चाख्यानं च्यवनो यत्र भार्गवः ||११७||` | "And also the tale of Sukanyā, where Cyavana of Bhṛgu's lineage [sage Bhārgava] appears. ||117||" |
| `Line 1042: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1043: शर्यातियज्ञे नासत्यौ कृतवान्सोमपीथिनौ |` | "In Śaryāti's sacrifice, he made the Nāsatyas [Aśvin twins] drinkers of Soma [ritual beverage]," |
| `Line 1044: ताभ्यां च यत्र स मुनिर्यौवनं प्रतिपादितः ||११८||` | "And where that sage was restored to youth by those two. ||118||" |
| `Line 1045: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1046: जन्तूपाख्यानमत्रैव यत्र पुत्रेण सोमकः |` | "Here also is the story of Jantu, where Somaka with his son," |
| `Line 1047: पुत्रार्थमयजद्राजा लेभे पुत्रशतं च सः ||११९||` | "The king performed a sacrifice for sons and obtained a hundred sons. ||119||" |
| `Line 1048: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1049: अष्टावक्रीयमत्रैव विवादे यत्र बन्दिनम् |` | "Here also is the story of Aṣṭāvakra [eight-crooked sage], where in a debate with Bandin," |
| `Line 1050: विजित्य सागरं प्राप्तं पितरं लब्धवानृषिः ||१२०||` | "Having conquered him, the sage recovered his father who had gone to the ocean. ||120||" |
| `Line 1051: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1052: अवाप्य दिव्यान्यस्त्राणि गुर्वर्थे सव्यसाचिना |` | "Having obtained divine weapons by Savyasāchin [Arjuna] for his teacher's sake," |
| `Line 1053: निवातकवचैर्युद्धं हिरण्यपुरवासिभिः ||१२१||` | "The battle with the Nivātakavacas [demon clan], dwellers of Hiraṇyapura [golden city]. ||121||" |
| `Line 1054: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1055: समागमश्च पार्थस्य भ्रातृभिर्गन्धमादने |` | "And the reunion of Pārtha [Arjuna] with his brothers at Gandhamādana [fragrant mountain]," |
| `Line 1056: घोषयात्रा च गन्धर्वैर्यत्र युद्धं किरीटिनः ||१२२||` | "The Ghoṣayātrā [cattle-station expedition] and where the battle of Kirīṭin [Arjuna] with the Gandharvas [celestial musicians] occurred. ||122||" |
| `Line 1057: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1058: पुनरागमनं चैव तेषां द्वैतवनं सरः |` | "And their return to the Dvaitavana [forest of duality] lake," |
| `Line 1059: जयद्रथेनापहारो द्रौपद्याश्चाश्रमान्तरात् ||१२३||` | "The abduction of Draupadī from the hermitage by Jayadratha. ||123||" |
| `Line 1060: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1061: यत्रैनमन्वयाद्भीमो वायुवेगसमो जवे |` | "Where Bhīma pursued him with speed equal to the wind," |
| `Line 1062: मार्कण्डेयसमस्यायामुपाख्यानानि भागशः ||१२४||` | "The various narratives during the meeting with Mārkaṇḍeya [sage]. ||124||" |
| `Line 1063: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1064: संदर्शनं च कृष्णस्य संवादश्चैव सत्यया |` | "The meeting with Kṛṣṇa and his conversation with Satyā [Draupadī]," |
| `Line 1065: व्रीहिद्रौणिकमाख्यानमैन्द्रद्युम्नं तथैव च ||१२५||` | "The tale of Vrīhidrauṇika [rice measure] and likewise that of Indradyumna. ||125||" |
| `Line 1066: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1067: सावित्र्यौद्दालकीयं च वैन्योपाख्यानमेव च |` | "The story of Sāvitrī, the tale of Uddālaka, and also the narrative of Vainya [King Pṛthu]," |
| `Line 1068: रामायणमुपाख्यानमत्रैव बहुविस्तरम् ||१२६||` | "The narrative of the Rāmāyaṇa [Rama's journey] is also here in great detail. ||126||" |
| `Line 1069: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1070: कर्णस्य परिमोषोऽत्र कुण्डलाभ्यां पुरंदरात् |` | "Here is the story of Karṇa being deprived of his earrings by Purandara [Indra]," |
| `Line 1071: आरणेयमुपाख्यानं यत्र धर्मोऽन्वशात्सुतम् ||१२७||` | "The Āraṇeya tale where Dharma [Yudhiṣṭhira] tested his son. ||127||" |
| `Line 1072: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1073: जग्मुर्लब्धवरा यत्र पाण्डवाः पश्चिमां दिशम् ||१२७||` | "Where the Pāṇḍavas, having obtained boons, went toward the western direction. ||127||" |
| `Line 1074: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1075: एतदारण्यकं पर्व तृतीयं परिकीर्तितम् |` | "This Āraṇyaka [Forest] Parva is proclaimed as the third book." |
| `Line 1076: अत्राध्यायशते द्वे तु सङ्ख्याते परमर्षिणा ||१२८||` | "Here, two hundred chapters have been enumerated by the great sage [paramarṣi]. ||128||" |
| `Line 1077: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1078: एकोनसप्ततिश्चैव तथाध्यायाः प्रकीर्तिताः ||१२८||` | "And sixty-nine chapters have thus been proclaimed. ||128||" |
| `Line 1079: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1080: एकादश सहस्राणि श्लोकानां षट्शतानि च |` | "Eleven thousand and six hundred" |
| `Line 1081: चतुःषष्टिस्तथा श्लोकाः पर्वैतत्परिकीर्तितम् ||१२९||` | "and sixty-four verses are declared in this parva [section]. ||129||" |
| `Line 1082: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1083: अतः परं निबोधेदं वैराटं पर्वविस्तरम् |` | "After this, understand the extensive Virāṭa Parva [section]," |
| `Line 1084: विराटनगरं गत्वा श्मशाने विपुलां शमीम् ||१३०||` | "where, having gone to Virāṭa's city, at a cremation ground, a large śamī tree [sacred tree] ||130||" |
| `Line 1085: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1086: दृष्ट्वा संनिदधुस्तत्र पाण्डवा आयुधान्युत ||१३०||` | "the Pāṇḍavas saw and concealed their weapons there. ||130||" |
| `Line 1087: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1088: यत्र प्रविश्य नगरं छद्मभिर्न्यवसन्त ते |` | "Where, entering the city in disguise, they dwelt," |
| `Line 1089: दुरात्मनो वधो यत्र कीचकस्य वृकोदरात् ||१३१||` | "where the wicked Kīcaka was slain by Vṛkodara [Bhīma]. ||131||" |
| `Line 1090: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1091: गोग्रहे यत्र पार्थेन निर्जिताः कुरवो युधि |` | "Where, in the cattle-raid, the Kauravas were defeated in battle by Pārtha [Arjuna]," |
| `Line 1092: गोधनं च विराटस्य मोक्षितं यत्र पाण्डवैः ||१३२||` | "and where Virāṭa's cattle wealth was liberated by the Pāṇḍavas. ||132||" |
| `Line 1093: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1094: विराटेनोत्तरा दत्ता स्नुषा यत्र किरीटिनः |` | "Where Uttarā was given by Virāṭa as daughter-in-law to the diadem-wearer [Arjuna]," |
| `Line 1095: अभिमन्युं समुद्दिश्य सौभद्रमरिघातिनम् ||१३३||` | "designating Abhimanyu, the son of Subhadrā, the slayer of foes. ||133||" |
| `Line 1096: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1097: चतुर्थमेतद्विपुलं वैराटं पर्व वर्णितम् |` | "This extensive Virāṭa Parva [section] is described as the fourth," |
| `Line 1098: अत्रापि परिसङ्ख्यातमध्यायानां महात्मना ||१३४||` | "here also the number of chapters by the great soul [sage] ||134||" |
| `Line 1099: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1100: सप्तषष्टिरथो पूर्णा श्लोकाग्रमपि मे शृणु |` | "is sixty-seven complete, and now hear from me the number of verses:" |
| `Line 1101: श्लोकानां द्वे सहस्रे तु श्लोकाः पञ्चाशदेव तु ||१३५||` | "Two thousand and fifty verses only ||135||" |
| `Line 1102: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1103: पर्वण्यस्मिन्समाख्याताः सङ्ख्यया परमर्षिणा ||१३५||` | "Have been enumerated in this Parva [section] by count by the great sage ||135||" |
| `Line 1104: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1105: उद्योगपर्व विज्ञेयं पञ्चमं शृण्वतः परम् |` | "The Udyoga Parva [Effort/Preparation section] should be known as the fifth, supremely worth listening to," |
| `Line 1106: उपप्लव्ये निविष्टेषु पाण्डवेषु जिगीषया ||१३६||` | "When the Pandavas were settled in Upaplavya with the desire for victory ||136||" |
| `Line 1107: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1108: दुर्योधनोऽर्जुनश्चैव वासुदेवमुपस्थितौ ||१३६||` | "Both Duryodhana and Arjuna approached Vasudeva [Krishna] ||136||" |
| `Line 1109: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1110: साहाय्यमस्मिन्समरे भवान्नौ कर्तुमर्हति |` | "'You should render assistance to us in this battle,'" |
| `Line 1111: इत्युक्ते वचने कृष्णो यत्रोवाच महामतिः ||१३७||` | "When these words were spoken, Krishna, the great-minded one, replied ||137||" |
| `Line 1112: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1113: अयुध्यमानमात्मानं मन्त्रिणं पुरुषर्षभौ |` | "'O best among men, myself non-fighting as an advisor,'" |
| `Line 1114: अक्षौहिणीं वा सैन्यस्य कस्य वा किं ददाम्यहम् ||१३८||` | "'Or an Akshauhini [large army unit] of troops - to whom shall I give what?' ||138||" |
| `Line 1115: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1116: वव्रे दुर्योधनः सैन्यं मन्दात्मा यत्र दुर्मतिः |` | "Where the dull-witted, evil-minded Duryodhana chose the army," |
| `Line 1117: अयुध्यमानं सचिवं वव्रे कृष्णं धनञ्जयः ||१३९||` | "Dhananjaya [Arjuna] chose Krishna as a non-fighting counselor ||139||" |
| `Line 1118: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1119: सञ्जयं प्रेषयामास शमार्थं पाण्डवान्प्रति |` | "He [Dhritarashtra] sent Sanjaya to the Pandavas for the purpose of peace," |
| `Line 1120: यत्र दूतं महाराजो धृतराष्ट्रः प्रतापवान् ||१४०||` | "Where the mighty king Dhritarashtra sent an envoy ||140||" |
| `Line 1121: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1122: श्रुत्वा च पाण्डवान्यत्र वासुदेवपुरोगमान् |` | "And having heard about the Pandavas led by Vasudeva [Krishna]," |
| `Line 1123: प्रजागरः सम्प्रजज्ञे धृतराष्ट्रस्य चिन्तया ||१४१||` | "Sleeplessness arose in Dhritarashtra due to anxiety ||141||" |
| `Line 1124: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1125: विदुरो यत्र वाक्यानि विचित्राणि हितानि च |` | "Where Vidura spoke words that were wonderful and beneficial," |
| `Line 1126: श्रावयामास राजानं धृतराष्ट्रं मनीषिणम् ||१४२||` | "He made the wise king Dhritarashtra listen. ||142||" |
| `Line 1127: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1128: तथा सनत्सुजातेन यत्राध्यात्ममनुत्तमम् |` | "Thus, through Sanatsujata [eternal youth sage], where the supreme spiritual knowledge," |
| `Line 1129: मनस्तापान्वितो राजा श्रावितः शोकलालसः ||१४३||` | "Was made to be heard by the king who was afflicted with mental anguish and overwhelmed with grief. ||143||" |
| `Line 1130: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1131: प्रभाते राजसमितौ सञ्जयो यत्र चाभिभोः |` | "At dawn, in the royal assembly, where Sanjaya [charioteer-messenger] of the sovereign," |
| `Line 1132: ऐकात्म्यं वासुदेवस्य प्रोक्तवानर्जुनस्य च ||१४४||` | "Declared the oneness of Vasudeva [Krishna] and Arjuna. ||144||" |
| `Line 1133: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1134: यत्र कृष्णो दयापन्नः सन्धिमिच्छन्महायशाः |` | "Where Krishna, filled with compassion, desiring peace, the greatly renowned one," |
| `Line 1135: स्वयमागाच्छमं कर्तुं नगरं नागसाह्वयम् ||१४५||` | "Himself came to make peace to the city called Nagasahvaya [Hastinapura]. ||145||" |
| `Line 1136: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1137: प्रत्याख्यानं च कृष्णस्य राज्ञा दुर्योधनेन वै |` | "And the rejection of Krishna by King Duryodhana indeed," |
| `Line 1138: शमार्थं याचमानस्य पक्षयोरुभयोर्हितम् ||१४६||` | "Who was pleading for peace, for the benefit of both sides. ||146||" |
| `Line 1139: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1140: कर्णदुर्योधनादीनां दुष्टं विज्ञाय मन्त्रितम् |` | "Having known the evil counsel of Karna, Duryodhana and others," |
| `Line 1141: योगेश्वरत्वं कृष्णेन यत्र राजसु दर्शितम् ||१४७||` | "Where Krishna displayed his lordship of yoga [divine powers] among the kings. ||147||" |
| `Line 1142: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1143: रथमारोप्य कृष्णेन यत्र कर्णोऽनुमन्त्रितः |` | "Where Karna was counseled by Krishna, having taken him up in his chariot," |
| `Line 1144: उपायपूर्वं शौण्डीर्यात्प्रत्याख्यातश्च तेन सः ||१४८||` | "With diplomatic means, but he (Karna) rejected him (Krishna) out of valor. ||148||" |
| `Line 1145: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1146: ततश्चाप्यभिनिर्यात्रा रथाश्वनरदन्तिनाम् |` | "And then also the marching forth of chariots, horses, men, and elephants," |
| `Line 1147: नगराद्धास्तिनपुराद्बलसङ्ख्यानमेव च ||१४९||` | "From the city of Hastinapura, and also the enumeration of forces. ||149||" |
| `Line 1148: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1149: यत्र राज्ञा उलूकस्य प्रेषणं पाण्डवान्प्रति |` | "Where the king's sending of Uluka [owl-named messenger] to the Pandavas," |
| `Line 1150: श्वोभाविनि महायुद्धे दूत्येन क्रूरवादिना ||१५०||` | "For the great battle to come tomorrow, as an envoy with harsh words. ||150||" |
| `Line 1151: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1152: रथातिरथसङ्ख्यानमम्बोपाख्यानमेव च ||१५०||` | "The enumeration of warriors and chariot-warriors, and also the narrative of Ambā [princess's story], ||150||" |
| `Line 1153: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1154: एतत्सुबहुवृत्तान्तं पञ्चमं पर्व भारते |` | "This fifth book in the Bhārata, containing many narratives," |
| `Line 1155: उद्योगपर्व निर्दिष्टं सन्धिविग्रहसंश्रितम् ||१५१||` | "Is designated as the Udyoga Parva [Effort Book], dealing with peace negotiations and conflict. ||151||" |
| `Line 1156: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1157: अध्यायाः सङ्ख्यया त्वत्र षडशीतिशतं स्मृतम् |` | "The number of chapters herein is remembered to be one hundred and eighty-six," |
| `Line 1158: श्लोकानां षट्सहस्राणि तावन्त्येव शतानि च ||१५२||` | "And six thousand verses, as well as the same number of hundreds [6,600 verses]. ||152||" |
| `Line 1159: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1160: श्लोकाश्च नवतिः प्रोक्तास्तथैवाष्टौ महात्मना |` | "And ninety-eight verses were composed by the great-souled," |
| `Line 1161: व्यासेनोदारमतिना पर्वण्यस्मिंस्तपोधनाः ||१५३||` | "Vyāsa of noble intellect in this book, O wealth of austerities [ascetics]. ||153||" |
| `Line 1162: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1163: अत ऊर्ध्वं विचित्रार्थं भीष्मपर्व प्रचक्षते |` | "After this, they speak of the Bhīṣma Parva [Bhishma Book], with its diverse contents," |
| `Line 1164: जम्बूखण्डविनिर्माणं यत्रोक्तं सञ्जयेन ह ||१५४||` | "Where the formation of Jambū-khaṇḍa [continent division] is described by Sañjaya. ||154||" |
| `Line 1165: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1166: यत्र युद्धमभूद्घोरं दशाहान्यतिदारुणम् |` | "Where there was a terrible battle, extremely fierce for ten days," |
| `Line 1167: यत्र यौधिष्ठिरं सैन्यं विषादमगमत्परम् ||१५५||` | "Where Yudhiṣṭhira's army fell into extreme despair. ||155||" |
| `Line 1168: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1169: कश्मलं यत्र पार्थस्य वासुदेवो महामतिः |` | "Where Vāsudeva [Krishna] of great wisdom dispelled the dejection," |
| `Line 1170: मोहजं नाशयामास हेतुभिर्मोक्षदर्शनैः ||१५६||` | "Born of delusion of Pārtha [Arjuna], with reasons showing the path to liberation. ||156||" |
| `Line 1171: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1172: शिखण्डिनं पुरस्कृत्य यत्र पार्थो महाधनुः |` | "Where Pārtha [Arjuna] of the mighty bow, placing Śikhaṇḍin in front," |
| `Line 1173: विनिघ्नन्निशितैर्बाणै रथाद्भीष्ममपातयत् ||१५७||` | "Striking with sharp arrows, made Bhīṣma fall from his chariot. ||157||" |
| `Line 1174: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1175: षष्ठमेतन्महापर्व भारते परिकीर्तितम् |` | "This sixth great book in the Bhārata is thus celebrated." |
| `Line 1176: अध्यायानां शतं प्रोक्तं सप्तदश तथापरे ||१५८||` | "One hundred chapters are declared, and seventeen more. ||158||" |
| `Line 1177: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1178: पञ्च श्लोकसहस्राणि सङ्ख्ययाष्टौ शतानि च |` | "Five thousand verses, and by count, eight hundred," |
| `Line 1179: श्लोकाश्च चतुराशीतिः पर्वण्यस्मिन्प्रकीर्तिताः ||१५९||` | "And eighty-four verses are proclaimed in this Parvan [book section]. ||159||" |
| `Line 1180: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1181: व्यासेन वेदविदुषा सङ्ख्याता भीष्मपर्वणि ||१५९||` | "Counted by Vyāsa [sage-compiler], the knower of Vedas, in the Bhīṣma-parvan [Bhishma book]. ||159||" |
| `Line 1182: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1183: द्रोणपर्व ततश्चित्रं बहुवृत्तान्तमुच्यते |` | "Then the Droṇa-parvan [Drona book], wondrous and containing many episodes, is described," |
| `Line 1184: यत्र संशप्तकाः पार्थमपनिन्यू रणाजिरात् ||१६०||` | "Where the Saṃśaptakas [oath-bound warriors] drew Pārtha [Arjuna] away from the battlefield. ||160||" |
| `Line 1185: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1186: भगदत्तो महाराजो यत्र शक्रसमो युधि |` | "Where the great king Bhagadatta, equal to Śakra [Indra] in battle," |
| `Line 1187: सुप्रतीकेन नागेन सह शस्तः किरीटिना ||१६१||` | "Along with his elephant Supratīka, was slain by Kirīṭin [Arjuna]. ||161||" |
| `Line 1188: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1189: यत्राभिमन्युं बहवो जघ्नुर्लोकमहारथाः |` | "Where many great warriors of the world slew Abhimanyu," |
| `Line 1190: जयद्रथमुखा बालं शूरमप्राप्तयौवनम् ||१६२||` | "Led by Jayadratha, the brave youth who had not yet reached full maturity. ||162||" |
| `Line 1191: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1192: हतेऽभिमन्यौ क्रुद्धेन यत्र पार्थेन संयुगे |` | "Where, after Abhimanyu was slain, by the enraged Pārtha [Arjuna] in battle," |
| `Line 1193: अक्षौहिणीः सप्त हत्वा हतो राजा जयद्रथः ||१६३||` | "After slaying seven Akṣauhiṇīs [army units], King Jayadratha was killed. ||163||" |
| `Line 1194: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1195: संशप्तकावशेषं च कृतं निःशेषमाहवे ||१६३||` | "And the remnants of the Saṃśaptakas [oath-bound warriors] were completely destroyed in battle. ||163||" |
| `Line 1196: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1197: अलम्बुसः श्रुतायुश्च जलसन्धश्च वीर्यवान् |` | "Alambusa, Śrutāyus, and the mighty Jalasandha," |
| `Line 1198: सौमदत्तिर्विराटश्च द्रुपदश्च महारथः ||१६४||` | "Saumadatti [Bhūriśravas], Virāṭa, and the great warrior Drupada, ||164||" |
| `Line 1199: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1200: घटोत्कचादयश्चान्ये निहता द्रोणपर्वणि ||१६४||` | "Ghaṭotkaca and others were slain in the Droṇa-parvan [Drona book]. ||164||" |
| `Line 1201: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1202: अश्वत्थामापि चात्रैव द्रोणे युधि निपातिते |` | "And here, when Drona was slain in battle," |
| `Line 1203: अस्त्रं प्रादुश्चकारोग्रं नारायणममर्षितः ||१६५||` | "Ashvatthama, enraged, unleashed the terrible Narayana [Vishnu's] weapon. ||165||" |
| `Line 1204: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1205: सप्तमं भारते पर्व महदेतदुदाहृतम् |` | "This is declared as the seventh great book in the Bharata [Mahabharata]," |
| `Line 1206: अत्र ते पृथिवीपालाः प्रायशो निधनं गताः ||१६६||` | "Wherein those rulers of the earth mostly met their death. ||166||" |
| `Line 1207: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1208: द्रोणपर्वणि ये शूरा निर्दिष्टाः पुरुषर्षभाः ||१६६||` | "Those heroes, the bulls among men, who are mentioned in the Drona Parva [book of Drona]. ||166||" |
| `Line 1209: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1210: अध्यायानां शतं प्रोक्तमध्यायाः सप्ततिस्तथा |` | "One hundred and seventy chapters are said to be," |
| `Line 1211: अष्टौ श्लोकसहस्राणि तथा नव शतानि च ||१६७||` | "Eight thousand and nine hundred verses. ||167||" |
| `Line 1212: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1213: श्लोका नव तथैवात्र सङ्ख्यातास्तत्त्वदर्शिना |` | "And nine verses are counted here by the truth-seer [sage]," |
| `Line 1214: पाराशर्येण मुनिना सञ्चिन्त्य द्रोणपर्वणि ||१६८||` | "By the sage Parasharyeya [Vyasa], after careful consideration, in the Drona Parva. ||168||" |
| `Line 1215: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1216: अतः परं कर्णपर्व प्रोच्यते परमाद्भुतम् |` | "After this, the Karna Parva [book of Karna], which is most wonderful, is described," |
| `Line 1217: सारथ्ये विनियोगश्च मद्रराजस्य धीमतः ||१६९||` | "And the appointment of the wise king of Madra [Shalya] as charioteer. ||169||" |
| `Line 1218: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1219: आख्यातं यत्र पौराणं त्रिपुरस्य निपातनम् ||१६९||` | "Where the ancient story of the destruction of Tripura [demon city] is narrated. ||169||" |
| `Line 1220: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1221: प्रयाणे परुषश्चात्र संवादः कर्णशल्ययोः |` | "And here, the harsh dialogue between Karna and Shalya during the march," |
| `Line 1222: हंसकाकीयमाख्यानमत्रैवाक्षेपसंहितम् ||१७०||` | "The tale of the swan and crow is also included here with criticisms. ||170||" |
| `Line 1223: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1224: अन्योन्यं प्रति च क्रोधो युधिष्ठिरकिरीटिनोः |` | "And the anger between Yudhishthira and Kiritina [Arjuna] toward each other," |
| `Line 1225: द्वैरथे यत्र पार्थेन हतः कर्णो महारथः ||१७१||` | "Where in single combat, Karna the great chariot-warrior was slain by Partha [Arjuna]. ||171||" |
| `Line 1226: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1227: अष्टमं पर्व निर्दिष्टमेतद्भारतचिन्तकैः |` | "This eighth parva [book section] is designated by the scholars of the Bharata," |
| `Line 1228: एकोनसप्ततिः प्रोक्ता अध्यायाः कर्णपर्वणि ||१७२||` | "Sixty-nine chapters are said to be in the Karna-parva [Karna's book]. ||172||" |
| `Line 1229: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1230: चत्वार्येव सहस्राणि नव श्लोकशतानि च ||१७२||` | "Four thousand and nine hundred verses [in total]. ||172||" |
| `Line 1231: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1232: अतः परं विचित्रार्थं शल्यपर्व प्रकीर्तितम् |` | "After this comes the Shalya-parva [Shalya's book], celebrated for its diverse contents," |
| `Line 1233: हतप्रवीरे सैन्ये तु नेता मद्रेश्वरोऽभवत् ||१७३||` | "When the chief warriors were slain, the king of Madra [Shalya] became the leader. ||173||" |
| `Line 1234: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1235: वृत्तानि रथयुद्धानि कीर्त्यन्ते यत्र भागशः |` | "Where chariot battles that occurred are described in various sections," |
| `Line 1236: विनाशः कुरुमुख्यानां शल्यपर्वणि कीर्त्यते ||१७४||` | "The destruction of the foremost Kurus is narrated in the Shalya-parva. ||174||" |
| `Line 1237: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1238: शल्यस्य निधनं चात्र धर्मराजान्महारथात् |` | "And herein is the death of Shalya at the hands of Dharmaraja [Yudhishthira], the great chariot-warrior," |
| `Line 1239: गदायुद्धं तु तुमुलमत्रैव परिकीर्तितम् ||१७५||` | "And the tumultuous mace battle is also described here. ||175||" |
| `Line 1240: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1241: सरस्वत्याश्च तीर्थानां पुण्यता परिकीर्तिता ||१७५||` | "The sanctity of the pilgrimage sites of Sarasvati [river goddess] is also celebrated. ||175||" |
| `Line 1242: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1243: नवमं पर्व निर्दिष्टमेतदद्भुतमर्थवत् |` | "This ninth parva is designated as wonderful and meaningful," |
| `Line 1244: एकोनषष्टिरध्यायास्तत्र सङ्ख्याविशारदैः ||१७६||` | "Fifty-nine chapters are counted there by those skilled in enumeration. ||176||" |
| `Line 1245: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1246: सङ्ख्याता बहुवृत्तान्ताः श्लोकाग्रं चात्र शस्यते |` | "Many narratives are counted, and the total number of verses here is declared to be," |
| `Line 1247: त्रीणि श्लोकसहस्राणि द्वे शते विंशतिस्तथा ||१७७||` | "Three thousand, two hundred and twenty verses. ||177||" |
| `Line 1248: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1249: मुनिना सम्प्रणीतानि कौरवाणां यशोभृताम् ||१७७||` | "Composed by the sage [Vyasa], about the glory-bearing Kauravas. ||177||" |
| `Line 1250: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1251: अतः परं प्रवक्ष्यामि सौप्तिकं पर्व दारुणम् |` | "Hereafter, I shall narrate the terrible Sauptika Parva [Sleeping Warriors chapter]," |
| `Line 1252: भग्नोरुं यत्र राजानं दुर्योधनममर्षणम् ||१७८||` | "Where the impatient king Duryodhana with broken thighs [was found]. ||178||" |
| `Line 1253: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1254: व्यपयातेषु पार्थेषु त्रयस्तेऽभ्याययू रथाः |` | "After the Parthas [Pandavas] had departed, those three warriors approached in chariots," |
| `Line 1255: कृतवर्मा कृपो द्रौणिः सायाह्ने रुधिरोक्षिताः ||१७९||` | "Kritavarma, Kripa, and Droni [Ashvatthama], blood-spattered, in the evening. ||179||" |
| `Line 1256: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1257: प्रतिजज्ञे दृढक्रोधो द्रौणिर्यत्र महारथः |` | "Where the great warrior Droni [Ashvatthama], firmly enraged, vowed," |
| `Line 1258: अहत्वा सर्वपाञ्चालान्धृष्टद्युम्नपुरोगमान् ||१८०||` | "Not without slaying all the Panchalas led by Dhrishtadyumna, ||180||" |
| `Line 1259: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1260: पाण्डवांश्च सहामात्यान्न विमोक्ष्यामि दंशनम् ||१८०||` | "And the Pandavas with their ministers, 'I shall not release my armor.' ||180||" |
| `Line 1261: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1262: प्रसुप्तान्निशि विश्वस्तान्यत्र ते पुरुषर्षभाः |` | "Where those bull among men [great warriors]," |
| `Line 1263: पाञ्चालान्सपरीवाराञ्जघ्नुर्द्रौणिपुरोगमाः ||१८१||` | "Slaughtered the sleeping, unsuspecting Panchalas with their attendants at night, led by Droni [Ashvatthama]. ||181||" |
| `Line 1264: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1265: यत्रामुच्यन्त पार्थास्ते पञ्च कृष्णबलाश्रयात् |` | "Where those five Parthas [Pandavas] were saved through Krishna's protection," |
| `Line 1266: सात्यकिश्च महेष्वासः शेषाश्च निधनं गताः ||१८२||` | "While Satyaki, the great archer, and the rest met their death. ||182||" |
| `Line 1267: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1268: द्रौपदी पुत्रशोकार्ता पितृभ्रातृवधार्दिता |` | "Where Draupadi, afflicted with grief for her sons, distressed by the slaughter of her father and brothers," |
| `Line 1269: कृतानशनसङ्कल्पा यत्र भर्तृनुपाविशत् ||१८३||` | "Having resolved to fast unto death, approached her husbands. ||183||" |
| `Line 1270: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1271: द्रौपदीवचनाद्यत्र भीमो भीमपराक्रमः |` | "Where, at Draupadi's words, Bhima of terrible prowess," |
| `Line 1272: अन्वधावत सङ्क्रुद्धो भारद्वाजं गुरोः सुतम् ||१८४||` | "Pursued in great anger Bharadvaja's son [Ashvatthama], the son of his guru. ||184||" |
| `Line 1273: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1274: भीमसेनभयाद्यत्र दैवेनाभिप्रचोदितः |` | "Where, out of fear of Bhimasena and impelled by fate," |
| `Line 1275: अपाण्डवायेति रुषा द्रौणिरस्त्रमवासृजत् ||१८५||` | "Droni [Ashvatthama] in anger released his weapon with the intent 'for the destruction of the Pandavas.' ||185||" |
| `Line 1276: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1277: मैवमित्यब्रवीत्कृष्णः शमयंस्तस्य तद्वचः |` | "Krishna spoke, 'Not so,' pacifying his words," |
| `Line 1278: यत्रास्त्रमस्त्रेण च तच्छमयामास फाल्गुनः ||१८६||` | "Where Phalguna [Arjuna] neutralized that weapon with another weapon. ||186||" |
| `Line 1279: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1280: द्रौणिद्वैपायनादीनां शापाश्चान्योन्यकारिताः |` | "The curses exchanged between Droni [Ashvatthama], Dvaipayana [Vyasa] and others," |
| `Line 1281: तोयकर्मणि सर्वेषां राज्ञामुदकदानिके ||१८७||` | "During the water ritual, the offering of water to all the kings. ||187||" |
| `Line 1282: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1283: गूढोत्पन्नस्य चाख्यानं कर्णस्य पृथयात्मनः |` | "And the account of the secretly born Karna, the son of Pritha [Kunti]," |
| `Line 1284: सुतस्यैतदिह प्रोक्तं दशमं पर्व सौप्तिकम् ||१८८||` | "This is declared here as the tenth Parva [book section], the Sauptika [sleeping warriors]. ||188||" |
| `Line 1285: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1286: अष्टादशास्मिन्नध्यायाः पर्वण्युक्ता महात्मना |` | "Eighteen chapters in this Parva have been narrated by the great soul," |
| `Line 1287: श्लोकाग्रमत्र कथितं शतान्यष्टौ तथैव च ||१८९||` | "The number of verses stated here are eight hundred as well. ||189||" |
| `Line 1288: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1289: श्लोकाश्च सप्ततिः प्रोक्ता यथावदभिसङ्ख्यया |` | "And seventy verses are declared according to the proper count," |
| `Line 1290: सौप्तिकैषीकसम्बन्धे पर्वण्यमितबुद्धिना ||१९०||` | "In the Parva related to Sauptika and Aishika [arrow section], by the one of boundless intellect. ||190||" |
| `Line 1291: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1292: अत ऊर्ध्वमिदं प्राहुः स्त्रीपर्व करुणोदयम् |` | "After this, they call the Stri Parva [women's book], the rise of compassion," |
| `Line 1293: विलापो वीरपत्नीनां यत्रातिकरुणः स्मृतः ||१९१||` | "Where the extremely sorrowful lamentations of the heroes' wives are remembered. ||191||" |
| `Line 1294: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1295: क्रोधावेशः प्रसादश्च गान्धारीधृतराष्ट्रयोः ||१९१||` | "The anger and the eventual calm of Gandhari and Dhritarashtra. ||191||" |
| `Line 1296: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1297: यत्र तान्क्षत्रियाञ्शूरान्दिष्टान्ताननिवर्तिनः |` | "Where those brave Kshatriyas [warrior class], who met their destined end without turning back," |
| `Line 1298: पुत्रान्भ्रातृन्पितृंश्चैव ददृशुर्निहतान्रणे ||१९२||` | "Sons, brothers, and fathers they saw slain in battle. ||192||" |
| `Line 1299: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1300: यत्र राजा महाप्राज्ञः सर्वधर्मभृतां वरः |` | "Where the king of great wisdom, the best among all upholders of dharma [righteousness]," |
| `Line 1301: राज्ञां तानि शरीराणि दाहयामास शास्त्रतः ||१९३||` | "He caused the bodies of those kings to be cremated according to the scriptures. ||193||" |
| `Line 1302: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1303: एतदेकादशं प्रोक्तं पर्वातिकरुणं महत् |` | "This has been declared as the eleventh Parva [section], extremely sorrowful and great." |
| `Line 1304: सप्तविंशतिरध्यायाः पर्वण्यस्मिन्नुदाहृताः ||१९४||` | "Twenty-seven chapters are enumerated in this Parva [section]. ||194||" |
| `Line 1305: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1306: श्लोकाः सप्तशतं चात्र पञ्चसप्ततिरुच्यते |` | "Seven hundred and seventy-five verses are said to be here," |
| `Line 1307: सङ्ख्यया भारताख्यानं कर्त्रा ह्यत्र महात्मना ||१९५||` | "By count in the Bharata narrative, composed here by the great-souled author. ||195||" |
| `Line 1308: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1309: प्रणीतं सज्जनमनोवैक्लव्याश्रुप्रवर्तकम् ||१९५||` | "Composed to bring forth tears of distress in the minds of good people. ||195||" |
| `Line 1310: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1311: अतः परं शान्तिपर्व द्वादशं बुद्धिवर्धनम् |` | "After this comes the Shanti Parva [Peace section], the twelfth, which increases wisdom," |
| `Line 1312: यत्र निर्वेदमापन्नो धर्मराजो युधिष्ठिरः ||१९६||` | "Where Dharmaraja [righteous king] Yudhishthira fell into despondency. ||196||" |
| `Line 1313: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1314: घातयित्वा पितृन्भ्रातृन्पुत्रान्सम्बन्धिबान्धवान् ||१९६||` | "After causing the slaughter of fathers, brothers, sons, relatives and kinsmen. ||196||" |
| `Line 1315: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1316: शान्तिपर्वणि धर्माश्च व्याख्याताः शरतल्पिकाः |` | "In the Shanti Parva [Peace section], the duties are explained to the one lying on the arrow-bed [Bhishma]," |
| `Line 1317: राजभिर्वेदितव्या ये सम्यङ्नयबुभुत्सुभिः ||१९७||` | "Which should be known by kings who properly desire to understand statecraft. ||197||" |
| `Line 1318: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1319: आपद्धर्माश्च तत्रैव कालहेतुप्रदर्शकाः |` | "And there also are the duties for times of distress, showing the causes of time [circumstances]," |
| `Line 1320: यान्बुद्ध्वा पुरुषः सम्यक्सर्वज्ञत्वमवाप्नुयात् ||१९८||` | "Understanding which, a person may properly attain omniscience. ||198||" |
| `Line 1321: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1322: मोक्षधर्माश्च कथिता विचित्रा बहुविस्तराः ||१९८||` | "And the duties relating to liberation are narrated, varied and extensive. ||198||" |
| `Line 1323: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1324: द्वादशं पर्व निर्दिष्टमेतत्प्राज्ञजनप्रियम् |` | "This twelfth Parva [section] is designated as dear to wise people," |
| `Line 1325: पर्वण्यत्र परिज्ञेयमध्यायानां शतत्रयम् ||१९९||` | "In this Parva [section], three hundred chapters are to be known. ||199||" |
| `Line 1326:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1327: त्रिंशच्चैव तथाध्याया नव चैव तपोधनाः ||१९९||` | "Thirty-nine chapters, O ascetics [wealth in penance] ॥199॥" |
| `Line 1328:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1329: श्लोकानां तु सहस्राणि कीर्तितानि चतुर्दश |` | "Fourteen thousand verses are declared," |
| `Line 1330: पञ्च चैव शतान्याहुः पञ्चविंशतिसङ्ख्यया ||२००||` | "And five hundred and twenty-five verses they proclaim ॥200॥" |
| `Line 1331:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1332: अत ऊर्ध्वं तु विज्ञेयमानुशासनमुत्तमम् |` | "After this should be known the excellent Anushasana [Instruction section]," |
| `Line 1333: यत्र प्रकृतिमापन्नः श्रुत्वा धर्मविनिश्चयम् ||२०१||` | "Where, having regained his natural state after hearing the definitive discourse on dharma [righteousness] ॥201॥" |
| `Line 1334:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1335: भीष्माद्भागीरथीपुत्रात्कुरुराजो युधिष्ठिरः ||२०१||` | "From Bhishma, son of Ganga [Bhagirathi's son], did King Yudhishthira of the Kurus ॥201॥" |
| `Line 1336:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1337: व्यवहारोऽत्र कार्त्स्न्येन धर्मार्थीयो निदर्शितः |` | "Herein is completely illustrated the conduct pertaining to dharma and artha [righteousness and prosperity]," |
| `Line 1338: विविधानां च दानानां फलयोगाः पृथग्विधाः ||२०२||` | "And the various fruits and connections of different kinds of charity ॥202॥" |
| `Line 1339:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1340: तथा पात्रविशेषाश्च दानानां च परो विधिः |` | "Also the special recipients and the supreme method of giving charity," |
| `Line 1341: आचारविधियोगश्च सत्यस्य च परा गतिः ||२०३||` | "And the connection with rules of conduct, and the supreme goal of truth ॥203॥" |
| `Line 1342:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1343: एतत्सुबहुवृत्तान्तमुत्तमं चानुशासनम् |` | "This Anushasana [Instruction section] contains many narratives and is excellent," |
| `Line 1344: भीष्मस्यात्रैव सम्प्राप्तिः स्वर्गस्य परिकीर्तिता ||२०४||` | "Herein is also described Bhishma's attainment of heaven [svarga] ॥204॥" |
| `Line 1345:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1346: एतत्त्रयोदशं पर्व धर्मनिश्चयकारकम् |` | "This is the thirteenth Parva [section], which establishes the certainty of dharma [righteousness]," |
| `Line 1347: अध्यायानां शतं चात्र षट्चत्वारिंशदेव च ||२०५||` | "And here are one hundred and forty-six chapters ॥205॥" |
| `Line 1348:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1349: श्लोकानां तु सहस्राणि षट्सप्तैव शतानि च ||२०५||` | "And six thousand and seven hundred verses ॥205॥" |
| `Line 1350:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1351: ततोऽश्वमेधिकं नाम पर्व प्रोक्तं चतुर्दशम् |` | "Then the fourteenth Parva [section] called Ashvamedha [Horse Sacrifice] is declared," |
| `Line 1352: तत्संवर्तमरुत्तीयं यत्राख्यानमनुत्तमम् ||२०६||` | "Where the excellent narrative of Samvarta and Marutta is told ॥206॥" |
| `Line 1353:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1354: सुवर्णकोशसम्प्राप्तिर्जन्म चोक्तं परिक्षितः |` | "The acquisition of the gold treasury and the birth of Parikshit [Abhimanyu's son] are narrated," |
| `Line 1355: दग्धस्यास्त्राग्निना पूर्वं कृष्णात्सञ्जीवनं पुनः ||२०७||` | "Who was previously burnt by the weapon-fire and then revived by Krishna ॥207॥" |
| `Line 1356:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1357: चर्यायां हयमुत्सृष्टं पाण्डवस्यानुगच्छतः |` | "The horse released for the ritual, followed by the Pandava [Arjuna]," |
| `Line 1358: तत्र तत्र च युद्धानि राजपुत्रैरमर्षणैः ||२०८||` | "And battles here and there with wrathful princes ॥208॥" |
| `Line 1359:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1360: चित्राङ्गदायाः पुत्रेण पुत्रिकाया धनञ्जयः |` | "Dhananjaya [Arjuna] with the son of Chitrangada [Manipur princess], his putrika-putra [son of daughter]," |
| `Line 1361: सङ्ग्रामे बभ्रुवाहेन संशयं चात्र दर्शितः ||२०९||` | "Is shown in a perilous situation in battle with Babhruvahana ॥209॥" |
| `Line 1362:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1363: अश्वमेधे महायज्ञे नकुलाख्यानमेव च ||२०९||` | "And also the story of Nakula in the great sacrifice of Ashvamedha ॥209॥" |
| `Line 1364:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1365: इत्याश्वमेधिकं पर्व प्रोक्तमेतन्महाद्भुतम् |` | "Thus is described this most wonderful Ashvamedha Parva," |
| `Line 1366: अत्राध्यायशतं त्रिंशत्त्रयोऽध्यायाश्च शब्दिताः ||२१०||` | "Here one hundred and thirty-three chapters are enumerated ॥210॥" |
| `Line 1367:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1368: त्रीणि श्लोकसहस्राणि तावन्त्येव शतानि च |` | "Three thousand verses and as many hundreds," |
| `Line 1369: विंशतिश्च तथा श्लोकाः सङ्ख्यातास्तत्त्वदर्शिना ||२११||` | "And twenty verses are counted by the knower of truth [Vyasa] ॥211॥" |
| `Line 1370:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1371: तत आश्रमवासाक्यं पर्व पञ्चदशं स्मृतम् |` | "Then the fifteenth Parva called Ashramavasa [Forest Dwelling] is remembered," |
| `Line 1372: यत्र राज्यं परित्यज्य गान्धारीसहितो नृपः ||२१२||` | "Where, abandoning the kingdom, the king [Dhritarashtra] with Gandhari ॥212॥" |
| `Line 1373:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1374: धृतराष्ट्राश्रमपदं विदुरश्च जगाम ह ||२१२||` | "And Vidura went to Dhritarashtra's hermitage ॥212॥" |
| `Line 1375:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1376: यं दृष्ट्वा प्रस्थितं साध्वी पृथाप्यनुययौ तदा |` | "Seeing him departing, the virtuous Pritha [Kunti] also followed then" |
| `Line 1377: पुत्रराज्यं परित्यज्य गुरुशुश्रूषणे रता ||२१३||` | "Abandoning her sons' kingdom, devoted to serving the elders [Dhritarashtra and Gandhari] ॥213॥" |
| `Line 1378:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1379: यत्र राजा हतान्पुत्रान्पौत्रानन्यांश्च पार्थिवान् |` | "Where the king [Dhritarashtra] saw his slain sons, grandsons, and other rulers" |
| `Line 1380: लोकान्तरगतान्वीरानपश्यत्पुनरागतान् ||२१४||` | "Those heroes who had gone to the other world, returned again [in vision] ॥214॥" |
| `Line 1381:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1382: ऋषेः प्रसादात्कृष्णस्य दृष्ट्वाश्चर्यमनुत्तमम् |` | "By the grace of the sage [Vyasa] and Krishna, having seen that supreme wonder" |
| `Line 1383: त्यक्त्वा शोकं सदारश्च सिद्धिं परमिकां गतः ||२१५||` | "Abandoning grief, he with his wife attained the highest perfection [spiritual liberation] ॥215॥" |
| `Line 1384:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1385: यत्र धर्मं समाश्रित्य विदुरः सुगतिं गतः |` | "Where Vidura, taking refuge in dharma [righteousness], attained a good destination [liberation]" |
| `Line 1386: सञ्जयश्च महामात्रो विद्वान्गावल्गणिर्वशी ||२१६||` | "And Sanjaya, the great minister, the wise son of Gavalgana, the self-controlled one ॥216॥" |
| `Line 1387:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1388: ददर्श नारदं यत्र धर्मराजो युधिष्ठिरः |` | "Where Dharmaraja [righteous king] Yudhishthira saw Narada" |
| `Line 1389: नारदाच्चैव शुश्राव वृष्णीनां कदनं महत् ||२१७||` | "And from Narada heard of the great destruction of the Vrishnis [Krishna's clan] ॥217॥" |
| `Line 1390:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1391: एतदाश्रमवासाख्यं पूर्वोक्तं सुमहाद्भुतम् |` | "This is the previously mentioned, very wonderful Ashramavasa [forest dwelling] Parva" |
| `Line 1392: द्विचत्वारिंशदध्यायाः पर्वैतदभिसङ्ख्यया ||२१८||` | "This section consists of forty-two chapters by count ॥218॥" |
| `Line 1393:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1394: सहस्रमेकं श्लोकानां पञ्च श्लोकशतानि च |` | "One thousand verses and five hundred verses" |
| `Line 1395: षडेव च तथा श्लोकाः सङ्ख्यातास्तत्त्वदर्शिना ||२१९||` | "And six verses have been counted by the knower of truth [Vyasa] ॥219॥" |
| `Line 1396:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1397: अतः परं निबोधेदं मौसलं पर्व दारुणम् |` | "After this, understand the terrible Mausala [club] Parva" |
| `Line 1398: यत्र ते पुरुषव्याघ्राः शस्त्रस्पर्शसहा युधि ||२२०||` | "Where those tiger-like men [Yadavas], who could withstand the touch of weapons in battle ॥220॥" |
| `Line 1399:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1400: ब्रह्मदण्डविनिष्पिष्टाः समीपे लवणाम्भसः ||२२०||` | "Were crushed by Brahma's rod [curse] near the salt waters [sea] ॥220॥" |
| `Line 1401:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1402: आपाने पानगलिता दैवेनाभिप्रचोदिताः |` | "Intoxicated at a drinking party, impelled by fate [divine force]," |
| `Line 1403: एरकारूपिभिर्वज्रैर्निजघ्नुरितरेतरम् ||२२१||` | "They slew one another with clubs [vajras] made from eraka grass ॥221॥" |
| `Line 1404:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1405: यत्र सर्वक्षयं कृत्वा तावुभौ रामकेशवौ |` | "Where, after the destruction of all, both Rama and Keshava [Krishna]," |
| `Line 1406: नातिचक्रमतुः कालं प्राप्तं सर्वहरं समम् ||२२२||` | "Did not transgress the appointed time, the universal destroyer [death] that comes to all equally ॥222॥" |
| `Line 1407:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1408: यत्रार्जुनो द्वारवतीमेत्य वृष्णिविनाकृताम् |` | "Where Arjuna, coming to Dwaraka [Krishna's city] bereft of the Vrishnis [Krishna's clan]," |
| `Line 1409: दृष्ट्वा विषादमगमत्परां चार्तिं नरर्षभः ||२२३||` | "Seeing it, fell into despair and extreme grief, that bull among men [heroic person] ॥223॥" |
| `Line 1410:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1411: स सत्कृत्य यदुश्रेष्ठं मातुलं शौरिमात्मनः |` | "He, having performed the last rites for the best of the Yadus [Krishna's clan], his maternal uncle Shauri [Krishna]," |
| `Line 1412: ददर्श यदुवीराणामापाने वैशसं महत् ||२२४||` | "Witnessed the great slaughter of the Yadu heroes at the drinking party ॥224॥" |
| `Line 1413:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1414: शरीरं वासुदेवस्य रामस्य च महात्मनः |` | "The body of Vasudeva [Krishna] and of the great-souled Rama [Balarama]," |
| `Line 1415: संस्कारं लम्भयामास वृष्णीनां च प्रधानतः ||२२५||` | "He ensured the funeral rites, especially for the foremost of the Vrishnis ॥225॥" |
| `Line 1416:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1417: स वृद्धबालमादाय द्वारवत्यास्ततो जनम् |` | "Taking the old and young people from Dwaraka," |
| `Line 1418: ददर्शापदि कष्टायां गाण्डीवस्य पराभवम् ||२२६||` | "He witnessed in that terrible calamity the failure of Gandiva [Arjuna's bow] ॥226॥" |
| `Line 1419:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1420: सर्वेषां चैव दिव्यानामस्त्राणामप्रसन्नताम् |` | "And the ineffectiveness of all divine weapons," |
| `Line 1421: नाशं वृष्णिकलत्राणां प्रभावानामनित्यताम् ||२२७||` | "The destruction of the Vrishni women, and the impermanence of powers ॥227॥" |
| `Line 1422:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1423: दृष्ट्वा निर्वेदमापन्नो व्यासवाक्यप्रचोदितः |` | "Seeing this, he became despondent and, prompted by Vyasa's words," |
| `Line 1424: धर्मराजं समासाद्य संन्यासं समरोचयेत् ||२२८||` | "Approaching Dharmaraja [Yudhishthira], he recommended renunciation ॥228॥" |
| `Line 1425:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1426: इत्येतन्मौसलं पर्व षोडशं परिकीर्तितम् |` | "Thus this Mausala Parva [Club section] is declared as the sixteenth," |
| `Line 1427: अध्यायाष्टौ समाख्याताः श्लोकानां च शतत्रयम् ||२२९||` | "Eight chapters are enumerated and three hundred verses ॥229॥" |
| `Line 1428:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1429: महाप्रस्थानिकं तस्मादूर्ध्वं सप्तदशं स्मृतम् |` | "After that, the seventeenth is known as Mahaprasthanika [Great Departure section]," |
| `Line 1430: यत्र राज्यं परित्यज्य पाण्डवाः पुरुषर्षभाः ||२३०||` | "Where, abandoning their kingdom, the Pandavas, those bulls among men [eminent heroes] ॥230॥" |
| `Line 1431:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1432: द्रौपद्या सहिता देव्या सिद्धिं परमिकां गताः ||२३०||` | "Together with the divine Draupadi, attained the supreme perfection [final liberation] ॥230॥" |
| `Line 1433:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1434: अत्राध्यायास्त्रयः प्रोक्ताः श्लोकानां च शतं तथा |` | "Here three chapters are declared, and likewise one hundred verses," |
| `Line 1435: विंशतिश्च तथा श्लोकाः सङ्ख्यातास्तत्त्वदर्शिना ||२३१||` | "And twenty verses are counted by the knower of truth [reality-seer] ॥231॥" |
| `Line 1436:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1437: स्वर्गपर्व ततो ज्ञेयं दिव्यं यत्तदमानुषम् |` | "Then should be known the Svarga Parva [Heaven section], which is divine and superhuman," |
| `Line 1438: अध्यायाः पञ्च सङ्ख्याताः पर्वैतदभिसङ्ख्यया ||२३२||` | "Five chapters are enumerated in this section by count ॥232॥" |
| `Line 1439:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1440: श्लोकानां द्वे शते चैव प्रसङ्ख्याते तपोधनाः ||२३२||` | "And two hundred verses are counted, O ascetics [wealth in penance] ॥232॥" |
| `Line 1441:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1442: अष्टादशैवमेतानि पर्वाण्युक्तान्यशेषतः |` | "Thus these eighteen sections have been described completely," |
| `Line 1443: खिलेषु हरिवंशश्च भविष्यच्च प्रकीर्तितम् ||२३३||` | "Among the supplements, the Harivamsha [Hari's lineage] and the Bhavishya [Future events] are proclaimed ॥233॥" |
| `Line 1444:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1445: एतदखिलमाख्यातं भारतं पर्वसङ्ग्रहात् |` | "This entire Bharata has been narrated in the compilation of sections," |
| `Line 1446: अष्टादश समाजग्मुरक्षौहिण्यो युयुत्सया ||२३४||` | "Eighteen akshauhinis [army units] came together with desire to fight ॥234॥" |
| `Line 1447:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1448: तन्महद्दारुणं युद्धमहान्यष्टादशाभवत् ||२३४||` | "That great terrible war lasted for eighteen days ॥234॥" |
| `Line 1449:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1450: यो विद्याच्चतुरो वेदान्साङ्गोपनिषदान्द्विजः |` | "That twice-born [Brahmin] who may know the four Vedas with their limbs [auxiliary texts] and Upanishads," |
| `Line 1451: न चाख्यानमिदं विद्यान्नैव स स्याद्विचक्षणः ||२३५||` | "One who does not know this narrative cannot be considered wise [discerning person] ॥235॥" |
| `Line 1452:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1453: श्रुत्वा त्विदमुपाख्यानं श्राव्यमन्यन्न रोचते |` | "After hearing this narrative, no other worthy story pleases," |
| `Line 1454: पुंस्कोकिलरुतं श्रुत्वा रूक्षा ध्वाङ्क्षस्य वागिव ||२३६||` | "Just as after hearing the male cuckoo's song, the harsh voice of a crow is displeasing ॥236॥" |
| `Line 1455:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1456: इतिहासोत्तमादस्माज्जायन्ते कविबुद्धयः |` | "From this supreme history [itihasa] arise the intellects of poets," |
| `Line 1457: पञ्चभ्य इव भूतेभ्यो लोकसंविधयस्त्रयः ||२३७||` | "Just as from the five elements arise the three worlds [lokas] ॥237॥" |
| `Line 1458:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1459: अस्याख्यानस्य विषये पुराणं वर्तते द्विजाः |` | "O twice-born ones [brahmins], all Puranas [ancient texts] exist within the scope of this narrative," |
| `Line 1460: अन्तरिक्षस्य विषये प्रजा इव चतुर्विधाः ||२३८||` | "Just as the four kinds of beings exist within the realm of the sky ॥238॥" |
| `Line 1461:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1462: क्रियागुणानां सर्वेषामिदमाख्यानमाश्रयः |` | "This narrative is the foundation of all actions and qualities," |
| `Line 1463: इन्द्रियाणां समस्तानां चित्रा इव मनःक्रियाः ||२३९||` | "Just as the mind's activities are the basis for all the senses ॥239॥" |
| `Line 1464:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1465: अनाश्रित्यैतदाख्यानं कथा भुवि न विद्यते |` | "Without relying on this narrative, no story exists on earth," |
| `Line 1466: आहारमनपाश्रित्य शरीरस्येव धारणम् ||२४०||` | "Just as there is no sustenance of the body without food ॥240॥" |
| `Line 1467:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1468: इदं सर्वैः कविवरैराख्यानमुपजीव्यते |` | "This narrative is the source of livelihood for all excellent poets," |
| `Line 1469: उदयप्रेप्सुभिर्भृत्यैरभिजात इवेश्वरः ||२४१||` | "Just as a noble lord is relied upon by servants seeking prosperity ॥241॥" |
| `Line 1470:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1471: द्वैपायनौष्ठपुटनिःसृतमप्रमेयं; पुण्यं पवित्रमथ पापहरं शिवं च |` | "Immeasurable, meritorious, pure, sin-destroying, and auspicious is that which emerged from the lips of Dvaipayana [Vyasa];" |
| `Line 1472: यो भारतं समधिगच्छति वाच्यमानं; किं तस्य पुष्करजलैरभिषेचनेन ||२४२||` | "For one who comprehends the Bharata when it is recited, what need is there for ablution with the waters of Pushkara [sacred lake]? ॥242॥" |
| `Line 1473:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1474: आख्यानं तदिदमनुत्तमं महार्थं; विन्यस्तं महदिह पर्वसङ्ग्रहेण |` | "This unsurpassed narrative of great meaning is arranged here in a collection of major sections [parvas];" |
| `Line 1475: श्रुत्वादौ भवति नृणां सुखावगाहं; विस्तीर्णं लवणजलं यथा प्लवेन ||२४३||` | "At first hearing it becomes easily accessible to men, just as the vast salt ocean becomes navigable with a boat ॥243॥" |
| `Line 1476:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1477:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1478:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1479:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1480:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1481:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1482: पौष्यपर्व` | "Paushya Parva [Paushya section]" |
| `Line 1483: ३` | "3" |
| `Line 1484:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1485:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1486: सूत उवाच||` | "Suta [bard sage] said:" |
| `Line 1487:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1488:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1489: जनमेजयः पारिक्षितः सह भ्रातृभिः कुरुक्षेत्रे दीर्घसत्रमुपास्ते |` | "Janamejaya, son of Parikshit, was performing a long sacrifice [dirgha-satra] at Kurukshetra [sacred field] with his brothers." |
| `Line 1490: तस्य भ्रातरस्त्रयः श्रुतसेन उग्रसेनो भीमसेन इति | ००१ |` | "His three brothers were Shrutasena, Ugrasena, and Bhimasena. |001|" |
| `Line 1491: तेषु तत्सत्रमुपासीनेषु तत्र श्वाभ्यागच्छत्सारमेयः |` | "While they were engaged in that sacrifice, a dog [offspring of Sarama] came there." |
| `Line 1492: स जनमेजयस्य भ्रातृभिरभिहतो रोरूयमाणो मातुः समीपमुपागच्छत् | ००२ |` | "Beaten by Janamejaya's brothers, it went whimpering to its mother. |002|" |
| `Line 1493: तं माता रोरूयमाणमुवाच |` | "The mother said to it as it was whimpering:" |
| `Line 1494: किं रोदिषि |` | "Why are you crying?" |
| `Line 1495: केनास्यभिहत इति | ००३ |` | "By whom have you been beaten? |003|" |
| `Line 1496: स एवमुक्तो मातरं प्रत्युवाच |` | "Thus addressed, it replied to its mother:" |
| `Line 1497: जनमेजयस्य भ्रातृभिरभिहतोऽस्मीति | ००४ |` | "I have been beaten by Janamejaya's brothers. |004|" |
| `Line 1498: तं माता प्रत्युवाच |` | "The mother replied to it:" |
| `Line 1499: व्यक्तं त्वया तत्रापराद्धं येनास्यभिहत इति | ००५ |` | "Clearly you must have committed some offense there, for which you were beaten. |005|" |
| `Line 1500: स तां पुनरुवाच |` | "It said to her again:" |
| `Line 1501: नापराध्यामि किञ्चित् |` | "I have not committed any offense." |
| `Line 1502: नावेक्षे हवींषि नावलिह इति | ००६ |` | "I neither looked at the sacrificial offerings nor licked them. |006|" |
| `Line 1503: तच्छ्रुत्वा तस्य माता सरमा पुत्रशोकार्ता तत्सत्रमुपागच्छद्यत्र स जनमेजयः सह भ्रातृभिर्दीर्घसत्रमुपास्ते | ००७ |` | "Hearing this, his mother Sarama [divine hound], distressed by her son's pain, went to that sacrifice where Janamejaya was performing the long sacrifice with his brothers. |007|" |
| `Line 1504: स तया क्रुद्धया तत्रोक्तः |` | "He was addressed there by her in anger:" |
| `Line 1505: अयं मे पुत्रो न किञ्चिदपराध्यति |` | "This son of mine has committed no offense." |
| `Line 1506: किमर्थमभिहत इति |` | "Why was he beaten?" |
| `Line 1507: यस्माच्चायमभिहतोऽनपकारी तस्माददृष्टं त्वां भयमागमिष्यतीति | ००८ |` | "Since he was beaten though innocent, therefore an unforeseen danger shall come upon you. |008|" |
| `Line 1508: स जनमेजय एवमुक्तो देवशुन्या सरमया दृढं सम्भ्रान्तो विषण्णश्चासीत् | ००९ |` | "Janamejaya, thus addressed by Sarama [divine hound], became deeply disturbed and dejected. |009|" |
| `Line 1509: स तस्मिन्सत्रे समाप्ते हास्तिनपुरं प्रत्येत्य पुरोहितमनुरूपमन्विच्छमानः परं यत्नमकरोद्यो मे पापकृत्यां शमयेदिति | ०१० |` | "After completing that sacrifice, he returned to Hastinapura [elephant city] and made great efforts to find a suitable priest who could absolve him of his sinful deed. |010|" |
| `Line 1510: स कदाचिन्मृगयां यातः पारिक्षितो जनमेजयः कस्मिंश्चित्स्वविषयोद्देशे आश्रममपश्यत् | ०११ |` | "Once, while hunting, Janamejaya, son of Parikshit, saw a hermitage in some region of his kingdom. |011|" |
| `Line 1511: तत्र कश्चिदृषिरासां चक्रे श्रुतश्रवा नाम |` | "There a certain sage named Shrutashrava was residing." |
| `Line 1512: तस्याभिमतः पुत्र आस्ते सोमश्रवा नाम | ०१२ |` | "His beloved son named Somashrava was staying there. |012|" |
| `Line 1513: तस्य तं पुत्रमभिगम्य जनमेजयः पारिक्षितः पौरोहित्याय वव्रे | ०१३ |` | "Approaching that son, Janamejaya, son of Parikshit, requested him to become his priest. |013|" |
| `Line 1514: स नमस्कृत्य तमृषिमुवाच |` | "He, bowing to that sage, said:" |
| `Line 1515: भगवन्नयं तव पुत्रो मम पुरोहितोऽस्त्विति | ०१४ |` | "Venerable one, may this son of yours become my priest. |014|" |
| `Line 1516: स एवमुक्तः प्रत्युवाच |` | "Thus addressed, he replied:" |
| `Line 1517: भो जनमेजय पुत्रोऽयं मम सर्प्यां जातः |` | "O Janamejaya, this son of mine was born of a serpent woman [sarpi]." |
| `Line 1518: महातपस्वी स्वाध्यायसम्पन्नो मत्तपोवीर्यसम्भृतो मच्छुक्रं पीतवत्यास्तस्याः कुक्षौ संवृद्धः |` | "He is of great austerity, accomplished in self-study, conceived through my ascetic power, grown in the womb of her who drank my seed." |
| `Line 1519: समर्थोऽयं भवतः सर्वाः पापकृत्याः शमयितुमन्तरेण महादेवकृत्याम् |` | "He is capable of absolving all your sinful deeds, except those against Mahadeva [Shiva]." |
| `Line 1520: अस्य त्वेकमुपांशुव्रतम् |` | "But he has one silent vow:" |
| `Line 1521: यदेनं कश्चिद्ब्राह्मणः कञ्चिदर्थमभियाचेत्तं तस्मै दद्यादयम् |` | "If any Brahmin should ask him for anything, he must give it to him." |
| `Line 1522: यद्येतदुत्सहसे ततो नयस्वैनमिति | ०१५ |` | "If you can endure this, then take him. |015|" |
| `Line 1523: तेनैवमुत्को जनमेजयस्तं प्रत्युवाच |` | "Thus addressed, Janamejaya replied to him:" |
| `Line 1524: भगवंस्तथा भविष्यतीति | ०१६ |` | "Venerable one, so be it. |016|" |
| `Line 1525: स तं पुरोहितमुपादायोपावृत्तो भ्रातृनुवाच |` | "Taking that priest with him and returning, he said to his brothers:" |
| `Line 1526: मयायं वृत उपाध्यायः |` | "This teacher has been chosen by me." |
| `Line 1527: यदयं ब्रूयात्तत्कार्यमविचारयद्भिरिति | ०१७ |` | "Whatever he says should be done by you without questioning. |017|" |
| `Line 1528: तेनैवमुक्ता भ्रातरस्तस्य तथा चक्रुः |` | "Thus instructed by him, his brothers did accordingly." |
| `Line 1529: स तथा भ्रातृन्संदिश्य तक्षशिलां प्रत्यभिप्रतस्थे |` | "Having thus instructed his brothers, he departed for Takshashila [ancient learning center]." |
| `Line 1530: तं च देशं वशे स्थापयामास | ०१८ |` | "And he brought that region under his control. |018|" |
| `Line 1531: एतस्मिन्नन्तरे कश्चिदृषिर्धौम्यो नामायोदः |` | "During this time, there was a sage named Dhaumya Ayoda [revered teacher]." |
| `Line 1532: तस्य शिष्यास्त्रयो बभूवुरुपमन्युरारुणिर्वेदश्चेति | ०१९ |` | "He had three disciples: Upamanyu, Aruni, and Veda. |019|" |
| `Line 1533: स एकं शिष्यमारुणिं पाञ्चाल्यं प्रेषयामास |` | "He sent one disciple, Aruni of Panchala [region name], saying:" |
| `Line 1534: गच्छ केदारखण्डं बधानेति | ०२० |` | "Go and repair the breach in the field [kedara-khanda]. |020|" |
| `Line 1535: स उपाध्यायेन संदिष्ट आरुणिः पाञ्चाल्यस्तत्र गत्वा तत्केदारखण्डं बद्धुं नाशक्नोत् | ०२१ |` | "Instructed by his teacher, Aruni of Panchala went there but was unable to repair that breach in the field. |021|" |
| `Line 1536: स क्लिश्यमानोऽपश्यदुपायम् |` | "Struggling, he saw a solution." |
| `Line 1537: भवत्वेवं करिष्यामीति | ०२२ |` | "Let it be so, I will do this," he thought. |022|" |
| `Line 1538: स तत्र संविवेश केदारखण्डे |` | "He lay down in the breach of the field." |
| `Line 1539: शयाने तस्मिंस्तदुदकं तस्थौ | ०२३ |` | "As he lay there, the water stopped flowing. |023|" |
| `Line 1540: ततः कदाचिदुपाध्याय आयोदो धौम्यः शिष्यानपृच्छत् |` | "Then, after some time, the teacher Dhaumya Ayoda asked his disciples:" |
| `Line 1541: क्व आरुणिः पाञ्चाल्यो गत इति | ०२४ |` | "Where has Aruni of Panchala gone? |024|" |
| `Line 1542: ते प्रत्यूचुः |` | "They replied:" |
| `Line 1543: भगवतैव प्रेषितो गच्छ केदारखण्डं बधानेति | ०२५ |` | "He was sent by your reverence yourself, saying 'Go and repair the breach in the field.' |025|" |
| `Line 1544: स एवमुक्तस्ताञ्शिष्यान्प्रत्युवाच |` | "Having heard this, he said to those disciples:" |
| `Line 1545: तस्मात्सर्वे तत्र गच्छामो यत्र स इति | ०२६ |` | "Therefore, let us all go where he is. |026|" |
| `Line 1546: स तत्र गत्वा तस्याह्वानाय शब्दं चकार |` | "Having gone there, he called out to him:" |
| `Line 1547: भो आरुणे पाञ्चाल्य क्वासि |` | "O Aruni of Panchala, where are you?" |
| `Line 1548: वत्सैहीति | ०२७ |` | "Come here, my child! |027|" |
| `Line 1549: स तच्छ्रुत्वा आरुणिरुपाध्यायवाक्यं तस्मात्केदारखण्डात्सहसोत्थाय तमुपाध्यायमुपतस्थे |` | "Hearing those words of his teacher, Aruni suddenly rose up from that breach in the field and approached his teacher." |
| `Line 1550: प्रोवाच चैनम् |` | "And he said to him:" |
| `Line 1551: अयमस्म्यत्र केदारखण्डे निःसरमाणमुदकमवारणीयं संरोद्धुं संविष्टो भगवच्छब्दं श्रुत्वैव सहसा विदार्य केदारखण्डं भवन्तमुपस्थितः |` | "Here I am, seated in this field section to stop the unstoppable flowing water, when upon hearing the venerable word, I suddenly broke through the field embankment and came before you." |
| `Line 1552: तदभिवादये भगवन्तम् |` | "Therefore, I pay my respects to you, venerable one." |
| `Line 1553: आज्ञापयतु भवान् |` | "Please command me, sir." |
| `Line 1554: किं करवाणीति | ०२८ |` | "What shall I do? |028|" |
| `Line 1555: तमुपाध्यायोऽब्रवीत् |` | "The teacher [upādhyāya] said to him:" |
| `Line 1556: यस्माद्भवान्केदारखण्डमवदार्योत्थितस्तस्माद्भवानुद्दालक एव नाम्ना भविष्यतीति | ०२९ |` | "Since you have risen by breaking through the field embankment, therefore you shall be known by the name Uddālaka [one who breaks through]. |029|" |
| `Line 1557: स उपाध्यायेनानुगृहीतः |` | "He was blessed by the teacher:" |
| `Line 1558: यस्मात्त्वया मद्वचोऽनुष्ठितं तस्माच्छ्रेयोऽवाप्स्यसीति |` | "Since you have followed my instruction, therefore you shall attain excellence." |
| `Line 1559: सर्वे च ते वेदाः प्रतिभास्यन्ति सर्वाणि च धर्मशास्त्राणीति | ०३० |` | "And all the Vedas [sacred texts] and all the treatises on dharma [righteousness] will become clear to you. |030|" |
| `Line 1560: स एवमुक्त उपाध्यायेनेष्टं देशं जगाम | ०३१ |` | "Having been thus addressed by the teacher, he went to his desired place. |031|" |
| `Line 1561: अथापरः शिष्यस्तस्यैवायोदस्य धौम्यस्योपमन्युर्नाम | ०३२ |` | "Now, another student of that same Āyoda Dhaumya was named Upamanyu. |032|" |
| `Line 1562: तमुपाध्यायः प्रेषयामास |` | "The teacher sent him:" |
| `Line 1563: वत्सोपमन्यो गा रक्षस्वेति | ०३३ |` | "Child Upamanyu, tend the cows. |033|" |
| `Line 1564: स उपाध्यायवचनादरक्षद्गाः |` | "Following the teacher's instruction, he tended the cows." |
| `Line 1565: स चाहनि गा रक्षित्वा दिवसक्षयेऽभ्यागम्योपाध्यायस्याग्रतः स्थित्वा नमश्चक्रे | ०३४ |` | "And after tending the cows during the day, at sunset he returned, stood before his teacher, and paid his respects. |034|" |
| `Line 1566: तमुपाध्यायः पीवानमपश्यत् |` | "The teacher saw that he was well-nourished." |
| `Line 1567: उवाच चैनम् |` | "And said to him:" |
| `Line 1568: वत्सोपमन्यो केन वृत्तिं कल्पयसि |` | "Child Upamanyu, how do you sustain yourself?" |
| `Line 1569: पीवानसि दृढमिति | ०३५ |` | "You are certainly well-nourished. |035|" |
| `Line 1570: स उपाध्यायं प्रत्युवाच |` | "He replied to the teacher:" |
| `Line 1571: भैक्षेण वृत्तिं कल्पयामीति | ०३६ |` | "I sustain myself by begging for alms. |036|" |
| `Line 1572: तमुपाध्यायः प्रत्युवाच |` | "The teacher replied to him:" |
| `Line 1573: ममानिवेद्य भैक्षं नोपयोक्तव्यमिति | ०३७ |` | "The alms should not be consumed without first offering them to me. |037|" |
| `Line 1574: स तथेत्युक्त्वा पुनररक्षद्गाः |` | "Having said 'so be it,' he again tended the cows." |
| `Line 1575: रक्षित्वा चागम्य तथैवोपाध्यायस्याग्रतः स्थित्वा नमश्चक्रे | ०३८ |` | "And after tending them and returning, he stood before his teacher in the same way and paid his respects. |038|" |
| `Line 1576: तमुपाध्यायस्तथापि पीवानमेव दृष्ट्वोवाच |` | "The teacher, seeing him still plump, said:" |
| `Line 1577: वत्सोपमन्यो सर्वमशेषतस्ते भैक्षं गृह्णामि |` | "Dear Upamanyu, I take all your alms without exception." |
| `Line 1578: केनेदानीं वृत्तिं कल्पयसीति | ०३९ |` | "How are you now sustaining yourself? |039|" |
| `Line 1579: स एवमुक्त उपाध्यायेन प्रत्युवाच |` | "Thus addressed by the teacher, he replied:" |
| `Line 1580: भगवते निवेद्य पूर्वमपरं चरामि |` | "After offering the first portion to you, venerable one, I go for a second round of alms." |
| `Line 1581: तेन वृत्तिं कल्पयामीति | ०४० |` | "By that means I sustain myself. |040|" |
| `Line 1582: तमुपाध्यायः प्रत्युवाच |` | "The teacher replied to him:" |
| `Line 1583: नैषा न्याय्या गुरुवृत्तिः |` | "This is not proper conduct toward a guru [teacher]." |
| `Line 1584: अन्येषामपि वृत्त्युपरोधं करोष्येवं वर्तमानः |` | "By acting this way, you are also obstructing the livelihood of others." |
| `Line 1585: लुब्धोऽसीति | ०४१ |` | "You are greedy. |041|" |
| `Line 1586: स तथेत्युक्त्वा गा अरक्षत् |` | "Saying 'so be it,' he tended the cows." |
| `Line 1587: रक्षित्वा च पुनरुपाध्यायगृहमागम्योपाध्यायस्याग्रतः स्थित्वा नमश्चक्रे | ०४२ |` | "After tending them, he returned to the teacher's house, stood before the teacher, and paid his respects. |042|" |
| `Line 1588: तमुपाध्यायस्तथापि पीवानमेव दृष्ट्वा पुनरुवाच |` | "The teacher, seeing him still plump, said again:" |
| `Line 1589: अहं ते सर्वं भैक्षं गृह्णामि न चान्यच्चरसि |` | "I take all your alms, and you do not go for a second round." |
| `Line 1590: पीवानसि |` | "Yet you are plump." |
| `Line 1591: केन वृत्तिं कल्पयसीति | ०४३ |` | "How are you sustaining yourself? |043|" |
| `Line 1592: स उपाध्यायं प्रत्युवाच |` | "He replied to the teacher:" |
| `Line 1593: भो एतासां गवां पयसा वृत्तिं कल्पयामीति | ०४४ |` | "Sir, I sustain myself with the milk of these cows. |044|" |
| `Line 1594: तमुपाध्यायः प्रत्युवाच |` | "The teacher replied to him:" |
| `Line 1595: नैतन्न्याय्यं पय उपयोक्तुं भवतो मयाननुज्ञातमिति | ०४५ |` | "It is not proper for you to consume milk without my permission. |045|" |
| `Line 1596: स तथेति प्रतिज्ञाय गा रक्षित्वा पुनरुपाध्यायगृहानेत्य गुरोरग्रतः स्थित्वा नमश्चक्रे | ०४६ |` | "Promising 'so be it,' he tended the cows, then returned to the teacher's house, stood before the guru, and paid his respects. |046|" |
| `Line 1597: तमुपाध्यायः पीवानमेवापश्यत् |` | "The teacher saw that he was still plump." |
| `Line 1598: उवाच चैनम् |` | "And he said to him:" |
| `Line 1599: भैक्षं नाश्नासि न चान्यच्चरसि |` | "You do not eat alms, nor do you go for a second round." |
| `Line 1600: पयो न पिबसि |` | "You do not drink milk." |
| `Line 1601: पीवानसि |` | "You are fat [well-fed]." |
| `Line 1602: केन वृत्तिं कल्पयसीति | ०४७ |` | "How do you sustain yourself [earn livelihood]? |047|" |
| `Line 1603: स एवमुक्त उपाध्यायं प्रत्युवाच |` | "Thus addressed, he replied to his teacher:" |
| `Line 1604: भोः फेनं पिबामि यमिमे वत्सा मातृणां स्तनं पिबन्त उद्गिरन्तीति | ०४८ |` | "Sir, I drink the foam which these calves spit out while drinking milk from their mothers' udders. |048|" |
| `Line 1605: तमुपाध्यायः प्रत्युवाच |` | "The teacher replied to him:" |
| `Line 1606: एते त्वदनुकम्पया गुणवन्तो वत्साः प्रभूततरं फेनमुद्गिरन्ति |` | "These virtuous calves, out of compassion for you, are spitting out more foam." |
| `Line 1607: तदेवमपि वत्सानां वृत्त्युपरोधं करोष्येवं वर्तमानः |` | "Even so, by acting this way, you are obstructing the livelihood of the calves." |
| `Line 1608: फेनमपि भवान्न पातुमर्हतीति | ०४९ |` | "You should not even drink the foam. |049|" |
| `Line 1609: स तथेति प्रतिज्ञाय निराहारस्ता गा अरक्षत् |` | "Having promised 'so be it,' he tended the cows without taking any food." |
| `Line 1610: तथा प्रतिषिद्धो भैक्षं नाश्नाति न चान्यच्चरति |` | "Thus prohibited, he neither ate alms nor did anything else." |
| `Line 1611: पयो न पिबति |` | "He did not drink milk." |
| `Line 1612: फेनं नोपयुङ्क्ते | ०५० |` | "He did not consume the foam. |050|" |
| `Line 1613: स कदाचिदरण्ये क्षुधार्तोऽर्कपत्राण्यभक्षयत् | ०५१ |` | "Once, tormented by hunger in the forest, he ate the leaves of the arka plant [milkweed]. |051|" |
| `Line 1614: स तैरर्कपत्रैर्भक्षितैः क्षारकटूष्णविपाकिभिश्चक्षुष्युपहतोऽन्धोऽभवत् |` | "By eating those arka leaves, which have caustic, pungent, and hot properties, his eyes were damaged and he became blind." |
| `Line 1615: सोऽन्धोऽपि चङ्क्रम्यमाणः कूपेऽपतत् | ०५२ |` | "Though blind, while wandering about, he fell into a well. |052|" |
| `Line 1616: अथ तस्मिन्ननागच्छत्युपाध्यायः शिष्यानवोचत् |` | "Then, when he did not return, the teacher said to his disciples:" |
| `Line 1617: मयोपमन्युः सर्वतः प्रतिषिद्धः |` | "Upamanyu has been prohibited by me from all sources of food." |
| `Line 1618: स नियतं कुपितः |` | "He must certainly be angry." |
| `Line 1619: ततो नागच्छति चिरगतश्चेति | ०५३ |` | "That is why he has not returned and has been gone so long. |053|" |
| `Line 1620: स एवमुक्त्वा गत्वारण्यमुपमन्योराह्वानं चक्रे |` | "Having said this, he went to the forest and called out for Upamanyu:" |
| `Line 1621: भो उपमन्यो क्वासि |` | "O Upamanyu, where are you?" |
| `Line 1622: वत्सैहीति | ०५४ |` | "Come here, my child! |054|" |
| `Line 1623: स तदाह्वानमुपाध्यायाच्छ्रुत्वा प्रत्युवाचोच्चैः |` | "Hearing that call from his teacher, he replied loudly:" |
| `Line 1624: अयमस्मि भो उपाध्याय कूपे पतित इति | ०५५ |` | "Here I am, O teacher, fallen into a well! |055|" |
| `Line 1625: तमुपाध्यायः प्रत्युवाच |` | "The teacher replied to him:" |
| `Line 1626: कथमसि कूपे पतित इति | ०५६ |` | "How did you fall into the well? |056|" |
| `Line 1627: स तं प्रत्युवाच |` | "He replied to him:" |
| `Line 1628: अर्कपत्राणि भक्षयित्वान्धीभूतोऽस्मि |` | "Having eaten arka [milkweed] leaves, I became blind." |
| `Line 1629: अतः कूपे पतित इति | ०५७ |` | "That is why I fell into the well. |057|" |
| `Line 1630: तमुपाध्यायः प्रत्युवाच |` | "The teacher replied to him:" |
| `Line 1631: अश्विनौ स्तुहि |` | "Praise the Ashvins [divine physician twins]." |
| `Line 1632: तौ त्वां चक्षुष्मन्तं करिष्यतो देवभिषजाविति | ०५८ |` | "Those divine physicians will restore your eyesight. |058|" |
| `Line 1633: स एवमुक्त उपाध्यायेन स्तोतुं प्रचक्रमे देवावश्विनौ वाग्भिरृग्भिः | ०५९ |` | "Thus instructed by the teacher, he began to praise the divine Ashvins with words and Rig Vedic verses. |059|" |
| `Line 1634: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1635: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1636: प्र पूर्वगौ पूर्वजौ चित्रभानू; गिरा वा शंसामि तपनावनन्तौ |` | "I praise with my voice the foremost ones, the first-born, of brilliant light; the radiant ones, the boundless ones." |
| `Line 1637: दिव्यौ सुपर्णौ विरजौ विमाना; वधिक्षियन्तौ भुवनानि विश्वा ||६०||` | "The two divine, well-winged, stainless, immeasurable ones, who rule over all the worlds. ||60||" |
| `Line 1638: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1639: हिरण्मयौ शकुनी साम्परायौ; नासत्यदस्रौ सुनसौ वैजयन्तौ |` | "The two golden birds, companions in the journey; the truthful and miraculous ones, with beautiful noses, victorious." |
| `Line 1640: शुक्रं वयन्तौ तरसा सुवेमा; वभि व्ययन्तावसितं विवस्वत् ||६१||` | "Weaving brightness with speed, with excellent work; dispelling the darkness of the sun. ||61||" |
| `Line 1641: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1642: ग्रस्तां सुपर्णस्य बलेन वर्तिका; ममुञ्चतामश्विनौ सौभगाय |` | "The quail [bird] seized by the might of the eagle; the Ashvins released it for good fortune." |
| `Line 1643: तावत्सुवृत्तावनमन्त मायया; सत्तमा गा अरुणा उदावहन् ||६२||` | "Those two excellent ones bowed with their power; the most excellent reddish cows they brought forth. ||62||" |
| `Line 1644: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1645: षष्टिश्च गावस्त्रिशताश्च धेनव; एकं वत्सं सुवते तं दुहन्ति |` | "Three hundred and sixty cows give birth to one calf and they all milk it." |
| `Line 1646: नानागोष्ठा विहिता एकदोहना; स्तावश्विनौ दुहतो घर्ममुक्थ्यम् ||६३||` | "Though in different cow-pens, they yield milk at once; those Ashvins milk the praiseworthy ghee [clarified butter]. ||63||" |
| `Line 1647: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1648: एकां नाभिं सप्तशता अराः श्रिताः; प्रधिष्वन्या विंशतिरर्पिता अराः |` | "Seven hundred spokes are fixed in one hub; in another rim, twenty spokes are fixed." |
| `Line 1649: अनेमि चक्रं परिवर्ततेऽजरं; मायाश्विनौ समनक्ति चर्षणी ||६४||` | "The rimless wheel revolves without aging; the power of the Ashvins unites the people. ||64||" |
| `Line 1650: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1651: एकं चक्रं वर्तते द्वादशारं प्रधि; षण्णाभिमेकाक्षममृतस्य धारणम् |` | "One wheel revolves with twelve spokes, six naves, and one axle, holding immortality [eternal essence]." |
| `Line 1652: यस्मिन्देवा अधि विश्वे विषक्ता; स्तावश्विनौ मुञ्चतो मा विषीदतम् ||६५||` | "Upon which all the gods are fixed; O Ashvins [divine twins], release me, let me not perish. ||65||" |
| `Line 1653: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1654: अश्विनाविन्द्रममृतं वृत्तभूयौ; तिरोधत्तामश्विनौ दासपत्नी |` | "The Ashvins, having become the immortal Indra [king of gods], concealed themselves; the Ashvins, masters of the Dāsa [servant class]." |
| `Line 1655: भित्त्वा गिरिमश्विनौ गामुदाचरन्तौ; तद्वृष्टमह्ना प्रथिता वलस्य ||६६||` | "Breaking through the mountain, the Ashvins brought forth the cow [or speech]; that rain by day is renowned as Vala's [demon's]. ||66||" |
| `Line 1656: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1657: युवां दिशो जनयथो दशाग्रे; समानं मूर्ध्नि रथया वियन्ति |` | "You two create the ten directions at the beginning; they spread out equally from the head in chariots." |
| `Line 1658: तासां यातमृषयोऽनुप्रयान्ति; देवा मनुष्याः क्षितिमाचरन्ति ||६७||` | "The sages follow their path; gods and humans traverse the earth. ||67||" |
| `Line 1659: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1660: युवां वर्णान्विकुरुथो विश्वरूपां; स्तेऽधिक्षियन्ति भुवनानि विश्वा |` | "You two create colors of universal forms; they pervade all the worlds." |
| `Line 1661: ते भानवोऽप्यनुसृताश्चरन्ति; देवा मनुष्याः क्षितिमाचरन्ति ||६८||` | "Those rays, being followed, move about; gods and humans traverse the earth. ||68||" |
| `Line 1662: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1663: तौ नासत्यावश्विनावामहे वां; स्रजं च यां बिभृथः पुष्करस्य |` | "We invoke you two, the Nāsatyas [truthful ones], the Ashvins, and the garland of the lotus that you both wear." |
| `Line 1664: तौ नासत्यावमृतावृतावृधा; वृते देवास्तत्प्रपदेन सूते ||६९||` | "Those two Nāsatyas, immortal, truth-increasing; the gods are enclosed by that forefoot in creation. ||69||" |
| `Line 1665: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1666: मुखेन गर्भं लभतां युवानौ; गतासुरेतत्प्रपदेन सूते |` | "May the young ones receive the embryo through the mouth; when life has departed, it gives birth through that forefoot." |
| `Line 1667: सद्यो जातो मातरमत्ति गर्भ; स्तावश्विनौ मुञ्चथो जीवसे गाः ||७०||` | "As soon as born, the embryo consumes its mother; O Ashvins, release the cows [or rays] for life. ||70||" |
| `Line 1668: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1669: एवं तेनाभिष्टुतावश्विनावाजग्मतुः |` | "Thus praised by him, the Ashvins arrived." |
| `Line 1670: आहतुश्चैनम् |` | "And they said to him:" |
| `Line 1671: प्रीतौ स्वः |` | "We are pleased with you." |
| `Line 1672: एष तेऽपूपः |` | "Here is a cake for you." |
| `Line 1673: अशानैनमिति | ०७१ |` | "Eat it. |071|" |
| `Line 1674: स एवमुक्तः प्रत्युवाच |` | "Being thus addressed, he replied:" |
| `Line 1675: नानृतमूचतुर्भवन्तौ |` | "You two have not spoken untruth." |
| `Line 1676: न त्वहमेतमपूपमुपयोक्तुमुत्सहे अनिवेद्य गुरव इति | ०७२ |` | "But I cannot bring myself to eat this cake without informing my teacher. |072|" |
| `Line 1677: ततस्तमश्विनावूचतुः |` | "Then the Ashvins [divine twin physicians] said to him:" |
| `Line 1678: आवाभ्यां पुरस्ताद्भवत उपाध्यायेनैवमेवाभिष्टुताभ्यामपूपः प्रीताभ्यां दत्तः |` | "Previously, your teacher himself offered a cake to us when we were pleased by his praises." |
| `Line 1679: उपयुक्तश्च स तेनानिवेद्य गुरवे |` | "And he consumed it without informing his own teacher." |
| `Line 1680: त्वमपि तथैव कुरुष्व यथा कृतमुपाध्यायेनेति | ०७३ |` | "You should also do just as your teacher did. |073|" |
| `Line 1681: स एवमुक्तः पुनरेव प्रत्युवाचैतौ |` | "Having been thus addressed, he again replied to them:" |
| `Line 1682: प्रत्यनुनये भवन्तावश्विनौ |` | "I beg your pardon, O Ashvins." |
| `Line 1683: नोत्सहेऽहमनिवेद्योपाध्यायायोपयोक्तुमिति | ०७४ |` | "I cannot bring myself to consume this without informing my teacher. |074|" |
| `Line 1684: तमश्विनावाहतुः |` | "The Ashvins said to him:" |
| `Line 1685: प्रीतौ स्वस्तवानया गुरुवृत्त्या |` | "We are pleased with your praise and this devotion to your teacher." |
| `Line 1686: उपाध्यायस्य ते कार्ष्णायसा दन्ताः |` | "Your teacher's teeth are of iron." |
| `Line 1687: भवतो हिरण्मया भविष्यन्ति |` | "Yours shall become golden." |
| `Line 1688: चक्षुष्मांश्च भविष्यसि |` | "And you shall regain your sight." |
| `Line 1689: श्रेयश्चावाप्स्यसीति | ०७५ |` | "And you shall attain prosperity. |075|" |
| `Line 1690: स एवमुक्तोऽश्विभ्यां लब्धचक्षुरुपाध्यायसकाशमागम्योपाध्यायमभिवाद्याचचक्षे |` | "Thus addressed by the Ashvins, having regained his sight, he went to his teacher, greeted him, and told him everything." |
| `Line 1691: स चास्य प्रीतिमानभूत् | ०७६ |` | "And the teacher was pleased with him. |076|" |
| `Line 1692: आह चैनम् |` | "And he said to him:" |
| `Line 1693: यथाश्विनावाहतुस्तथा त्वं श्रेयोऽवाप्स्यसीति |` | "As the Ashvins have said, so shall you attain prosperity." |
| `Line 1694: सर्वे च ते वेदाः प्रतिभास्यन्तीति | ०७७ |` | "And all the Vedas [sacred texts] shall become clear to you. |077|" |
| `Line 1695: एषा तस्यापि परीक्षोपमन्योः | ०७८ |` | "This was the test of Upamanyu as well. |078|" |
| `Line 1696: अथापरः शिष्यस्तस्यैवायोदस्य धौम्यस्य वेदो नाम | ०७९ |` | "Now, another disciple of that same Ayoda Dhaumya was named Veda. |079|" |
| `Line 1697: तमुपाध्यायः संदिदेश |` | "The teacher instructed him:" |
| `Line 1698: वत्स वेद इहास्यताम् |` | "Dear Veda, stay here." |
| `Line 1699: भवता मद्गृहे कञ्चित्कालं शुश्रूषमाणेन भवितव्यम् |` | "You must serve in my house for some time." |
| `Line 1700: श्रेयस्ते भविष्यतीति | ०८० |` | "It will be beneficial for you. |080|" |
| `Line 1701: स तथेत्युक्त्वा गुरुकुले दीर्घकालं गुरुशुश्रूषणपरोऽवसत् |` | "Having said 'so be it,' he lived in the teacher's household for a long time, devoted to serving his guru." |
| `Line 1702: गौरिव नित्यं गुरुषु धूर्षु नियुज्यमानः शीतोष्णक्षुत्तृष्णादुःखसहः सर्वत्राप्रतिकूलः | ०८१ |` | "Like an ox, constantly engaged in heavy tasks by his teachers, enduring the suffering of cold, heat, hunger and thirst, never being contrary in any situation. |081|" |
| `Line 1703: तस्य महता कालेन गुरुः परितोषं जगाम |` | "After a long time, his teacher became completely satisfied with him." |
| `Line 1704: तत्परितोषाच्च श्रेयः सर्वज्ञतां चावाप |` | "And from that satisfaction, he attained excellence and omniscience." |
| `Line 1705: एषा तस्यापि परीक्षा वेदस्य | ०८२ |` | "This was also his test by Veda [sage/teacher]. |082|" |
| `Line 1706: स उपाध्यायेनानुज्ञातः समावृत्तस्तस्माद्गुरुकुलवासाद्गृहाश्रमं प्रत्यपद्यत |` | "Having been permitted by his teacher, he completed his education and departed from the teacher's residence to enter the householder stage [gṛhastha āśrama]." |
| `Line 1707: तस्यापि स्वगृहे वसतस्त्रयः शिष्या बभूवुः | ०८३ |` | "While living in his own house, he too had three disciples. |083|" |
| `Line 1708: स शिष्यान्न किञ्चिदुवाच |` | "He did not say anything to his disciples." |
| `Line 1709: कर्म वा क्रियतां गुरुशुश्रूषा वेति |` | "Neither 'perform this work' nor 'serve the teacher.'" |
| `Line 1710: दुःखाभिज्ञो हि गुरुकुलवासस्य शिष्यान्परिक्लेशेन योजयितुं नेयेष | ०८४ |` | "For having known the hardships of living in a teacher's household, he did not wish to subject his disciples to such suffering. |084|" |
| `Line 1711: अथ कस्यचित्कालस्य वेदं ब्राह्मणं जनमेजयः पौष्यश्च क्षत्रियावुपेत्योपाध्यायं वरयां चक्रतुः | ०८५ |` | "Then after some time, Janamejaya and Paushya, two Kshatriyas [warrior class], approached Veda the Brahmin and chose him as their teacher. |085|" |
| `Line 1712: स कदाचिद्याज्यकार्येणाभिप्रस्थित उत्तङ्कं नाम शिष्यं नियोजयामास |` | "Once, when departing for a sacrificial ceremony, he instructed his disciple named Uttanka:" |
| `Line 1713: भो उत्तङ्क यत्किञ्चिदस्मद्गृहे परिहीयते तदिच्छाम्यहमपरिहीणं भवता क्रियमाणमिति | ०८६ |` | "O Uttanka, whatever needs to be maintained in our house, I wish that you would keep it all in good order. |086|" |
| `Line 1714: स एवं प्रतिसमादिश्योत्तङ्कं वेदः प्रवासं जगाम | ०८७ |` | "Having given these instructions to Uttanka, Veda went away on his journey. |087|" |
| `Line 1715: अथोत्तङ्को गुरुशुश्रूषुर्गुरुनियोगमनुतिष्ठमानस्तत्र गुरुकुले वसति स्म | ०८८ |` | "Then Uttanka, eager to serve his teacher and following his instructions, continued to live in the teacher's household. |088|" |
| `Line 1716: स वसंस्तत्रोपाध्यायस्त्रीभिः सहिताभिराहूयोक्तः |` | "While living there, he was called and told by the teacher's wives together:" |
| `Line 1717: उपाध्यायिनी ते ऋतुमती |` | "Your teacher's wife is in her fertile period [menstruating]." |
| `Line 1718: उपाध्यायश्च प्रोषितः |` | "And the teacher is away from home." |
| `Line 1719: अस्या यथायमृतुर्वन्ध्यो न भवति तथा क्रियताम् |` | "Act in such a way that her fertile period does not go in vain." |
| `Line 1720: एतद्विषीदतीति | ०८९ |` | "She is distressed about this. |089|" |
| `Line 1721: स एवमुक्तस्ताः स्त्रियः प्रत्युवाच |` | "Having been told this, he replied to those women:" |
| `Line 1722: न मया स्त्रीणां वचनादिदमकार्यं कार्यम् |` | "I should not do this improper act at the word of women." |
| `Line 1723: न ह्यहमुपाध्यायेन संदिष्टः |` | "For I have not been instructed by my teacher to do this." |
| `Line 1724: अकार्यमपि त्वया कार्यमिति | ०९० |` | "That even improper acts should be done by me. |090|" |
| `Line 1725: तस्य पुनरुपाध्यायः कालान्तरेण गृहानुपजगाम तस्मात्प्रवासात् |` | "After some time, his teacher returned home from that journey." |
| `Line 1726: स तद्वृत्तं तस्याशेषमुपलभ्य प्रीतिमानभूत् | ०९१ |` | "Having learned the entire account of his conduct, he became pleased. |091|" |
| `Line 1727: उवाच चैनम् |` | "And he said to him:" |
| `Line 1728: वत्सोत्तङ्क किं ते प्रियं करवाणीति |` | "My child Uttanka, what may I do for you that would be pleasing?" |
| `Line 1729: धर्मतो हि शुश्रूषितोऽस्मि भवता |` | "Indeed, you have served me according to dharma [righteous duty]." |
| `Line 1730: तेन प्रीतिः परस्परेण नौ संवृद्धा |` | "Through this, affection between us has grown." |
| `Line 1731: तदनुजाने भवन्तम् |` | "Therefore, I give you permission [to depart]." |
| `Line 1732: सर्वामेव सिद्धिं प्राप्स्यसि |` | "You will attain complete success." |
| `Line 1733: गम्यतामिति | ०९२ |` | "You may go. |092|" |
| `Line 1734: स एवमुक्तः प्रत्युवाच |` | "Thus addressed, he replied:" |
| `Line 1735: किं ते प्रियं करवाणीति |` | "What may I do that would please you?" |
| `Line 1736: एवं ह्याहुः | ०९३ |` | "For thus they say: |093|" |
| `Line 1737: यश्चाधर्मेण विब्रूयाद्यश्चाधर्मेण पृच्छति | ०९४ |` | "He who speaks unrighteously and he who questions unrighteously, |094|" |
| `Line 1738: तयोरन्यतरः प्रैति विद्वेषं चाधिगच्छति |` | "One of them perishes and incurs hatred." |
| `Line 1739: सोऽहमनुज्ञातो भवता इच्छामीष्टं ते गुर्वर्थमुपहर्तुमिति | ०९५ |` | "Having been permitted by you, I wish to bring you a desired guru-dakshina [teacher's gift]. |095|" |
| `Line 1740: तेनैवमुक्त उपाध्यायः प्रत्युवाच |` | "Thus addressed, the teacher replied:" |
| `Line 1741: वत्सोत्तङ्क उष्यतां तावदिति | ०९६ |` | "Child Uttanka, stay for now. |096|" |
| `Line 1742: स कदाचित्तमुपाध्यायमाहोत्तङ्कः |` | "Once Uttanka said to his teacher:" |
| `Line 1743: आज्ञापयतु भवान् |` | "May you command me." |
| `Line 1744: किं ते प्रियमुपहरामि गुर्वर्थमिति | ०९७ |` | "What pleasing thing shall I bring you as guru-dakshina [teacher's fee]? |097|" |
| `Line 1745: तमुपाध्यायः प्रत्युवाच |` | "The teacher replied to him:" |
| `Line 1746: वत्सोत्तङ्क बहुशो मां चोदयसि गुर्वर्थमुपहरेयमिति |` | "Child Uttanka, you repeatedly urge me saying 'I should bring something as guru-dakshina.'" |
| `Line 1747: तद्गच्छ |` | "Therefore, go." |
| `Line 1748: एनां प्रविश्योपाध्यायिनीं पृच्छ किमुपहरामीति |` | "Go to my wife [teacher's wife] and ask her, 'What should I bring?'" |
| `Line 1749: एषा यद्ब्रवीति तदुपहरस्वेति | ०९८ |` | "Whatever she says, bring that. |098|" |
| `Line 1750: स एवमुक्त उपाध्यायेनोपाध्यायिनीमपृच्छत् |` | "Thus instructed by his teacher, he asked the teacher's wife:" |
| `Line 1751: भवत्युपाध्यायेनास्म्यनुज्ञातो गृहं गन्तुम् |` | "I have been permitted by your honorable teacher to go home." |
| `Line 1752: तदिच्छामीष्टं ते गुर्वर्थमुपहृत्यानृणो गन्तुम् |` | "Therefore, I wish to bring a suitable gift for the teacher and depart free from debt." |
| `Line 1753: तदाज्ञापयतु भवती |` | "So please instruct me, respected lady [teacher's wife]." |
| `Line 1754: किमुपहरामि गुर्वर्थमिति | ०९९ |` | "What should I bring as a gift for the teacher? |099|" |
| `Line 1755: सैवमुक्तोपाध्यायिन्युत्तङ्कं प्रत्युवाच |` | "Thus addressed, the teacher's wife replied to Uttanka:" |
| `Line 1756: गच्छ पौष्यं राजानम् |` | "Go to King Paushya." |
| `Line 1757: भिक्षस्व तस्य क्षत्रियया पिनद्धे कुण्डले |` | "Request the earrings worn by his queen [Kshatriya woman]." |
| `Line 1758: ते आनयस्व |` | "Bring those here." |
| `Line 1759: इतश्चतुर्थेऽहनि पुण्यकं भविता |` | "Four days from now there will be an auspicious ceremony [punyaka]." |
| `Line 1760: ताभ्यामाबद्धाभ्यां ब्राह्मणान्परिवेष्टुमिच्छामि |` | "I wish to serve the Brahmins while wearing those earrings." |
| `Line 1761: शोभमाना यथा ताभ्यां कुण्डलाभ्यां तस्मिन्नहनि सम्पादयस्व |` | "Ensure that I am adorned with those earrings on that day." |
| `Line 1762: श्रेयो हि ते स्यात्क्षणं कुर्वत इति | १०० |` | "It will be auspicious for you if you accomplish this task. |100|" |
| `Line 1763: स एवमुक्त उपाध्यायिन्या प्रातिष्ठतोत्तङ्कः |` | "Thus instructed by the teacher's wife, Uttanka set forth." |
| `Line 1764: स पथि गच्छन्नपश्यदृषभमतिप्रमाणं तमधिरूढं च पुरुषमतिप्रमाणमेव | १०१ |` | "While going along the path, he saw an enormous bull and a man of enormous size mounted on it. |101|" |
| `Line 1765: स पुरुष उत्तङ्कमभ्यभाषत |` | "That man addressed Uttanka:" |
| `Line 1766: उत्तङ्कैतत्पुरीषमस्य ऋषभस्य भक्षयस्वेति | १०२ |` | "Uttanka, eat this dung of this bull. |102|" |
| `Line 1767: स एवमुक्तो नैच्छत् | १०३ |` | "Thus addressed, he refused. |103|" |
| `Line 1768: तमाह पुरुषो भूयः |` | "The man spoke to him again:" |
| `Line 1769: भक्षयस्वोत्तङ्क |` | "Eat it, Uttanka." |
| `Line 1770: मा विचारय |` | "Do not hesitate." |
| `Line 1771: उपाध्यायेनापि ते भक्षितं पूर्वमिति | १०४ |` | "Your teacher also ate it before. |104|" |
| `Line 1772: स एवमुक्तो बाढमित्युक्त्वा तदा तदृषभस्य पुरीषं मूत्रं च भक्षयित्वोत्तङ्कः प्रतस्थे यत्र स क्षत्रियः पौष्यः | १०५ |` | "Thus addressed, saying 'Very well,' Uttanka then ate the dung and urine of that bull and proceeded to where King Paushya was. |105|" |
| `Line 1773: तमुपेत्यापश्यदुत्तङ्क आसीनम् |` | "Approaching, Uttanka saw him seated." |
| `Line 1774: स तमुपेत्याशीर्भिरभिनन्द्योवाच |` | "He approached him, greeted him with blessings, and said:" |
| `Line 1775: अर्थी भवन्तमुपगतोऽस्मीति | १०६ |` | "I have come to you as a petitioner. |106|" |
| `Line 1776: स एनमभिवाद्योवाच |` | "He greeted him respectfully and said:" |
| `Line 1777: भगवन्पौष्यः खल्वहम् |` | "Venerable sir, I am Paushya [a king]." |
| `Line 1778: किं करवाणीति | १०७ |` | "What can I do for you? |107|" |
| `Line 1779: तमुवाचोत्तङ्कः |` | "Uttanka said to him:" |
| `Line 1780: गुर्वर्थे कुण्डलाभ्यामर्थ्यागतोऽस्मीति ये ते क्षत्रियया पिनद्धे कुण्डले ते भवान्दातुमर्हतीति | १०८ |` | "I have come to request the earrings for my teacher's sake. Those earrings worn by your queen [kshatriya wife], you should give them to me. |108|" |
| `Line 1781: तं पौष्यः प्रत्युवाच |` | "Paushya replied to him:" |
| `Line 1782: प्रविश्यान्तःपुरं क्षत्रिया याच्यतामिति | १०९ |` | "Enter the inner chambers and ask the queen yourself. |109|" |
| `Line 1783: स तेनैवमुक्तः प्रविश्यान्तःपुरं क्षत्रियां नापश्यत् | ११० |` | "Having been thus instructed by him, he entered the inner chambers but did not see the queen. |110|" |
| `Line 1784: स पौष्यं पुनरुवाच |` | "He said again to Paushya:" |
| `Line 1785: न युक्तं भवता वयमनृतेनोपचरितुम् |` | "It is not proper for you to deceive us with falsehood." |
| `Line 1786: न हि ते क्षत्रियान्तःपुरे संनिहिता |` | "Your queen is not present in the inner chambers." |
| `Line 1787: नैनां पश्यामीति | १११ |` | "I do not see her. |111|" |
| `Line 1788: स एवमुक्तः पौष्यस्तं प्रत्युवाच |` | "Thus addressed, Paushya replied to him:" |
| `Line 1789: सम्प्रति भवानुच्छिष्टः |` | "At present you are impure [with food remnants]." |
| `Line 1790: स्मर तावत् |` | "Think about it for a moment." |
| `Line 1791: न हि सा क्षत्रिया उच्छिष्टेनाशुचिना वा शक्या द्रष्टुम् |` | "Indeed, the queen cannot be seen by someone who is impure or has food remnants." |
| `Line 1792: पतिव्रतात्वादेषा नाशुचेर्दर्शनमुपैतीति | ११२ |` | "Because of her devotion to her husband, she does not appear before one who is impure. |112|" |
| `Line 1793: अथैवमुक्त उत्तङ्कः स्मृत्वोवाच |` | "Then, thus addressed, Uttanka remembered and said:" |
| `Line 1794: अस्ति खलु मयोच्छिष्टेनोपस्पृष्टं शीघ्रं गच्छता चेति | ११३ |` | "Indeed, I did touch food remnants while hurrying here. |113|" |
| `Line 1795: तं पौष्यः प्रत्युवाच |` | "Paushya said to him:" |
| `Line 1796: एतत्तदेवं हि |` | "That is indeed so." |
| `Line 1797: न गच्छतोपस्पृष्टं भवति न स्थितेनेति | ११४ |` | "One should not touch food remnants while walking or standing. |114|" |
| `Line 1798: अथोत्तङ्कस्तथेत्युक्त्वा प्राङ्मुख उपविश्य सुप्रक्षालितपाणिपादवदनोऽशब्दाभिर् हृदयङ्गमाभिरद्भिरुपस्पृश्य त्रिः पीत्वा द्विः परिमृज्य खान्यद्भिरुपस्पृश्यान्तःपुरं प्रविश्य तां क्षत्रियामपश्यत् | ११५ |` | "Then Uttanka, saying 'So be it,' sat facing east, thoroughly washed his hands, feet, and face, sipped water silently that was pleasing to the heart, drank thrice, wiped twice, touched the bodily apertures with water, and entering the inner chambers, he saw the queen. |115|" |
| `Line 1799: सा च दृष्ट्वैवोत्तङ्कमभ्युत्थायाभिवाद्योवाच |` | "And she, upon seeing Uttanka, rose up, greeted him respectfully and said:" |
| `Line 1800: स्वागतं ते भगवन् |` | "Welcome to you, venerable sir." |
| `Line 1801: आज्ञापय किं करवाणीति | ११६ |` | "Command me, what shall I do? |116|" |
| `Line 1802: स तामुवाच |` | "He said to her:" |
| `Line 1803: एते कुण्डले गुर्वर्थं मे भिक्षिते दातुमर्हसीति | ११७ |` | "You should give me these earrings which I am begging for my teacher's sake. |117|" |
| `Line 1804: सा प्रीता तेन तस्य सद्भावेन पात्रमयमनतिक्रमणीयश्चेति मत्वा ते कुण्डले अवमुच्यास्मै प्रायच्छत् | ११८ |` | "She, pleased with his sincerity and thinking 'he is a worthy recipient who should not be refused,' removed those earrings and gave them to him. |118|" |
| `Line 1805: आह चैनम् |` | "And she said to him:" |
| `Line 1806: एते कुण्डले तक्षको नागराजः प्रार्थयति |` | "Takshaka, the serpent king [naga ruler], desires these earrings." |
| `Line 1807: अप्रमत्तो नेतुमर्हसीति | ११९ |` | "You should carry them vigilantly. |119|" |
| `Line 1808: स एवमुक्तस्तां क्षत्रियां प्रत्युवाच |` | "Having been thus addressed, he replied to that Kshatriya woman [warrior class]:" |
| `Line 1809: भवति सुनिर्वृता भव |` | "Lady, be at ease." |
| `Line 1810: न मां शक्तस्तक्षको नागराजो धर्षयितुमिति | १२० |` | "Takshaka, the serpent king, is not capable of assailing me. |120|" |
| `Line 1811: स एवमुक्त्वा तां क्षत्रियामामन्त्र्य पौष्यसकाशमागच्छत् | १२१ |` | "Having spoken thus and taking leave of that Kshatriya woman, he went to Paushya. |121|" |
| `Line 1812: स तं दृष्ट्वोवाच |` | "Seeing him, he said:" |
| `Line 1813: भोः पौष्य प्रीतोऽस्मीति | १२२ |` | "O Paushya, I am pleased. |122|" |
| `Line 1814: तं पौष्यः प्रत्युवाच |` | "Paushya replied to him:" |
| `Line 1815: भगवंश्चिरस्य पात्रमासाद्यते |` | "Venerable sir, after a long time a worthy recipient has arrived." |
| `Line 1816: भवांश्च गुणवानतिथिः |` | "And you are a virtuous guest." |
| `Line 1817: तत्करिष्ये श्राद्धम् |` | "Therefore, I will perform a Shraddha [ancestral rite]." |
| `Line 1818: क्षणः क्रियतामिति | १२३ |` | "Please wait a moment. |123|" |
| `Line 1819: तमुत्तङ्कः प्रत्युवाच |` | "Uttanka replied to him:" |
| `Line 1820: कृतक्षण एवास्मि |` | "I have already waited enough." |
| `Line 1821: शीघ्रमिच्छामि यथोपपन्नमन्नमुपहृतं भवतेति | १२४ |` | "I wish that whatever food is readily available be quickly brought to me. |124|" |
| `Line 1822: स तथेत्युक्त्वा यथोपपन्नेनान्नेनैनं भोजयामास | १२५ |` | "Having said 'so be it,' he fed him with whatever food was available. |125|" |
| `Line 1823: अथोत्तङ्कः शीतमन्नं सकेशं दृष्ट्वा अशुच्येतदिति मत्वा पौष्यमुवाच |` | "Then Uttanka, seeing the food was cold and had hair in it, thinking 'this is impure,' said to Paushya:" |
| `Line 1824: यस्मान्मे अशुच्यन्नं ददासि तस्मदन्धो भविष्यसीति | १२६ |` | "Since you give me impure food, you shall become blind. |126|" |
| `Line 1825: तं पौष्यः प्रत्युवाच |` | "Paushya replied to him:" |
| `Line 1826: यस्मात्त्वमप्यदुष्टमन्नं दूषयसि तस्मादनपत्यो भविष्यसीति | १२७ |` | "Since you too defame food that is not defiled, therefore you shall be childless. |127|" |
| `Line 1827: सोऽथ पौष्यस्तस्याशुचिभावमन्नस्यागमयामास | १२८ |` | "Then Paushya [the teacher] verified the impurity of that food. |128|" |
| `Line 1828: अथ तदन्नं मुक्तकेश्या स्त्रियोपहृतं सकेशमशुचि मत्वोत्तङ्कं प्रसादयामास |` | "Then, realizing that the food brought by a woman with loose hair contained hair and was impure, he appeased Uttanka." |
| `Line 1829: भगवन्नज्ञानादेतदन्नं सकेशमुपहृतं शीतं च |` | "Venerable sir, through ignorance this food was brought with hair in it and cold." |
| `Line 1830: तत्क्षामये भवन्तम् |` | "For that I beg your pardon." |
| `Line 1831: न भवेयमन्ध इति | १२९ |` | "May I not become blind. |129|" |
| `Line 1832: तमुत्तङ्कः प्रत्युवाच |` | "Uttanka replied to him:" |
| `Line 1833: न मृषा ब्रवीमि |` | "I do not speak falsely." |
| `Line 1834: भूत्वा त्वमन्धो नचिरादनन्धो भविष्यसीति |` | "You will become blind, but before long you will regain your sight." |
| `Line 1835: ममापि शापो न भवेद्भवता दत्त इति | १३० |` | "And may the curse given by you to me not take effect. |130|" |
| `Line 1836: तं पौष्यः प्रत्युवाच |` | "Paushya replied to him:" |
| `Line 1837: नाहं शक्तः शापं प्रत्यादातुम् |` | "I am not able to take back the curse." |
| `Line 1838: न हि मे मन्युरद्याप्युपशमं गच्छति |` | "For my anger has not yet subsided." |
| `Line 1839: किं चैतद्भवता न ज्ञायते यथा | १३१ |` | "And do you not know this, that: |131|" |
| `Line 1840: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1841: नावनीतं हृदयं ब्राह्मणस्य; वाचि क्षुरो निहितस्तीक्ष्णधारः |` | "The heart of a Brahmin is like butter, but a sharp-edged razor is placed in his speech." |
| `Line 1842: विपरीतमेतदुभयं क्षत्रियस्य; वाङ्नावनीती हृदयं तीक्ष्णधारम् ||१३२||` | "For a Kshatriya [warrior class], both these are reversed: his speech is like butter, but his heart has a sharp edge. ||132||" |
| `Line 1843: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1844: इति |` | "Thus." |
| `Line 1845: तदेवं गते न शक्तोऽहं तीक्ष्णहृदयत्वात्तं शापमन्यथा कर्तुम् |` | "This being so, I am unable, due to my sharp-heartedness, to alter that curse." |
| `Line 1846: गम्यतामिति | १३३ |` | "You may go. |133|" |
| `Line 1847: तमुत्तङ्कः प्रत्युवाच |` | "Uttanka replied to him:" |
| `Line 1848: भवताहमन्नस्याशुचिभावमागमय्य प्रत्यनुनीतः |` | "After verifying the impurity of the food, you have apologized to me." |
| `Line 1849: प्राक्च तेऽभिहितम् |` | "And previously you said to me:" |
| `Line 1850: यस्माददुष्टमन्नं दूषयसि तस्मादनपत्यो भविष्यसीति |` | "'Since you defame food that is not defiled, therefore you shall be childless.'" |
| `Line 1851: दुष्टे चान्ने नैष मम शापो भविष्यतीति | १३४ |` | "And if the food is spoiled, this curse of mine will not take effect. |134|" |
| `Line 1852: साधयामस्तावदित्युक्त्वा प्रातिष्ठतोत्तङ्कस्ते कुण्डले गृहीत्वा | १३५ |` | "Having said, 'I will accomplish this,' Uttanka departed, taking those earrings. |135|" |
| `Line 1853: सोऽपश्यत्पथि नग्नं श्रमणमागच्छन्तं मुहुर्मुहुर्दृश्यमानमदृश्यमानं च |` | "On the way, he saw a naked ascetic [śramaṇa] approaching, who was repeatedly appearing and disappearing." |
| `Line 1854: अथोत्तङ्कस्ते कुण्डले भूमौ निक्षिप्योदकार्थं प्रचक्रमे | १३६ |` | "Then Uttanka, placing those earrings on the ground, proceeded to get water. |136|" |
| `Line 1855: एतस्मिन्नन्तरे स श्रमणस्त्वरमाण उपसृत्य ते कुण्डले गृहीत्वा प्राद्रवत् |` | "Meanwhile, that ascetic, approaching hurriedly, took those earrings and ran away." |
| `Line 1856: तमुत्तङ्कोऽभिसृत्य जग्राह |` | "Uttanka, rushing after him, seized him." |
| `Line 1857: स तद्रूपं विहाय तक्षकरूपं कृत्वा सहसा धरण्यां विवृतं महाबिलं विवेश | १३७ |` | "He, abandoning that form and taking the form of Takshaka [serpent king], suddenly entered a large hole that opened in the earth. |137|" |
| `Line 1858: प्रविश्य च नागलोकं स्वभवनमगच्छत् |` | "And having entered the realm of serpents [nāga-loka], he went to his own abode." |
| `Line 1859: तमुत्तङ्कोऽन्वाविवेश तेनैव बिलेन |` | "Uttanka followed him through that very hole." |
| `Line 1860: प्रविश्य च नागानस्तुवदेभिः श्लोकैः | १३८ |` | "And having entered, he praised the serpents with these verses: |138|" |
| `Line 1861:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1862: य ऐरावतराजानः सर्पाः समितिशोभनाः |` | "Those serpent kings of Airāvata lineage [noble serpent race], who are splendid in assemblies," |
| `Line 1863: वर्षन्त इव जीमूताः सविद्युत्पवनेरिताः ||१३९||` | "Are like rain clouds driven by wind with lightning. ||139||" |
| `Line 1864:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1865: सुरूपाश्च विरूपाश्च तथा कल्माषकुण्डलाः |` | "Both beautiful and misshapen, as well as those with spotted coils," |
| `Line 1866: आदित्यवन्नाकपृष्ठे रेजुरैरावतोद्भवाः ||१४०||` | "The descendants of Airāvata shine in the vault of heaven like the sun. ||140||" |
| `Line 1867:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1868: बहूनि नागवर्त्मानि गङ्गायास्तीर उत्तरे |` | "Many are the paths of serpents on the northern bank of the Ganges [sacred river]," |
| `Line 1869: इच्छेत्कोऽर्कांशुसेनायां चर्तुमैरावतं विना ||१४१||` | "Who would wish to move in the army of the sun's rays without Airāvata? ||141||" |
| `Line 1870:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1871: शतान्यशीतिरष्टौ च सहस्राणि च विंशतिः |` | "Eighty-eight hundreds and twenty thousand," |
| `Line 1872: सर्पाणां प्रग्रहा यान्ति धृतराष्ट्रो यदेजति ||१४२||` | "Serpents move as attendants when Dhritarashtra [serpent king] stirs. ||142||" |
| `Line 1873:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1874: ये चैनमुपसर्पन्ति ये च दूरं परं गताः |` | "Those who approach him and those who have gone far away," |
| `Line 1875: अहमैरावतज्येष्ठभ्रातृभ्योऽकरवं नमः ||१४३||` | "I offer salutations to the elder brothers of Airāvata. ||143||" |
| `Line 1876: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1877: यस्य वासः कुरुक्षेत्रे खाण्डवे चाभवत्सदा |` | "Whose dwelling was always in Kurukshetra [sacred battlefield] and in Khandava [forest region]," |
| `Line 1878: तं काद्रवेयमस्तौषं कुण्डलार्थाय तक्षकम् ||१४४||` | "I praised that Kadraveya [son of Kadru] Takshaka for the sake of the earrings. ||144||" |
| `Line 1879: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1880: तक्षकश्चाश्वसेनश्च नित्यं सहचरावुभौ |` | "Both Takshaka and Ashvasena [snake king's son], always companions together," |
| `Line 1881: कुरुक्षेत्रे निवसतां नदीमिक्षुमतीमनु ||१४५||` | "Dwelling in Kurukshetra along the river Ikshumati [sugarcane river]. ||145||" |
| `Line 1882: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1883: जघन्यजस्तक्षकस्य श्रुतसेनेति यः श्रुतः |` | "The younger-born of Takshaka, who is known as Shrutasena [famed army]," |
| `Line 1884: अवसद्यो महद्द्युम्नि प्रार्थयन्नागमुख्यताम् ||१४६||` | "Who dwelled in Mahaddyumni [great splendor], aspiring for leadership among the nagas [serpents]. ||146||" |
| `Line 1885: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1886: करवाणि सदा चाहं नमस्तस्मै महात्मने ||१४६||` | "I always offer salutations to that great soul. ||146||" |
| `Line 1887: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1888: एवं स्तुवन्नपि नागान्यदा ते कुण्डले नालभदथापश्यत्स्त्रियौ तन्त्रे अधिरोप्य पटं वयन्त्यौ | १४७ |` | "Even while praising the nagas thus, when he did not obtain those earrings, he then saw two women weaving cloth on a loom. |147|" |
| `Line 1889: तस्मिंश्च तन्त्रे कृष्णाः सिताश्च तन्तवः |` | "And on that loom were black and white threads," |
| `Line 1890: चक्रं चापश्यत्षड्भिः कुमारैः परिवर्त्यमानम् |` | "And he saw a wheel being rotated by six youths," |
| `Line 1891: पुरुषं चापश्यद्दर्शनीयम् | १४८ |` | "And he saw a handsome man. |148|" |
| `Line 1892: स तान्सर्वांस्तुष्टाव एभिर्मन्त्रवादश्लोकैः | १४९ |` | "He praised them all with these mantra-verses: |149|" |
| `Line 1893: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1894: त्रीण्यर्पितान्यत्र शतानि मध्ये; षष्टिश्च नित्यं चरति ध्रुवेऽस्मिन् |` | "Three hundred are fixed here in the middle; and sixty constantly move in this fixed (wheel)," |
| `Line 1895: चक्रे चतुर्विंशतिपर्वयोगे; षड्यत्कुमाराः परिवर्तयन्ति ||१५०||` | "In this wheel with twenty-four divisions, which six youths rotate. ||150||" |
| `Line 1896: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1897: तन्त्रं चेदं विश्वरूपं युवत्यौ; वयतस्तन्तून्सततं वर्तयन्त्यौ |` | "And these two young women weave this universal-formed loom, constantly turning the threads," |
| `Line 1898: कृष्णान्सितांश्चैव विवर्तयन्त्यौ; भूतान्यजस्रं भुवनानि चैव ||१५१||` | "Weaving the black and white threads, (representing) beings and worlds continuously. ||151||" |
| `Line 1899: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1900: वज्रस्य भर्ता भुवनस्य गोप्ता; वृत्रस्य हन्ता नमुचेर्निहन्ता |` | "The wielder of the thunderbolt [Indra], the protector of the world, the slayer of Vritra [demon], the destroyer of Namuchi [demon]," |
| `Line 1901: कृष्णे वसानो वसने महात्मा; सत्यानृते यो विविनक्ति लोके ||१५२||` | "The great soul who wears dark garments, who distinguishes between truth and falsehood in the world. ||152||" |
| `Line 1902: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1903: यो वाजिनं गर्भमपां पुराणं; वैश्वानरं वाहनमभ्युपेतः |` | "Who has approached the ancient horse-embryo of the waters, Vaishvanara [universal fire] as his vehicle." |
| `Line 1904: नमः सदास्मै जगदीश्वराय; लोकत्रयेशाय पुरंदराय ||१५३||` | "Salutations always to him, the lord of the universe, the ruler of the three worlds, the destroyer of cities [Indra]. ||153||" |
| `Line 1905: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1906: ततः स एनं पुरुषः प्राह |` | "Then that person said to him:" |
| `Line 1907: प्रीतोऽस्मि तेऽहमनेन स्तोत्रेण |` | "I am pleased with you by this hymn of praise." |
| `Line 1908: किं ते प्रियं करवाणीति | १५४ |` | "What favor shall I do for you? |154|" |
| `Line 1909: स तमुवाच |` | "He said to him:" |
| `Line 1910: नागा मे वशमीयुरिति | १५५ |` | "Let the Nagas [serpent beings] come under my control. |155|" |
| `Line 1911: स एनं पुरुषः पुनरुवाच |` | "That person said to him again:" |
| `Line 1912: एतमश्वमपाने धमस्वेति | १५६ |` | "Blow on this horse in its rear end. |156|" |
| `Line 1913: स तमश्वमपानेऽधमत् |` | "He blew on that horse in its rear end." |
| `Line 1914: अथाश्वाद्धम्यमानात्सर्वस्रोतोभ्यः सधूमा अर्चिषोऽग्नेर्निष्पेतुः | १५७ |` | "Then from the horse being blown upon, smoky flames of fire shot forth from all its openings. |157|" |
| `Line 1915: ताभिर्नागलोको धूपितः | १५८ |` | "By those flames, the world of the Nagas was fumigated. |158|" |
| `Line 1916: अथ ससम्भ्रमस्तक्षकोऽग्नितेजोभयविषण्णस्ते कुण्डले गृहीत्वा सहसा स्वभवनान्निष्क्रम्योत्तङ्कमुवाच |` | "Then Takshaka [serpent king], agitated and distressed by the fear of the fire's power, suddenly took those earrings and coming out of his abode, said to Uttanka:" |
| `Line 1917: एते कुण्डले प्रतिगृह्णातु भवानिति | १५९ |` | "Let your honor accept these earrings. |159|" |
| `Line 1918: स ते प्रतिजग्राहोत्तङ्कः |` | "Uttanka accepted those earrings." |
| `Line 1919: कुण्डले प्रतिगृह्याचिन्तयत् |` | "Having received the earrings, he thought:" |
| `Line 1920: अद्य तत्पुण्यकमुपाध्यायिन्याः |` | "Today is that auspicious day of my teacher's wife." |
| `Line 1921: दूरं चाहमभ्यागतः |` | "And I have come from afar." |
| `Line 1922: कथं नु खलु सम्भावयेयमिति | १६० |` | "How indeed shall I reach there in time? |160|" |
| `Line 1923: तत एनं चिन्तयानमेव स पुरुष उवाच |` | "Then as he was thinking thus, that person said to him:" |
| `Line 1924: उत्तङ्क एनमश्वमधिरोह |` | "Uttanka, mount this horse." |
| `Line 1925: एष त्वां क्षणादेवोपाध्यायकुलं प्रापयिष्यतीति | १६१ |` | "This will take you to your teacher's house in an instant. |161|" |
| `Line 1926: स तथेत्युक्त्वा तमश्वमधिरुह्य प्रत्याजगामोपाध्यायकुलम् |` | "He, saying 'So be it,' mounted that horse and returned to his teacher's house." |
| `Line 1927: उपाध्यायिनी च स्नाता केशानावपयन्त्युपविष्टोत्तङ्को नागच्छतीति शापायास्य मनो दधे | १६२ |` | "And the teacher's wife, having bathed and sitting down to dry her hair, set her mind to curse him, thinking 'Uttanka is not coming.' |162|" |
| `Line 1928: अथोत्तङ्कः प्रविश्य उपाध्यायिनीमभ्यवादयत् |` | "Then Uttanka entered and greeted the teacher's wife." |
| `Line 1929: ते चास्यै कुण्डले प्रायच्छत् | १६३ |` | "And he presented the earrings to her. |163|" |
| `Line 1930: सा चैनं प्रत्युवाच |` | "And she replied to him:" |
| `Line 1931: उत्तङ्क देशे कालेऽभ्यागतः |` | "Uttanka, you have arrived at the right place and time." |
| `Line 1932: स्वागतं ते वत्स |` | "Welcome to you, my child." |
| `Line 1933: मनागसि मया न शप्तः |` | "You were almost cursed by me." |
| `Line 1934: श्रेयस्तवोपस्थितम् |` | "Good fortune has come to you." |
| `Line 1935: सिद्धिमाप्नुहीति | १६४ |` | "May you attain success. |164|" |
| `Line 1936: अथोत्तङ्क उपाध्यायमभ्यवादयत् |` | "Then Uttanka greeted his teacher." |
| `Line 1937: तमुपाध्यायः प्रत्युवाच |` | "The teacher replied to him:" |
| `Line 1938: वत्सोत्तङ्क स्वागतं ते |` | "Child Uttanka, welcome to you." |
| `Line 1939: किं चिरं कृतमिति | १६५ |` | "Why have you taken so long? |165|" |
| `Line 1940: तमुत्तङ्क उपाध्यायं प्रत्युवाच |` | "Uttanka replied to his teacher:" |
| `Line 1941: भोस्तक्षकेण नागराजेन विघ्नः कृतोऽस्मिन्कर्मणि |` | "Sir, Takshaka [serpent king] created an obstacle in this task." |
| `Line 1942: तेनास्मि नागलोकं नीतः | १६६ |` | "By him I was taken to the serpent world [Naga-loka]. |166|" |
| `Line 1943: तत्र च मया दृष्टे स्त्रियौ तन्त्रेऽधिरोप्य पटं वयन्त्यौ |` | "And there I saw two women weaving a cloth on a loom." |
| `Line 1944: तस्मिंश्च तन्त्रे कृष्णाः सिताश्च तन्तवः |` | "And in that loom were black and white threads." |
| `Line 1945: किं तत् | १६७ |` | "What was that? |167|" |
| `Line 1946: तत्र च मया चक्रं दृष्टं द्वादशारम् |` | "And there I saw a wheel with twelve spokes." |
| `Line 1947: षट्चैनं कुमाराः परिवर्तयन्ति |` | "And six youths were turning it." |
| `Line 1948: तदपि किम् | १६८ |` | "What was that also? |168|" |
| `Line 1949: पुरुषश्चापि मया दृष्टः |` | "And I also saw a man." |
| `Line 1950: स पुनः कः | १६९ |` | "Who was he? |169|" |
| `Line 1951: अश्वश्चातिप्रमाणयुक्तः |` | "And the horse was of extraordinary size." |
| `Line 1952: स चापि कः | १७० |` | "And who was he? |170|" |
| `Line 1953: पथि गच्छता मया ऋषभो दृष्टः |` | "While traveling on the road, I saw a bull." |
| `Line 1954: तं च पुरुषोऽधिरूढः |` | "And a man was mounted upon it." |
| `Line 1955: तेनास्मि सोपचारमुक्तः |` | "By him I was addressed with courtesy." |
| `Line 1956: उत्तङ्कास्य ऋषभस्य पुरीषं भक्षय |` | "'Uttanka, eat the dung of this bull.'" |
| `Line 1957: उपाध्यायेनापि ते भक्षितमिति |` | "'Your teacher has also eaten it.'" |
| `Line 1958: ततस्तद्वचनान्मया तदृषभस्य पुरीषमुपयुक्तम् |` | "Then, following his words, I consumed the dung of that bull." |
| `Line 1959: तदिच्छामि भवतोपदिष्टं किं तदिति | १७१ |` | "I wish to know what was that which you have explained. |171|" |
| `Line 1960: तेनैवमुक्त उपाध्यायः प्रत्युवाच |` | "Thus addressed, the teacher replied:" |
| `Line 1961: ये ते स्त्रियौ धाता विधाता च |` | "Those two women were Dhata and Vidhata [creator deities]." |
| `Line 1962: ये च ते कृष्णाः सिताश्च तन्तवस्ते रात्र्यहनी | १७२ |` | "And those black and white threads were night and day. |172|" |
| `Line 1963: यदपि तच्चक्रं द्वादशारं षट्कुमाराः परिवर्तयन्ति ते ऋतवः षट्संवत्सरश्चक्रम् |` | "That wheel with twelve spokes which six youths rotate is the year-cycle with six seasons." |
| `Line 1964: यः पुरुषः स पर्जन्यः |` | "The man was Parjanya [rain deity]." |
| `Line 1965: योऽश्वः सोऽग्निः | १७३ |` | "The horse was Agni [fire deity]. |173|" |
| `Line 1966: य ऋषभस्त्वया पथि गच्छता दृष्टः स ऐरावतो नागराजः |` | "The bull you saw while traveling on the road was Airavata, the king of elephants." |
| `Line 1967: यश्चैनमधिरूढः स इन्द्रः |` | "And he who was mounted on it was Indra [king of gods]." |
| `Line 1968: यदपि ते पुरीषं भक्षितं तस्य ऋषभस्य तदमृतम् | १७४ |` | "And the dung of that bull which you ate was amrita [nectar of immortality]. |174|" |
| `Line 1969: तेन खल्वसि न व्यापन्नस्तस्मिन्नागभवने |` | "It was because of that you were not destroyed in the abode of the nagas [serpents]." |
| `Line 1970: स चापि मम सखा इन्द्रः | १७५ |` | "And that Indra is my friend. |175|" |
| `Line 1971: तदनुग्रहात्कुण्डले गृहीत्वा पुनरभ्यागतोऽसि |` | "By his grace, having retrieved the earrings, you have returned again." |
| `Line 1972: तत्सौम्य गम्यताम् |` | "Therefore, gentle one, you may go." |
| `Line 1973: अनुजाने भवन्तम् |` | "I give you permission." |
| `Line 1974: श्रेयोऽवाप्स्यसीति | १७६ |` | "You will attain prosperity. |176|" |
| `Line 1975: स उपाध्यायेनानुज्ञात उत्तङ्कः क्रुद्धस्तक्षकस्य प्रतिचिकीर्षमाणो हास्तिनपुरं प्रतस्थे | १७७ |` | "Having been dismissed by his teacher, Uttanka, angry and desiring to take revenge on Takshaka [serpent king], set out for Hastinapura [capital city]. |177|" |
| `Line 1976:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1977: स हास्तिनपुरं प्राप्य नचिराद्द्विजसत्तमः |` | "That foremost of twice-born [brahmin sage], having reached Hastinapura [Kuru capital] before long," |
| `Line 1978: समागच्छत राजानमुत्तङ्को जनमेजयम् ||१७८||` | "Uttanka approached King Janamejaya. ||178||" |
| `Line 1979:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1980: पुरा तक्षशिलातस्तं निवृत्तमपराजितम् |` | "Having returned undefeated from Takshashila [northern city]," |
| `Line 1981: सम्यग्विजयिनं दृष्ट्वा समन्तान्मन्त्रिभिर्वृतम् ||१७९||` | "Seeing him as a complete victor, surrounded on all sides by ministers. ||179||" |
| `Line 1982:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1983: तस्मै जयाशिषः पूर्वं यथान्यायं प्रयुज्य सः |` | "Having first properly offered him blessings of victory according to custom," |
| `Line 1984: उवाचैनं वचः काले शब्दसम्पन्नया गिरा ||१८०||` | "He addressed him at the appropriate time with eloquent speech. ||180||" |
| `Line 1985:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1986: अन्यस्मिन्करणीये त्वं कार्ये पार्थिवसत्तम |` | "In another matter that should be done, O best of kings [pārthiva-sattama]," |
| `Line 1987: बाल्यादिवान्यदेव त्वं कुरुषे नृपसत्तम ||१८१||` | "You seem to be doing something else, as if from childishness, O best of rulers. ||181||" |
| `Line 1988:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1989: एवमुक्तस्तु विप्रेण स राजा प्रत्युवाच ह |` | "Thus addressed by the brahmin [vipra], that king replied," |
| `Line 1990: जनमेजयः प्रसन्नात्मा सम्यक्सम्पूज्य तं मुनिम् ||१८२||` | "Janamejaya, with a pleased heart, having properly honored that sage. ||182||" |
| `Line 1991:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1992: आसां प्रजानां परिपालनेन; स्वं क्षत्रधर्मं परिपालयामि |` | "By protecting these subjects, I am fulfilling my Kshatriya duty [warrior code];" |
| `Line 1993: प्रब्रूहि वा किं क्रियतां द्विजेन्द्र; शुश्रूषुरस्म्यद्य वचस्त्वदीयम् ||१८३||` | "Tell me what should be done, O best of twice-born; today I am eager to hear your words. ||183||" |
| `Line 1994:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1995: स एवमुक्तस्तु नृपोत्तमेन; द्विजोत्तमः पुण्यकृतां वरिष्ठः |` | "Thus addressed by the best of kings, the best of twice-born, foremost among the virtuous," |
| `Line 1996: उवाच राजानमदीनसत्त्वं; स्वमेव कार्यं नृपतेश्च यत्तत् ||१८४||` | "Spoke to the king of undaunted courage about what was indeed the king's own duty. ||184||" |
| `Line 1997:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 1998: तक्षकेण नरेन्द्रेन्द्र येन ते हिंसितः पिता |` | "O lord of lords [supreme king], by Takshaka [serpent king] who killed your father," |
| `Line 1999: तस्मै प्रतिकुरुष्व त्वं पन्नगाय दुरात्मने ||१८५||` | "Take revenge on that evil-minded serpent [pannaga]. ||185||" |
| `Line 2000:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2001: कार्यकालं च मन्येऽहं विधिदृष्टस्य कर्मणः |` | "I believe the time has come for the action ordained by fate." |
| `Line 2002: तद्गच्छापचितिं राजन्पितुस्तस्य महात्मनः ||१८६||` | "Therefore, O king, go and perform the atonement for your noble-souled father. |186|" |
| `Line 2003: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2004: तेन ह्यनपराधी स दष्टो दुष्टान्तरात्मना |` | "For he, though innocent, was bitten by that evil-minded one." |
| `Line 2005: पञ्चत्वमगमद्राजा वज्राहत इव द्रुमः ||१८७||` | "The king met his death [five elements], like a tree struck by lightning. |187|" |
| `Line 2006: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2007: बलदर्पसमुत्सिक्तस्तक्षकः पन्नगाधमः |` | "Takshaka, the vilest of serpents, intoxicated with pride of strength," |
| `Line 2008: अकार्यं कृतवान्पापो योऽदशत्पितरं तव ||१८८||` | "That sinful one committed a wrongful deed when he bit your father. |188|" |
| `Line 2009: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2010: राजर्षिवंशगोप्तारममरप्रतिमं नृपम् |` | "The protector of the royal-sage lineage, the king who was like an immortal," |
| `Line 2011: जघान काश्यपं चैव न्यवर्तयत पापकृत् ||१८९||` | "That evil-doer killed him and also turned back Kashyapa [sage]. |189|" |
| `Line 2012: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2013: दग्धुमर्हसि तं पापं ज्वलिते हव्यवाहने |` | "You should burn that sinner in the blazing fire [oblation-carrier]," |
| `Line 2014: सर्पसत्रे महाराज त्वयि तद्धि विधीयते ||१९०||` | "In a serpent sacrifice [sarpa-satra], O great king, for this is ordained for you. |190|" |
| `Line 2015: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2016: एवं पितुश्चापचितिं गतवांस्त्वं भविष्यसि |` | "Thus you will have performed the atonement for your father," |
| `Line 2017: मम प्रियं च सुमहत्कृतं राजन्भविष्यति ||१९१||` | "And a great favor will have been done to me, O king. |191|" |
| `Line 2018: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2019: कर्मणः पृथिवीपाल मम येन दुरात्मना |` | "O protector of the earth, by that evil soul," |
| `Line 2020: विघ्नः कृतो महाराज गुर्वर्थं चरतोऽनघ ||१९२||` | "An obstacle was created for me, O great king, while I was performing a task for my teacher, O sinless one. |192|" |
| `Line 2021: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2022: एतच्छ्रुत्वा तु नृपतिस्तक्षकस्य चुकोप ह |` | "Hearing this, the king became angry at Takshaka." |
| `Line 2023: उत्तङ्कवाक्यहविषा दीप्तोऽग्निर्हविषा यथा ||१९३||` | "Inflamed by Uttanka's words as fire is kindled by oblations. |193|" |
| `Line 2024: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2025: अपृच्छच्च तदा राजा मन्त्रिणः स्वान्सुदुःखितः |` | "Then the deeply grieved king questioned his ministers," |
| `Line 2026: उत्तङ्कस्यैव सांनिध्ये पितुः स्वर्गगतिं प्रति ||१९४||` | "In Uttanka's very presence, regarding his father's journey to heaven. ||194||" |
| `Line 2027: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2028: तदैव हि स राजेन्द्रो दुःखशोकाप्लुतोऽभवत् |` | "Indeed, at that very moment, that king [raja-indra] became overwhelmed with grief and sorrow." |
| `Line 2029: यदैव पितरं वृत्तमुत्तङ्कादशृणोत्तदा ||१९५||` | "When he heard from Uttanka about what had happened to his father. ||195||" |
| `Line 2030: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2031: पौलोमपर्व` | "Pauloma Parva [Section about Puloma]" |
| `Line 2032: ४` | "4" |
| `Line 2033: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2034: लोमहर्षणपुत्र उग्रश्रवाः सूतः पौराणिको नैमिषारण्ये शौनकस्य कुलपतेर्द्वादशवार्षिके सत्रे ऋषीनभ्यागतानुपतस्थे | ००१ |` | "Ugrashravas, the son of Lomaharshana, a suta [bard/storyteller] and expert in Puranas, approached the sages who had arrived at the twelve-year sacrificial session of Shaunaka, the kulapati [head of school], in the Naimisha forest. |001|" |
| `Line 2035: पौराणिकः पुराणे कृतश्रमः स तान्कृताञ्जलिरुवाच |` | "That Pauranika [Purana expert], well-versed in the Puranas, with folded hands addressed them:" |
| `Line 2036: किं भवन्तः श्रोतुमिच्छन्ति |` | "What do you honorable ones wish to hear?" |
| `Line 2037: किमहं ब्रुवाणीति | ००२ |` | "What shall I narrate? |002|" |
| `Line 2038: तमृषय ऊचुः |` | "The sages said to him:" |
| `Line 2039: परमं लोमहर्षणे प्रक्ष्यामस्त्वां वक्ष्यसि च नः शुश्रूषतां कथायोगम् |` | "O son of Lomaharshana, we shall ask you the highest (knowledge), and you shall tell us, who are eager to listen, the proper sequence of stories." |
| `Line 2040: तद्भगवांस्तु तावच्छौनकोऽग्निशरणमध्यास्ते | ००३ |` | "But for now, the venerable Shaunaka is seated at the fire sanctuary [agni-sharana]. |003|" |
| `Line 2041: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2042: योऽसौ दिव्याः कथा वेद देवतासुरसङ्कथाः |` | "He who knows divine stories, tales of gods and asuras [demons]," |
| `Line 2043: मनुष्योरगगन्धर्वकथा वेद च सर्वशः ||४||` | "And knows completely the stories of humans, nagas [serpents], and gandharvas [celestial musicians]. ||4||" |
| `Line 2044: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2045: स चाप्यस्मिन्मखे सौते विद्वान्कुलपतिर्द्विजः |` | "And in this sacrifice, O Suta, he is the learned kulapati [head of school], a twice-born [dvija]," |
| `Line 2046: दक्षो धृतव्रतो धीमाञ्शास्त्रे चारण्यके गुरुः ||५||` | "Skilled, steadfast in vows, wise, and a master in the scriptures and Aranyakas [forest texts]. ||5||" |
| `Line 2047: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2048: सत्यवादी शमपरस्तपस्वी नियतव्रतः |` | "Truthful, devoted to tranquility, ascetic, firm in his vows," |
| `Line 2049: सर्वेषामेव नो मान्यः स तावत्प्रतिपाल्यताम् ||६||` | "Respected by all of us—let us wait for him for now. ||6||" |
| `Line 2050: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2051: तस्मिन्नध्यासति गुरावासनं परमार्चितम् |` | "When the guru sits on the highly honored seat," |
| `Line 2052: ततो वक्ष्यसि यत्त्वां स प्रक्ष्यति द्विजसत्तमः ||७||` | "Then you shall speak what that best of twice-born [brahmin sage] asks you. ||7||" |
| `Line 2053: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2054: सूत उवाच||` | "Suta [bard/narrator] said:" |
| `Line 2055: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2056: एवमस्तु गुरौ तस्मिन्नुपविष्टे महात्मनि |` | "Let it be so. When that great-souled guru was seated," |
| `Line 2057: तेन पृष्टः कथाः पुण्या वक्ष्यामि विविधाश्रयाः ||८||` | "Being asked by him, I shall narrate sacred stories of various kinds. ||8||" |
| `Line 2058: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2059: सोऽथ विप्रर्षभः कार्यं कृत्वा सर्वं यथाक्रमम् |` | "Then that bull among brahmins [eminent sage], having performed all duties in proper sequence," |
| `Line 2060: देवान्वाग्भिः पितृनद्भिस्तर्पयित्वाजगाम ह ||९||` | "Having satisfied the gods with words and the ancestors with water, he arrived. ||9||" |
| `Line 2061: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2062: यत्र ब्रह्मर्षयः सिद्धास्त आसीना यतव्रताः |` | "Where the brahmarshis [brahmin sages], the siddhas [perfected beings], and those of controlled vows were seated," |
| `Line 2063: यज्ञायतनमाश्रित्य सूतपुत्रपुरःसराः ||१०||` | "Taking refuge in the sacrificial hall, with the son of Suta leading them. ||10||" |
| `Line 2064: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2065: ऋत्विक्ष्वथ सदस्येषु स वै गृहपतिस्ततः |` | "Then, when the priests and the assembly members were seated, that householder [sacrifice patron]," |
| `Line 2066: उपविष्टेषूपविष्टः शौनकोऽथाब्रवीदिदम् ||११||` | "Having seated himself among those seated, Shaunaka [sage] then spoke this. ||11||" |
| `Line 2067: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2068: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2069: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2070: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2071: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2072: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2073: ५` | "5" |
| `Line 2074: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2075: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2076: शौनक उवाच॥` | "Shaunaka said:" |
| `Line 2077: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2078: पुराणमखिलं तात पिता तेऽधीतवान्पुरा |` | "O dear one, your father had formerly studied the entire Purana [ancient text]." |
| `Line 2079: कच्चित्त्वमपि तत्सर्वमधीषे लोमहर्षणे ॥१॥` | "O Lomaharshana [son of Suta], have you also studied all of it? ||1||" |
| `Line 2080: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2081: पुराणे हि कथा दिव्या आदिवंशाश्च धीमताम् |` | "For in the Purana are divine stories and the original lineages of the wise." |
| `Line 2082: कथ्यन्ते ताः पुरास्माभिः श्रुताः पूर्वं पितुस्तव ॥२॥` | "Those were previously heard by us from your father. ||2||" |
| `Line 2083: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2084: तत्र वंशमहं पूर्वं श्रोतुमिच्छामि भार्गवम् |` | "Among those, I first wish to hear about the lineage of Bhargava [descendants of Bhrigu]." |
| `Line 2085: कथयस्व कथामेतां कल्याः स्म श्रवणे तव ॥३॥` | "Narrate this story; we are eager to listen to you. ||3||" |
| `Line 2086: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2087: सूत उवाच॥` | "Suta [bard/narrator] said:" |
| `Line 2088: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2089: यदधीतं पुरा सम्यग्द्विजश्रेष्ठ महात्मभिः |` | "O best of the twice-born [Brahmins], what was properly studied before by the great souls," |
| `Line 2090: वैशम्पायनविप्राद्यैस्तैश्चापि कथितं पुरा ॥४॥` | "By Vaishampayana and other learned Brahmins, and what was narrated by them before, ||4||" |
| `Line 2091: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2092: यदधीतं च पित्रा मे सम्यक्चैव ततो मया |` | "And what was properly studied by my father and then by me," |
| `Line 2093: तत्तावच्छृणु यो देवैः सेन्द्रैः साग्निमरुद्गणैः ॥५॥` | "Listen to that much about the one who by the gods, along with Indra [king of gods], Agni [fire deity], and the Maruts [storm deities], ||5||" |
| `Line 2094: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2095: पूजितः प्रवरो वंशो भृगूणां भृगुनन्दन ॥५॥` | "Was honored—the excellent lineage of the Bhrigus, O descendant of Bhrigu. ||5||" |
| `Line 2096: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2097: इमं वंशमहं ब्रह्मन्भार्गवं ते महामुने |` | "O Brahmin, O great sage, I shall narrate to you this lineage of the Bhargavas [Bhrigu's descendants]," |
| `Line 2098: निगदामि कथायुक्तं पुराणाश्रयसंयुतम् ॥६॥` | "Along with its stories, supported by the Puranas [ancient texts]. ||6||" |
| `Line 2099: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2100: भृगोः सुदयितः पुत्रश्च्यवनो नाम भार्गवः |` | "The beloved son of Bhrigu was named Chyavana, a descendant of Bhrigu." |
| `Line 2101: च्यवनस्यापि दायादः प्रमतिर्नाम धार्मिकः ||७||` | "Chyavana's descendant was the righteous one named Pramati. ||7||" |
| `Line 2102:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2103: प्रमतेरप्यभूत्पुत्रो घृताच्यां रुरुरित्युत ||७||` | "And Pramati's son, born of Ghritachi [celestial nymph], was named Ruru. ||7||" |
| `Line 2104:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2105: रुरोरपि सुतो जज्ञे शुनको वेदपारगः |` | "Ruru's son was born as Shunaka, master of the Vedas [scripture expert]," |
| `Line 2106: प्रमद्वरायां धर्मात्मा तव पूर्वपितामहात् ||८||` | "Born to Pramadvara, righteous one, from your great-grandfather. ||8||" |
| `Line 2107:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2108: तपस्वी च यशस्वी च श्रुतवान्ब्रह्मवित्तमः |` | "He was austere, famous, learned, and the foremost knower of Brahman [absolute reality]," |
| `Line 2109: धर्मिष्ठः सत्यवादी च नियतो नियतेन्द्रियः ||९||` | "Most righteous, truthful, disciplined, and with controlled senses. ||9||" |
| `Line 2110:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2111: शौनक उवाच||` | "Shaunaka said:" |
| `Line 2112:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2113: सूतपुत्र यथा तस्य भार्गवस्य महात्मनः |` | "O son of Suta [bard caste], how that great-souled descendant of Bhrigu [Bhargava]" |
| `Line 2114: च्यवनत्वं परिख्यातं तन्ममाचक्ष्व पृच्छतः ||१०||` | "Came to be known as Chyavana, tell this to me who asks. ||10||" |
| `Line 2115:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2116: सूत उवाच||` | "Suta said:" |
| `Line 2117:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2118: भृगोः सुदयिता भार्या पुलोमेत्यभिविश्रुता |` | "Bhrigu's beloved wife was well-known as Puloma," |
| `Line 2119: तस्यां गर्भः समभवद्भृगोर्वीर्यसमुद्भवः ||११||` | "In her a fetus was conceived, born of Bhrigu's virility. ||11||" |
| `Line 2120:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2121: तस्मिन्गर्भे सम्भृतेऽथ पुलोमायां भृगूद्वह |` | "When that fetus was developing in Puloma, O carrier of Bhrigu's lineage," |
| `Line 2122: समये समशीलिन्यां धर्मपत्न्यां यशस्विनः ||१२||` | "At that time, in his virtuous and lawful wife of the illustrious one. ||12||" |
| `Line 2123:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2124: अभिषेकाय निष्क्रान्ते भृगौ धर्मभृतां वरे |` | "When Bhrigu, the best among the upholders of dharma, went out for his ritual bath [abhisheka]," |
| `Line 2125: आश्रमं तस्य रक्षोऽथ पुलोमाभ्याजगाम ह ||१३||` | "A demon [raksha] then came to his hermitage, approaching Puloma. ||13||" |
| `Line 2126: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2127: तं प्रविश्याश्रमं दृष्ट्वा भृगोर्भार्यामनिन्दिताम् |` | "Having entered that hermitage, seeing Bhrigu's blameless wife," |
| `Line 2128: हृच्छयेन समाविष्टो विचेताः समपद्यत ||१४||` | "He became possessed by desire and lost his senses. ||14||" |
| `Line 2129: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2130: अभ्यागतं तु तद्रक्षः पुलोमा चारुदर्शना |` | "But Puloma [Bhrigu's wife], beautiful to behold, welcomed that rakshasa [demon] who had arrived," |
| `Line 2131: न्यमन्त्रयत वन्येन फलमूलादिना तदा ||१५||` | "And invited him with forest fruits, roots and other such things. ||15||" |
| `Line 2132: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2133: तां तु रक्षस्ततो ब्रह्मन्हृच्छयेनाभिपीडितम् |` | "Then that rakshasa, O Brahmin, tormented by desire," |
| `Line 2134: दृष्ट्वा हृष्टमभूत्तत्र जिहीर्षुस्तामनिन्दिताम् ||१६||` | "Became excited there, wishing to abduct that blameless woman. ||16||" |
| `Line 2135: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2136: अथाग्निशरणेऽपश्यज्ज्वलितं जातवेदसम् |` | "Then, in the fire sanctuary, he saw the blazing Jatavedas [fire deity]," |
| `Line 2137: तमपृच्छत्ततो रक्षः पावकं ज्वलितं तदा ||१७||` | "Then the rakshasa questioned the blazing Pavaka [fire god]. ||17||" |
| `Line 2138: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2139: शंस मे कस्य भार्येयमग्ने पृष्ट ऋतेन वै |` | "Tell me truthfully, O Agni [fire god], when asked, whose wife is this?" |
| `Line 2140: सत्यस्त्वमसि सत्यं मे वद पावक पृच्छते ||१८||` | "You are truthful, so speak the truth to me who asks, O Pavaka [fire god]. ||18||" |
| `Line 2141: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2142: मया हीयं पूर्ववृता भार्यार्थे वरवर्णिनी |` | "This fair-complexioned woman was previously chosen by me as a wife," |
| `Line 2143: पश्चात्त्विमां पिता प्रादाद्भृगवेऽनृतकारिणे ||१९||` | "But afterwards her father gave her to Bhrigu, acting falsely. ||19||" |
| `Line 2144: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2145: सेयं यदि वरारोहा भृगोर्भार्या रहोगता |` | "If this beautiful woman is indeed Bhrigu's wife, now alone," |
| `Line 2146: तथा सत्यं समाख्याहि जिहीर्षाम्याश्रमादिमाम् ||२०||` | "Then tell me the truth, for I wish to take her away from this hermitage. ||20||" |
| `Line 2147: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2148: मन्युर्हि हृदयं मेऽद्य प्रदहन्निव तिष्ठति |` | "For anger burns in my heart today," |
| `Line 2149: मत्पुर्वभार्यां यदिमां भृगुः प्राप सुमध्यमाम् ||२१||` | "That Bhrigu has obtained this slender-waisted woman who was first promised to me. ||21||" |
| `Line 2150: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2151: तद्रक्ष एवमामन्त्र्य ज्वलितं जातवेदसम् |` | "That rakshasa [demon], having thus addressed the blazing Jatavedas [Agni/fire god]," |
| `Line 2152: शङ्कमानो भृगोर्भार्यां पुनः पुनरपृच्छत ||२२||` | "Suspecting (the identity of) Bhrigu's wife, asked again and again. ||22||" |
| `Line 2153: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2154: त्वमग्ने सर्वभूतानामन्तश्चरसि नित्यदा |` | "You, O Agni [fire god], always move within all beings," |
| `Line 2155: साक्षिवत्पुण्यपापेषु सत्यं ब्रूहि कवे वचः ||२३||` | "As a witness to virtuous and sinful deeds, speak the truth, O sage [wise one], speak the words. ||23||" |
| `Line 2156: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2157: मत्पूर्वभार्यापहृता भृगुणानृतकारिणा |` | "My former wife was taken away by Bhrigu, the untruthful one," |
| `Line 2158: सेयं यदि तथा मे त्वं सत्यमाख्यातुमर्हसि ||२४||` | "If this is she, then you should tell me the truth. ||24||" |
| `Line 2159: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2160: श्रुत्वा त्वत्तो भृगोर्भार्यां हरिष्याम्यहमाश्रमात् |` | "Having heard from you that she is Bhrigu's wife, I will take her away from the ashram [hermitage]," |
| `Line 2161: जातवेदः पश्यतस्ते वद सत्यां गिरं मम ||२५||` | "O Jatavedas [fire god], before your very eyes, speak the truth to my words. ||25||" |
| `Line 2162: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2163: तस्य तद्वचनं श्रुत्वा सप्तार्चिर्दुःखितो भृशम् |` | "Having heard those words of his, Saptarchi [seven-flamed fire] became greatly distressed," |
| `Line 2164: भीतोऽनृताच्च शापाच्च भृगोरित्यब्रवीच्छनैः ||२६||` | "Afraid of both untruth and the curse of Bhrigu, he spoke thus slowly. ||26||" |
| `Line 2165: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2166: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2167: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2168: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2169: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2170: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2171: ६` | "6" |
| `Line 2172: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2173: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2174: सूत उवाच||` | "Suta [bard/narrator] said:" |
| `Line 2175: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2176: अग्नेरथ वचः श्रुत्वा तद्रक्षः प्रजहार ताम् |` | "Having heard the words of Agni [fire god], that rakshasa [demon] seized her," |
| `Line 2177: ब्रह्मन्वराहरूपेण मनोमारुतरंहसा ||१||` | "O Brahmin, in the form of a boar, with the speed of mind and wind. ||1||" |
| `Line 2178: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2179: ततः स गर्भो निवसन्कुक्षौ भृगुकुलोद्वह |` | "Then that embryo, residing in her womb, O upholder of Bhrigu's lineage," |
| `Line 2180: रोषान्मातुश्च्युतः कुक्षेश्च्यवनस्तेन सोऽभवत् ||२||` | "Fell from the mother's womb due to her fear, and thus he became known as Chyavana [the fallen]. ||2||" |
| `Line 2181: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2182: तं दृष्ट्वा मातुरुदराच्च्युतमादित्यवर्चसम् |` | "Seeing him fallen from the mother's womb, radiant like the sun," |
| `Line 2183: तद्रक्षो भस्मसाद्भूतं पपात परिमुच्य ताम् ||३||` | "That rakshasa was reduced to ashes and fell, releasing her. ||3||" |
| `Line 2184: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2185: सा तमादाय सुश्रोणी ससार भृगुनन्दनम् |` | "She, with beautiful hips, taking him, the son of Bhrigu," |
| `Line 2186: च्यवनं भार्गवं ब्रह्मन्पुलोमा दुःखमूर्च्छिता ||४||` | "Chyavana of Bhrigu's lineage, O Brahmin, Puloma [wife of Bhrigu] proceeded, overcome with grief. ||4||" |
| `Line 2187: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2188: तां ददर्श स्वयं ब्रह्मा सर्वलोकपितामहः |` | "Brahma himself, the grandfather of all worlds, saw her," |
| `Line 2189: रुदतीं बाष्पपूर्णाक्षीं भृगोर्भार्यामनिन्दिताम् ||५||` | "Weeping, with eyes full of tears, the blameless wife of Bhrigu. ||5||" |
| `Line 2190: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2191: सान्त्वयामास भगवान्वधूं ब्रह्मा पितामहः ||५||` | "The lord Brahma, the grandfather, consoled the bride. ||5||" |
| `Line 2192: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2193: अश्रुबिन्दूद्भवा तस्याः प्रावर्तत महानदी |` | "From her teardrops flowed a great river," |
| `Line 2194: अनुवर्तती सृतिं तस्या भृगोः पत्न्या यशस्विनः ||६||` | "Following the path of her, the wife of the illustrious Bhrigu. ||6||" |
| `Line 2195: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2196: तस्या मार्गं सृतवतीं दृष्ट्वा तु सरितं तदा |` | "Seeing that river flowing along her path then," |
| `Line 2197: नाम तस्यास्तदा नद्याश्चक्रे लोकपितामहः ||७||` | "The grandfather of the worlds then gave a name to that river. ||7||" |
| `Line 2198: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2199: वधूसरेति भगवांश्च्यवनस्याश्रमं प्रति ||७||` | "Vadhusara [bride's flow], said the lord, (as she went) toward Chyavana's hermitage. ||7||" |
| `Line 2200: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2201: स एवं च्यवनो जज्ञे भृगोः पुत्रः प्रतापवान् |` | "Thus was born Chyavana, the mighty son of Bhrigu." |
| `Line 2202: तं ददर्श पिता तत्र च्यवनं तां च भामिनीम् ॥८॥` | "There, the father saw Chyavana and that beautiful woman [Puloma]. ||8||" |
| `Line 2203: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2204: स पुलोमां ततो भार्यां पप्रच्छ कुपितो भृगुः |` | "Then the enraged Bhrigu asked his wife Puloma:" |
| `Line 2205: केनासि रक्षसे तस्मै कथितेह जिहीर्षवे ॥९॥` | "By whom were you revealed to that demon who wished to abduct you here? ||9||" |
| `Line 2206: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2207: न हि त्वां वेद तद्रक्षो मद्भार्यां चारुहासिनीम् ॥९॥` | "For that demon could not have known you, my sweet-smiling wife, on his own. ||9||" |
| `Line 2208: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2209: तत्त्वमाख्याहि तं ह्यद्य शप्तुमिच्छाम्यहं रुषा |` | "Therefore, tell me who it was, for I wish to curse him today in my anger." |
| `Line 2210: बिभेति को न शापान्मे कस्य चायं व्यतिक्रमः ॥१०॥` | "Who does not fear my curses, and whose transgression is this? ||10||" |
| `Line 2211: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2212: पुलोमोवाच॥` | "Puloma said:" |
| `Line 2213: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2214: अग्निना भगवंस्तस्मै रक्षसेऽहं निवेदिता |` | "O lord, I was revealed to that demon by Agni [fire deity]." |
| `Line 2215: ततो मामनयद्रक्षः क्रोशन्तीं कुररीमिव ॥११॥` | "Then the demon carried me away as I cried out like an osprey. ||11||" |
| `Line 2216: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2217: साहं तव सुतस्यास्य तेजसा परिमोक्षिता |` | "I was freed by the power of this son of yours," |
| `Line 2218: भस्मीभूतं च तद्रक्षो मामुत्सृज्य पपात वै ॥१२॥` | "And that demon, releasing me, fell down reduced to ashes. ||12||" |
| `Line 2219: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2220: सूत उवाच॥` | "Suta [bard/narrator] said:" |
| `Line 2221: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2222: इति श्रुत्वा पुलोमाया भृगुः परममन्युमान् |` | "Having heard this from Puloma, Bhrigu, filled with extreme anger," |
| `Line 2223: शशापाग्निमभिक्रुद्धः सर्वभक्षो भविष्यसि ॥१३॥` | "Cursed Agni in great wrath: 'You shall become the consumer of everything!' ||13||" |
| `Line 2224: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2225: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2226:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2227:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2228:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2229:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2230: ७` | "7" |
| `Line 2231:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2232:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2233: सूत उवाच||` | "Suta said:" |
| `Line 2234:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2235: शप्तस्तु भृगुणा वह्निः क्रुद्धो वाक्यमथाब्रवीत् |` | "When cursed by Bhrigu, Agni [fire deity], angered, then spoke these words:" |
| `Line 2236: किमिदं साहसं ब्रह्मन्कृतवानसि साम्प्रतम् ||१||` | "What is this rash act, O Brahmin, that you have committed now? ||1||" |
| `Line 2237:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2238: धर्मे प्रयतमानस्य सत्यं च वदतः समम् |` | "While I was striving to uphold dharma [righteousness] and speaking the truth equally," |
| `Line 2239: पृष्टो यदब्रुवं सत्यं व्यभिचारोऽत्र को मम ||२||` | "When asked, I spoke the truth - what transgression is there in this on my part? ||2||" |
| `Line 2240:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2241: पृष्टो हि साक्षी यः साक्ष्यं जानमानोऽन्यथा वदेत् |` | "Indeed, a witness who, when questioned, knowingly gives false testimony," |
| `Line 2242: स पूर्वानात्मनः सप्त कुले हन्यात्तथा परान् ||३||` | "He destroys seven generations before him in his family and seven after. ||3||" |
| `Line 2243:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2244: यश्च कार्यार्थतत्त्वज्ञो जानमानो न भाषते |` | "And he who knows the truth of a matter but does not speak it," |
| `Line 2245: सोऽपि तेनैव पापेन लिप्यते नात्र संशयः ||४||` | "He too is tainted by that same sin - there is no doubt in this. ||4||" |
| `Line 2246:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2247: शक्तोऽहमपि शप्तुं त्वां मान्यास्तु ब्राह्मणा मम |` | "I too am capable of cursing you, but Brahmins are worthy of my respect," |
| `Line 2248: जानतोऽपि च ते व्यक्तं कथयिष्ये निबोध तत् ||५||` | "And though you know it, I shall clearly explain it to you - listen to that. ||5||" |
| `Line 2249:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2250: योगेन बहुधात्मानं कृत्वा तिष्ठामि मूर्तिषु |` | "Through yoga [divine power], I manifest myself in many forms and exist in various embodiments," |
| `Line 2251: अग्निहोत्रेषु सत्रेषु क्रियास्वथ मखेषु च ||६||` | "In Agnihotra [fire sacrifices], satras [long rituals], other rites, and makhas [ceremonial sacrifices]. ||6||" |
| `Line 2252: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2253: वेदोक्तेन विधानेन मयि यद्धूयते हविः |` | "When oblations are offered into me according to Vedic injunctions," |
| `Line 2254: देवताः पितरश्चैव तेन तृप्ता भवन्ति वै ||७||` | "The deities and the ancestors indeed become satisfied by that. ||7||" |
| `Line 2255: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2256: आपो देवगणाः सर्वे आपः पितृगणास्तथा |` | "All hosts of gods are waters, and likewise the hosts of ancestors are waters," |
| `Line 2257: दर्शश्च पौर्णमासश्च देवानां पितृभिः सह ||८||` | "The new moon (Darsha) and full moon (Paurnamasa) sacrifices are for gods along with ancestors. ||8||" |
| `Line 2258: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2259: देवताः पितरस्तस्मात्पितरश्चापि देवताः |` | "Therefore, the deities are ancestors and the ancestors are also deities," |
| `Line 2260: एकीभूताश्च पूज्यन्ते पृथक्त्वेन च पर्वसु ||९||` | "They are worshipped as unified and also separately during sacred occasions. ||9||" |
| `Line 2261: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2262: देवताः पितरश्चैव जुह्वते मयि यत्सदा |` | "The deities and ancestors always offer oblations through me," |
| `Line 2263: त्रिदशानां पितृणां च मुखमेवमहं स्मृतः ||१०||` | "Thus I am considered the mouth of the thirty gods [Tridasha] and the ancestors. ||10||" |
| `Line 2264: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2265: अमावास्यां च पितरः पौर्णमास्यां च देवताः |` | "On the new moon day the ancestors, and on the full moon day the deities," |
| `Line 2266: मन्मुखेनैव हूयन्ते भुञ्जते च हुतं हविः ||११||` | "Are invoked through my mouth alone, and they consume the offered oblations. ||11||" |
| `Line 2267: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2268: सर्वभक्षः कथं तेषां भविष्यामि मुखं त्वहम् ||११||` | "How shall I, becoming an eater of everything, remain their mouth? ||11||" |
| `Line 2269: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2270: चिन्तयित्वा ततो वह्निश्चक्रे संहारमात्मनः |` | "Having thought thus, Vahni [fire god] then withdrew himself," |
| `Line 2271: द्विजानामग्निहोत्रेषु यज्ञसत्रक्रियासु च ||१२||` | "From the Agnihotra rituals of the twice-born [Brahmins] and from sacrificial ceremonies. ||12||" |
| `Line 2272: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2273: निरोङ्कारवषट्काराः स्वधास्वाहाविवर्जिताः |` | "Deprived of Om, Vashat [ritual exclamations], Svadha and Svaha [sacred utterances]," |
| `Line 2274: विनाग्निना प्रजाः सर्वास्तत आसन्सुदुःखिताः ||१३||` | "Without fire, all creatures thereafter became extremely miserable. ||13||" |
| `Line 2275: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2276: अथर्षयः समुद्विग्ना देवान्गत्वाब्रुवन्वचः |` | "Then the rishis [sages], greatly alarmed, went to the devas [gods] and spoke these words:" |
| `Line 2277: अग्निनाशात्क्रियाभ्रंशाद्भ्रान्ता लोकास्त्रयोऽनघाः ||१४||` | "Due to Agni's [fire god's] disappearance and the cessation of rituals, the three worlds are confused, O sinless ones. ||14||" |
| `Line 2278: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2279: विधध्वमत्र यत्कार्यं न स्यात्कालात्ययो यथा ||१४||` | "Please ordain what should be done in this matter so that there is no delay beyond the proper time. ||14||" |
| `Line 2280: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2281: अथर्षयश्च देवाश्च ब्रह्माणमुपगम्य तु |` | "Then the rishis [sages] and devas [gods], approaching Brahma [creator deity]," |
| `Line 2282: अग्नेरावेदयञ्शापं क्रियासंहारमेव च ||१५||` | "Informed him about Agni's [fire god's] curse and the cessation of rituals. ||15||" |
| `Line 2283: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2284: भृगुणा वै महाभाग शप्तोऽग्निः कारणान्तरे |` | "O greatly fortunate one, Agni [fire god] was cursed by Bhrigu [sage] for a particular reason," |
| `Line 2285: कथं देवमुखो भूत्वा यज्ञभागाग्रभुक्तथा ||१६||` | "How can he, being the mouth of the gods and the foremost consumer of sacrificial offerings, ||16||" |
| `Line 2286: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2287: हुतभुक्सर्वलोकेषु सर्वभक्षत्वमेष्यति ||१६||` | "The fire [oblation-eater] in all worlds, come to consume everything? ||16||" |
| `Line 2288: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2289: श्रुत्वा तु तद्वचस्तेषामग्निमाहूय लोककृत् |` | "Having heard their words, the Creator [world-maker] summoned Agni [fire god]," |
| `Line 2290: उवाच वचनं श्लक्ष्णं भूतभावनमव्ययम् ||१७||` | "And spoke gentle words that were nurturing to beings and imperishable. ||17||" |
| `Line 2291: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2292: लोकानामिह सर्वेषां त्वं कर्ता चान्त एव च |` | "You are both the creator and the end of all these worlds," |
| `Line 2293: त्वं धारयसि लोकांस्त्रीन्क्रियाणां च प्रवर्तकः ||१८||` | "You sustain the three worlds and are the initiator of all rituals. ||18||" |
| `Line 2294: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2295: स तथा कुरु लोकेश नोच्छिद्येरन्क्रिया यथा ||१८||` | "Therefore, O Lord of worlds, act in such a way that the rituals are not destroyed. ||18||" |
| `Line 2296: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2297: कस्मादेवं विमूढस्त्वमीश्वरः सन्हुताशनः |` | "Why are you so confused, being the lord, O consumer of oblations [fire god]?" |
| `Line 2298: त्वं पवित्रं यदा लोके सर्वभूतगतश्च ह ||१९||` | "When you are the purifier in the world and present in all beings, ||19||" |
| `Line 2299: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2300: न त्वं सर्वशरीरेण सर्वभक्षत्वमेष्यसि |` | "You shall not consume everything with your entire body." |
| `Line 2301: उपादानेऽर्चिषो यास्ते सर्वं धक्ष्यन्ति ताः शिखिन् ॥२०॥` | "When kindled, your flames shall consume everything, O Fire [Agni]. ||20||" |
| `Line 2302: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2303: यथा सूर्यांशुभिः स्पृष्टं सर्वं शुचि विभाव्यते |` | "Just as everything touched by the sun's rays is considered pure," |
| `Line 2304: तथा त्वदर्चिर्निर्दग्धं सर्वं शुचि भविष्यति ॥२१॥` | "So too shall everything burnt by your flames become pure. ||21||" |
| `Line 2305: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2306: तदग्ने त्वं महत्तेजः स्वप्रभावाद्विनिर्गतम् |` | "Therefore, O Agni, with your great splendor emanating from your own power," |
| `Line 2307: स्वतेजसैव तं शापं कुरु सत्यमृषेर्विभो ॥२२॥` | "Make the sage's curse come true through your own brilliance, O mighty one. ||22||" |
| `Line 2308: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2309: देवानां चात्मनो भागं गृहाण त्वं मुखे हुतम् ॥२२॥` | "And receive in your mouth the portion offered to the gods and yourself. ||22||" |
| `Line 2310: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2311: एवमस्त्विति तं वह्निः प्रत्युवाच पितामहम् |` | "So be it," replied the fire [Agni] to Pitamaha [Brahma]," |
| `Line 2312: जगाम शासनं कर्तुं देवस्य परमेष्ठिनः ॥२३॥` | "And went to carry out the command of the supreme deity [Parameshthina]. ||23||" |
| `Line 2313: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2314: देवर्षयश्च मुदितास्ततो जग्मुर्यथागतम् |` | "Then the divine sages [devarshis], delighted, departed as they had come," |
| `Line 2315: ऋषयश्च यथापूर्वं क्रियाः सर्वाः प्रचक्रिरे ॥२४॥` | "And the sages resumed performing all their rituals as before. ||24||" |
| `Line 2316: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2317: दिवि देवा मुमुदिरे भूतसङ्घाश्च लौकिकाः |` | "The gods rejoiced in heaven, as did the hosts of worldly beings," |
| `Line 2318: अग्निश्च परमां प्रीतिमवाप हतकल्मषः ॥२५॥` | "And Agni, freed from sin [kalmasha], attained supreme satisfaction. ||25||" |
| `Line 2319: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2320: एवमेष पुरावृत्त इतिहासोऽग्निशापजः |` | "Thus is this ancient tale about the curse of Agni," |
| `Line 2321: पुलोमस्य विनाशश्च च्यवनस्य च सम्भवः ॥२६॥` | "The destruction of Puloma and the birth of Chyavana. ||26||" |
| `Line 2322: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2323: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2324: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2325: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2326: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2327: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2328: ८` | "8 [chapter number]" |
| `Line 2329: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2330: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2331: सूत उवाच॥` | "Suta [bard/narrator] said:" |
| `Line 2332: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2333: स चापि च्यवनो ब्रह्मन्भार्गवोऽजनयत्सुतम् |` | "And that Chyavana, O Brahmin [priest/sage], the descendant of Bhrigu, begot a son" |
| `Line 2334: सुकन्यायां महात्मानं प्रमतिं दीप्ततेजसम् ॥१॥` | "with Sukanya, a noble soul named Pramati, of brilliant splendor. ||1||" |
| `Line 2335: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2336: प्रमतिस्तु रुरुं नाम घृताच्यां समजीजनत् |` | "And Pramati begot a son named Ruru with Ghritachi [celestial nymph]," |
| `Line 2337: रुरुः प्रमद्वरायां तु शुनकं समजीजनत् ॥२॥` | "And Ruru begot Shunaka with Pramadvara. ||2||" |
| `Line 2338: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2339: तस्य ब्रह्मन्रुरोः सर्वं चरितं भूरितेजसः |` | "O Brahmin, I shall now narrate in detail the entire story of that Ruru of great splendor," |
| `Line 2340: विस्तरेण प्रवक्ष्यामि तच्छृणु त्वमशेषतः ॥३॥` | "Listen to it completely without omission. ||3||" |
| `Line 2341: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2342: ऋषिरासीन्महान्पूर्वं तपोविद्यासमन्वितः |` | "There was once a great sage endowed with austerity and knowledge," |
| `Line 2343: स्थूलकेश इति ख्यातः सर्वभूतहिते रतः ॥४॥` | "Known as Sthulakesha [thick-haired sage], devoted to the welfare of all beings. ||4||" |
| `Line 2344: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2345: एतस्मिन्नेव काले तु मेनकायां प्रजज्ञिवान् |` | "At this very time, Menaka [celestial nymph] gave birth to a child," |
| `Line 2346: गन्धर्वराजो विप्रर्षे विश्वावसुरिति श्रुतः ॥५॥` | "Fathered by the king of Gandharvas [celestial musicians], O sage, known as Vishvavasu. ||5||" |
| `Line 2347: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2348: अथाप्सरा मेनका सा तं गर्भं भृगुनन्दन |` | "Then that Apsara [celestial nymph] Menaka, O descendant of Bhrigu," |
| `Line 2349: उत्ससर्ज यथाकालं स्थूलकेशाश्रमं प्रति ॥६॥` | "Abandoned that child in due time near the hermitage of Sthulakesha. ||6||" |
| `Line 2350: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2351: उत्सृज्य चैव तं गर्भं नद्यास्तीरे जगाम ह |` | "And having abandoned that child on the riverbank, she went away," |
| `Line 2352: कन्याममरगर्भाभां ज्वलन्तीमिव च श्रिया ||७||` | "A girl radiant like the child of immortals, shining as if with divine splendor. ||7||" |
| `Line 2353:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2354: तां ददर्श समुत्सृष्टां नदीतीरे महानृषिः |` | "The great sage saw her abandoned on the riverbank," |
| `Line 2355: स्थूलकेशः स तेजस्वी विजने बन्धुवर्जिताम् ||८||` | "Sthulakesha [thick-haired sage], that radiant one, saw her in a desolate place, bereft of relatives. ||8||" |
| `Line 2356:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2357: स तां दृष्ट्वा तदा कन्यां स्थूलकेशो द्विजोत्तमः |` | "Upon seeing that girl, Sthulakesha, the foremost among twice-born [Brahmin]," |
| `Line 2358: जग्राहाथ मुनिश्रेष्ठः कृपाविष्टः पुपोष च ||९||` | "The excellent sage, filled with compassion, took her and nurtured her. ||9||" |
| `Line 2359:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2360: ववृधे सा वरारोहा तस्याश्रमपदे शुभा ||९||` | "That beautiful maiden with lovely hips grew up in his auspicious hermitage. ||9||" |
| `Line 2361:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2362: प्रमदाभ्यो वरा सा तु सर्वरूपगुणान्विता |` | "She was the most excellent among women, endowed with all beauty and virtues," |
| `Line 2363: ततः प्रमद्वरेत्यस्या नाम चक्रे महानृषिः ||१०||` | "Therefore, the great sage named her Pramadvara [supremely intoxicating]. ||10||" |
| `Line 2364:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2365: तामाश्रमपदे तस्य रुरुर्दृष्ट्वा प्रमद्वराम् |` | "Seeing that Pramadvara in his hermitage, Ruru [sage's name]," |
| `Line 2366: बभूव किल धर्मात्मा मदनानुगतात्मवान् ||११||` | "That righteous soul indeed became possessed by love. ||11||" |
| `Line 2367:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2368: पितरं सखिभिः सोऽथ वाचयामास भार्गवः |` | "Then that descendant of Bhrigu [Bhargava] had his father approached through friends," |
| `Line 2369: प्रमतिश्चाभ्ययाच्छ्रुत्वा स्थूलकेशं यशस्विनम् ||१२||` | "And Pramati, having heard, requested the illustrious Sthulakesha. ||12||" |
| `Line 2370:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2371: ततः प्रादात्पिता कन्यां रुरवे तां प्रमद्वराम् |` | "Then the father gave that maiden Pramadvara to Ruru," |
| `Line 2372: विवाहं स्थापयित्वाग्रे नक्षत्रे भगदैवते ||१३||` | "Having fixed the wedding at the auspicious time under the Uttara Phalguni [Bhaga's constellation]. ||13||" |
| `Line 2373:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2374: ततः कतिपयाहस्य विवाहे समुपस्थिते |` | "Then, when a few days remained before the wedding," |
| `Line 2375: सखीभिः क्रीडती सार्धं सा कन्या वरवर्णिनी ||१४||` | "That fair-complexioned maiden, while playing with her friends, ||14||" |
| `Line 2376: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 2377: नापश्यत प्रसुप्तं वै भुजगं तिर्यगायतम् |` | "She did not see the sleeping serpent [bhujaga] lying across (her path)," |
| `Line 2378: पदा चैनं समाक्रामन्मुमूर्षुः कालचोदिता ||१५||` | "And stepped on it with her foot, destined to die, impelled by fate [kala]. ||15||" |
| `Line 2379: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 2380: स तस्याः सम्प्रमत्तायाश्चोदितः कालधर्मणा |` | "That serpent, provoked by her carelessness and driven by the law of death [kala-dharma]," |
| `Line 2381: विषोपलिप्तान्दशनान्भृशमङ्गे न्यपातयत् ||१६||` | "Plunged its venom-coated fangs deeply into her body. ||16||" |
| `Line 2382: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 2383: सा दष्टा सहसा भूमौ पतिता गतचेतना |` | "Suddenly bitten, she fell to the ground unconscious," |
| `Line 2384: व्यसुरप्रेक्षणीयापि प्रेक्षणीयतमाकृतिः ||१७||` | "Though lifeless, her form remained most beautiful to behold. ||17||" |
| `Line 2385: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 2386: प्रसुप्तेवाभवच्चापि भुवि सर्पविषार्दिता |` | "Afflicted by the serpent's poison, she lay on the ground as if asleep," |
| `Line 2387: भूयो मनोहरतरा बभूव तनुमध्यमा ||१८||` | "The slender-waisted one [tanu-madhyama] became even more enchanting in death. ||18||" |
| `Line 2388: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 2389: ददर्श तां पिता चैव ते चैवान्ये तपस्विनः |` | "Her father and those other ascetics [tapasvinah] saw her," |
| `Line 2390: विचेष्टमानां पतितां भूतले पद्मवर्चसम् ||१९||` | "Fallen on the ground, writhing, with a lotus-like radiance [padma-varchasam]. ||19||" |
| `Line 2391: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 2392: ततः सर्वे द्विजवराः समाजग्मुः कृपान्विताः |` | "Then all those excellent twice-born [dvija-varah] gathered, filled with compassion," |
| `Line 2393: स्वस्त्यात्रेयो महाजानुः कुशिकः शङ्खमेखलः ||२०||` | "Svastyatreya, Mahajanu, Kushika, Shankhamekala, ||20||" |
| `Line 2394: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 2395: भारद्वाजः कौणकुत्स आर्ष्टिषेणोऽथ गौतमः |` | "Bharadvaja, Kaunakutsa, Arshtishena, and Gautama," |
| `Line 2396: प्रमतिः सह पुत्रेण तथान्ये वनवासिनः ||२१||` | "Pramati with his son, and other forest-dwellers [vana-vasinah]. ||21||" |
| `Line 2397: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 2398: तां ते कन्यां व्यसुं दृष्ट्वा भुजगस्य विषार्दिताम् |` | "Seeing that maiden lifeless, afflicted by the serpent's poison," |
| `Line 2399: रुरुदुः कृपयाविष्टा रुरुस्त्वार्तो बहिर्ययौ ||२२||` | "They wept, overcome with compassion, while Ruru, grief-stricken, went outside. ||22||" |
| `Line 2400: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 2401: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2402: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2403: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2404: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2405: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2406: ९` | "9" [Chapter or section number] |
| `Line 2407: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2408: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2409: सूत उवाच||` | "Suta [bard-narrator] said:" |
| `Line 2410: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2411: तेषु तत्रोपविष्टेषु ब्राह्मणेषु समन्ततः |` | "When all those brahmanas [priests] were seated there all around," |
| `Line 2412: रुरुश्चुक्रोश गहनं वनं गत्वा सुदुःखितः ||१||` | "Ruru [sage's name], extremely distressed, went to the dense forest and cried out. ||1||" |
| `Line 2413: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2414: शोकेनाभिहतः सोऽथ विलपन्करुणं बहु |` | "Struck by grief, he then lamented piteously many times," |
| `Line 2415: अब्रवीद्वचनं शोचन्प्रियां चिन्त्य प्रमद्वराम् ||२||` | "And spoke these words in sorrow, thinking of his beloved Pramadvara [his wife]. ||2||" |
| `Line 2416: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2417: शेते सा भुवि तन्वङ्गी मम शोकविवर्धिनी |` | "She lies on the ground, that slender-limbed one, increasing my sorrow," |
| `Line 2418: बान्धवानां च सर्वेषां किं नु दुःखमतः परम् ||३||` | "For all relatives, what sorrow could be greater than this? ||3||" |
| `Line 2419: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2420: यदि दत्तं तपस्तप्तं गुरवो वा मया यदि |` | "If I have given charity, performed austerities, or if I have properly served my teachers," |
| `Line 2421: सम्यगाराधितास्तेन सञ्जीवतु मम प्रिया ||४||` | "By the merit of these acts, may my beloved come back to life. ||4||" |
| `Line 2422: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2423: यथा जन्मप्रभृति वै यतात्माहं धृतव्रतः |` | "As from birth I have been self-controlled and steadfast in my vows," |
| `Line 2424: प्रमद्वरा तथाद्यैव समुत्तिष्ठतु भामिनी ||५||` | "So may Pramadvara, that radiant lady, rise up this very day. ||5||" |
| `Line 2425: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2426: देवदूत उवाच॥` | "The divine messenger [Devaduta] said:" |
| `Line 2427: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2428: अभिधत्से ह यद्वाचा रुरो दुःखेन तन्मृषा |` | "O Ruru, what you speak with sorrow is in vain," |
| `Line 2429: न तु मर्त्यस्य धर्मात्मन्नायुरस्ति गतायुषः ॥६॥` | "O righteous one [Dharmatman], a mortal whose life-span has ended cannot regain life. ||6||" |
| `Line 2430: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2431: गतायुरेषा कृपणा गन्धर्वाप्सरसोः सुता |` | "This poor girl, daughter of a Gandharva and an Apsara, has exhausted her life-span," |
| `Line 2432: तस्माच्छोके मनस्तात मा कृथास्त्वं कथञ्चन ॥७॥` | "Therefore, dear one [Tata], do not grieve in your mind in any way. ||7||" |
| `Line 2433: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2434: उपायश्चात्र विहितः पूर्वं देवैर्महात्मभिः |` | "However, a remedy has been ordained by the great-souled gods [Mahatma]," |
| `Line 2435: तं यदीच्छसि कर्तुं त्वं प्राप्स्यसीमां प्रमद्वराम् ॥८॥` | "If you wish to perform it, you shall regain this Pramadvara. ||8||" |
| `Line 2436: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2437: रुरुरुवाच॥` | "Ruru said:" |
| `Line 2438: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2439: क उपायः कृतो देवैर्ब्रूहि तत्त्वेन खेचर |` | "What remedy has been ordained by the gods? Tell me truthfully, O sky-traveler [Khechara]," |
| `Line 2440: करिष्ये तं तथा श्रुत्वा त्रातुमर्हति मां भवान् ॥९॥` | "Having heard it, I shall perform it accordingly. You ought to save me. ||9||" |
| `Line 2441: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2442: देवदूत उवाच॥` | "The divine messenger said:" |
| `Line 2443: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2444: आयुषोऽर्धं प्रयच्छस्व कन्यायै भृगुनन्दन |` | "Give half of your life-span to the maiden, O descendant of Bhrigu [Bhrigunandana]," |
| `Line 2445: एवमुत्थास्यति रुरो तव भार्या प्रमद्वरा ॥१०॥` | "Thus, O Ruru, your wife Pramadvara will rise again. ||10||" |
| `Line 2446: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2447: रुरुरुवाच॥` | "Ruru said:" |
| `Line 2448: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2449: आयुषोऽर्धं प्रयच्छामि कन्यायै खेचरोत्तम |` | "I give half of my life-span to the maiden, O best of sky-travelers [Khecharottama]," |
| `Line 2450: शृङ्गाररूपाभरणा उत्तिष्ठतु मम प्रिया ॥११॥` | "Let my beloved rise again, adorned with beautiful ornaments. ||11||" |
| `Line 2451: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 2452: सूत उवाच॥` | "Suta [bard/narrator] said:" |
| `Line 2453: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 2454: ततो गन्धर्वराजश्च देवदूतश्च सत्तमौ |` | "Then the king of Gandharvas [celestial musicians] and the divine messenger [Yama's emissary], both excellent beings," |
| `Line 2455: धर्मराजमुपेत्येदं वचनं प्रत्यभाषताम् ॥१२॥` | "Approached Dharmaraja [lord of justice/Yama] and spoke these words. ||12||" |
| `Line 2456: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 2457: धर्मराजायुषोऽर्धेन रुरोर्भार्या प्रमद्वरा |` | "O Dharmaraja, let Pramadvara, Ruru's wife, with half of Ruru's lifespan," |
| `Line 2458: समुत्तिष्ठतु कल्याणी मृतैव यदि मन्यसे ॥१३॥` | "Rise up again, auspicious one, though dead, if you deem it proper. ||13||" |
| `Line 2459: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 2460: धर्मराज उवाच॥` | "Dharmaraja [Yama] said:" |
| `Line 2461: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 2462: प्रमद्वरा रुरोर्भार्या देवदूत यदीच्छसि |` | "If you wish, O divine messenger, let Pramadvara, Ruru's wife," |
| `Line 2463: उत्तिष्ठत्वायुषोऽर्धेन रुरोरेव समन्विता ॥१४॥` | "Rise up, endowed with half of Ruru's lifespan. ||14||" |
| `Line 2464: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 2465: सूत उवाच॥` | "Suta [bard/narrator] said:" |
| `Line 2466: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 2467: एवमुक्ते ततः कन्या सोदतिष्ठत्प्रमद्वरा |` | "When this was said, then the maiden Pramadvara rose up," |
| `Line 2468: रुरोस्तस्यायुषोऽर्धेन सुप्तेव वरवर्णिनी ॥१५॥` | "With half of Ruru's lifespan, as if from sleep, that fair-complexioned one. ||15||" |
| `Line 2469: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 2470: एतद्दृष्टं भविष्ये हि रुरोरुत्तमतेजसः |` | "This was foreseen in the future for Ruru of excellent splendor," |
| `Line 2471: आयुषोऽतिप्रवृद्धस्य भार्यार्थेऽर्धं ह्रसत्विति ॥१६॥` | "That half of his greatly extended lifespan would be diminished for his wife's sake. ||16||" |
| `Line 2472: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 2473: तत इष्टेऽहनि तयोः पितरौ चक्रतुर्मुदा |` | "Then, on an auspicious day, their parents joyfully performed," |
| `Line 2474: विवाहं तौ च रेमाते परस्परहितैषिणौ ॥१७॥` | "Their wedding, and the two enjoyed themselves, seeking each other's welfare. ||17||" |
| `Line 2475: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 2476: स लब्ध्वा दुर्लभां भार्यां पद्मकिञ्जल्कसप्रभाम् |` | "Having obtained his rare wife, who had the radiance of lotus stamens," |
| `Line 2477: व्रतं चक्रे विनाशाय जिह्मगानां धृतव्रतः ||१८||` | "The resolute one made a vow to destroy all serpents [jihmaga]. ||18||" |
| `Line 2478:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2479: स दृष्ट्वा जिह्मगान्सर्वांस्तीव्रकोपसमन्वितः |` | "Seeing any serpent, filled with intense anger," |
| `Line 2480: अभिहन्ति यथासन्नं गृह्य प्रहरणं सदा ||१९||` | "He would always strike it when encountered, seizing a weapon. ||19||" |
| `Line 2481:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2482: स कदाचिद्वनं विप्रो रुरुरभ्यागमन्महत् |` | "Once that Brahmin [vipra] Ruru entered a great forest," |
| `Line 2483: शयानं तत्र चापश्यड्डुण्डुभं वयसान्वितम् ||२०||` | "And there he saw a Dundubha [non-venomous snake] lying, advanced in age. ||20||" |
| `Line 2484:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2485: तत उद्यम्य दण्डं स कालदण्डोपमं तदा |` | "Then, raising a staff resembling the rod of Death [Kaladanda]," |
| `Line 2486: अभ्यघ्नद्रुषितो विप्रस्तमुवाचाथ डुण्डुभः ||२१||` | "The enraged Brahmin struck at it, whereupon the Dundubha spoke to him: ||21||" |
| `Line 2487:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2488: नापराध्यामि ते किञ्चिदहमद्य तपोधन |` | "I have done you no wrong today, O wealth of austerities [tapodana]," |
| `Line 2489: संरम्भात्तत्किमर्थं मामभिहंसि रुषान्वितः ||२२||` | "Why then do you strike me in haste, filled with anger? ||22||" |
| `Line 2490:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2491:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2492:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2493:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2494:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2495:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2496: १०` | "10" |
| `Line 2497:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2498:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2499: रुरुरुवाच||` | "Ruru said:" |
| `Line 2500:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2501: मम प्राणसमा भार्या दष्टासीद्भुजगेन ह |` | "My wife, who was dear to me as life itself, was bitten by a serpent." |
| `Line 2502: तत्र मे समयो घोर आत्मनोरग वै कृतः ||१||` | "At that time, I made a terrible vow to myself regarding serpents. ||1||" |
| `Line 2503: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2504: हन्यां सदैव भुजगं यं यं पश्येयमित्युत |` | "That I would always kill any serpent that I might see," |
| `Line 2505: ततोऽहं त्वां जिघांसामि जीवितेन विमोक्ष्यसे ||२||` | "Therefore I wish to kill you, and you shall be released from your life. ||2||" |
| `Line 2506: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2507: डुण्डुभ उवाच||` | "Dundubha [snake-sage] said:" |
| `Line 2508: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2509: अन्ये ते भुजगा विप्र ये दशन्तीह मानवान् |` | "O brahmin [twice-born], those are different serpents who bite humans here," |
| `Line 2510: डुण्डुभानहिगन्धेन न त्वं हिंसितुमर्हसि ||३||` | "You should not kill Dundubhas who merely have the scent of snakes. ||3||" |
| `Line 2511: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2512: एकानर्थान्पृथगर्थानेकदुःखान्पृथक्सुखान् |` | "We have different purposes, different goals, different sorrows, and different pleasures," |
| `Line 2513: डुण्डुभान्धर्मविद्भूत्वा न त्वं हिंसितुमर्हसि ||४||` | "Being knowledgeable in dharma [righteousness], you should not kill Dundubhas. ||4||" |
| `Line 2514: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2515: सूत उवाच||` | "Suta [bard-narrator] said:" |
| `Line 2516: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2517: इति श्रुत्वा वचस्तस्य भुजगस्य रुरुस्तदा |` | "Having heard these words of that serpent, Ruru then," |
| `Line 2518: नावधीद्भयसंविग्न ऋषिं मत्वाथ डुण्डुभम् ||५||` | "Did not kill him, being struck with awe, thinking the Dundubha to be a sage. ||5||" |
| `Line 2519: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2520: उवाच चैनं भगवान्रुरुः संशमयन्निव |` | "And the venerable Ruru spoke to him, as if calming him," |
| `Line 2521: कामया भुजग ब्रूहि कोऽसीमां विक्रियां गतः ||६||` | "Please tell me, O serpent, who are you that has undergone this transformation? ||6||" |
| `Line 2522: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2523: डुण्डुभ उवाच||` | "Dundubha [snake-sage] said:" |
| `Line 2524: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2525: अहं पुरा रुरो नाम्ना ऋषिरासं सहस्रपात् |` | "I was formerly a sage named Ruru, the thousand-footed [powerful sage]," |
| `Line 2526: सोऽहं शापेन विप्रस्य भुजगत्वमुपागतः ||७||` | "Thus I, by the curse of a brahmin [twice-born sage], have attained the state of a serpent. ||7||" |
| `Line 2527: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2528: रुरुरुवाच||` | "Ruru said:" |
| `Line 2529: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2530: किमर्थं शप्तवान्क्रुद्धो द्विजस्त्वां भुजगोत्तम |` | "For what reason did the angry twice-born [brahmin] curse you, O best of serpents?" |
| `Line 2531: कियन्तं चैव कालं ते वपुरेतद्भविष्यति ||८||` | "And for how long will you have this body? ||8||" |
| `Line 2532: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2533: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2534: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2535: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2536: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2537: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2538: ११` | "11" [Chapter or section number] |
| `Line 2539: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2540: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2541: डुण्डुभ उवाच||` | "Dundubha [serpent's name] said:" |
| `Line 2542: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2543: सखा बभूव मे पूर्वं खगमो नाम वै द्विजः |` | "I formerly had a friend, a twice-born [brahmin] named Khagama," |
| `Line 2544: भृशं संशितवाक्तात तपोबलसमन्वितः ||१||` | "Who was extremely precise in speech and endowed with the power of austerities. ||1||" |
| `Line 2545: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2546: स मया क्रीडता बाल्ये कृत्वा तार्णमथोरगम् |` | "While playing in my childhood, I made a snake of grass," |
| `Line 2547: अग्निहोत्रे प्रसक्तः सन्भीषितः प्रमुमोह वै ||२||` | "And frightened him while he was engaged in the Agnihotra [fire ritual], causing him to faint. ||2||" |
| `Line 2548: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2549: लब्ध्वा च स पुनः सञ्ज्ञां मामुवाच तपोधनः |` | "And when he regained consciousness, that ascetic [wealth of austerities] said to me," |
| `Line 2550: निर्दहन्निव कोपेन सत्यवाक्संशितव्रतः ||३||` | "As if burning with anger, that truthful speaker of firm vows: ||3||" |
| `Line 2551: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2552: यथावीर्यस्त्वया सर्पः कृतोऽयं मद्बिभीषया |` | "As you have created this snake with power to frighten me," |
| `Line 2553: तथावीर्यो भुजङ्गस्त्वं मम कोपाद्भविष्यसि ||४||` | "So shall you become a serpent [bhujanga] with similar power due to my anger. ||4||" |
| `Line 2554: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2555: तस्याहं तपसो वीर्यं जानमानस्तपोधन |` | "Knowing the power of his austerities, O ascetic [tapodhan]," |
| `Line 2556: भृशमुद्विग्नहृदयस्तमवोचं वनौकसम् ||५||` | "With an extremely anxious heart, I addressed that forest-dweller [vanaukasa]. ||5||" |
| `Line 2557: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2558: प्रयतः सम्भ्रमाच्चैव प्राञ्जलिः प्रणतः स्थितः |` | "Standing with folded hands [pranjali], bowing down in agitation," |
| `Line 2559: सखेति हसतेदं ते नर्मार्थं वै कृतं मया ||६||` | "'Friend,' I said, 'this was done by me merely in jest [narmartha], laughing.' ||6||" |
| `Line 2560: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2561: क्षन्तुमर्हसि मे ब्रह्मञ्शापोऽयं विनिवर्त्यताम् |` | "'You ought to forgive me, O Brahmin [brahman], may this curse be withdrawn,'" |
| `Line 2562: सोऽथ मामब्रवीद्दृष्ट्वा भृशमुद्विग्नचेतसम् ||७||` | "Then he, seeing me extremely distressed in mind, said to me: ||7||" |
| `Line 2563: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2564: मुहुरुष्णं विनिःश्वस्य सुसम्भ्रान्तस्तपोधनः |` | "Sighing deeply and repeatedly, the greatly agitated ascetic [tapodhanah]," |
| `Line 2565: नानृतं वै मया प्रोक्तं भवितेदं कथञ्चन ||८||` | "'What I have spoken cannot become untrue in any way. ||8||'" |
| `Line 2566: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2567: यत्तु वक्ष्यामि ते वाक्यं शृणु तन्मे धृतव्रत |` | "'But listen to these words that I will speak to you, O steadfast in vows [dhritavrata]," |
| `Line 2568: श्रुत्वा च हृदि ते वाक्यमिदमस्तु तपोधन ||९||` | "'Having heard them, may these words remain in your heart, O ascetic [tapodhan]. ||9||'" |
| `Line 2569: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2570: उत्पत्स्यति रुरुर्नाम प्रमतेरात्मजः शुचिः |` | "'There will be born one named Ruru, the pure son of Pramati [Pramati's son]," |
| `Line 2571: तं दृष्ट्वा शापमोक्षस्ते भविता नचिरादिव ||१०||` | "'Upon seeing him, your release from the curse will happen without delay. ||10||'" |
| `Line 2572: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2573: स त्वं रुरुरिति ख्यातः प्रमतेरात्मजः शुचिः |` | "'You are that Ruru, renowned as the pure son of Pramati," |
| `Line 2574: स्वरूपं प्रतिलभ्याहमद्य वक्ष्यामि ते हितम् ||११||` | "'Having regained my true form, I shall now tell you what is beneficial for you. ||11||'" |
| `Line 2575: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2576: अहिंसा परमो धर्मः सर्वप्राणभृतां स्मृतः |` | "Non-violence is the highest dharma [righteous duty], remembered for all living beings." |
| `Line 2577: तस्मात्प्राणभृतः सर्वान्न हिंस्याद्ब्राह्मणः क्वचित् ॥१२॥` | "Therefore, a Brahmin [priestly class] should never harm any living beings anywhere. ||12||" |
| `Line 2578: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 2579: ब्राह्मणः सौम्य एवेह जायतेति परा श्रुतिः |` | "A Brahmin is born gentle in this world - thus declares the supreme scripture [Vedas]," |
| `Line 2580: वेदवेदाङ्गवित्तात सर्वभूताभयप्रदः ॥१३॥` | "O dear one, knower of Vedas and Vedangas [auxiliary texts], bestower of fearlessness to all beings. ||13||" |
| `Line 2581: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 2582: अहिंसा सत्यवचनं क्षमा चेति विनिश्चितम् |` | "Non-violence, truthful speech, and forgiveness - these are established" |
| `Line 2583: ब्राह्मणस्य परो धर्मो वेदानां धरणादपि ॥१४॥` | "As the highest dharma of a Brahmin, even more than upholding the Vedas. ||14||" |
| `Line 2584: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 2585: क्षत्रियस्य तु यो धर्मः स नेहेष्यति वै तव |` | "But the dharma of a Kshatriya [warrior class] is not suitable for you," |
| `Line 2586: दण्डधारणमुग्रत्वं प्रजानां परिपालनम् ॥१५॥` | "Wielding punishment, fierceness, and protection of subjects. ||15||" |
| `Line 2587: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 2588: तदिदं क्षत्रियस्यासीत्कर्म वै शृणु मे रुरो |` | "Listen to me, Ruru, about this duty that belonged to a Kshatriya," |
| `Line 2589: जनमेजयस्य धर्मात्मन्सर्पाणां हिंसनं पुरा ॥१६॥` | "O righteous one, about Janamejaya's destruction of serpents in ancient times. ||16||" |
| `Line 2590: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 2591: परित्राणं च भीतानां सर्पाणां ब्राह्मणादपि |` | "And the rescue of the frightened serpents by a Brahmin," |
| `Line 2592: तपोवीर्यबलोपेताद्वेदवेदाङ्गपारगात् ॥१७॥` | "Endowed with the power of austerity and strength, who had mastered the Vedas and Vedangas. ||17||" |
| `Line 2593: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 2594: आस्तीकाद्द्विजमुख्याद्वै सर्पसत्रे द्विजोत्तम ॥१७॥` | "From Astika [sage's name], the foremost of the twice-born, at the serpent sacrifice, O best of Brahmins. ||17||" |
| `Line 2595: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 2596: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 2597: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 2598: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 2599: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 2600: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 2601: १२` | "12" |
| `Line 2602:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2603:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2604: रुरुरुवाच॥` | "Ruru said:" |
| `Line 2605:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2606: कथं हिंसितवान्सर्पान्क्षत्रियो जनमेजयः |` | "How did the Kshatriya [warrior-king] Janamejaya destroy the serpents?" |
| `Line 2607: सर्पा वा हिंसितास्तात किमर्थं द्विजसत्तम ॥१॥` | "And why, O father [term of respect], O best of twice-born [Brahmin], were the serpents destroyed? ||1||" |
| `Line 2608:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2609: किमर्थं मोक्षिताश्चैव पन्नगास्तेन शंस मे |` | "And why were the serpents [pannaga] released by him? Tell me," |
| `Line 2610: आस्तीकेन तदाचक्ष्व श्रोतुमिच्छाम्यशेषतः ॥२॥` | "Narrate to me about Astika; I wish to hear it completely. ||2||" |
| `Line 2611:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2612: ऋषिरुवाच॥` | "The sage said:" |
| `Line 2613:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2614: श्रोष्यसि त्वं रुरो सर्वमास्तीकचरितं महत् |` | "You shall hear, O Ruru, the entire great story of Astika," |
| `Line 2615: ब्राह्मणानां कथयतामित्युक्त्वान्तरधीयत ॥३॥` | "As told by the Brahmins." Having said this, he disappeared. ||3||" |
| `Line 2616:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2617: सूत उवाच॥` | "Suta [bard-narrator] said:" |
| `Line 2618:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2619: रुरुश्चापि वनं सर्वं पर्यधावत्समन्ततः |` | "And Ruru ran throughout the entire forest in all directions," |
| `Line 2620: तमृषिं द्रष्टुमन्विच्छन्संश्रान्तो न्यपतद्भुवि ॥४॥` | "Seeking to see that sage, and exhausted, he fell to the ground. ||4||" |
| `Line 2621:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2622: लब्धसञ्ज्ञो रुरुश्चायात्तच्चाचख्यौ पितुस्तदा |` | "Having regained consciousness, Ruru went and told everything to his father then," |
| `Line 2623: पिता चास्य तदाख्यानं पृष्टः सर्वं न्यवेदयत् ॥५॥` | "And his father, when asked, narrated the entire story. ||5||" |
| `Line 2624:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2625:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2626: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2627: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2628: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2629: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2630: आस्तीकपर्व` | "Āstīka Parva [Astika chapter]" |
| `Line 2631: १३` | "13" |
| `Line 2632: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2633: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2634: शौनक उवाच||` | "Shaunaka [sage-listener] said:" |
| `Line 2635: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2636: किमर्थं राजशार्दूलः स राजा जनमेजयः |` | "For what purpose did that tiger among kings [mighty ruler], King Janamejaya," |
| `Line 2637: सर्पसत्रेण सर्पाणां गतोऽन्तं तद्वदस्व मे ||१||` | "Seek to destroy the serpents through the snake sacrifice? Tell me about that. ||1||" |
| `Line 2638: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2639: आस्तीकश्च द्विजश्रेष्ठः किमर्थं जपतां वरः |` | "And for what reason did Āstīka, the foremost of twice-born [brahmin], the best among chanters," |
| `Line 2640: मोक्षयामास भुजगान्दीप्तात्तस्माद्धुताशनात् ||२||` | "Free the serpents from that blazing fire [sacrificial flame]? ||2||" |
| `Line 2641: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2642: कस्य पुत्रः स राजासीत्सर्पसत्रं य आहरत् |` | "Whose son was that king who performed the snake sacrifice," |
| `Line 2643: स च द्विजातिप्रवरः कस्य पुत्रो वदस्व मे ||३||` | "And that foremost of twice-born [brahmin], whose son was he? Tell me. ||3||" |
| `Line 2644: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2645: सूत उवाच||` | "Sūta [bard-narrator] said:" |
| `Line 2646: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2647: महदाख्यानमास्तीकं यत्रैतत्प्रोच्यते द्विज |` | "This great narrative of Āstīka wherein this is told, O twice-born [brahmin]," |
| `Line 2648: सर्वमेतदशेषेण शृणु मे वदतां वर ||४||` | "Listen to all of this completely from me, O best among speakers. ||4||" |
| `Line 2649: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2650: शौनक उवाच||` | "Shaunaka [sage-listener] said:" |
| `Line 2651: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2652: श्रोतुमिच्छाम्यशेषेण कथामेतां मनोरमाम् |` | "I wish to hear completely this delightful story," |
| `Line 2653: आस्तीकस्य पुराणस्य ब्राह्मणस्य यशस्विनः ||५||` | "Of Āstīka, the ancient brahmin [twice-born sage] of great fame. ||5||" |
| `Line 2654: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2655: सूत उवाच||` | "Sūta [bard sage] said:" |
| `Line 2656: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2657: इतिहासमिमं वृद्धाः पुराणं परिचक्षते |` | "The elders [venerable sages] describe this history as an ancient tale [purāṇa]," |
| `Line 2658: कृष्णद्वैपायनप्रोक्तं नैमिषारण्यवासिनः ||६||` | "Narrated by Kṛṣṇa Dvaipāyana [Vyāsa], to the dwellers of Naimiṣāraṇya [sacred forest]. ||6||" |
| `Line 2659: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2660: पूर्वं प्रचोदितः सूतः पिता मे लोमहर्षणः |` | "Formerly, my father Lomaharṣaṇa, the sūta [bard sage]," |
| `Line 2661: शिष्यो व्यासस्य मेधावी ब्राह्मणैरिदमुक्तवान् ||७||` | "The intelligent disciple of Vyāsa, narrated this to the brahmins. ||7||" |
| `Line 2662: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2663: तस्मादहमुपश्रुत्य प्रवक्ष्यामि यथातथम् |` | "Therefore, having heard it from him, I shall narrate it exactly as it is," |
| `Line 2664: इदमास्तीकमाख्यानं तुभ्यं शौनक पृच्छते ||८||` | "This tale of Āstīka to you, O Śaunaka, who has asked. ||8||" |
| `Line 2665: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2666: आस्तीकस्य पिता ह्यासीत्प्रजापतिसमः प्रभुः |` | "Āstīka's father was a lord equal to Prajāpati [creator deity]," |
| `Line 2667: ब्रह्मचारी यताहारस्तपस्युग्रे रतः सदा ||९||` | "A celibate [brahmacharī] with controlled diet, always engaged in severe austerities. ||9||" |
| `Line 2668: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2669: जरत्कारुरिति ख्यात ऊर्ध्वरेता महानृषिः |` | "He was known as Jaratkāru, the great sage who preserved his vital fluid [celibate]," |
| `Line 2670: यायावराणां धर्मज्ञः प्रवरः संशितव्रतः ||१०||` | "Foremost among the wandering ascetics [yāyāvaras], knower of dharma, of firm vows. ||10||" |
| `Line 2671: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2672: अटमानः कदाचित्स स्वान्ददर्श पितामहान् |` | "Once while wandering, he saw his own forefathers [ancestors]," |
| `Line 2673: लम्बमानान्महागर्ते पादैरूर्ध्वैरधोमुखान् ||११||` | "Hanging in a great pit, with feet upward and faces downward. ||11||" |
| `Line 2674: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2675: तानब्रवीत्स दृष्ट्वैव जरत्कारुः पितामहान् |` | "Upon seeing them, Jaratkāru addressed those forefathers [ancestors]:" |
| `Line 2676: के भवन्तोऽवलम्बन्ते गर्तेऽस्मिन्वा अधोमुखाः ||१२||` | "Who are you hanging in this pit with faces downward? ||12||" |
| `Line 2677: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 2678: वीरणस्तम्बके लग्नाः सर्वतः परिभक्षिते |` | "Clinging to a reed-grass clump that is gnawed all around" |
| `Line 2679: मूषकेन निगूढेन गर्तेऽस्मिन्नित्यवासिना ||१३||` | "By a hidden mouse that permanently dwells in this pit. ||13||" |
| `Line 2680: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 2681: पितर ऊचुः||` | "The ancestors [pitrs] said:" |
| `Line 2682: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 2683: यायावरा नाम वयमृषयः संशितव्रताः |` | "We are sages called Yayavaras [wandering ascetics], of strict vows," |
| `Line 2684: सन्तानप्रक्षयाद्ब्रह्मन्नधो गच्छाम मेदिनीम् ||१४||` | "Due to the extinction of our lineage, O Brahmin, we are descending to the earth. ||14||" |
| `Line 2685: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 2686: अस्माकं सन्ततिस्त्वेको जरत्कारुरिति श्रुतः |` | "Our sole descendant is known as Jaratkaru," |
| `Line 2687: मन्दभाग्योऽल्पभाग्यानां तप एव समास्थितः ||१५||` | "Unfortunate one of the unfortunate, devoted only to austerities. ||15||" |
| `Line 2688: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 2689: न स पुत्राञ्जनयितुं दारान्मूढश्चिकीर्षति |` | "That foolish one does not wish to take a wife to produce sons," |
| `Line 2690: तेन लम्बामहे गर्ते सन्तानप्रक्षयादिह ||१६||` | "Therefore we hang in this pit due to the extinction of our lineage. ||16||" |
| `Line 2691: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 2692: अनाथास्तेन नाथेन यथा दुष्कृतिनस्तथा |` | "We are like orphans with that protector, just like evildoers," |
| `Line 2693: कस्त्वं बन्धुरिवास्माकमनुशोचसि सत्तम ||१७||` | "Who are you who grieves for us like a relative, O excellent one? ||17||" |
| `Line 2694: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 2695: ज्ञातुमिच्छामहे ब्रह्मन्को भवानिह धिष्ठितः |` | "We wish to know, O Brahmin, who you are standing here," |
| `Line 2696: किमर्थं चैव नः शोच्याननुकम्पितुमर्हसि ||१८||` | "And why do you deserve to show compassion to us who are pitiable? ||18||" |
| `Line 2697: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 2698: जरत्कारुरुवाच||` | "Jaratkaru said:" |
| `Line 2699: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 2700: मम पूर्वे भवन्तो वै पितरः सपितामहाः |` | "You are indeed my ancestors [forefathers] along with my grandfathers," |
| `Line 2701: ब्रूत किं करवाण्यद्य जरत्कारुरहं स्वयम् ||१९||` | "Tell me what I should do now, I myself am Jaratkaru. ||19||" |
| `Line 2702:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2703: पितर ऊचुः||` | "The ancestors [pitrs] said:" |
| `Line 2704:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2705: यतस्व यत्नवांस्तात सन्तानाय कुलस्य नः |` | "Strive diligently, dear son, for the continuation of our lineage," |
| `Line 2706: आत्मनोऽर्थेऽस्मदर्थे च धर्म इत्येव चाभिभो ||२०||` | "For your own sake and for our sake, this is indeed dharma [righteous duty], O illustrious one. ||20||" |
| `Line 2707:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2708: न हि धर्मफलैस्तात न तपोभिः सुसञ्चितैः |` | "Not by the fruits of dharma, dear son, nor by well-accumulated austerities," |
| `Line 2709: तां गतिं प्राप्नुवन्तीह पुत्रिणो यां व्रजन्ति ह ||२१||` | "Can one attain in this world the state which those with sons achieve. ||21||" |
| `Line 2710:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2711: तद्दारग्रहणे यत्नं सन्तत्यां च मनः कुरु |` | "Therefore, make an effort to take a wife and set your mind on progeny," |
| `Line 2712: पुत्रकास्मन्नियोगात्त्वमेतन्नः परमं हितम् ||२२||` | "O son, by our command, this is our highest welfare. ||22||" |
| `Line 2713:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2714: जरत्कारुरुवाच||` | "Jaratkaru said:" |
| `Line 2715:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2716: न दारान्वै करिष्यामि सदा मे भावितं मनः |` | "I shall not take a wife - this has always been my resolved mind," |
| `Line 2717: भवतां तु हितार्थाय करिष्ये दारसङ्ग्रहम् ||२३||` | "But for your welfare, I shall take a wife. ||23||" |
| `Line 2718:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2719: समयेन च कर्ताहमनेन विधिपूर्वकम् |` | "And I shall do so with this condition, according to proper procedure," |
| `Line 2720: तथा यद्युपलप्स्यामि करिष्ये नान्यथा त्वहम् ||२४||` | "Only if I find such a one shall I do it, not otherwise. ||24||" |
| `Line 2721:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2722: सनाम्नी या भवित्री मे दित्सिता चैव बन्धुभिः |` | "She who will be of the same name as mine and is offered by her relatives," |
| `Line 2723: भैक्षवत्तामहं कन्यामुपयंस्ये विधानतः ||२५||` | "Such a maiden, given as alms, I shall marry according to the proper rites. ||25||" |
| `Line 2724:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2725: दरिद्राय हि मे भार्यां को दास्यति विशेषतः |` | "For who would give a wife to a poor man like me, especially," |
| `Line 2726: प्रतिग्रहीष्ये भिक्षां तु यदि कश्चित्प्रदास्यति ॥२६॥` | "I will accept alms [as bride] if someone offers them. ||26||" |
| `Line 2727:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2728: एवं दारक्रियाहेतोः प्रयतिष्ये पितामहाः |` | "Thus, O grandfathers [ancestors], I will strive for the purpose of marriage," |
| `Line 2729: अनेन विधिना शश्वन्न करिष्येऽहमन्यथा ॥२७॥` | "In this manner always, and I shall not do otherwise. ||27||" |
| `Line 2730:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2731: तत्र चोत्पत्स्यते जन्तुर्भवतां तारणाय वै |` | "And there a being will be born for your deliverance indeed," |
| `Line 2732: शाश्वतं स्थानमासाद्य मोदन्तां पितरो मम ॥२८॥` | "May my ancestors rejoice having attained the eternal abode. ||28||" |
| `Line 2733:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2734: सूत उवाच॥` | "Suta [bard-narrator] said:" |
| `Line 2735:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2736: ततो निवेशाय तदा स विप्रः संशितव्रतः |` | "Then, for the purpose of settlement, that Brahmin [vipra] of firm vows," |
| `Line 2737: महीं चचार दारार्थी न च दारानविन्दत ॥२९॥` | "Wandered the earth seeking a wife, but did not find a wife. ||29||" |
| `Line 2738:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2739: स कदाचिद्वनं गत्वा विप्रः पितृवचः स्मरन् |` | "Once, having gone to the forest, that Brahmin, remembering his father's words," |
| `Line 2740: चुक्रोश कन्याभिक्षार्थी तिस्रो वाचः शनैरिव ॥३०॥` | "Called out three times slowly, begging for a maiden as alms. ||30||" |
| `Line 2741:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2742: तं वासुकिः प्रत्यगृह्णादुद्यम्य भगिनीं तदा |` | "Then Vasuki [serpent king] approached him, offering his sister," |
| `Line 2743: न स तां प्रतिजग्राह न सनाम्नीति चिन्तयन् ॥३१॥` | "But he did not accept her, thinking, 'She is not of the same name.' ||31||" |
| `Line 2744:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2745: सनाम्नीमुद्यतां भार्यां गृह्णीयामिति तस्य हि |` | "For his mind was fixed on the idea, 'I shall accept a wife who has the same name as mine,'" |
| `Line 2746: मनो निविष्टमभवज्जरत्कारोर्महात्मनः ॥३२॥` | "Such was the mind of the great-souled Jaratkaru. ||32||" |
| `Line 2747:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2748: तमुवाच महाप्राज्ञो जरत्कारुर्महातपाः |` | "The highly wise Jaratkaru of great austerity said to him," |
| `Line 2749: किंनाम्नी भगिनीयं ते ब्रूहि सत्यं भुजङ्गम ॥३३॥` | "What is the name of this sister of yours? Speak the truth, O serpent [bhujangama]. ||33||" |
| `Line 2750:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2751: वासुकिरुवाच॥` | "Vāsuki [serpent king] said:" |
| `Line 2752: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2753: जरत्कारो जरत्कारुः स्वसेयमनुजा मम |` | "O Jaratkāru, this Jaratkāru is my younger sister," |
| `Line 2754: त्वदर्थं रक्षिता पूर्वं प्रतीच्छेमां द्विजोत्तम ॥३४॥` | "Kept safe earlier for you; accept her, O best of the twice-born [brahmin]. ||34||" |
| `Line 2755: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2756: सूत उवाच॥` | "Sūta [bard-narrator] said:" |
| `Line 2757: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2758: मात्रा हि भुजगाः शप्ताः पूर्वं ब्रह्मविदां वर |` | "For the serpents were previously cursed by their mother, O best of the knowers of Brahman [spiritual scholars]," |
| `Line 2759: जनमेजयस्य वो यज्ञे धक्ष्यत्यनिलसारथिः ॥३५॥` | "Saying, 'The fire [wind-charioteer] will consume you in Janamejaya's sacrifice.' ||35||" |
| `Line 2760: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2761: तस्य शापस्य शान्त्यर्थं प्रददौ पन्नगोत्तमः |` | "For the pacification of that curse, the best of serpents [Vāsuki] gave" |
| `Line 2762: स्वसारमृषये तस्मै सुव्रताय तपस्विने ॥३६॥` | "His sister to that sage, who was of good vows and austere. ||36||" |
| `Line 2763: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2764: स च तां प्रतिजग्राह विधिदृष्टेन कर्मणा |` | "And he accepted her through the ceremony prescribed by the scriptures," |
| `Line 2765: आस्तीको नाम पुत्रश्च तस्यां जज्ञे महात्मनः ॥३७॥` | "And a son named Āstīka was born to that great soul through her. ||37||" |
| `Line 2766: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2767: तपस्वी च महात्मा च वेदवेदाङ्गपारगः |` | "He was austere and noble-souled, master of the Vedas and Vedāṅgas [auxiliary texts]," |
| `Line 2768: समः सर्वस्य लोकस्य पितृमातृभयापहः ॥३८॥` | "Equal toward all beings, and one who removed the fear of his fathers and mother. ||38||" |
| `Line 2769: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2770: अथ कालस्य महतः पाण्डवेयो नराधिपः |` | "Then after a long time, the Pāṇḍava descendant [Kuru king], the ruler of men," |
| `Line 2771: आजहार महायज्ञं सर्पसत्रमिति श्रुतिः ॥३९॥` | "Performed the great sacrifice known as the Sarpa-satra [serpent sacrifice], so it is heard. ||39||" |
| `Line 2772: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2773: तस्मिन्प्रवृत्ते सत्रे तु सर्पाणामन्तकाय वै |` | "When that sacrifice, meant for the destruction of the serpents, was in progress," |
| `Line 2774: मोचयामास तं शापमास्तीकः सुमहायशाः ॥४०॥` | "Āstīka, of great fame, freed them from that curse. ||40||" |
| `Line 2775: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2776: नागांश्च मातुलांश्चैव तथा चान्यान्स बान्धवान् |` | "And the Nāgas [serpent beings] who were his maternal uncles, as well as other relatives," |
| `Line 2777: पितृंश्च तारयामास सन्तत्या तपसा तथा ||४१||` | "And his forefathers [ancestors] he delivered through progeny and through austerities as well. ||41||" |
| `Line 2778: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2779: व्रतैश्च विविधैर्ब्रह्मन्स्वाध्यायैश्चानृणोऽभवत् ||४१||` | "Through various vows, O Brahmin [twice-born sage], and through Vedic study, he became free from debt. ||41||" |
| `Line 2780: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2781: देवांश्च तर्पयामास यज्ञैर्विविधदक्षिणैः |` | "He satisfied the gods through sacrifices with various gifts [dakṣiṇā]," |
| `Line 2782: ऋषींश्च ब्रह्मचर्येण सन्तत्या च पितामहान् ||४२||` | "The sages through celibacy, and his ancestors through progeny. ||42||" |
| `Line 2783: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2784: अपहृत्य गुरुं भारं पितृणां संशितव्रतः |` | "Having removed the heavy burden of his forefathers, firm in his vows," |
| `Line 2785: जरत्कारुर्गतः स्वर्गं सहितः स्वैः पितामहैः ||४३||` | "Jaratkāru went to heaven together with his ancestors. ||43||" |
| `Line 2786: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2787: आस्तीकं च सुतं प्राप्य धर्मं चानुत्तमं मुनिः |` | "Having obtained a son in Āstīka and having fulfilled the highest dharma [righteousness], the sage," |
| `Line 2788: जरत्कारुः सुमहता कालेन स्वर्गमीयिवान् ||४४||` | "Jaratkāru, after a very long time, ascended to heaven. ||44||" |
| `Line 2789: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2790: एतदाख्यानमास्तीकं यथावत्कीर्तितं मया |` | "This story of Āstīka has been properly narrated by me," |
| `Line 2791: प्रब्रूहि भृगुशार्दूल किं भूयः कथ्यतामिति ||४५||` | "Tell me, O tiger among the Bhṛgus [eminent sage], what more should be narrated? ||45||" |
| `Line 2792: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2793: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2794: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2795: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2796: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2797: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2798: १४` | "14" |
| `Line 2799: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2800: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2801: शौनक उवाच॥` | "Shaunaka [sage, narrator] said:" |
| `Line 2802: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 2803: सौते कथय तामेतां विस्तरेण कथां पुनः |` | "O Sauti [bard, narrator], tell that story again in detail," |
| `Line 2804: आस्तीकस्य कवेः साधोः शुश्रूषा परमा हि नः ॥१॥` | "For we have the greatest desire to hear about the virtuous sage Astika. ||1||" |
| `Line 2805: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 2806: मधुरं कथ्यते सौम्य श्लक्ष्णाक्षरपदं त्वया |` | "You narrate sweetly, O gentle one, with smooth syllables and words," |
| `Line 2807: प्रीयामहे भृशं तात पितेवेदं प्रभाषसे ॥२॥` | "We are greatly pleased, dear one, as you speak like a father. ||2||" |
| `Line 2808: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 2809: अस्मच्छुश्रूषणे नित्यं पिता हि निरतस्तव |` | "Your father was always engaged in serving us," |
| `Line 2810: आचष्टैतद्यथाख्यानं पिता ते त्वं तथा वद ॥३॥` | "As your father narrated this story, so you should tell it. ||3||" |
| `Line 2811: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 2812: सूत उवाच॥` | "Suta [bard, narrator] said:" |
| `Line 2813: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 2814: आयुष्यमिदमाख्यानमास्तीकं कथयामि ते |` | "I will narrate to you this life-giving story of Astika," |
| `Line 2815: यथा श्रुतं कथयतः सकाशाद्वै पितुर्मया ॥४॥` | "Just as I heard it from my father when he was telling it. ||4||" |
| `Line 2816: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 2817: पुरा देवयुगे ब्रह्मन्प्रजापतिसुते शुभे |` | "Long ago in the divine age, O Brahmin, there were two auspicious daughters of Prajapati [creator deity]," |
| `Line 2818: आस्तां भगिन्यौ रूपेण समुपेतेऽद्भुतेऽनघे ॥५॥` | "There were two sisters endowed with wonderful, flawless beauty. ||5||" |
| `Line 2819: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 2820: ते भार्ये कश्यपस्यास्तां कद्रूश्च विनता च ह |` | "They were the wives of Kashyapa [sage, progenitor]: Kadru and Vinata," |
| `Line 2821: प्रादात्ताभ्यां वरं प्रीतः प्रजापतिसमः पतिः ॥६॥` | "Their husband, equal to Prajapati, pleased, granted them a boon. ||6||" |
| `Line 2822: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 2823: कश्यपो धर्मपत्नीभ्यां मुदा परमया युतः ॥६॥` | "Kashyapa, filled with supreme joy, to his righteous wives ||6||" |
| `Line 2824: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 2825: वरातिसर्गं श्रुत्वैव कश्यपादुत्तमं च ते |` | "Having heard the excellent granting of boons from Kashyapa, they" |
| `Line 2826: हर्षादप्रतिमां प्रीतिं प्रापतुः स्म वरस्त्रियौ ||७||` | "The two excellent women experienced incomparable joy and delight. ||7||" |
| `Line 2827:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2828: वव्रे कद्रूः सुतान्नागान्सहस्रं तुल्यतेजसः |` | "Kadru chose a thousand serpent sons of equal splendor," |
| `Line 2829: द्वौ पुत्रौ विनता वव्रे कद्रूपुत्राधिकौ बले ||८||` | "While Vinata chose two sons superior in strength to Kadru's offspring. ||8||" |
| `Line 2830:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2831: ओजसा तेजसा चैव विक्रमेणाधिकौ सुतौ ||८||` | "Sons superior in vigor, brilliance, and prowess. ||8||" |
| `Line 2832:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2833: तस्यै भर्ता वरं प्रादादध्यर्धं पुत्रमीप्सितम् |` | "Her husband granted her the desired boon of one and a half sons," |
| `Line 2834: एवमस्त्विति तं चाह कश्यपं विनता तदा ||९||` | "And Vinata then said to Kashyapa, 'So be it.' ||9||" |
| `Line 2835:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2836: कृतकृत्या तु विनता लब्ध्वा वीर्याधिकौ सुतौ |` | "Vinata, having accomplished her purpose by obtaining two sons of superior strength," |
| `Line 2837: कद्रूश्च लब्ध्वा पुत्राणां सहस्रं तुल्यतेजसाम् ||१०||` | "And Kadru, having obtained a thousand sons of equal splendor, ||10||" |
| `Line 2838:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2839: धार्यौ प्रयत्नतो गर्भावित्युक्त्वा स महातपाः |` | "After saying, 'Carefully nurture your pregnancies,' that great ascetic [Kashyapa]," |
| `Line 2840: ते भार्ये वरसंहृष्टे कश्यपो वनमाविशत् ||११||` | "Kashyapa departed for the forest, leaving his two wives delighted with their boons. ||11||" |
| `Line 2841:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2842: कालेन महता कद्रूरण्डानां दशतीर्दश |` | "After a long time, Kadru laid ten hundred eggs," |
| `Line 2843: जनयामास विप्रेन्द्र द्वे अण्डे विनता तदा ||१२||` | "While Vinata, O best of brahmins [vipra-indra], produced two eggs then. ||12||" |
| `Line 2844:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2845: तयोरण्डानि निदधुः प्रहृष्टाः परिचारिकाः |` | "The delighted attendants placed their eggs," |
| `Line 2846: सोपस्वेदेषु भाण्डेषु पञ्च वर्षशतानि च ||१३||` | "In warm vessels for five hundred years. ||13||" |
| `Line 2847:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2848: ततः पञ्चशते काले कद्रूपुत्रा विनिःसृताः |` | "Then, after five hundred years had passed, Kadru's sons emerged," |
| `Line 2849: अण्डाभ्यां विनतायास्तु मिथुनं न व्यदृश्यत ||१४||` | "But from Vinata's two eggs, no pair was yet seen. ||14||" |
| `Line 2850:` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2851: ततः पुत्रार्थिणी देवी व्रीडिता सा तपस्विनी |` | "Then that goddess [Vinatā], desiring a son, being ashamed, that ascetic woman," |
| `Line 2852: अण्डं बिभेद विनता तत्र पुत्रमदृक्षत ||१५||` | "Vinatā broke open the egg and there beheld her son. ||15||" |
| `Line 2853: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2854: पूर्वार्धकायसम्पन्नमितरेणाप्रकाशता |` | "He was complete in the upper half of his body, but the lower part was undeveloped," |
| `Line 2855: स पुत्रो रोषसम्पन्नः शशापैनामिति श्रुतिः ||१६||` | "That son, filled with anger, cursed her, thus it is heard. ||16||" |
| `Line 2856: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2857: योऽहमेवं कृतो मातस्त्वया लोभपरीतया |` | "Since I have been made thus by you, mother, overcome with impatience," |
| `Line 2858: शरीरेणासमग्रोऽद्य तस्माद्दासी भविष्यसि ||१७||` | "With an incomplete body today, therefore you shall become a slave. ||17||" |
| `Line 2859: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2860: पञ्च वर्षशतान्यस्या यया विस्पर्धसे सह |` | "For five hundred years to her with whom you compete," |
| `Line 2861: एष च त्वां सुतो मातर्दास्यत्वान्मोक्षयिष्यति ||१८||` | "And this son [Garuḍa], mother, will free you from slavery. ||18||" |
| `Line 2862: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2863: यद्येनमपि मातस्त्वं मामिवाण्डविभेदनात् |` | "If you, mother, do not make him also, like me, through breaking his egg," |
| `Line 2864: न करिष्यस्यदेहं वा व्यङ्गं वापि तपस्विनम् ||१९||` | "Either incomplete in body or deformed, O ascetic one. ||19||" |
| `Line 2865: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2866: प्रतिपालयितव्यस्ते जन्मकालोऽस्य धीरया |` | "You must wait patiently for his time of birth," |
| `Line 2867: विशिष्टबलमीप्सन्त्या पञ्चवर्षशतात्परः ||२०||` | "Desiring superior strength for him, after five hundred years. ||20||" |
| `Line 2868: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2869: एवं शप्त्वा ततः पुत्रो विनतामन्तरिक्षगः |` | "Having thus cursed Vinatā, then that son, the sky-traveler," |
| `Line 2870: अरुणो दृश्यते ब्रह्मन्प्रभातसमये सदा ||२१||` | "Aruṇa [dawn deity] is seen, O Brahmin, always at the time of dawn. ||21||" |
| `Line 2871: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2872: गरुडोऽपि यथाकालं जज्ञे पन्नगसूदनः |` | "Garuḍa [divine eagle] too was born at the proper time, the destroyer of serpents," |
| `Line 2873: स जातमात्रो विनतां परित्यज्य खमाविशत् ||२२||` | "He, as soon as born, leaving Vinatā, entered the sky. ||22||" |
| `Line 2874: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2875: आदास्यन्नात्मनो भोज्यमन्नं विहितमस्य यत् |` | "To take for himself the food that was ordained for him," |
| `Line 2876: विधात्रा भृगुशार्दूल क्षुधितस्य बुभुक्षतः ||२३||` | "By the Creator [Brahma], O tiger among the Bhrigus [sage], for one who is hungry and starving. ||23||" |
| `Line 2877: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2878: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2879: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2880: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2881: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2882: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2883: १५` | "15" [chapter number] |
| `Line 2884: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2885: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2886: सूत उवाच||` | "Sūta [bard-narrator] said:" |
| `Line 2887: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2888: एतस्मिन्नेव काले तु भगिन्यौ ते तपोधन |` | "At this very time, O wealth of austerities [sage], those two sisters" |
| `Line 2889: अपश्यतां समायान्तमुच्चैःश्रवसमन्तिकात् ||१||` | "Saw Uccaiḥśravas [divine horse] approaching from nearby. ||1||" |
| `Line 2890: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2891: यं तं देवगणाः सर्वे हृष्टरूपा अपूजयन् |` | "Whom all the hosts of gods, in delighted form, worshipped," |
| `Line 2892: मथ्यमानेऽमृते जातमश्वरत्नमनुत्तमम् ||२||` | "Born when the nectar [amrita] was being churned, the unsurpassed jewel among horses. ||2||" |
| `Line 2893: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2894: महौघबलमश्वानामुत्तमं जवतां वरम् |` | "Of immense strength among horses, the best among the swift ones," |
| `Line 2895: श्रीमन्तमजरं दिव्यं सर्वलक्षणलक्षितम् ||३||` | "Splendid, ageless, divine, marked with all auspicious signs. ||3||" |
| `Line 2896: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2897: शौनक उवाच||` | "Śaunaka [sage-listener] said:" |
| `Line 2898: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2899: कथं तदमृतं देवैर्मथितं क्व च शंस मे |` | "How was that nectar churned by the gods, and where? Tell me," |
| `Line 2900: यत्र जज्ञे महावीर्यः सोऽश्वराजो महाद्युतिः ||४||` | "Where was born that mighty one, that king of horses of great splendor. ||4||" |
| `Line 2901: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2902: सूत उवाच॥` | "Sūta [bard-narrator] said:" |
| `Line 2903: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2904: ज्वलन्तमचलं मेरुं तेजोराशिमनुत्तमम् |` | "The blazing, immovable Mount Meru [cosmic mountain], an unsurpassed mass of splendor," |
| `Line 2905: आक्षिपन्तं प्रभां भानोः स्वशृङ्गैः काञ्चनोज्ज्वलैः ॥५॥` | "Outshining the radiance of the sun with its golden-brilliant peaks. ||5||" |
| `Line 2906: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2907: काञ्चनाभरणं चित्रं देवगन्धर्वसेवितम् |` | "Adorned with golden ornaments, marvelous, frequented by gods and gandharvas [celestial musicians]," |
| `Line 2908: अप्रमेयमनाधृष्यमधर्मबहुलैर्जनैः ॥६॥` | "Immeasurable, unapproachable by people abundant in unrighteousness. ||6||" |
| `Line 2909: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2910: व्यालैराचरितं घोरैर्दिव्यौषधिविदीपितम् |` | "Inhabited by fearsome serpents, illuminated by divine herbs," |
| `Line 2911: नाकमावृत्य तिष्ठन्तमुच्छ्रयेण महागिरिम् ॥७॥` | "The great mountain standing, covering heaven with its height. ||7||" |
| `Line 2912: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2913: अगम्यं मनसाप्यन्यैर्नदीवृक्षसमन्वितम् |` | "Inaccessible even in thought to others, filled with rivers and trees," |
| `Line 2914: नानापतगसङ्घैश्च नादितं सुमनोहरैः ॥८॥` | "And resounding with flocks of various enchanting birds. ||8||" |
| `Line 2915: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2916: तस्य पृष्ठमुपारुह्य बहुरत्नाचितं शुभम् |` | "Having ascended to its summit, abundant with many jewels, auspicious," |
| `Line 2917: अनन्तकल्पमुद्विद्धं सुराः सर्वे महौजसः ॥९॥` | "Lofty as if eternal, all the mighty gods [suras]. ||9||" |
| `Line 2918: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2919: ते मन्त्रयितुमारब्धास्तत्रासीना दिवौकसः |` | "Those heaven-dwellers, seated there, began to deliberate," |
| `Line 2920: अमृतार्थे समागम्य तपोनियमसंस्थिताः ॥१०॥` | "Having assembled for the purpose of amṛta [nectar of immortality], established in austerities and observances. ||10||" |
| `Line 2921: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2922: तत्र नारायणो देवो ब्रह्माणमिदमब्रवीत् |` | "There, the god Nārāyaṇa [Vishnu] spoke this to Brahmā [creator deity]," |
| `Line 2923: चिन्तयत्सु सुरेष्वेवं मन्त्रयत्सु च सर्वशः ॥११॥` | "While the gods were thus pondering and deliberating in every way. ||11||" |
| `Line 2924: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2925: देवैरसुरसङ्घैश्च मथ्यतां कलशोदधिः |` | "Let the ocean of milk be churned by the gods and hosts of asuras [demons]," |
| `Line 2926: भविष्यत्यमृतं तत्र मथ्यमाने महोदधौ ||१२||` | "There will be amṛta [immortality nectar] when the great ocean is churned. ||12||" |
| `Line 2927: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2928: सर्वौषधीः समावाप्य सर्वरत्नानि चैव हि |` | "Having gathered all herbs and indeed all jewels," |
| `Line 2929: मन्थध्वमुदधिं देवा वेत्स्यध्वममृतं ततः ||१३||` | "Churn the ocean, O gods, and you shall obtain the amṛta [immortality nectar] from it. ||13||" |
| `Line 2930: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2931: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2932: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2933: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2934: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2935: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2936: १६` | "16" [chapter number] |
| `Line 2937: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2938: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2939: सूत उवाच||` | "Sūta [bard-narrator] said:" |
| `Line 2940: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2941: ततोऽभ्रशिखराकारैर्गिरिशृङ्गैरलङ्कृतम् |` | "Then, adorned with mountain peaks resembling the summits of clouds," |
| `Line 2942: मन्दरं पर्वतवरं लताजालसमावृतम् ||१||` | "Mandara, the excellent mountain, covered with a network of creepers. ||1||" |
| `Line 2943: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2944: नानाविहगसङ्घुष्टं नानादंष्ट्रिसमाकुलम् |` | "Resounding with various birds, teeming with various fanged creatures [wild animals]," |
| `Line 2945: किंनरैरप्सरोभिश्च देवैरपि च सेवितम् ||२||` | "Frequented by Kinnaras [half-human beings], Apsaras [celestial nymphs], and also by gods. ||2||" |
| `Line 2946: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2947: एकादश सहस्राणि योजनानां समुच्छ्रितम् |` | "Eleven thousand yojanas [ancient measure] in height," |
| `Line 2948: अधो भूमेः सहस्रेषु तावत्स्वेव प्रतिष्ठितम् ||३||` | "And established just as many thousands (of yojanas) below the earth. ||3||" |
| `Line 2949: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2950: तमुद्धर्तुं न शक्ता वै सर्वे देवगणास्तदा |` | "All the hosts of gods were then unable to uproot it [the mountain]," |
| `Line 2951: विष्णुमासीनमभ्येत्य ब्रह्माणं चेदमब्रुवन् ||४||` | "Approaching Vishnu [preserver deity] who was seated, and Brahma [creator deity], they said this. ||4||" |
| `Line 2952: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2953: भवन्तावत्र कुरुतां बुद्धिं नैःश्रेयसीं पराम् |` | "May both of you devise here the highest wisdom for ultimate good," |
| `Line 2954: मन्दरोद्धरणे यत्नः क्रियतां च हिताय नः ||५||` | "And let efforts be made to lift Mount Mandara [churning mountain] for our benefit. ||5||" |
| `Line 2955: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2956: तथेति चाब्रवीद्विष्णुर्ब्रह्मणा सह भार्गव |` | "So be it," said Vishnu along with Brahma, O descendant of Bhrigu [sage]," |
| `Line 2957: ततोऽनन्तः समुत्थाय ब्रह्मणा परिचोदितः ||६||` | "Then Ananta [cosmic serpent] arose, urged by Brahma. ||6||" |
| `Line 2958: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2959: नारायणेन चाप्युक्तस्तस्मिन्कर्मणि वीर्यवान् ||६||` | "And instructed by Narayana [Vishnu] too, the mighty one, for that task. ||6||" |
| `Line 2960: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2961: अथ पर्वतराजानं तमनन्तो महाबलः |` | "Then Ananta of great strength," |
| `Line 2962: उज्जहार बलाद्ब्रह्मन्सवनं सवनौकसम् ||७||` | "Forcibly lifted that king of mountains, O Brahmin, along with its forests and forest-dwellers. ||7||" |
| `Line 2963: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2964: ततस्तेन सुराः सार्धं समुद्रमुपतस्थिरे |` | "Then with it, the gods approached the ocean," |
| `Line 2965: तमूचुरमृतार्थाय निर्मथिष्यामहे जलम् ||८||` | "And said to him, 'For the sake of amrita [nectar], we will churn your waters.' ||8||" |
| `Line 2966: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2967: अपाम्पतिरथोवाच ममाप्यंशो भवेत्ततः |` | "Then the lord of waters [ocean] said, 'Let there be a share for me also," |
| `Line 2968: सोढास्मि विपुलं मर्दं मन्दरभ्रमणादिति ||९||` | "For I will endure the immense churning from the rotation of Mandara.' ||9||" |
| `Line 2969: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2970: ऊचुश्च कूर्मराजानमकूपारं सुरासुराः |` | "And the gods and asuras [demons] said to Akupara, the king of turtles [cosmic turtle]," |
| `Line 2971: गिरेरधिष्ठानमस्य भवान्भवितुमर्हति ||१०||` | "'You should become the foundation of this mountain.' ||10||" |
| `Line 2972: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2973: कूर्मेण तु तथेत्युक्त्वा पृष्ठमस्य समर्पितम् |` | "The turtle, saying 'So be it,' offered his back," |
| `Line 2974: तस्य शैलस्य चाग्रं वै यन्त्रेणेन्द्रोऽभ्यपीडयत् ||११||` | "And Indra [king of gods] with a machine pressed down the top of that mountain. ||11||" |
| `Line 2975: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2976: मन्थानं मन्दरं कृत्वा तथा नेत्रं च वासुकिम् |` | "Making Mount Mandara [cosmic mountain] the churning rod and Vāsuki [serpent king] the rope," |
| `Line 2977: देवा मथितुमारब्धाः समुद्रं निधिमम्भसाम् ||१२||` | "The gods began to churn the ocean, the repository of waters. ||12||" |
| `Line 2978: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2979: अमृतार्थिनस्ततो ब्रह्मन्सहिता दैत्यदानवाः ||१२||` | "Then, O Brahmin [sage], the Daityas and Dānavas [demon classes] joined together, seeking the nectar [amrita]. ||12||" |
| `Line 2980: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2981: एकमन्तमुपाश्लिष्टा नागराज्ञो महासुराः |` | "The great Asuras [demons] grasped one end of the serpent king," |
| `Line 2982: विबुधाः सहिताः सर्वे यतः पुच्छं ततः स्थिताः ||१३||` | "While all the gods together positioned themselves at the tail end. ||13||" |
| `Line 2983: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2984: अनन्तो भगवान्देवो यतः नारायणस्ततः |` | "Where Lord Nārāyaṇa [Vishnu] was, there was Ananta [cosmic serpent]," |
| `Line 2985: शिर उद्यम्य नागस्य पुनः पुनरवाक्षिपत् ||१४||` | "Who, raising the serpent's head, pulled it down again and again. ||14||" |
| `Line 2986: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2987: वासुकेरथ नागस्य सहसाक्षिप्यतः सुरैः |` | "As the gods suddenly pulled the serpent Vāsuki," |
| `Line 2988: सधूमाः सार्चिषो वाता निष्पेतुरसकृन्मुखात् ||१५||` | "Smoky, fiery breaths repeatedly issued from his mouth. ||15||" |
| `Line 2989: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2990: ते धूमसङ्घाः सम्भूता मेघसङ्घाः सविद्युतः |` | "Those masses of smoke transformed into clouds with lightning," |
| `Line 2991: अभ्यवर्षन्सुरगणाञ्श्रमसन्तापकर्शितान् ||१६||` | "And rained upon the hosts of gods who were exhausted by fatigue and heat. ||16||" |
| `Line 2992: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2993: तस्माच्च गिरिकूटाग्रात्प्रच्युताः पुष्पवृष्टयः |` | "From the peak of that mountain, showers of flowers fell," |
| `Line 2994: सुरासुरगणान्माल्यैः सर्वतः समवाकिरन् ||१७||` | "Covering the hosts of gods and Asuras with garlands from all sides. ||17||" |
| `Line 2995: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2996: बभूवात्र महाघोषो महामेघरवोपमः |` | "There arose a great sound resembling the rumbling of mighty clouds," |
| `Line 2997: उदधेर्मथ्यमानस्य मन्दरेण सुरासुरैः ||१८||` | "As the ocean was being churned by Mount Mandara by the gods and Asuras. ||18||" |
| `Line 2998: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 2999: तत्र नानाजलचरा विनिष्पिष्टा महाद्रिणा |` | "There, various aquatic creatures, crushed by the great mountain," |
| `Line 3000: विलयं समुपाजग्मुः शतशो लवणाम्भसि ||१९||` | "Met their destruction by the hundreds in the salty waters. ||19||" |
| `Line 3001: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3002: वारुणानि च भूतानि विविधानि महीधरः |` | "And the mountain [Mandara] destroyed various aquatic creatures [of Varuna]" |
| `Line 3003: पातालतलवासीनि विलयं समुपानयत् ||२०||` | "And those dwelling in the depths of Patala [netherworld] were brought to destruction. ||20||" |
| `Line 3004: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3005: तस्मिंश्च भ्राम्यमाणेऽद्रौ सङ्घृष्यन्तः परस्परम् |` | "And as that mountain was being rotated, rubbing against each other," |
| `Line 3006: न्यपतन्पतगोपेताः पर्वताग्रान्महाद्रुमाः ||२१||` | "Great trees with birds fell from the mountain peaks. ||21||" |
| `Line 3007: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3008: तेषां सङ्घर्षजश्चाग्निरर्चिर्भिः प्रज्वलन्मुहुः |` | "And the fire born from their friction, repeatedly blazing with flames," |
| `Line 3009: विद्युद्भिरिव नीलाभ्रमावृणोन्मन्दरं गिरिम् ||२२||` | "Enveloped Mount Mandara like lightning in dark clouds. ||22||" |
| `Line 3010: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3011: ददाह कुञ्जरांश्चैव सिंहांश्चैव विनिःसृतान् |` | "It burned the elephants and lions that had fled," |
| `Line 3012: विगतासूनि सर्वाणि सत्त्वानि विविधानि च ||२३||` | "And various other creatures were deprived of their lives. ||23||" |
| `Line 3013: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3014: तमग्निममरश्रेष्ठः प्रदहन्तं ततस्ततः |` | "That fire which was burning everywhere, the best of immortals [Indra]" |
| `Line 3015: वारिणा मेघजेनेन्द्रः शमयामास सर्वतः ||२४||` | "Indra extinguished completely with water produced from clouds. ||24||" |
| `Line 3016: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3017: ततो नानाविधास्तत्र सुस्रुवुः सागराम्भसि |` | "Then various kinds flowed there into the ocean waters," |
| `Line 3018: महाद्रुमाणां निर्यासा बहवश्चौषधीरसाः ||२५||` | "The sap of great trees and many juices of medicinal herbs. ||25||" |
| `Line 3019: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3020: तेषाममृतवीर्याणां रसानां पयसैव च |` | "From these juices with immortal potency and with the milk [of ocean]," |
| `Line 3021: अमरत्वं सुरा जग्मुः काञ्चनस्य च निःस्रवात् ||२६||` | "The gods attained immortality, and from the flow of gold. ||26||" |
| `Line 3022: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3023: अथ तस्य समुद्रस्य तज्जातमुदकं पयः |` | "Then the water of that ocean became milk," |
| `Line 3024: रसोत्तमैर्विमिश्रं च ततः क्षीरादभूद्घृतम् ||२७||` | "Mixed with the finest essences, and from that milk arose ghee [clarified butter]. ||27||" |
| `Line 3025: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3026: ततो ब्रह्माणमासीनं देवा वरदमब्रुवन् |` | "Then the gods addressed Brahmā [creator deity] who was seated, the bestower of boons:" |
| `Line 3027: श्रान्ताः स्म सुभृशं ब्रह्मन्नोद्भवत्यमृतं च तत् ||२८||` | "We are extremely exhausted, O Brahman, and that amṛta [immortality nectar] does not arise. ||28||" |
| `Line 3028: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3029: ऋते नारायणं देवं दैत्या नागोत्तमास्तथा |` | "Except for the god Nārāyaṇa [Vishnu], the daityas [demons] and the foremost nāgas [serpents] as well," |
| `Line 3030: चिरारब्धमिदं चापि सागरस्यापि मन्थनम् ||२९||` | "And this churning of the ocean has been going on for a long time. ||29||" |
| `Line 3031: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3032: ततो नारायणं देवं ब्रह्मा वचनमब्रवीत् |` | "Then Brahmā spoke these words to the god Nārāyaṇa [Vishnu]:" |
| `Line 3033: विधत्स्वैषां बलं विष्णो भवानत्र परायणम् ||३०||` | "Grant them strength, O Viṣṇu, you are the ultimate refuge here. ||30||" |
| `Line 3034: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3035: विष्णुरुवाच||` | "Viṣṇu [preserver deity] said:" |
| `Line 3036: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3037: बलं ददामि सर्वेषां कर्मैतद्ये समास्थिताः |` | "I give strength to all who are engaged in this task." |
| `Line 3038: क्षोभ्यतां कलशः सर्वैर्मन्दरः परिवर्त्यताम् ||३१||` | "Let the ocean be churned by all, let Mandara [churning mountain] be rotated. ||31||" |
| `Line 3039: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3040: सूत उवाच||` | "Sūta [bard-narrator] said:" |
| `Line 3041: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3042: नारायणवचः श्रुत्वा बलिनस्ते महोदधेः |` | "Hearing Nārāyaṇa's words, those mighty ones of the great ocean," |
| `Line 3043: तत्पयः सहिता भूयश्चक्रिरे भृशमाकुलम् ||३२||` | "Together, they again made its waters extremely agitated. ||32||" |
| `Line 3044: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3045: ततः शतसहस्रांशुः समान इव सागरात् |` | "Then, like the thousand-rayed one [sun], from the ocean," |
| `Line 3046: प्रसन्नभाः समुत्पन्नः सोमः शीतांशुरुज्ज्वलः ||३३||` | "Arose the serene-rayed Soma [moon], the cool-rayed one, brilliant. ||33||" |
| `Line 3047: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3048: श्रीरनन्तरमुत्पन्ना घृतात्पाण्डुरवासिनी |` | "Śrī [goddess of fortune] arose next, clad in white, from the ghee [clarified butter]," |
| `Line 3049: सुरा देवी समुत्पन्ना तुरगः पाण्डुरस्तथा ||३४||` | "The goddess Surā [wine deity] arose, and likewise the white horse [Uccaiḥśravas]. ||34||" |
| `Line 3050: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3051: कौस्तुभश्च मणिर्दिव्य उत्पन्नोऽमृतसम्भवः |` | "And the divine Kaustubha [celestial gem] arose, born from the churning for amṛta [immortality nectar]," |
| `Line 3052: मरीचिविकचः श्रीमान्नारायण उरोगतः ||३५||` | "Radiant with light rays, the glorious gem adorned the chest of Nārāyaṇa [Vishnu]. ||35||" |
| `Line 3053: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3054: श्रीः सुरा चैव सोमश्च तुरगश्च मनोजवः |` | "Śrī [goddess of fortune], Surā [goddess of wine], Soma [moon god], and the swift-minded horse [Uccaiḥśravas]," |
| `Line 3055: यतो देवास्ततो जग्मुरादित्यपथमाश्रिताः ||३६||` | "Went in the same direction as the gods, taking refuge in the path of Āditya [sun]. ||36||" |
| `Line 3056: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3057: धन्वन्तरिस्ततो देवो वपुष्मानुदतिष्ठत |` | "Then arose the handsome god Dhanvantari [divine physician]," |
| `Line 3058: श्वेतं कमण्डलुं बिभ्रदमृतं यत्र तिष्ठति ||३७||` | "Holding a white kamaṇḍalu [water vessel] in which the amṛta [immortality nectar] was contained. ||37||" |
| `Line 3059: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3060: एतदत्यद्भुतं दृष्ट्वा दानवानां समुत्थितः |` | "Seeing this great wonder, there arose among the Dānavas [demons]," |
| `Line 3061: अमृतार्थे महान्नादो ममेदमिति जल्पताम् ||३८||` | "A great clamor for the amṛta [immortality nectar], as they shouted, 'This is mine!' ||38||" |
| `Line 3062: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3063: ततो नारायणो मायामास्थितो मोहिनीं प्रभुः |` | "Then Nārāyaṇa [Vishnu], the lord, resorted to māyā [divine illusion] in the form of Mohinī [enchantress]," |
| `Line 3064: स्त्रीरूपमद्भुतं कृत्वा दानवानभिसंश्रितः ||३९||` | "Taking a wondrous female form, he approached the Dānavas [demons]. ||39||" |
| `Line 3065: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3066: ततस्तदमृतं तस्यै ददुस्ते मूढचेतसः |` | "Then those bewildered-minded ones gave the amṛta [immortality nectar] to her," |
| `Line 3067: स्त्रियै दानवदैतेयाः सर्वे तद्गतमानसाः ||४०||` | "All the Dānava-Daityas [demon clans], their minds captivated by that woman. ||40||" |
| `Line 3068: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3069: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3070: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3071: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3072: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3073: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3074: १७` | "17" [chapter number] |
| `Line 3075: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3076: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3077: सूत उवाच||` | "Suta [bard narrator] said:" |
| `Line 3078: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3079: अथावरणमुख्यानि नानाप्रहरणानि च |` | "Then, taking up their principal shields and various weapons," |
| `Line 3080: प्रगृह्याभ्यद्रवन्देवान्सहिता दैत्यदानवाः ||१||` | "The united Daityas and Danavas [demon clans] rushed against the gods. ||1||" |
| `Line 3081: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3082: ततस्तदमृतं देवो विष्णुरादाय वीर्यवान् |` | "Then the mighty god Vishnu [preserver deity], taking that amrita [immortality nectar]," |
| `Line 3083: जहार दानवेन्द्रेभ्यो नरेण सहितः प्रभुः ||२||` | "The lord, accompanied by Nara [divine sage], stole it away from the Danava lords. ||2||" |
| `Line 3084: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3085: ततो देवगणाः सर्वे पपुस्तदमृतं तदा |` | "Then all the hosts of gods drank that amrita," |
| `Line 3086: विष्णोः सकाशात्सम्प्राप्य सम्भ्रमे तुमुले सति ||३||` | "Having received it from Vishnu, while there was tumultuous confusion. ||3||" |
| `Line 3087: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3088: ततः पिबत्सु तत्कालं देवेष्वमृतमीप्सितम् |` | "Then, while the gods were drinking that desired amrita at that time," |
| `Line 3089: राहुर्विबुधरूपेण दानवः प्रापिबत्तदा ||४||` | "Rahu [eclipse demon], a Danava in the form of a god, also drank it then. ||4||" |
| `Line 3090: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3091: तस्य कण्ठमनुप्राप्ते दानवस्यामृते तदा |` | "When the amrita had reached the throat of that Danava," |
| `Line 3092: आख्यातं चन्द्रसूर्याभ्यां सुराणां हितकाम्यया ||५||` | "It was reported by the Sun and Moon [celestial bodies], out of desire for the gods' welfare. ||5||" |
| `Line 3093: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3094: ततो भगवता तस्य शिरश्छिन्नमलङ्कृतम् |` | "Then the Lord cut off his adorned head," |
| `Line 3095: चक्रायुधेन चक्रेण पिबतोऽमृतमोजसा ||६||` | "With his discus weapon, as he was forcefully drinking the amrita. ||6||" |
| `Line 3096: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3097: तच्छैलशृङ्गप्रतिमं दानवस्य शिरो महत् |` | "That great head of the Danava, resembling a mountain peak," |
| `Line 3098: चक्रेणोत्कृत्तमपतच्चालयद्वसुधातलम् ||७||` | "Severed by the discus, fell down and shook the surface of the earth. ||7||" |
| `Line 3099: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3100: ततो वैरविनिर्बन्धः कृतो राहुमुखेन वै |` | "Then a perpetual enmity was established by Rahu's head [severed head]," |
| `Line 3101: शाश्वतश्चन्द्रसूर्याभ्यां ग्रसत्यद्यापि चैव तौ ||८||` | "Eternal [Rahu], even today, continues to devour both the moon and sun. ||8||" |
| `Line 3102: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3103: विहाय भगवांश्चापि स्त्रीरूपमतुलं हरिः |` | "And the Lord Hari [Vishnu] abandoned his incomparable female form," |
| `Line 3104: नानाप्रहरणैर्भीमैर्दानवान्समकम्पयत् ||९||` | "And made the demons tremble with various terrifying weapons. ||9||" |
| `Line 3105: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3106: ततः प्रवृत्तः सङ्ग्रामः समीपे लवणाम्भसः |` | "Then commenced a battle near the salt waters [ocean]," |
| `Line 3107: सुराणामसुराणां च सर्वघोरतरो महान् ||१०||` | "A great and most terrible conflict between the gods and demons. ||10||" |
| `Line 3108: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3109: प्रासाः सुविपुलास्तीक्ष्णा न्यपतन्त सहस्रशः |` | "Thousands of large, sharp javelins [prasas] fell," |
| `Line 3110: तोमराश्च सुतीक्ष्णाग्राः शस्त्राणि विविधानि च ||११||` | "And lances [tomaras] with very sharp points, and various other weapons. ||11||" |
| `Line 3111: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3112: ततोऽसुराश्चक्रभिन्ना वमन्तो रुधिरं बहु |` | "Then the demons, pierced by the discus [chakra], vomiting much blood," |
| `Line 3113: असिशक्तिगदारुग्णा निपेतुर्धरणीतले ||१२||` | "Broken by swords, spears, and maces, fell upon the earth. ||12||" |
| `Line 3114: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3115: छिन्नानि पट्टिशैश्चापि शिरांसि युधि दारुणे |` | "Heads severed by spears [pattishas] in the terrible battle," |
| `Line 3116: तप्तकाञ्चनजालानि निपेतुरनिशं तदा ||१३||` | "Adorned with heated golden ornaments, fell continuously then. ||13||" |
| `Line 3117: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3118: रुधिरेणावलिप्ताङ्गा निहताश्च महासुराः |` | "And the great demons, their bodies smeared with blood, slain," |
| `Line 3119: अद्रीणामिव कूटानि धातुरक्तानि शेरते ||१४||` | "Lay like mountain peaks reddened with mineral deposits. ||14||" |
| `Line 3120: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3121: हाहाकारः समभवत्तत्र तत्र सहस्रशः |` | "Cries of distress arose here and there by the thousands," |
| `Line 3122: अन्योन्यं छिन्दतां शस्त्रैरादित्ये लोहितायति ||१५||` | "As they cut each other with weapons while the sun [Aditya] turned red. ||15||" |
| `Line 3123: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3124: परिघैश्चायसैः पीतैः संनिकर्षे च मुष्टिभिः |` | "With iron clubs [parighas] gleaming yellow, and in close combat with fists," |
| `Line 3125: निघ्नतां समरेऽन्योन्यं शब्दो दिवमिवास्पृशत् ||१६||` | "The sound of them striking each other in battle seemed to touch the heavens. ||16||" |
| `Line 3126: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3127: छिन्धि भिन्धि प्रधावध्वं पातयाभिसरेति च |` | "Cut, split, charge forward, strike down, attack! - such" |
| `Line 3128: व्यश्रूयन्त महाघोराः शब्दास्तत्र समन्ततः ||१७||` | "Terrifying shouts were heard there from all directions. ||17||" |
| `Line 3129: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3130: एवं सुतुमुले युद्धे वर्तमाने भयावहे |` | "While this tumultuous and frightening battle was raging," |
| `Line 3131: नरनारायणौ देवौ समाजग्मतुराहवम् ||१८||` | "The divine Nara and Narayana [sage-deities] arrived at the battlefield. ||18||" |
| `Line 3132: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3133: तत्र दिव्यं धनुर्दृष्ट्वा नरस्य भगवानपि |` | "There, seeing the divine bow of Nara, the Lord [Vishnu] himself" |
| `Line 3134: चिन्तयामास वै चक्रं विष्णुर्दानवसूदनम् ||१९||` | "Vishnu, the destroyer of demons, thought of his discus [chakra]. ||19||" |
| `Line 3135: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3136: ततोऽम्बराच्चिन्तितमात्रमागतं; महाप्रभं चक्रममित्रतापनम् |` | "Then, merely by thinking of it, from the sky came the brilliant discus, the tormentor of enemies," |
| `Line 3137: विभावसोस्तुल्यमकुण्ठमण्डलं; सुदर्शनं भीममजय्यमुत्तमम् ||२०||` | "Equal to fire in brilliance, with unblunted rim, the Sudarshana [divine discus], fearsome, invincible, supreme. ||20||" |
| `Line 3138: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3139: तदागतं ज्वलितहुताशनप्रभं; भयङ्करं करिकरबाहुरच्युतः |` | "That arrived, blazing like sacrificial fire, terrifying; Achyuta [Vishnu], with arms like elephant trunks," |
| `Line 3140: मुमोच वै चपलमुदग्रवेगव; न्महाप्रभं परनगरावदारणम् ||२१||` | "Released the swift, tremendously forceful, brilliantly shining, destroyer of enemy cities. ||21||" |
| `Line 3141: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3142: तदन्तकज्वलनसमानवर्चसं; पुनः पुनर्न्यपतत वेगवत्तदा |` | "That discus, with splendor equal to the fire of destruction, fell again and again with great speed," |
| `Line 3143: विदारयद्दितिदनुजान्सहस्रशः; करेरितं पुरुषवरेण संयुगे ||२२||` | "Tearing apart thousands of Diti's and Danu's sons [demons], hurled by the hand of the Supreme Person in battle. ||22||" |
| `Line 3144: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3145: दहत्क्वचिज्ज्वलन इवावलेलिह; त्प्रसह्य तानसुरगणान्न्यकृन्तत |` | "Sometimes burning like fire, licking up, forcibly cutting down those hosts of asuras," |
| `Line 3146: प्रवेरितं वियति मुहुः क्षितौ तदा; पपौ रणे रुधिरमथो पिशाचवत् ||२३||` | "Propelled repeatedly through the sky and earth, it then drank blood in battle like a pishacha [flesh-eating demon]. ||23||" |
| `Line 3147: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3148: अथासुरा गिरिभिरदीनचेतसो; मुहुर्मुहुः सुरगणमर्दयंस्तदा |` | "Then the undaunted asuras, with mountains, repeatedly crushed the hosts of gods," |
| `Line 3149: महाबला विगलितमेघवर्चसः; सहस्रशो गगनमभिप्रपद्य ह ||२४||` | "The mighty ones, with splendor like dispersed clouds, thousands of them, ascending to the sky indeed. ||24||" |
| `Line 3150: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3151: अथाम्बराद्भयजननाः प्रपेदिरे; सपादपा बहुविधमेघरूपिणः |` | "Then from the sky, fear-inducing, many-formed clouds with trees fell down;" |
| `Line 3152: महाद्रयः प्रविगलिताग्रसानवः; परस्परं द्रुतमभिहत्य सस्वनाः ||२५||` | "Great mountains with their peaks and summits crumbling, quickly struck against each other with loud noise. ||25||" |
| `Line 3153: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3154: ततो मही प्रविचलिता सकानना; महाद्रिपाताभिहता समन्ततः |` | "Then the earth with its forests trembled, struck all around by the falling of great mountains;" |
| `Line 3155: परस्परं भृशमभिगर्जतां मुहू; रणाजिरे भृशमभिसम्प्रवर्तिते ||२६||` | "As they repeatedly roared fiercely at each other, while the battlefield intensely raged on. ||26||" |
| `Line 3156: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3157: नरस्ततो वरकनकाग्रभूषणै; र्महेषुभिर्गगनपथं समावृणोत् |` | "Then Nara [Arjuna] covered the path of the sky with great arrows adorned with excellent golden tips;" |
| `Line 3158: विदारयन्गिरिशिखराणि पत्रिभि; र्महाभयेऽसुरगणविग्रहे तदा ||२७||` | "Splitting mountain peaks with feathered arrows, during that great terrifying battle with the hosts of asuras [demons]. ||27||" |
| `Line 3159: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3160: ततो महीं लवणजलं च सागरं; महासुराः प्रविविशुरर्दिताः सुरैः |` | "Then the great asuras [demons], tormented by the gods, entered the earth, the salt waters, and the ocean;" |
| `Line 3161: वियद्गतं ज्वलितहुताशनप्रभं; सुदर्शनं परिकुपितं निशाम्य च ||२८||` | "Having seen the Sudarśana [divine discus] in the sky, blazing with the radiance of fire, greatly enraged. ||28||" |
| `Line 3162: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3163: ततः सुरैर्विजयमवाप्य मन्दरः; स्वमेव देशं गमितः सुपूजितः |` | "Then, after the gods had achieved victory, Mandara [churning mountain], well-honored, was returned to its own place;" |
| `Line 3164: विनाद्य खं दिवमपि चैव सर्वश; स्ततो गताः सलिलधरा यथागतम् ||२९||` | "After resounding through the sky and heaven in all directions, then the clouds returned to where they had come from. ||29||" |
| `Line 3165: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3166: ततोऽमृतं सुनिहितमेव चक्रिरे; सुराः परां मुदमभिगम्य पुष्कलाम् |` | "Then the gods, having attained abundant supreme joy, secured the amṛta [immortality nectar];" |
| `Line 3167: ददौ च तं निधिममृतस्य रक्षितुं; किरीटिने बलभिदथामरैः सह ||३०||` | "And Balabhid [Indra] along with the immortals entrusted that treasure of amṛta to Kirīṭin [Arjuna, crown-wearer] to protect. ||30||" |
| `Line 3168: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3169: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3170: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3171: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3172: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3173: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3174: १८` | "18" |
| `Line 3175: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3176: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3177: सूत उवाच||` | "Sūta [bard-narrator] said:" |
| `Line 3178: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3179: एतत्ते सर्वमाख्यातममृतं मथितं यथा |` | "All this has been told to you about how the amṛta [immortality nectar] was churned," |
| `Line 3180: यत्र सोऽश्वः समुत्पन्नः श्रीमानतुलविक्रमः ||१||` | "During which that magnificent horse of incomparable prowess was produced. ||1||" |
| `Line 3181: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3182: यं निशाम्य तदा कद्रूर्विनतामिदमब्रवीत् |` | "Upon seeing that horse, Kadrū [serpent mother] then said this to Vinatā [bird mother]:" |
| `Line 3183: उच्चैःश्रवा नु किंवर्णो भद्रे जानीहि माचिरम् ||२||` | "What color is Uccaiḥśravas [divine horse]? Good lady, tell me without delay. ||2||" |
| `Line 3184: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3185: विनतोवाच||` | "Vinatā [bird mother] said:" |
| `Line 3186: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3187: श्वेत एवाश्वराजोऽयं किं वा त्वं मन्यसे शुभे |` | "This king of horses is indeed white. What do you think, auspicious one?" |
| `Line 3188: ब्रूहि वर्णं त्वमप्यस्य ततोऽत्र विपणावहे ||३||` | "Tell me what color you think it is, and then let us wager on it. ||3||" |
| `Line 3189: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3190: कद्रूरुवाच||` | "Kadrū [serpent mother] said:" |
| `Line 3191: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3192: कृष्णवालमहं मन्ये हयमेनं शुचिस्मिते |` | "I think this horse has a black tail, O pure-smiling one." |
| `Line 3193: एहि सार्धं मया दीव्य दासीभावाय भामिनि ||४||` | "Come, bet with me for servitude, O beautiful lady. ||4||" |
| `Line 3194: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3195: सूत उवाच||` | "Sūta [bard-narrator] said:" |
| `Line 3196: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3197: एवं ते समयं कृत्वा दासीभावाय वै मिथः |` | "Having thus made an agreement between themselves for servitude," |
| `Line 3198: जग्मतुः स्वगृहानेव श्वो द्रक्ष्याव इति स्म ह ||५||` | "They both went to their homes, saying, 'We shall see tomorrow.' ||5||" |
| `Line 3199: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3200: ततः पुत्रसहस्रं तु कद्रूर्जिह्मं चिकीर्षती |` | "Then Kadrū [serpent mother], wishing to act deceitfully, commanded her thousand sons," |
| `Line 3201: आज्ञापयामास तदा वाला भूत्वाञ्जनप्रभाः ||६||` | "She commanded them then to become dark-colored [like collyrium] serpents. ||6||" |
| `Line 3202: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3203: आविशध्वं हयं क्षिप्रं दासी न स्यामहं यथा |` | "Enter the horse quickly so that I may not become a slave," |
| `Line 3204: तद्वाक्यं नान्वपद्यन्त ताञ्शशाप भुजङ्गमान् ||७||` | "They did not comply with her words, so she cursed those serpents [snake offspring]. ||7||" |
| `Line 3205: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3206: सर्पसत्रे वर्तमाने पावको वः प्रधक्ष्यति |` | "During the serpent sacrifice [sarpasatra], the fire [Pavaka] will consume you," |
| `Line 3207: जनमेजयस्य राजर्षेः पाण्डवेयस्य धीमतः ||८||` | "At the ceremony of the wise royal sage Janamejaya, descendant of the Pandavas. ||8||" |
| `Line 3208: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3209: शापमेनं तु शुश्राव स्वयमेव पितामहः |` | "The Grandfather [Brahma] himself heard this curse," |
| `Line 3210: अतिक्रूरं समुद्दिष्टं कद्र्वा दैवादतीव हि ||९||` | "Extremely cruel, pronounced by Kadru, indeed by fate's design. ||9||" |
| `Line 3211: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3212: सार्धं देवगणैः सर्वैर्वाचं तामन्वमोदत |` | "Together with all the hosts of gods, he approved that pronouncement," |
| `Line 3213: बहुत्वं प्रेक्ष्य सर्पाणां प्रजानां हितकाम्यया ||१०||` | "Considering the multitude of serpents, for the welfare of the people. ||10||" |
| `Line 3214: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3215: तिग्मवीर्यविषा ह्येते दन्दशूका महाबलाः |` | "For these biters [snakes] are of potent venom and great strength," |
| `Line 3216: तेषां तीक्ष्णविषत्वाद्धि प्रजानां च हिताय वै ||११||` | "Due to their deadly poison, and for the welfare of the people indeed, ||11||" |
| `Line 3217: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3218: प्रादाद्विषहणीं विद्यां काश्यपाय महात्मने ||११||` | "He bestowed the knowledge of counteracting poison to the great-souled Kashyapa. ||11||" |
| `Line 3219: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3220: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3221: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3222: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3223: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3224: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3225: १९` | "19" |
| `Line 3226: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3227: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3228: सूत उवाच||` | "Suta [bard-narrator] said:" |
| `Line 3229: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3230: ततो रजन्यां व्युष्टायां प्रभात उदिते रवौ |` | "Then, when the night had passed and the sun [Ravi] had risen at dawn," |
| `Line 3231: कद्रूश्च विनता चैव भगिन्यौ ते तपोधन ||१||` | "Kadru and Vinata, those two sisters, O wealth of austerities [addressing the listener], ||1||" |
| `Line 3232: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3233: अमर्षिते सुसंरब्धे दास्ये कृतपणे तदा |` | "Enraged and highly agitated, having wagered servitude," |
| `Line 3234: जग्मतुस्तुरगं द्रष्टुमुच्छैःश्रवसमन्तिकात् ||२||` | "Went to see the horse Uchchaihshravas [celestial steed] from nearby. ||2||" |
| `Line 3235: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3236: ददृशाते तदा तत्र समुद्रं निधिमम्भसाम् |` | "Then they both saw there the ocean, the repository of waters," |
| `Line 3237: तिमिङ्गिलझषाकीर्णं मकरैरावृतं तथा ||३||` | "Filled with timingilas [whale-eaters], fish, and likewise covered with makaras [sea monsters]. ||3||" |
| `Line 3238: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3239: सत्त्वैश्च बहुसाहस्रैर्नानारूपैः समावृतम् |` | "Teeming with many thousands of creatures of various forms," |
| `Line 3240: उग्रैर्नित्यमनाधृष्यं कूर्मग्राहसमाकुलम् ||४||` | "Fierce, ever unapproachable, crowded with turtles and crocodiles. ||4||" |
| `Line 3241: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3242: आकरं सर्वरत्नानामालयं वरुणस्य च |` | "The source of all jewels and the abode of Varuna [ocean deity]," |
| `Line 3243: नागानामालयं रम्यमुत्तमं सरितां पतिम् ||५||` | "The beautiful dwelling of serpents [nagas], the supreme lord of rivers. ||5||" |
| `Line 3244: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3245: पातालज्वलनावासमसुराणां च बन्धनम् |` | "The home of the submarine fire [Vadavagni] and the prison of the demons [asuras]," |
| `Line 3246: भयङ्करं च सत्त्वानां पयसां निधिमर्णवम् ||६||` | "Terrifying to creatures, the ocean, the repository of waters. ||6||" |
| `Line 3247: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3248: शुभं दिव्यममर्त्यानाममृतस्याकरं परम् |` | "Auspicious, divine, belonging to immortals, the supreme source of nectar [amrita]," |
| `Line 3249: अप्रमेयमचिन्त्यं च सुपुण्यजलमद्भुतम् ||७||` | "Immeasurable, inconceivable, with most sacred waters, wondrous. ||7||" |
| `Line 3250: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3251: घोरं जलचरारावरौद्रं भैरवनिस्वनम् |` | "Terrible with the fierce roars of aquatic creatures, with fearsome sounds," |
| `Line 3252: गम्भीरावर्तकलिलं सर्वभूतभयङ्करम् ||८||` | "Filled with deep whirlpools, causing fear to all beings. ||8||" |
| `Line 3253: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3254: वेलादोलानिलचलं क्षोभोद्वेगसमुत्थितम् |` | "Moving with winds that swing the shoreline, arising with agitation and turbulence," |
| `Line 3255: वीचीहस्तैः प्रचलितैर्नृत्यन्तमिव सर्वशः ||९||` | "Seemingly dancing everywhere with the moving hands of waves. ||9||" |
| `Line 3256: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3257: चन्द्रवृद्धिक्षयवशादुद्वृत्तोर्मिदुरासदम् |` | "With swollen waves difficult to approach due to the moon's waxing and waning," |
| `Line 3258: पाञ्चजन्यस्य जननं रत्नाकरमनुत्तमम् ||१०||` | "The birthplace of Pāñcajanya [Vishnu's conch], the unsurpassed treasury of jewels. ||10||" |
| `Line 3259: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3260: गां विन्दता भगवता गोविन्देनामितौजसा |` | "Stirred internally by the Lord Govinda [earth-finder] of immeasurable power," |
| `Line 3261: वराहरूपिणा चान्तर्विक्षोभितजलाविलम् ||११||` | "Who in the form of a boar [Varaha] made its waters turbid. ||11||" |
| `Line 3262: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3263: ब्रह्मर्षिणा च तपता वर्षाणां शतमत्रिणा |` | "And by the Brahmarishi [divine sage] Atri who performed austerities for a hundred years," |
| `Line 3264: अनासादितगाधं च पातालतलमव्ययम् ||१२||` | "With its unfathomable depths and imperishable netherworld floor. ||12||" |
| `Line 3265: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3266: अध्यात्मयोगनिद्रां च पद्मनाभस्य सेवतः |` | "Serving as the bed for the spiritual yoga-sleep of Padmanābha [lotus-naveled Vishnu]," |
| `Line 3267: युगादिकालशयनं विष्णोरमिततेजसः ||१३||` | "The resting place at the beginning of each age for Vishnu of immeasurable splendor. ||13||" |
| `Line 3268: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3269: वडवामुखदीप्ताग्नेस्तोयहव्यप्रदं शुभम् |` | "Auspiciously offering water oblations to the blazing fire of Vaḍavāmukha [submarine fire]," |
| `Line 3270: अगाधपारं विस्तीर्णमप्रमेयं सरित्पतिम् ||१४||` | "The lord of rivers, with unfathomable shores, vast and immeasurable. ||14||" |
| `Line 3271: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3272: महानदीभिर्बह्वीभिः स्पर्धयेव सहस्रशः |` | "As if being approached in rivalry by thousands of great rivers," |
| `Line 3273: अभिसार्यमाणमनिशं ददृशाते महार्णवम् ||१५||` | "They both beheld the great ocean being continuously approached. ||15||" |
| `Line 3274: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3275: गम्भीरं तिमिमकरोग्रसङ्कुलं तं; गर्जन्तं जलचररावरौद्रनादैः |` | "Deep, teeming with fierce whales and sea monsters, roaring with the terrible sounds of aquatic creatures;" |
| `Line 3276: विस्तीर्णं ददृशतुरम्बरप्रकाशं; तेऽगाधं निधिमुरुमम्भसामनन्तम् ||१६||` | "They both beheld it vast and sky-bright; that boundless, immense repository of endless waters. ||16||" |
| `Line 3277: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3278: इत्येवं झषमकरोर्मिसङ्कुलं तं; गम्भीरं विकसितमम्बरप्रकाशम् |` | "Thus, that ocean teeming with fish, sea monsters and waves; deep and expansive with sky-like radiance," |
| `Line 3279: पातालज्वलनशिखाविदीपितं तं; पश्यन्त्यौ द्रुतमभिपेततुस्तदानीम् ||१७||` | "Illuminated by the flames of the pātāla [netherworld] fire; seeing it, they both swiftly flew toward it then. ||17||" |
| `Line 3280: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3281: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3282: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3283: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3284: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3285: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3286: २०` | "20" |
| `Line 3287: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3288: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3289: सूत उवाच||` | "Sūta [bard-narrator] said:" |
| `Line 3290: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3291: तं समुद्रमतिक्रम्य कद्रूर्विनतया सह |` | "Having crossed that ocean, Kadrū [serpent mother] along with Vinatā [bird mother]," |
| `Line 3292: न्यपतत्तुरगाभ्याशे नचिरादिव शीघ्रगा ||१||` | "Descended near the horse very quickly, as if in no time at all, swift as they were. ||1||" |
| `Line 3293: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3294: निशाम्य च बहून्वालान्कृष्णान्पुच्छं समाश्रितान् |` | "And seeing many black hairs attached to the tail," |
| `Line 3295: विनतां विषण्णवदनां कद्रूर्दास्ये न्ययोजयत् ||२||` | "Kadrū made the dejected-faced Vinatā enter into servitude. ||2||" |
| `Line 3296: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3297: ततः सा विनता तस्मिन्पणितेन पराजिता |` | "Then Vinatā, defeated in that wager," |
| `Line 3298: अभवद्दुःखसन्तप्ता दासीभावं समास्थिता ||३||` | "Became afflicted with sorrow, having entered the state of servitude. ||3||" |
| `Line 3299: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3300: एतस्मिन्नन्तरे चैव गरुडः काल आगते |` | "And at this time, when the moment arrived, Garuḍa [divine eagle]" |
| `Line 3301: विना मात्रा महातेजा विदार्याण्डमजायत ||४||` | "Without his mother, the mighty one [Garuḍa] was born, breaking open the egg. ||4||" |
| `Line 3302: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3303: अग्निराशिरिवोद्भासन्समिद्धोऽतिभयङ्करः |` | "Shining like a mass of fire, blazing and terrifying," |
| `Line 3304: प्रवृद्धः सहसा पक्षी महाकायो नभोगतः ||५||` | "The bird suddenly grew enormous, with a massive body, soaring in the sky. ||5||" |
| `Line 3305: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3306: तं दृष्ट्वा शरणं जग्मुः प्रजाः सर्वा विभावसुम् |` | "Seeing him, all creatures sought refuge with Vibhāvasu [fire deity]," |
| `Line 3307: प्रणिपत्याब्रुवंश्चैनमासीनं विश्वरूपिणम् ||६||` | "And bowing down, they addressed him who was seated in his universal form. ||6||" |
| `Line 3308: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3309: अग्ने मा त्वं प्रवर्धिष्ठाः कच्चिन्नो न दिधक्षसि |` | "O Agni [fire god], do not grow so large! Do you not wish to burn us?" |
| `Line 3310: असौ हि राशिः सुमहान्समिद्धस्तव सर्पति ||७||` | "For that great blazing mass of yours is spreading. ||7||" |
| `Line 3311: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3312: अग्निरुवाच||` | "Agni [fire god] said:" |
| `Line 3313: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3314: नैतदेवं यथा यूयं मन्यध्वमसुरार्दनाः |` | "It is not as you think, O tormentors of asuras [demons]," |
| `Line 3315: गरुडो बलवानेष मम तुल्यः स्वतेजसा ||८||` | "This is the mighty Garuḍa [divine bird], equal to me in his splendor. ||8||" |
| `Line 3316: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3317: सूत उवाच||` | "Sūta [bard-narrator] said:" |
| `Line 3318: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3319: एवमुक्तास्ततो गत्वा गरुडं वाग्भिरस्तुवन् |` | "Thus addressed, they then went and praised Garuḍa with words," |
| `Line 3320: अदूरादभ्युपेत्यैनं देवाः सर्षिगणास्तदा ||९||` | "Approaching him from nearby, the gods along with the groups of sages. ||9||" |
| `Line 3321: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3322: त्वमृषिस्त्वं महाभागस्त्वं देवः पतगेश्वरः |` | "You are a sage, you are most fortunate, you are a god, the lord of birds," |
| `Line 3323: त्वं प्रभुस्तपनप्रख्यस्त्वं नस्त्राणमनुत्तमम् ||१०||` | "You are the master, radiant like the sun, you are our supreme protector. ||10||" |
| `Line 3324: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3325: बलोर्मिमान्साधुरदीनसत्त्वः; समृद्धिमान्दुष्प्रसहस्त्वमेव |` | "You are full of surging strength, virtuous, of undaunted spirit; prosperous and invincible you alone are," |
| `Line 3326: तपः श्रुतं सर्वमहीनकीर्ते; अनागतं चोपगतं च सर्वम् ||११||` | "Your austerity, learning, and unfailing fame; all that is yet to come and all that has already come to pass. ||11||" |
| `Line 3327: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3328: त्वमुत्तमः सर्वमिदं चराचरं; गभस्तिभिर्भानुरिवावभाससे |` | "You are supreme, illuminating all this world of moving and unmoving beings with your rays, like the sun [Bhanu]," |
| `Line 3329: समाक्षिपन्भानुमतः प्रभां मुहु; स्त्वमन्तकः सर्वमिदं ध्रुवाध्रुवम् ||१२||` | "Repeatedly eclipsing the radiance of the sun, you are the destroyer [Antaka] of all this, both permanent and impermanent. ||12||" |
| `Line 3330: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3331: दिवाकरः परिकुपितो यथा दहे; त्प्रजास्तथा दहसि हुताशनप्रभ |` | "As the sun [Divakara] when enraged burns the creatures, so do you burn them, O you who shine like fire [Hutashana]," |
| `Line 3332: भयङ्करः प्रलय इवाग्निरुत्थितो; विनाशयन्युगपरिवर्तनान्तकृत् ||१३||` | "Terrifying like the fire risen at dissolution [pralaya], destroying, bringing an end to the cycle of ages. ||13||" |
| `Line 3333: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3334: खगेश्वरं शरणमुपस्थिता वयं; महौजसं वितिमिरमभ्रगोचरम् |` | "We have come seeking refuge in the lord of birds [Khageshvara], of great splendor, dispeller of darkness, moving through the clouds," |
| `Line 3335: महाबलं गरुडमुपेत्य खेचरं; परावरं वरदमजय्यविक्रमम् ||१४||` | "Having approached the mighty Garuda, the sky-traveler, knower of high and low, bestower of boons, of unconquerable prowess. ||14||" |
| `Line 3336: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3337: एवं स्तुतः सुपर्णस्तु देवैः सर्षिगणैस्तदा |` | "Thus praised, Suparna [Garuda] by the gods along with the groups of sages then," |
| `Line 3338: तेजसः प्रतिसंहारमात्मनः स चकार ह ||१५||` | "Withdrew his own radiance indeed. ||15||" |
| `Line 3339: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3340: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3341: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3342: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3343: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3344: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3345: २१` | "21" |
| `Line 3346: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3347: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3348: सूत उवाच||` | "Suta [bard-narrator] said:" |
| `Line 3349: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3350: ततः कामगमः पक्षी महावीर्यो महाबलः |` | "Then that bird [Garuda] who could fly at will, of great valor and mighty strength," |
| `Line 3351: मातुरन्तिकमागच्छत्परं तीरं महोदधेः ||१||` | "He came to his mother on the far shore of the great ocean. ||1||" |
| `Line 3352: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3353: यत्र सा विनता तस्मिन्पणितेन पराजिता |` | "Where that Vinatā [bird mother], defeated in that wager," |
| `Line 3354: अतीव दुःखसन्तप्ता दासीभावमुपागता ||२||` | "Extremely afflicted with sorrow, had entered into the state of servitude. ||2||" |
| `Line 3355: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3356: ततः कदाचिद्विनतां प्रवणां पुत्रसंनिधौ |` | "Then once, when Vinatā was humbly present in her son's company," |
| `Line 3357: काल आहूय वचनं कद्रूरिदमभाषत ||३||` | "Kadrū [serpent mother], calling at the right time, spoke these words: ||3||" |
| `Line 3358: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3359: नागानामालयं भद्रे सुरम्यं रमणीयकम् |` | "To the beautiful abode of the nāgas [serpents], delightful and charming," |
| `Line 3360: समुद्रकुक्षावेकान्ते तत्र मां विनते वह ||४||` | "In a secluded place in the ocean's depths, there carry me, O Vinatā. ||4||" |
| `Line 3361: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3362: ततः सुपर्णमाता तामवहत्सर्पमातरम् |` | "Then the mother of Suparṇa [Garuḍa] carried that mother of serpents," |
| `Line 3363: पन्नगान्गरुडश्चापि मातुर्वचनचोदितः ||५||` | "And Garuḍa too carried the serpents, urged by his mother's words. ||5||" |
| `Line 3364: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3365: स सूर्यस्याभितो याति वैनतेयो विहङ्गमः |` | "That Vainateya [son of Vinatā], the bird, traveled close to the sun," |
| `Line 3366: सूर्यरश्मिपरीताश्च मूर्च्छिताः पन्नगाभवन् ||६||` | "And the serpents, surrounded by the sun's rays, became unconscious. ||6||" |
| `Line 3367: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3368: तदवस्थान्सुतान्दृष्ट्वा कद्रूः शक्रमथास्तुवत् ||६||` | "Seeing her sons in that condition, Kadrū then praised Śakra [Indra]. ||6||" |
| `Line 3369: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3370: नमस्ते देवदेवेश नमस्ते बलसूदन |` | "Salutations to you, lord of lords of gods, salutations to you, destroyer of Bala [demon]," |
| `Line 3371: नमुचिघ्न नमस्तेऽस्तु सहस्राक्ष शचीपते ||७||` | "Slayer of Namuci [demon], salutations be to you, thousand-eyed one, lord of Śacī [Indra's wife]. ||7||" |
| `Line 3372: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3373: सर्पाणां सूर्यतप्तानां वारिणा त्वं प्लवो भव |` | "For these serpents scorched by the sun, be you a rain-shower with water," |
| `Line 3374: त्वमेव परमं त्राणमस्माकममरोत्तम ||८||` | "You alone are our supreme protection, O best of immortals. ||8||" |
| `Line 3375: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3376: ईशो ह्यसि पयः स्रष्टुं त्वमनल्पं पुरंदर |` | "You are the lord capable of creating abundant waters, O Purandara [city-destroyer, Indra]," |
| `Line 3377: त्वमेव मेघस्त्वं वायुस्त्वमग्निर्वैद्युतोऽम्बरे ||९||` | "You alone are the cloud, you are the wind, you are the lightning fire in the sky. ||9||" |
| `Line 3378: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3379: त्वमभ्रघनविक्षेप्ता त्वामेवाहुः पुनर्घनम् |` | "You are the disperser of dense clouds, and they call you again the cloud itself," |
| `Line 3380: त्वं वज्रमतुलं घोरं घोषवांस्त्वं बलाहकः ||१०||` | "You are the incomparable terrible thunderbolt, you are the thundering rain cloud. ||10||" |
| `Line 3381: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3382: स्रष्टा त्वमेव लोकानां संहर्ता चापराजितः |` | "You alone are the creator of worlds and the unconquered destroyer," |
| `Line 3383: त्वं ज्योतिः सर्वभूतानां त्वमादित्यो विभावसुः ||११||` | "You are the light of all beings, you are Āditya [sun deity], the radiant one. ||11||" |
| `Line 3384: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3385: त्वं महद्भूतमाश्चर्यं त्वं राजा त्वं सुरोत्तमः |` | "You are the great wondrous being, you are the king, you are the foremost among gods," |
| `Line 3386: त्वं विष्णुस्त्वं सहस्राक्षस्त्वं देवस्त्वं परायणम् ||१२||` | "You are Viṣṇu [preserver deity], you are Sahasrākṣa [thousand-eyed one], you are the god, you are the supreme refuge. ||12||" |
| `Line 3387: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3388: त्वं सर्वममृतं देव त्वं सोमः परमार्चितः |` | "You are all immortality, O god, you are Soma [moon deity], the highly worshipped," |
| `Line 3389: त्वं मुहूर्तस्तिथिश्च त्वं लवस्त्वं वै पुनः क्षणः ||१३||` | "You are the muhūrta [time unit], the tithi [lunar day], you are the lava [time fraction], and indeed you are the kṣaṇa [moment]. ||13||" |
| `Line 3390: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3391: शुक्लस्त्वं बहुलश्चैव कला काष्ठा त्रुटिस्तथा |` | "You are the bright fortnight and the dark fortnight, the kalā [time unit], kāṣṭhā [time unit], and truṭi [time unit] as well," |
| `Line 3392: संवत्सरर्तवो मासा रजन्यश्च दिनानि च ||१४||` | "The years, seasons, months, nights, and days too. ||14||" |
| `Line 3393: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3394: त्वमुत्तमा सगिरिवना वसुन्धरा; सभास्करं वितिमिरमम्बरं तथा |` | "You are the excellent earth with its mountains and forests; and likewise the sky with its sun, free from darkness," |
| `Line 3395: महोदधिः सतिमितिमिङ्गिलस्तथा; महोर्मिमान्बहुमकरो झषालयः ||१५||` | "The great ocean with its timitimiṅgila [sea monsters], with mighty waves, many makaras [sea creatures], the abode of fish. ||15||" |
| `Line 3396: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3397: महद्यशस्त्वमिति सदाभिपूज्यसे; मनीषिभिर्मुदितमना महर्षिभिः |` | "You are of great fame, thus you are always worshipped by the wise and joyful-minded great sages," |
| `Line 3398: अभिष्टुतः पिबसि च सोममध्वरे; वषट्कृतान्यपि च हवींषि भूतये ||१६||` | "Being praised, you drink Soma [ritual drink] at the sacrifice, and also the oblations offered with the Vaṣaṭ [ritual exclamation] for prosperity. ||16||" |
| `Line 3399: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3400: त्वं विप्रैः सततमिहेज्यसे फलार्थं; वेदाङ्गेष्वतुलबलौघ गीयसे च |` | "You are constantly worshipped here by the brahmins for rewards; and you, of incomparable strength, are celebrated in the Vedāṅgas [auxiliary texts of Vedas]," |
| `Line 3401: त्वद्धेतोर्यजनपरायणा द्विजेन्द्रा; वेदाङ्गान्यभिगमयन्ति सर्ववेदैः ||१७||` | "For your sake, the foremost twice-born [Brahmins] devoted to sacrifices master the Vedāṅgas [Vedic auxiliaries] along with all the Vedas. ||17||" |
| `Line 3402: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3403: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3404: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3405: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3406: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3407: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3408: २२` | "22" |
| `Line 3409: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3410: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3411: सूत उवाच||` | "Sūta [bard-narrator] said:" |
| `Line 3412: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3413: एवं स्तुतस्तदा कद्र्वा भगवान्हरिवाहनः |` | "Thus praised by Kadrū [serpent mother], the divine one who carries Hari [Viṣṇu]," |
| `Line 3414: नीलजीमूतसङ्घातैर्व्योम सर्वं समावृणोत् ||१||` | "Covered the entire sky with masses of dark clouds. ||1||" |
| `Line 3415: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3416: ते मेघा मुमुचुस्तोयं प्रभूतं विद्युदुज्ज्वलाः |` | "Those clouds, brilliant with lightning, released abundant water," |
| `Line 3417: परस्परमिवात्यर्थं गर्जन्तः सततं दिवि ||२||` | "Thundering excessively, as if at one another, continuously in the sky. ||2||" |
| `Line 3418: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3419: सङ्घातितमिवाकाशं जलदैः सुमहाद्भुतैः |` | "The sky seemed compressed by those most wonderful clouds," |
| `Line 3420: सृजद्भिरतुलं तोयमजस्रं सुमहारवैः ||३||` | "Which poured incomparable water incessantly with tremendous sounds. ||3||" |
| `Line 3421: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3422: सम्प्रनृत्तमिवाकाशं धारोर्मिभिरनेकशः |` | "The sky seemed to dance with the numerous waves of raindrops," |
| `Line 3423: मेघस्तनितनिर्घोषमम्बरं समपद्यत ||४||` | "The firmament became filled with the roaring thunder of clouds. ||4||" |
| `Line 3424: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3425: नागानामुत्तमो हर्शस्तदा वर्षति वासवे |` | "Great joy came to the serpents when Vāsava [Indra] rained," |
| `Line 3426: आपूर्यत मही चापि सलिलेन समन्ततः ||५||` | "And the earth was filled with water on all sides. ||5||" |
| `Line 3427: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3428: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3429: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3430: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3431: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3432: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3433: २३` | "23 [chapter number]" |
| `Line 3434: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3435: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3436: सूत उवाच||` | "Sūta [bard-narrator] said:" |
| `Line 3437: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3438: सुपर्णेनोह्यमानास्ते जग्मुस्तं देशमाशु वै |` | "Carried by Suparṇa [Garuḍa], they quickly reached that place," |
| `Line 3439: सागराम्बुपरिक्षिप्तं पक्षिसङ्घनिनादितम् ||१||` | "Surrounded by ocean waters, resonating with flocks of birds. ||1||" |
| `Line 3440: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3441: विचित्रफलपुष्पाभिर्वनराजिभिरावृतम् |` | "Covered with rows of forests filled with various fruits and flowers," |
| `Line 3442: भवनैरावृतं रम्यैस्तथा पद्माकरैरपि ||२||` | "Surrounded by beautiful dwellings and also lotus ponds. ||2||" |
| `Line 3443: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3444: प्रसन्नसलिलैश्चापि ह्रदैश्चित्रैर्विभूषितम् |` | "Adorned with clear-watered and wonderful lakes," |
| `Line 3445: दिव्यगन्धवहैः पुण्यैर्मारुतैरुपवीजितम् ||३||` | "Fanned by sacred breezes carrying divine fragrances. ||3||" |
| `Line 3446: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3447: उपजिघ्रद्भिराकाशं वृक्षैर्मलयजैरपि |` | "With sandalwood [malayaja] trees that seemed to perfume the sky," |
| `Line 3448: शोभितं पुष्पवर्षाणि मुञ्चद्भिर्मारुतोद्धुतैः ||४||` | "Beautified by trees releasing showers of flowers stirred by the wind. ||4||" |
| `Line 3449: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3450: किरद्भिरिव तत्रस्थान्नागान्पुष्पाम्बुवृष्टिभिः |` | "As if sprinkling the nāgas [serpents] dwelling there with showers of flowers and water," |
| `Line 3451: मनःसंहर्षणं पुण्यं गन्धर्वाप्सरसां प्रियम् ||५||` | "Delighting to the mind, sacred, beloved by Gandharvas [celestial musicians] and Apsaras [heavenly nymphs]. ||5||" |
| `Line 3452: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3453: नानापक्षिरुतं रम्यं कद्रूपुत्रप्रहर्षणम् ||५||` | "Charming with the songs of various birds, bringing joy to the sons of Kadru [serpents]. ||5||" |
| `Line 3454: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3455: तत्ते वनं समासाद्य विजह्रुः पन्नगा मुदा |` | "Having reached that forest, the serpents [pannagas] roamed about with joy," |
| `Line 3456: अब्रुवंश्च महावीर्यं सुपर्णं पतगोत्तमम् ||६||` | "And they spoke to the mighty Suparna [Garuda], the foremost among birds. ||6||" |
| `Line 3457: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3458: वहास्मानपरं द्वीपं सुरम्यं विपुलोदकम् |` | "Carry us to another island, beautiful and with abundant waters," |
| `Line 3459: त्वं हि देशान्बहून्रम्यान्पतन्पश्यसि खेचर ||७||` | "For you, O sky-traveler [Khechara], flying, see many beautiful lands. ||7||" |
| `Line 3460: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3461: स विचिन्त्याब्रवीत्पक्षी मातरं विनतां तदा |` | "After reflecting, the bird then spoke to his mother Vinata," |
| `Line 3462: किं कारणं मया मातः कर्तव्यं सर्पभाषितम् ||८||` | "Why, mother, should I do what the serpents have asked? ||8||" |
| `Line 3463: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3464: विनतोवाच||` | "Vinata said:" |
| `Line 3465: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3466: दासीभूतास्म्यनार्याया भगिन्याः पतगोत्तम |` | "I have become a slave to my ignoble sister, O best of birds [Patagottama]," |
| `Line 3467: पणं वितथमास्थाय सर्पैरुपधिना कृतम् ||९||` | "Having accepted a false wager that was deceitfully arranged by the serpents. ||9||" |
| `Line 3468: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3469: सूत उवाच||` | "Suta [bard-narrator] said:" |
| `Line 3470: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3471: तस्मिंस्तु कथिते मात्रा कारणे गगनेचरः |` | "When that reason was explained by his mother, the sky-traveler [Gaganechara]," |
| `Line 3472: उवाच वचनं सर्पांस्तेन दुःखेन दुःखितः ||१०||` | "Spoke these words to the serpents, pained by her sorrow. ||10||" |
| `Line 3473: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3474: किमाहृत्य विदित्वा वा किं वा कृत्वेह पौरुषम् |` | "By bringing what, or knowing what, or by performing what heroic deed here," |
| `Line 3475: दास्याद्वो विप्रमुच्येयं सत्यं शंसत लेलिहाः ||११||` | "Might I free you from slavery? Tell me truly, O tongue-flickering ones [serpents]. ||11||" |
| `Line 3476: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3477: श्रुत्वा तमब्रुवन्सर्पा आहरामृतमोजसा |` | "Hearing him, the serpents said, 'Bring the amṛta [immortality nectar] by your prowess," |
| `Line 3478: ततो दास्याद्विप्रमोक्षो भविता तव खेचर ||१२||` | "Then, upon giving it, there will be release from servitude for you, O sky-traveler [Garuḍa].' ||12||" |
| `Line 3479: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3480: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3481: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3482: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3483: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3484: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3485: २४` | "24" |
| `Line 3486: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3487: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3488: सूत उवाच||` | "Sūta [bard-narrator] said:" |
| `Line 3489: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3490: इत्युक्तो गरुडः सर्पैस्ततो मातरमब्रवीत् |` | "Thus addressed by the serpents, Garuḍa [divine eagle] then said to his mother," |
| `Line 3491: गच्छाम्यमृतमाहर्तुं भक्ष्यमिच्छामि वेदितुम् ||१||` | "I will go to bring the amṛta [immortality nectar], but I wish to know what food I may eat. ||1||" |
| `Line 3492: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3493: विनतोवाच||` | "Vinatā [Garuḍa's mother] said:" |
| `Line 3494: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3495: समुद्रकुक्षावेकान्ते निषादालयमुत्तमम् |` | "In a secluded place in the ocean's belly is an excellent dwelling of Niṣādas [tribal hunters]," |
| `Line 3496: सहस्राणामनेकानां तान्भुक्त्वामृतमानय ||२||` | "Eat those many thousands (of Niṣādas) and bring the amṛta [immortality nectar]. ||2||" |
| `Line 3497: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3498: न तु ते ब्राह्मणं हन्तुं कार्या बुद्धिः कथञ्चन |` | "But you must never entertain the thought of killing a Brāhmaṇa [priest-scholar]," |
| `Line 3499: अवध्यः सर्वभूतानां ब्राह्मणो ह्यनलोपमः ||३||` | "For a Brāhmaṇa is inviolable to all beings, indeed comparable to fire [agni]. ||3||" |
| `Line 3500: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3501: अग्निरर्को विषं शस्त्रं विप्रो भवति कोपितः |` | "Fire, the sun, poison, weapons—a brāhmaṇa [twice-born priest] becomes these when angered." |
| `Line 3502: भूतानामग्रभुग्विप्रो वर्णश्रेष्ठः पिता गुरुः ||४||` | "The brāhmaṇa eats before all beings, is foremost among castes, and is like a father and teacher. ||4||" |
| `Line 3503: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3504: गरुड उवाच||` | "Garuḍa [divine eagle] said:" |
| `Line 3505: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3506: यथाहमभिजानीयां ब्राह्मणं लक्षणैः शुभैः |` | "How might I recognize a brāhmaṇa by his auspicious characteristics?" |
| `Line 3507: तन्मे कारणतो मातः पृच्छतो वक्तुमर्हसि ||५||` | "O Mother, you should tell me the reasons when I ask. ||5||" |
| `Line 3508: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3509: विनतोवाच||` | "Vinatā [Garuḍa's mother] said:" |
| `Line 3510: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3511: यस्ते कण्ठमनुप्राप्तो निगीर्णं बडिशं यथा |` | "He who, having reached your throat, would be like a swallowed hook," |
| `Line 3512: दहेदङ्गारवत्पुत्र तं विद्याद्बाह्मणर्षभम् ||६||` | "Burning like a coal, my son—know him to be a foremost brāhmaṇa. ||6||" |
| `Line 3513: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3514: सूत उवाच||` | "Sūta [bard-narrator] said:" |
| `Line 3515: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3516: प्रोवाच चैनं विनता पुत्रहार्दादिदं वचः |` | "Vinatā spoke these words to him out of affection for her son," |
| `Line 3517: जानन्त्यप्यतुलं वीर्यमाशीर्वादसमन्वितम् ||७||` | "Though knowing his matchless strength, she accompanied it with a blessing. ||7||" |
| `Line 3518: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3519: पक्षौ ते मारुतः पातु चन्द्रः पृष्ठं तु पुत्रक |` | "May the wind protect your wings, and the moon your back, my son," |
| `Line 3520: शिरस्तु पातु ते वह्निर्भास्करः सर्वमेव तु ||८||` | "May fire protect your head, and the sun protect your entire being. ||8||" |
| `Line 3521: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3522: अहं च ते सदा पुत्र शान्तिस्वस्तिपरायणा |` | "And I, my son, always devoted to your peace and well-being," |
| `Line 3523: अरिष्टं व्रज पन्थानं वत्स कार्यार्थसिद्धये ||९||` | "Go on a safe path, my child, for the accomplishment of your task. ||9||" |
| `Line 3524: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3525: ततः स मातुर्वचनं निशम्य; वितत्य पक्षौ नभ उत्पपात |` | "Then, having heard his mother's words, he spread his wings and flew up into the sky." |
| `Line 3526: ततो निषादान्बलवानुपागम; द्बुभुक्षितः काल इवान्तको महान् ||१०||` | "Then the mighty one approached the Niṣādas [tribal hunters], hungry like the great Antaka [death god] at the time of dissolution. ||10||" |
| `Line 3527: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3528: स तान्निषादानुपसंहरंस्तदा; रजः समुद्धूय नभःस्पृशं महत् |` | "He then gathered those Niṣādas, raising a great dust cloud touching the sky," |
| `Line 3529: समुद्रकुक्षौ च विशोषयन्पयः; समीपगान्भूमिधरान्विचालयन् ||११||` | "Drying up the waters in the ocean's belly and shaking the nearby mountains. ||11||" |
| `Line 3530: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3531: ततः स चक्रे महदाननं तदा; निषादमार्गं प्रतिरुध्य पक्षिराट् |` | "Then the king of birds [Garuḍa] made a great opening of his mouth, blocking the path of the Niṣādas," |
| `Line 3532: ततो निषादास्त्वरिताः प्रवव्रजु; र्यतो मुखं तस्य भुजङ्गभोजिनः ||१२||` | "Then the Niṣādas hurriedly rushed toward the mouth of that serpent-eater. ||12||" |
| `Line 3533: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3534: तदाननं विवृतमतिप्रमाणव; त्समभ्ययुर्गगनमिवार्दिताः खगाः |` | "They entered that wide-open mouth of immense proportion, like distressed birds entering the sky," |
| `Line 3535: सहस्रशः पवनरजोभ्रमोहिता; महानिलप्रचलितपादपे वने ||१३||` | "By thousands, confused by the wind-blown dust, in a forest where trees were shaken by the great wind. ||13||" |
| `Line 3536: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3537: ततः खगो वदनममित्रतापनः; समाहरत्परिचपलो महाबलः |` | "Then the bird [Garuḍa], tormentor of enemies, very swift and mighty, closed his mouth," |
| `Line 3538: निषूदयन्बहुविधमत्स्यभक्षिणो; बुभुक्षितो गगनचरेश्वरस्तदा ||१४||` | "Destroying those various fish-eaters, as the hungry lord of sky-travelers [Garuḍa] then did. ||14||" |
| `Line 3539: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3540: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3541: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3542: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3543: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3544: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3545: २५` | "25 [chapter number]" |
| `Line 3546: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3547: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3548: सूत उवाच||` | "Sūta [bard-narrator] said:" |
| `Line 3549: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3550: तस्य कण्ठमनुप्राप्तो ब्राह्मणः सह भार्यया |` | "A Brāhmaṇa [priest] with his wife reached his throat," |
| `Line 3551: दहन्दीप्त इवाङ्गारस्तमुवाचान्तरिक्षगः ||१||` | "Burning brightly like a coal, the sky-traveler [Garuḍa] said to him: ||1||" |
| `Line 3552: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3553: द्विजोत्तम विनिर्गच्छ तूर्णमास्यादपावृतात् |` | "O best of twice-born [Brahmin], quickly exit from this opened mouth." |
| `Line 3554: न हि मे ब्राह्मणो वध्यः पापेष्वपि रतः सदा ||२||` | "For a Brahmin is not to be killed by me, even if he is always engaged in sins. ||2||" |
| `Line 3555: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3556: ब्रुवाणमेवं गरुडं ब्राह्मणः समभाषत |` | "To Garuḍa speaking thus, the Brahmin replied:" |
| `Line 3557: निषादी मम भार्येयं निर्गच्छतु मया सह ||३||` | "This Niṣādī [tribal woman] is my wife; let her come out with me. ||3||" |
| `Line 3558: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3559: गरुड उवाच||` | "Garuḍa said:" |
| `Line 3560: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3561: एतामपि निषादीं त्वं परिगृह्याशु निष्पत |` | "Taking this Niṣādī woman also, quickly come out." |
| `Line 3562: तूर्णं सम्भावयात्मानमजीर्णं मम तेजसा ||४||` | "Quickly save yourself undigested from my fiery energy. ||4||" |
| `Line 3563: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3564: सूत उवाच||` | "Sūta [bard-narrator] said:" |
| `Line 3565: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3566: ततः स विप्रो निष्क्रान्तो निषादीसहितस्तदा |` | "Then that Brahmin came out together with the Niṣādī woman." |
| `Line 3567: वर्धयित्वा च गरुडमिष्टं देशं जगाम ह ||५||` | "And after blessing Garuḍa, he went to his desired place. ||5||" |
| `Line 3568: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3569: सहभार्ये विनिष्क्रान्ते तस्मिन्विप्रे स पक्षिराट् |` | "When that Brahmin had exited with his wife, the king of birds [Garuḍa]" |
| `Line 3570: वितत्य पक्षावाकाशमुत्पपात मनोजवः ||६||` | "Spread his wings to the sky and flew up with the speed of mind. ||6||" |
| `Line 3571: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3572: ततोऽपश्यत्स पितरं पृष्टश्चाख्यातवान्पितुः |` | "Then he saw his father and, being asked, told his father:" |
| `Line 3573: अहं हि सर्पैः प्रहितः सोममाहर्तुमुद्यतः ||७||` | "I have been sent by the serpents and am prepared to bring the Soma [divine elixir]. ||7||" |
| `Line 3574: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3575: मातुर्दास्यविमोक्षार्थमाहरिष्ये तमद्य वै ||७||` | "To free my mother from servitude, I shall bring it today indeed. ||7||" |
| `Line 3576: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3577: मात्रा चास्मि समादिष्टो निषादान्भक्षयेति वै |` | "And I was instructed by my mother to devour the Nishadas [tribal people]," |
| `Line 3578: न च मे तृप्तिरभवद्भक्षयित्वा सहस्रशः ||८||` | "But I did not feel satisfied even after devouring thousands of them. ||8||" |
| `Line 3579: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3580: तस्माद्भोक्तव्यमपरं भगवन्प्रदिशस्व मे |` | "Therefore, O Lord [Bhagavan], direct me to something else I should eat," |
| `Line 3581: यद्भुक्त्वामृतमाहर्तुं समर्थः स्यामहं प्रभो ||९||` | "By eating which I might become capable of bringing back the amrita [nectar of immortality], O Master. ||9||" |
| `Line 3582: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3583: कश्यप उवाच||` | "Kashyapa said:" |
| `Line 3584: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3585: आसीद्विभावसुर्नाम महर्षिः कोपनो भृशम् |` | "There was a great sage [maharshi] named Vibhavasu, extremely prone to anger," |
| `Line 3586: भ्राता तस्यानुजश्चासीत्सुप्रतीको महातपाः ||१०||` | "And he had a younger brother named Supratika, of great austerity [mahatapas]. ||10||" |
| `Line 3587: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3588: स नेच्छति धनं भ्रात्रा सहैकस्थं महामुनिः |` | "That great sage [mahamuni] did not wish to keep his wealth together with his brother," |
| `Line 3589: विभागं कीर्तयत्येव सुप्रतीकोऽथ नित्यशः ||११||` | "And Supratika constantly spoke about division (of property). ||11||" |
| `Line 3590: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3591: अथाब्रवीच्च तं भ्राता सुप्रतीकं विभावसुः |` | "Then his brother Vibhavasu said to Supratika," |
| `Line 3592: विभागं बहवो मोहात्कर्तुमिच्छन्ति नित्यदा ||१२||` | "Many, out of delusion, always desire to make divisions. ||12||" |
| `Line 3593: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3594: ततो विभक्ता अन्योन्यं नाद्रियन्तेऽर्थमोहिताः ||१२||` | "Then, once divided, they disregard each other, deluded by wealth. ||12||" |
| `Line 3595: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3596: ततः स्वार्थपरान्मूढान्पृथग्भूतान्स्वकैर्धनैः |` | "Then, those who are selfish fools, separated with their own wealth," |
| `Line 3597: विदित्वा भेदयन्त्येतानमित्रा मित्ररूपिणः ||१३||` | "Are divided by enemies disguised as friends who recognize their vulnerability. ||13||" |
| `Line 3598: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3599: विदित्वा चापरे भिन्नानन्तरेषु पतन्त्यथ |` | "And others, knowing them to be divided, attack them in their weakness," |
| `Line 3600: भिन्नानामतुलो नाशः क्षिप्रमेव प्रवर्तते ||१४||` | "For those who are divided, unparalleled destruction quickly follows. ||14||" |
| `Line 3601: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3602: तस्माच्चैव विभागार्थं न प्रशंसन्ति पण्डिताः |` | "Therefore, for the sake of division (of wealth), the learned ones [paṇḍitas] do not praise" |
| `Line 3603: गुरुशास्त्रे निबद्धानामन्योन्यमभिशङ्किनाम् ||१५||` | "those who, though bound by the teacher's precepts [guru-śāstra], are suspicious of one another. ||15||" |
| `Line 3604: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3605: नियन्तुं न हि शक्यस्त्वं भेदतो धनमिच्छसि |` | "You cannot be restrained and desire wealth through division," |
| `Line 3606: यस्मात्तस्मात्सुप्रतीक हस्तित्वं समवाप्स्यसि ||१६||` | "Therefore, O Supratīka, you shall attain the state of an elephant. ||16||" |
| `Line 3607: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3608: शप्तस्त्वेवं सुप्रतीको विभावसुमथाब्रवीत् |` | "Being thus cursed, Supratīka then said to Vibhāvasu [fire-like one]," |
| `Line 3609: त्वमप्यन्तर्जलचरः कच्छपः सम्भविष्यसि ||१७||` | "You too shall become a turtle [kacchapa] dwelling in water. ||17||" |
| `Line 3610: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3611: एवमन्योन्यशापात्तौ सुप्रतीकविभावसू |` | "Thus, due to mutual curses, Supratīka and Vibhāvasu," |
| `Line 3612: गजकच्छपतां प्राप्तावर्थार्थं मूढचेतसौ ||१८||` | "Became an elephant and a turtle, their minds deluded by desire for wealth. ||18||" |
| `Line 3613: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3614: रोषदोषानुषङ्गेण तिर्यग्योनिगतावपि |` | "Due to the attachment to the fault of anger, even though born in animal wombs," |
| `Line 3615: परस्परद्वेषरतौ प्रमाणबलदर्पितौ ||१९||` | "They remained engaged in mutual hatred, proud of their immense strength. ||19||" |
| `Line 3616: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3617: सरस्यस्मिन्महाकायौ पूर्ववैरानुसारिणौ |` | "In this lake, these two massive creatures, following their previous enmity," |
| `Line 3618: तयोरेकतरः श्रीमान्समुपैति महागजः ||२०||` | "One of them, the magnificent great elephant, approaches. ||20||" |
| `Line 3619: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3620: तस्य बृंहितशब्देन कूर्मोऽप्यन्तर्जलेशयः |` | "By the trumpeting sound of that (elephant), the turtle [kūrma] dwelling in the water," |
| `Line 3621: उत्थितोऽसौ महाकायः कृत्स्नं सङ्क्षोभयन्सरः ||२१||` | "That huge-bodied one rose up, agitating the entire lake. ||21||" |
| `Line 3622: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3623: तं दृष्ट्वावेष्टितकरः पतत्येष गजो जलम् |` | "Seeing him, this elephant with its trunk coiled plunges into the water," |
| `Line 3624: दन्तहस्ताग्रलाङ्गूलपादवेगेन वीर्यवान् ||२२||` | "The powerful one, with the force of its tusks, trunk, tail, and feet. ||22||" |
| `Line 3625: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3626: तं विक्षोभयमाणं तु सरो बहुझषाकुलम् |` | "As he was agitating that lake teeming with many fish," |
| `Line 3627: कूर्मोऽप्यभ्युद्यतशिरा युद्धायाभ्येति वीर्यवान् ||२३||` | "The powerful turtle also approached for battle with its head raised. ||23||" |
| `Line 3628: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3629: षडुच्छ्रितो योजनानि गजस्तद्द्विगुणायतः |` | "The elephant was six yojanas [ancient measure] in height and twice that in length," |
| `Line 3630: कूर्मस्त्रियोजनोत्सेधो दशयोजनमण्डलः ||२४||` | "The turtle was three yojanas in height with a shell ten yojanas in circumference. ||24||" |
| `Line 3631: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3632: तावेतौ युद्धसंमत्तौ परस्परजयैषिणौ |` | "These two, mad for battle and each desiring victory over the other," |
| `Line 3633: उपयुज्याशु कर्मेदं साधयेप्सितमात्मनः ||२५||` | "Use them quickly and accomplish your desired task. ||25||" |
| `Line 3634: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3635: सूत उवाच||` | "Sūta [bard-narrator] said:" |
| `Line 3636: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3637: स तच्छ्रुत्वा पितुर्वाक्यं भीमवेगोऽन्तरिक्षगः |` | "Having heard his father's words, the terribly swift sky-traveler," |
| `Line 3638: नखेन गजमेकेन कूर्ममेकेन चाक्षिपत् ||२६||` | "Seized the elephant with one talon and the turtle with another. ||26||" |
| `Line 3639: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3640: समुत्पपात चाकाशं तत उच्चैर्विहङ्गमः |` | "Then the bird soared high into the sky," |
| `Line 3641: सोऽलम्बतीर्थमासाद्य देववृक्षानुपागमत् ||२७||` | "And reaching Alambatīrtha [sacred place], he approached the divine trees. ||27||" |
| `Line 3642: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3643: ते भीताः समकम्पन्त तस्य पक्षानिलाहताः |` | "Those trees trembled in fear, struck by the wind from his wings," |
| `Line 3644: न नो भञ्ज्यादिति तदा दिव्याः कनकशाखिनः ||२८||` | "The divine golden-branched trees thought, 'May he not break us.' ||28||" |
| `Line 3645: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3646: प्रचलाङ्गान्स तान्दृष्ट्वा मनोरथफलाङ्कुरान् |` | "Seeing them trembling, with fruits that fulfill all desires," |
| `Line 3647: अन्यानतुलरूपाङ्गानुपचक्राम खेचरः ||२९||` | "The sky-traveler approached other trees of incomparable form. ||29||" |
| `Line 3648: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3649: काञ्चनै राजतैश्चैव फलैर्वैडूर्यशाखिनः |` | "Trees with golden and silver fruits, with branches of lapis lazuli," |
| `Line 3650: सागराम्बुपरिक्षिप्तान्भ्राजमानान्महाद्रुमान् ||३०||` | "Great trees surrounded by ocean waters, shining brilliantly. ||30||" |
| `Line 3651: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 3652: तमुवाच खगश्रेष्ठं तत्र रोहिणपादपः |` | "There, the Rohiṇa tree [red-wood tree] spoke to that foremost of birds [Garuḍa]," |
| `Line 3653: अतिप्रवृद्धः सुमहानापतन्तं मनोजवम् ||३१||` | "The exceedingly tall and massive tree, to him who was descending with the speed of mind. ||31||" |
| `Line 3654: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 3655: यैषा मम महाशाखा शतयोजनमायता |` | "This great branch of mine, extending a hundred yojanas [distance measure]," |
| `Line 3656: एतामास्थाय शाखां त्वं खादेमौ गजकच्छपौ ||३२||` | "Perch upon this branch and eat these two, the elephant and the tortoise. ||32||" |
| `Line 3657: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 3658: ततो द्रुमं पतगसहस्रसेवितं; महीधरप्रतिमवपुः प्रकम्पयन् |` | "Then, shaking that tree frequented by thousands of birds, with a body resembling a mountain," |
| `Line 3659: खगोत्तमो द्रुतमभिपत्य वेगवा; न्बभञ्ज तामविरलपत्रसंवृताम् ||३३||` | "The foremost of birds [Garuḍa], swiftly swooping down with great speed, broke that branch thickly covered with leaves. ||33||" |
| `Line 3660: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 3661: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 3662: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 3663: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 3664: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 3665: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 3666: २६` | "26 [chapter number]" |
| `Line 3667: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 3668: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 3669: सूत उवाच||` | "Sūta [bard-narrator] said:" |
| `Line 3670: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 3671: स्पृष्टमात्रा तु पद्भ्यां सा गरुडेन बलीयसा |` | "Merely touched by the feet of the mighty Garuḍa," |
| `Line 3672: अभज्यत तरोः शाखा भग्नां चैनामधारयत् ||१||` | "The branch of the tree broke, and he held that broken branch. ||1||" |
| `Line 3673: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 3674: तां भग्नां स महाशाखां स्मयन्समवलोकयन् |` | "Smiling, he looked at that broken great branch," |
| `Line 3675: अथात्र लम्बतोऽपश्यद्वालखिल्यानधोमुखान् ||२||` | "And then he saw the Vālakhilyas [thumb-sized sages] hanging there, with their heads downward. ||2||" |
| `Line 3676: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3677: स तद्विनाशसन्त्रासादनुपत्य खगाधिपः |` | "The lord of birds [Garuḍa], fearing their destruction, flew after them," |
| `Line 3678: शाखामास्येन जग्राह तेषामेवान्ववेक्षया ||३||` | "And caught a branch in his mouth, keeping them in his sight. ||3||" |
| `Line 3679: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3680: शनैः पर्यपतत्पक्षी पर्वतान्प्रविशातयन् ||३||` | "The bird flew slowly, splitting mountains as he passed. ||3||" |
| `Line 3681: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3682: एवं सोऽभ्यपतद्देशान्बहून्सगजकच्छपः |` | "Thus he flew over many lands, carrying the elephant and tortoise," |
| `Line 3683: दयार्थं वालखिल्यानां न च स्थानमविन्दत ||४||` | "Out of compassion for the Vālakhilyas [thumb-sized sages], but could not find a place. ||4||" |
| `Line 3684: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3685: स गत्वा पर्वतश्रेष्ठं गन्धमादनमव्ययम् |` | "Going to the foremost mountain, the imperishable Gandhamādana [fragrant mountain]," |
| `Line 3686: ददर्श कश्यपं तत्र पितरं तपसि स्थितम् ||५||` | "He saw Kaśyapa there, his father, established in austerity. ||5||" |
| `Line 3687: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3688: ददर्श तं पिता चापि दिव्यरूपं विहङ्गमम् |` | "And his father also saw him, the divine-formed bird," |
| `Line 3689: तेजोवीर्यबलोपेतं मनोमारुतरंहसम् ||६||` | "Endowed with splendor, vigor and strength, swift as mind and wind. ||6||" |
| `Line 3690: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3691: शैलशृङ्गप्रतीकाशं ब्रह्मदण्डमिवोद्यतम् |` | "Resembling a mountain peak, like the upraised staff of Brahma [creator god]," |
| `Line 3692: अचिन्त्यमनभिज्ञेयं सर्वभूतभयङ्करम् ||७||` | "Inconceivable, unknowable, terrifying to all beings. ||7||" |
| `Line 3693: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3694: मायावीर्यधरं साक्षादग्निमिद्धमिवोद्यतम् |` | "Possessing magical power, like a blazing fire risen up," |
| `Line 3695: अप्रधृष्यमजेयं च देवदानवराक्षसैः ||८||` | "Unapproachable and unconquerable by gods, demons and rākṣasas [man-eaters]. ||8||" |
| `Line 3696: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3697: भेत्तारं गिरिशृङ्गाणां नदीजलविशोषणम् |` | "Splitter of mountain peaks, dryer of river waters," |
| `Line 3698: लोकसंलोडनं घोरं कृतान्तसमदर्शनम् ||९||` | "Terrible churner of worlds, appearing like Death [Kṛtānta] himself. ||9||" |
| `Line 3699: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3700: तमागतमभिप्रेक्ष्य भगवान्कश्यपस्तदा |` | "Seeing him arrived thus, the venerable Kaśyapa then" |
| `Line 3701: विदित्वा चास्य सङ्कल्पमिदं वचनमब्रवीत् ||१०||` | "Knowing his resolve, (Kashyapa) spoke these words. ||10||" |
| `Line 3702: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3703: पुत्र मा साहसं कार्षीर्मा सद्यो लप्स्यसे व्यथाम् |` | "Son, do not act rashly, lest you immediately experience pain," |
| `Line 3704: मा त्वा दहेयुः सङ्क्रुद्धा वालखिल्या मरीचिपाः ||११||` | "Let not the angry Valakhilyas [thumb-sized sages], the descendants of Marichi, burn you. ||11||" |
| `Line 3705: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3706: प्रसादयामास स तान्कश्यपः पुत्रकारणात् |` | "Kashyapa then appeased them for the sake of his son," |
| `Line 3707: वालखिल्यांस्तपःसिद्धानिदमुद्दिश्य कारणम् ||१२||` | "Those Valakhilyas perfected through austerities [tapas-siddhas], explaining this reason: ||12||" |
| `Line 3708: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3709: प्रजाहितार्थमारम्भो गरुडस्य तपोधनाः |` | "O wealthy in austerities [tapodhanās], Garuda's undertaking is for the welfare of beings," |
| `Line 3710: चिकीर्षति महत्कर्म तदनुज्ञातुमर्हथ ||१३||` | "He wishes to perform a great deed, please grant him permission. ||13||" |
| `Line 3711: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3712: एवमुक्ता भगवता मुनयस्ते समभ्ययुः |` | "Thus addressed by the venerable one [Bhagavata], those sages departed," |
| `Line 3713: मुक्त्वा शाखां गिरिं पुण्यं हिमवन्तं तपोर्थिनः ||१४||` | "Leaving the branch, they went to the sacred mountain Himavat [Himalayas], seeking austerities. ||14||" |
| `Line 3714: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3715: ततस्तेष्वपयातेषु पितरं विनतात्मजः |` | "Then, after they had departed, the son of Vinata [Garuda]," |
| `Line 3716: शाखाव्याक्षिप्तवदनः पर्यपृच्छत कश्यपम् ||१५||` | "With his mouth still holding the branch, asked Kashyapa: ||15||" |
| `Line 3717: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3718: भगवन्क्व विमुञ्चामि तरुशाखामिमामहम् |` | "Lord, where should I release this tree branch?" |
| `Line 3719: वर्जितं ब्राह्मणैर्देशमाख्यातु भगवान्मम ||१६||` | "Let the venerable one tell me of a place uninhabited by Brahmanas [priests]. ||16||" |
| `Line 3720: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3721: ततो निष्पुरुषं शैलं हिमसंरुद्धकन्दरम् |` | "Then Kashyapa told him of a mountain uninhabited by humans, with snow-blocked caverns," |
| `Line 3722: अगम्यं मनसाप्यन्यैस्तस्याचख्यौ स कश्यपः ||१७||` | "Inaccessible even in thought to others, which Kashyapa described to him. ||17||" |
| `Line 3723: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3724: तं पर्वतमहाकुक्षिमाविश्य मनसा खगः |` | "The bird [Garuda] mentally envisioned that great mountain hollow," |
| `Line 3725: जवेनाभ्यपतत्तार्क्ष्यः सशाखागजकच्छपः ||१८||` | "And Tarkshya [Garuda] swiftly flew there with the branch, elephant, and tortoise. ||18||" |
| `Line 3726: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3727: न तां वध्रः परिणहेच्छतचर्मा महानणुः |` | "Neither a strap, nor a large or small being with a hundred hides could encircle" |
| `Line 3728: शाखिनो महतीं शाखां यां प्रगृह्य ययौ खगः ||१९||` | "that great branch of the tree which the bird [khaga] grasped and carried away. ||19||" |
| `Line 3729: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3730: ततः स शतसाहस्रं योजनान्तरमागतः |` | "Then he, having traveled a distance of one hundred thousand yojanas [distance measure]," |
| `Line 3731: कालेन नातिमहता गरुडः पततां वरः ||२०||` | "in not too great a time, Garuḍa, the best among flying creatures. ||20||" |
| `Line 3732: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3733: स तं गत्वा क्षणेनैव पर्वतं वचनात्पितुः |` | "Having reached that mountain in an instant, as per his father's instruction," |
| `Line 3734: अमुञ्चन्महतीं शाखां सस्वनां तत्र खेचरः ||२१||` | "The sky-traveler [khechara] released that great branch there with a loud sound. ||21||" |
| `Line 3735: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3736: पक्षानिलहतश्चास्य प्राकम्पत स शैलराट् |` | "Struck by the wind from his wings, that king of mountains [shaila-rāṭ] trembled," |
| `Line 3737: मुमोच पुष्पवर्षं च समागलितपादपः ||२२||` | "And with trees shaken, it released a shower of flowers. ||22||" |
| `Line 3738: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3739: शृङ्गाणि च व्यशीर्यन्त गिरेस्तस्य समन्ततः |` | "And the peaks of that mountain crumbled all around," |
| `Line 3740: मणिकाञ्चनचित्राणि शोभयन्ति महागिरिम् ||२३||` | "Adorned with jewels and gold, they beautified the great mountain. ||23||" |
| `Line 3741: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3742: शाखिनो बहवश्चापि शाखयाभिहतास्तया |` | "And many trees struck by that branch," |
| `Line 3743: काञ्चनैः कुसुमैर्भान्ति विद्युत्वन्त इवाम्बुदाः ||२४||` | "Shone with golden flowers like lightning-filled clouds. ||24||" |
| `Line 3744: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3745: ते हेमविकचा भूयो युक्ताः पर्वतधातुभिः |` | "Those trees with golden blossoms, further mixed with mountain minerals," |
| `Line 3746: व्यराजञ्शाखिनस्तत्र सूर्यांशुप्रतिरञ्जिताः ||२५||` | "Shone there, illuminated by the rays of the sun. ||25||" |
| `Line 3747: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3748: ततस्तस्य गिरेः शृङ्गमास्थाय स खगोत्तमः |` | "Then, perching on a peak of that mountain, that best of birds [khagottama]," |
| `Line 3749: भक्षयामास गरुडस्तावुभौ गजकच्छपौ ||२६||` | "Garuḍa devoured both the elephant and the turtle. ||26||" |
| `Line 3750: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3751: ततः पर्वतकूटाग्रादुत्पपात मनोजवः |` | "Then, swift as thought, he flew up from the mountain peak," |
| `Line 3752: प्रावर्तन्ताथ देवानामुत्पाता भयवेदिनः ||२७||` | "And then portents foreboding danger began to appear among the gods. ||27||" |
| `Line 3753: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3754: इन्द्रस्य वज्रं दयितं प्रजज्वाल व्यथान्वितम् |` | "Indra's [king of gods] beloved vajra [thunderbolt] blazed forth in agitation," |
| `Line 3755: सधूमा चापतत्सार्चिर्दिवोल्का नभसश्च्युता ||२८||` | "And a meteor fell from the sky with smoke and flames. ||28||" |
| `Line 3756: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3757: तथा वसूनां रुद्राणामादित्यानां च सर्वशः |` | "Likewise, among all the Vasus [wealth deities], Rudras [storm deities], and Ādityas [solar deities]," |
| `Line 3758: साध्यानां मरुतां चैव ये चान्ये देवतागणाः ||२९||` | "The Sādhyas [celestial beings], Maruts [wind gods], and all other groups of deities, ||29||" |
| `Line 3759: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3760: स्वं स्वं प्रहरणं तेषां परस्परमुपाद्रवत् ||२९||` | "Their respective weapons rushed against one another. ||29||" |
| `Line 3761: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3762: अभूतपूर्वं सङ्ग्रामे तदा देवासुरेऽपि च |` | "Unprecedented even in the battles between gods and demons," |
| `Line 3763: ववुर्वाताः सनिर्घाताः पेतुरुल्काः समन्ततः ||३०||` | "Winds blew with thunderclaps, and meteors fell from all directions. ||30||" |
| `Line 3764: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3765: निरभ्रमपि चाकाशं प्रजगर्ज महास्वनम् |` | "Though cloudless, the sky thundered with a mighty sound," |
| `Line 3766: देवानामपि यो देवः सोऽप्यवर्षदसृक्तदा ||३१||` | "And even the god of gods [Indra] rained blood at that time. ||31||" |
| `Line 3767: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3768: मम्लुर्माल्यानि देवानां शेमुस्तेजांसि चैव हि |` | "The garlands of the gods withered and their splendors dimmed," |
| `Line 3769: उत्पातमेघा रौद्राश्च ववर्षुः शोणितं बहु ||३२||` | "And ominous, terrible clouds rained much blood. ||32||" |
| `Line 3770: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3771: रजांसि मुकुटान्येषामुत्थितानि व्यधर्षयन् ||३२||` | "Rising dust defiled their crowns. ||32||" |
| `Line 3772: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3773: ततस्त्राससमुद्विग्नः सह देवैः शतक्रतुः |` | "Then Śatakratu [Indra, performer of hundred sacrifices], alarmed and agitated along with the gods," |
| `Line 3774: उत्पातान्दारुणान्पश्यन्नित्युवाच बृहस्पतिम् ||३३||` | "Seeing these terrible portents, spoke thus to Bṛhaspati [preceptor of gods]. ||33||" |
| `Line 3775: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3776: किमर्थं भगवन्घोरा महोत्पाताः समुत्थिताः |` | "For what reason, O Lord, have these terrible portents [bad omens] arisen?" |
| `Line 3777: न च शत्रुं प्रपश्यामि युधि यो नः प्रधर्षयेत् ||३४||` | "I do not see any enemy who could challenge us in battle. ||34||" |
| `Line 3778: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 3779: बृहस्पतिरुवाच||` | "Bṛhaspati [preceptor of gods] said:" |
| `Line 3780: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 3781: तवापराधाद्देवेन्द्र प्रमादाच्च शतक्रतो |` | "Due to your offense, O Indra [king of gods], and due to your negligence, O Śatakratu [hundred-sacrificer]," |
| `Line 3782: तपसा वालखिल्यानां भूतमुत्पन्नमद्भुतम् ||३५||` | "By the austerities of the Vālakhilyas [thumb-sized sages], a wonderful being has been born. ||35||" |
| `Line 3783: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 3784: कश्यपस्य मुनेः पुत्रो विनतायाश्च खेचरः |` | "A son of sage Kaśyapa and Vinatā, a sky-traveler [bird]," |
| `Line 3785: हर्तुं सोममनुप्राप्तो बलवान्कामरूपवान् ||३६||` | "Has arrived to steal the Soma [divine nectar], powerful and able to assume any form at will. ||36||" |
| `Line 3786: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 3787: समर्थो बलिनां श्रेष्ठो हर्तुं सोमं विहङ्गमः |` | "This bird, foremost among the strong, is capable of stealing the Soma," |
| `Line 3788: सर्वं सम्भावयाम्यस्मिन्नसाध्यमपि साधयेत् ||३७||` | "I believe he can accomplish anything, even what is impossible. ||37||" |
| `Line 3789: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 3790: सूत उवाच||` | "Sūta [bard-narrator] said:" |
| `Line 3791: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 3792: श्रुत्वैतद्वचनं शक्रः प्रोवाचामृतरक्षिणः |` | "Hearing these words, Śakra [Indra] spoke to the guardians of the amṛta [immortality nectar]:" |
| `Line 3793: महावीर्यबलः पक्षी हर्तुं सोममिहोद्यतः ||३८||` | "A bird of great power and strength has set out to steal the Soma here. ||38||" |
| `Line 3794: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 3795: युष्मान्सम्बोधयाम्येष यथा स न हरेद्बलात् |` | "I alert you all so that he may not take it away by force." |
| `Line 3796: अतुलं हि बलं तस्य बृहस्पतिरुवाच मे ||३९||` | "For Bṛhaspati has told me his strength is unmatched. ||39||" |
| `Line 3797: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 3798: तच्छ्रुत्वा विबुधा वाक्यं विस्मिता यत्नमास्थिताः |` | "Hearing those words, the gods [wise ones], astonished, made efforts," |
| `Line 3799: परिवार्यामृतं तस्थुर्वज्री चेन्द्रः शतक्रतुः ||४०||` | "And surrounded the amṛta, along with the wielder of the thunderbolt, Indra, the performer of a hundred sacrifices. ||40||" |
| `Line 3800: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 3801: धारयन्तो महार्हाणि कवचानि मनस्विनः |` | "Wearing magnificent armor, those high-minded ones," |
| `Line 3802: काञ्चनानि विचित्राणि वैडूर्यविकृतानि च ||४१||` | "Made of gold, variegated, and adorned with cat's eye gems. ||41||" |
| `Line 3803: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3804: विविधानि च शस्त्राणि घोररूपाण्यनेकशः |` | "And various weapons, terrible in form, of many kinds," |
| `Line 3805: शिततीक्ष्णाग्रधाराणि समुद्यम्य सहस्रशः ||४२||` | "With sharp, keen-edged blades, raised up by the thousands. ||42||" |
| `Line 3806: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3807: सविस्फुलिङ्गज्वालानि सधूमानि च सर्वशः |` | "Emitting sparks and flames, and smoke on all sides," |
| `Line 3808: चक्राणि परिघांश्चैव त्रिशूलानि परश्वधान् ||४३||` | "Discuses [chakras], iron clubs, tridents, and battle-axes. ||43||" |
| `Line 3809: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3810: शक्तीश्च विविधास्तीक्ष्णाः करवालांश्च निर्मलान् |` | "Various sharp spears [śaktis] and gleaming swords," |
| `Line 3811: स्वदेहरूपाण्यादाय गदाश्चोग्रप्रदर्शनाः ||४४||` | "Taking forms suited to their bodies, and fierce-looking maces. ||44||" |
| `Line 3812: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3813: तैः शस्त्रैर्भानुमद्भिस्ते दिव्याभरणभूषिताः |` | "With those radiant weapons, adorned with divine ornaments," |
| `Line 3814: भानुमन्तः सुरगणास्तस्थुर्विगतकल्मषाः ||४५||` | "The radiant hosts of gods stood, free from impurity. ||45||" |
| `Line 3815: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3816: अनुपमबलवीर्यतेजसो; धृतमनसः परिरक्षणेऽमृतस्य |` | "Of incomparable strength, valor and splendor; with minds fixed on protecting the amṛta [nectar of immortality]," |
| `Line 3817: असुरपुरविदारणाः सुरा; ज्वलनसमिद्धवपुःप्रकाशिनः ||४६||` | "The gods, destroyers of demon cities, their bodies blazing like kindled fire. ||46||" |
| `Line 3818: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3819: इति समरवरं सुरास्थितं; परिघसहस्रशतैः समाकुलम् |` | "Thus the gods stood ready for excellent battle, crowded with hundreds of thousands of iron clubs," |
| `Line 3820: विगलितमिव चाम्बरान्तरे; तपनमरीचिविभासितं बभौ ||४७||` | "Appearing as if melting in the sky, shining with the rays of the sun. ||47||" |
| `Line 3821: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3822: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3823: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3824: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3825: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3826: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3827: २७` | "27" |
| `Line 3828: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3829: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3830: शौनक उवाच||` | "Shaunaka said:" |
| `Line 3831: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3832: कोऽपराधो महेन्द्रस्य कः प्रमादश्च सूतज |` | "What was the offense of Mahendra [great Indra], and what was his negligence, O son of Suta?" |
| `Line 3833: तपसा वालखिल्यानां सम्भूतो गरुडः कथम् ||१||` | "How was Garuda born from the austerities of the Valakhilyas [thumb-sized sages]? ||1||" |
| `Line 3834: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3835: कश्यपस्य द्विजातेश्च कथं वै पक्षिराट्सुतः |` | "And how did the king of birds become the son of Kashyapa, the lord of the twice-born [dvijatesha]?" |
| `Line 3836: अधृष्यः सर्वभूतानामवध्यश्चाभवत्कथम् ||२||` | "How did he become invincible and unkillable by all beings? ||2||" |
| `Line 3837: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3838: कथं च कामचारी स कामवीर्यश्च खेचरः |` | "And how did he become free to roam at will, with strength at will, this sky-traveler [khecara]?" |
| `Line 3839: एतदिच्छाम्यहं श्रोतुं पुराणे यदि पठ्यते ||३||` | "This I wish to hear, if it is recited in the Purana [ancient text]. ||3||" |
| `Line 3840: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3841: सूत उवाच||` | "Suta said:" |
| `Line 3842: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3843: विषयोऽयं पुराणस्य यन्मां त्वं परिपृच्छसि |` | "This subject about which you question me is indeed part of the Purana," |
| `Line 3844: शृणु मे वदतः सर्वमेतत्सङ्क्षेपतो द्विज ||४||` | "Listen as I tell you everything in brief, O twice-born [dvija]. ||4||" |
| `Line 3845: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3846: यजतः पुत्रकामस्य कश्यपस्य प्रजापतेः |` | "When Kashyapa, the lord of creatures [Prajapati], was performing a sacrifice desiring a son," |
| `Line 3847: साहाय्यमृषयो देवा गन्धर्वाश्च ददुः किल ||५||` | "The sages, gods, and Gandharvas [celestial musicians] indeed gave their assistance. ||5||" |
| `Line 3848: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3849: तत्रेध्मानयने शक्रो नियुक्तः कश्यपेन ह |` | "There, Shakra [Indra] was appointed by Kashyapa to bring the sacrificial firewood," |
| `Line 3850: मुनयो वालखिल्याश्च ये चान्ये देवतागणाः ||६||` | "As were the sages, the Valakhilyas, and other groups of deities. ||6||" |
| `Line 3851: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 3852: शक्रस्तु वीर्यसदृशमिध्मभारं गिरिप्रभम् |` | "Śakra [Indra], however, lifted a mountain-like load of firewood befitting his strength," |
| `Line 3853: समुद्यम्यानयामास नातिकृच्छ्रादिव प्रभुः ||७||` | "The lord carried it without much difficulty, as it seemed. ||7||" |
| `Line 3854: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 3855: अथापश्यदृषीन्ह्रस्वानङ्गुष्ठोदरपर्वणः |` | "Then he saw tiny sages [rishis] with joints the size of a thumb," |
| `Line 3856: पलाशवृन्तिकामेकां सहितान्वहतः पथि ||८||` | "Carrying together a single palāśa leaf-stalk on the path. ||8||" |
| `Line 3857: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 3858: प्रलीनान्स्वेष्विवाङ्गेषु निराहारांस्तपोधनान् |` | "These ascetics [tapodhanān], who seemed withdrawn into their own bodies, were fasting," |
| `Line 3859: क्लिश्यमानान्मन्दबलान्गोष्पदे सम्प्लुतोदके ||९||` | "Struggling with little strength, in water collected in a cow's footprint. ||9||" |
| `Line 3860: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 3861: तांश्च सर्वान्स्मयाविष्टो वीर्योन्मत्तः पुरंदरः |` | "And Purandara [Indra], filled with pride and intoxicated with his own strength," |
| `Line 3862: अवहस्यात्यगाच्छीघ्रं लङ्घयित्वावमन्य च ||१०||` | "Laughed at them all, quickly passed by, leaping over them with contempt. ||10||" |
| `Line 3863: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 3864: तेऽथ रोषसमाविष्टाः सुभृशं जातमन्यवः |` | "Then they, filled with intense anger and greatly enraged," |
| `Line 3865: आरेभिरे महत्कर्म तदा शक्रभयङ्करम् ||११||` | "Began a great ritual then, terrifying to Śakra [Indra]. ||11||" |
| `Line 3866: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 3867: जुहुवुस्ते सुतपसो विधिवज्जातवेदसम् |` | "Those great ascetics offered oblations to Jātavedas [fire deity] according to proper ritual," |
| `Line 3868: मन्त्रैरुच्चावचैर्विप्रा येन कामेन तच्छृणु ||१२||` | "With various mantras, O Vipra [learned one], listen to what purpose they did this. ||12||" |
| `Line 3869: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 3870: कामवीर्यः कामगमो देवराजभयप्रदः |` | "One with desired strength, moving at will, causing fear to the king of gods," |
| `Line 3871: इन्द्रोऽन्यः सर्वदेवानां भवेदिति यतव्रताः ||१३||` | "May there be another Indra of all the gods—thus (prayed) the ascetics of controlled vows. ||13||" |
| `Line 3872: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 3873: इन्द्राच्छतगुणः शौर्ये वीर्ये चैव मनोजवः |` | "A hundred times greater than Indra in valor and strength, and swift as thought," |
| `Line 3874: तपसो नः फलेनाद्य दारुणः सम्भवत्विति ||१४||` | "By the fruit of our austerities, may a formidable one be born today—thus (they prayed). ||14||" |
| `Line 3875: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 3876: तद्बुद्ध्वा भृशसन्तप्तो देवराजः शतक्रतुः |` | "Understanding this, Śatakratu [hundred-sacrifice performer], the king of gods, became deeply distressed," |
| `Line 3877: जगाम शरणं तत्र कश्यपं संशितव्रतम् ||१५||` | "And went there for refuge to Kaśyapa [sage progenitor] of steadfast vows. ||15||" |
| `Line 3878: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3879: तच्छ्रुत्वा देवराजस्य कश्यपोऽथ प्रजापतिः |` | "Hearing this from the king of gods, Kaśyapa, the Prajāpati [lord of creatures]," |
| `Line 3880: वालखिल्यानुपागम्य कर्मसिद्धिमपृच्छत ||१६||` | "Approached the Vālakhilyas [thumb-sized sages] and asked about the success of their undertaking. ||16||" |
| `Line 3881: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3882: एवमस्त्विति तं चापि प्रत्यूचुः सत्यवादिनः |` | "And those truth-speakers replied to him, 'So be it,'" |
| `Line 3883: तान्कश्यप उवाचेदं सान्त्वपूर्वं प्रजापतिः ||१७||` | "Then Kaśyapa, the Prajāpati, spoke these conciliatory words to them: ||17||" |
| `Line 3884: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3885: अयमिन्द्रस्त्रिभुवने नियोगाद्ब्रह्मणः कृतः |` | "This Indra was appointed in the three worlds by the command of Brahmā [creator god]," |
| `Line 3886: इन्द्रार्थं च भवन्तोऽपि यत्नवन्तस्तपोधनाः ||१८||` | "And you too, rich in austerities, have striven for the sake of an Indra. ||18||" |
| `Line 3887: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3888: न मिथ्या ब्रह्मणो वाक्यं कर्तुमर्हथ सत्तमाः |` | "O excellent ones, you should not render Brahmā's word false," |
| `Line 3889: भवतां च न मिथ्यायं सङ्कल्पो मे चिकीर्षितः ||१९||` | "Nor do I wish to make your resolution fruitless. ||19||" |
| `Line 3890: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3891: भवत्वेष पतत्रीणामिन्द्रोऽतिबलसत्त्ववान् |` | "Let there be this exceedingly powerful and mighty Indra of the winged creatures," |
| `Line 3892: प्रसादः क्रियतां चैव देवराजस्य याचतः ||२०||` | "And let grace be shown to the king of gods who now beseeches you. ||20||" |
| `Line 3893: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3894: एवमुक्ताः कश्यपेन वालखिल्यास्तपोधनाः |` | "Thus addressed by Kaśyapa, the Vālakhilyas, rich in austerities," |
| `Line 3895: प्रत्यूचुरभिसम्पूज्य मुनिश्रेष्ठं प्रजापतिम् ||२१||` | "Replied, after duly honoring the foremost of sages, the Prajāpati: ||21||" |
| `Line 3896: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3897: इन्द्रार्थोऽयं समारम्भः सर्वेषां नः प्रजापते |` | "O Prajāpati, this undertaking of all of us was for the sake of an Indra," |
| `Line 3898: अपत्यार्थं समारम्भो भवतश्चायमीप्सितः ||२२||` | "And this undertaking of yours is desired for the sake of offspring. ||22||" |
| `Line 3899: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3900: तदिदं सफलं कर्म त्वया वै प्रतिगृह्यताम् |` | "Therefore, let this fruitful work be accepted by you." |
| `Line 3901: तथा चैव विधत्स्वात्र यथा श्रेयोऽनुपश्यसि ||२३||` | "And arrange matters here as you see best for our welfare. ||23||" |
| `Line 3902: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 3903: एतस्मिन्नेव काले तु देवी दाक्षायणी शुभा |` | "At this very time, the auspicious goddess Dākṣāyaṇī [daughter of Dakṣa]," |
| `Line 3904: विनता नाम कल्याणी पुत्रकामा यशस्विनी ||२४||` | "Named Vinatā, virtuous, desiring sons, and illustrious, ||24||" |
| `Line 3905: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 3906: तपस्तप्त्वा व्रतपरा स्नाता पुंसवने शुचिः |` | "Having performed austerities, devoted to vows, bathed in the puṃsavana [male-child ceremony], purified," |
| `Line 3907: उपचक्राम भर्तारं तामुवाचाथ कश्यपः ||२५||` | "Approached her husband, and then Kaśyapa said to her: ||25||" |
| `Line 3908: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 3909: आरम्भः सफलो देवि भवितायं तवेप्सितः |` | "O goddess, this endeavor of yours will be successful as desired," |
| `Line 3910: जनयिष्यसि पुत्रौ द्वौ वीरौ त्रिभुवनेश्वरौ ||२६||` | "You will give birth to two heroic sons who will be lords of the three worlds. ||26||" |
| `Line 3911: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 3912: तपसा वालखिल्यानां मम सङ्कल्पजौ तथा |` | "Born from the austerities of the Vālakhilyas [thumb-sized sages] and from my intention," |
| `Line 3913: भविष्यतो महाभागौ पुत्रौ ते लोकपूजितौ ||२७||` | "Your two sons will be greatly fortunate and worshipped by the worlds. ||27||" |
| `Line 3914: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 3915: उवाच चैनां भगवान्मारीचः पुनरेव ह |` | "And the lord Mārīca [Kaśyapa] spoke to her again:" |
| `Line 3916: धार्यतामप्रमादेन गर्भोऽयं सुमहोदयः ||२८||` | "Bear this womb with great care, for it will bring tremendous prosperity. ||28||" |
| `Line 3917: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 3918: एकः सर्वपतत्रीणामिन्द्रत्वं कारयिष्यति |` | "One will attain the position of Indra among all winged creatures," |
| `Line 3919: लोकसम्भावितो वीरः कामवीर्यो विहङ्गमः ||२९||` | "A hero respected by the worlds, a bird with strength according to his will. ||29||" |
| `Line 3920: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 3921: शतक्रतुमथोवाच प्रीयमाणः प्रजापतिः |` | "Then the pleased Prajāpati [lord of creatures] said to Śatakratu [Indra]:" |
| `Line 3922: त्वत्सहायौ खगावेतौ भ्रातरौ ते भविष्यतः ||३०||` | "These two bird-brothers will be your allies. ||30||" |
| `Line 3923: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 3924: नैताभ्यां भविता दोषः सकाशात्ते पुरंदर |` | "No harm will come to you from them, O Purandara [city-destroyer]," |
| `Line 3925: व्येतु ते शक्र सन्तापस्त्वमेवेन्द्रो भविष्यसि ||३१||` | "Let your anxiety depart, O Śakra [Indra], you alone will remain Indra. ||31||" |
| `Line 3926: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3927: न चाप्येवं त्वया भूयः क्षेप्तव्या ब्रह्मवादिनः |` | "And never again should you thus insult the Brahmavādins [Vedic scholars]," |
| `Line 3928: न चावमान्या दर्पात्ते वाग्विषा भृशकोपनाः ||३२||` | "Nor should you disrespect out of pride those whose words are venomous and easily angered. ||32||" |
| `Line 3929: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3930: एवमुक्तो जगामेन्द्रो निर्विशङ्कस्त्रिविष्टपम् |` | "Thus addressed, Indra [king of gods] went without fear to Triviṣṭapa [heaven]," |
| `Line 3931: विनता चापि सिद्धार्था बभूव मुदिता तदा ||३३||` | "And Vinatā too, having achieved her purpose, became joyful then. ||33||" |
| `Line 3932: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3933: जनयामास पुत्रौ द्वावरुणं गरुडं तथा |` | "She gave birth to two sons, Aruṇa and Garuḍa," |
| `Line 3934: अरुणस्तयोस्तु विकल आदित्यस्य पुरःसरः ||३४||` | "Of those two, Aruṇa was crippled and became the charioteer [forerunner] of Āditya [the sun]. ||34||" |
| `Line 3935: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3936: पतत्रीणां तु गरुड इन्द्रत्वेनाभ्यषिच्यत |` | "And Garuḍa was consecrated as the Indra [sovereign] of the winged creatures," |
| `Line 3937: तस्यैतत्कर्म सुमहच्छ्रूयतां भृगुनन्दन ||३५||` | "Listen to his great deed, O Bhṛgunandana [descendant of Bhṛgu]. ||35||" |
| `Line 3938: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3939: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3940: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3941: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3942: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3943: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3944: २८` | "28" |
| `Line 3945: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3946: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3947: सूत उवाच||` | "Sūta [bard/narrator] said:" |
| `Line 3948: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3949: ततस्तस्मिन्द्विजश्रेष्ठ समुदीर्णे तथाविधे |` | "Then, O best of the twice-born [Brahmin], when that situation arose thus," |
| `Line 3950: गरुत्मान्पक्षिराट्तूर्णं सम्प्राप्तो विबुधान्प्रति ||१||` | "Garutmān [Garuḍa], the king of birds, swiftly approached the gods. ||1||" |
| `Line 3951: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3952: तं दृष्ट्वातिबलं चैव प्राकम्पन्त समन्ततः |` | "Seeing him of extraordinary strength, they trembled all around," |
| `Line 3953: परस्परं च प्रत्यघ्नन्सर्वप्रहरणान्यपि ||२||` | "And all their weapons struck against each other. ||2||" |
| `Line 3954: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3955: तत्र चासीदमेयात्मा विद्युदग्निसमप्रभः |` | "There was one of immeasurable spirit, radiant like lightning and fire," |
| `Line 3956: भौवनः सुमहावीर्यः सोमस्य परिरक्षिता ||३||` | "Bhauvana [earth-born guardian], of great valor, the protector of Soma [moon/sacred drink]. ||3||" |
| `Line 3957: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3958: स तेन पतगेन्द्रेण पक्षतुण्डनखैः क्षतः |` | "He was wounded by that lord of birds [Garuda] with wings, beak, and talons," |
| `Line 3959: मुहूर्तमतुलं युद्धं कृत्वा विनिहतो युधि ||४||` | "And after fighting an incomparable battle for a moment, was slain in combat. ||4||" |
| `Line 3960: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3961: रजश्चोद्धूय सुमहत्पक्षवातेन खेचरः |` | "The sky-traveler [Garuda] raised a great cloud of dust with the wind of his wings," |
| `Line 3962: कृत्वा लोकान्निरालोकांस्तेन देवानवाकिरत् ||५||` | "Making the worlds lightless, he scattered the gods with it. ||5||" |
| `Line 3963: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3964: तेनावकीर्णा रजसा देवा मोहमुपागमन् |` | "Covered by that dust, the gods became confused," |
| `Line 3965: न चैनं ददृशुश्छन्ना रजसामृतरक्षिणः ||६||` | "And the guardians of amrita [immortality nectar], concealed by the dust, could not see him. ||6||" |
| `Line 3966: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3967: एवं संलोडयामास गरुडस्त्रिदिवालयम् |` | "Thus Garuda churned up the abode of the thirty gods [heaven]," |
| `Line 3968: पक्षतुण्डप्रहारैश्च देवान्स विददार ह ||७||` | "And with blows from his wings and beak, he tore apart the gods indeed. ||7||" |
| `Line 3969: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3970: ततो देवः सहस्राक्षस्तूर्णं वायुमचोदयत् |` | "Then the thousand-eyed god [Indra] quickly urged the wind," |
| `Line 3971: विक्षिपेमां रजोवृष्टिं तवैतत्कर्म मारुत ||८||` | "'Disperse this shower of dust, this is your task, O Wind [Maruta].' ||8||" |
| `Line 3972: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3973: अथ वायुरपोवाह तद्रजस्तरसा बली |` | "Then the mighty Wind swiftly carried away that dust," |
| `Line 3974: ततो वितिमिरे जाते देवाः शकुनिमार्दयन् ||९||` | "When the darkness was gone, the gods attacked the bird [Garuda]. ||9||" |
| `Line 3975: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 3976: ननाद चोच्चैर्बलवान्महामेघरवः खगः |` | "The mighty bird [Garuḍa], with a sound like great thunder, roared loudly," |
| `Line 3977: वध्यमानः सुरगणैः सर्वभूतानि भीषयन् ||१०||` | "While being attacked by hosts of gods, terrifying all beings. ||10||" |
| `Line 3978: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 3979: उत्पपात महावीर्यः पक्षिराट्परवीरहा ||१०||` | "The immensely powerful king of birds [Garuḍa], slayer of enemy heroes, soared upward. ||10||" |
| `Line 3980: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 3981: तमुत्पत्यान्तरिक्षस्थं देवानामुपरि स्थितम् |` | "As he flew up into the sky, positioned above the gods," |
| `Line 3982: वर्मिणो विबुधाः सर्वे नानाशस्त्रैरवाकिरन् ||११||` | "All the armored immortals [gods] showered him with various weapons. ||11||" |
| `Line 3983: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 3984: पट्टिशैः परिघैः शूलैर्गदाभिश्च सवासवाः |` | "With spears, iron clubs, tridents, and maces, the gods including Vāsava [Indra]," |
| `Line 3985: क्षुरान्तैर्ज्वलितैश्चापि चक्रैरादित्यरूपिभिः ||१२||` | "With razor-edged weapons, flaming discs shining like the sun. ||12||" |
| `Line 3986: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 3987: नानाशस्त्रविसर्गैश्च वध्यमानः समन्ततः |` | "Though attacked from all sides with discharges of various weapons," |
| `Line 3988: कुर्वन्सुतुमुलं युद्धं पक्षिराण्न व्यकम्पत ||१३||` | "The king of birds, waging a fierce battle, did not waver. ||13||" |
| `Line 3989: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 3990: विनर्दन्निव चाकाशे वैनतेयः प्रतापवान् |` | "Roaring in the sky, the mighty Vainateya [son of Vinatā, Garuḍa]," |
| `Line 3991: पक्षाभ्यामुरसा चैव समन्ताद्व्याक्षिपत्सुरान् ||१४||` | "Scattered the gods in all directions with his wings and chest. ||14||" |
| `Line 3992: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 3993: ते विक्षिप्तास्ततो देवाः प्रजग्मुर्गरुडार्दिताः |` | "Those gods, thus scattered and afflicted by Garuḍa, fled," |
| `Line 3994: नखतुण्डक्षताश्चैव सुस्रुवुः शोणितं बहु ||१५||` | "Wounded by his claws and beak, they bled profusely. ||15||" |
| `Line 3995: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 3996: साध्याः प्राचीं सगन्धर्वा वसवो दक्षिणां दिशम् |` | "The Sādhyas [celestial beings] with the Gandharvas fled to the east, the Vasus to the south," |
| `Line 3997: प्रजग्मुः सहिता रुद्रैः पतगेन्द्रप्रधर्षिताः ||१६||` | "They fled together with the Rudras, all harassed by the lord of birds. ||16||" |
| `Line 3998: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 3999: दिशं प्रतीचीमादित्या नासत्या उत्तरां दिशम् |` | "The Ādityas fled to the west, the Nāsatyas [Aśvins] to the north," |
| `Line 4000: मुहुर्मुहुः प्रेक्षमाणा युध्यमाना महौजसम् ||१७||` | "Repeatedly looking back while fighting the mighty one [Garuḍa]. ||17||" |
| `Line 4001: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4002: अश्वक्रन्देन वीरेण रेणुकेन च पक्षिणा |` | "With the heroic Aśvakranda [horse-neigher], the bird Reṇuka [dust-maker]," |
| `Line 4003: क्रथनेन च शूरेण तपनेन च खेचरः ||१८||` | "And with the valiant Krathana [roarer] and the sky-traveler Tapana [scorcher]. ||18||" |
| `Line 4004: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4005: उलूकश्वसनाभ्यां च निमेषेण च पक्षिणा |` | "With Ulūka [owl] and Śvasana [wind-like], and with the bird Nimeṣa [blink]," |
| `Line 4006: प्ररुजेन च संयुद्धं चकार प्रलिहेन च ||१९||` | "He fought with Praruja [destroyer] and Praliha [licker]. ||19||" |
| `Line 4007: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4008: तान्पक्षनखतुण्डाग्रैरभिनद्विनतासुतः |` | "The son of Vinatā [Garuḍa] tore them with the tips of his wings, claws, and beak," |
| `Line 4009: युगान्तकाले सङ्क्रुद्धः पिनाकीव महाबलः ||२०||` | "Like the mighty Pinākin [Śiva] enraged at the time of cosmic dissolution. ||20||" |
| `Line 4010: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4011: महावीर्या महोत्साहास्तेन ते बहुधा क्षताः |` | "Though of great valor and great enthusiasm, they were wounded in many ways by him," |
| `Line 4012: रेजुरभ्रघनप्रख्या रुधिरौघप्रवर्षिणः ||२१||` | "They shone like dense clouds, pouring forth streams of blood. ||21||" |
| `Line 4013: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4014: तान्कृत्वा पतगश्रेष्ठः सर्वानुत्क्रान्तजीवितान् |` | "Having deprived all of them of their lives, the foremost of birds [Garuḍa]," |
| `Line 4015: अतिक्रान्तोऽमृतस्यार्थे सर्वतोऽग्निमपश्यत ||२२||` | "Advancing for the sake of amṛta [nectar], saw fire on all sides. ||22||" |
| `Line 4016: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4017: आवृण्वानं महाज्वालमर्चिर्भिः सर्वतोऽम्बरम् |` | "Covering the sky on all sides with great flames and rays," |
| `Line 4018: दहन्तमिव तीक्ष्णांशुं घोरं वायुसमीरितम् ||२३||` | "Like the fierce, scorching sun, stirred by wind. ||23||" |
| `Line 4019: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4020: ततो नवत्या नवतीर्मुखानां; कृत्वा तरस्वी गरुडो महात्मा |` | "Then the mighty, great-souled Garuḍa, creating ninety times ninety mouths," |
| `Line 4021: नदीः समापीय मुखैस्ततस्तैः; सुशीघ्रमागम्य पुनर्जवेन ||२४||` | "Drank up rivers with those mouths, and swiftly returned with speed. ||24||" |
| `Line 4022: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4023: ज्वलन्तमग्निं तममित्रतापनः; समास्तरत्पत्ररथो नदीभिः |` | "The tormentor of enemies [Garuḍa], riding on wings, extinguished the blazing fire with those rivers," |
| `Line 4024: ततः प्रचक्रे वपुरन्यदल्पं; प्रवेष्टुकामोऽग्निमभिप्रशाम्य ||२५||` | "Then, having quenched the fire, he made his body small, desiring to enter. ||25||" |
| `Line 4025: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4026: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 4027: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 4028: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 4029: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 4030: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 4031: २९` | "29 [chapter number]" |
| `Line 4032: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 4033: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 4034: सूत उवाच||` | "Sūta [bard-narrator] said:" |
| `Line 4035: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 4036: जाम्बूनदमयो भूत्वा मरीचिविकचोज्ज्वलः |` | "Becoming golden [jāmbūnada-gold] and radiant with gleaming rays," |
| `Line 4037: प्रविवेश बलात्पक्षी वारिवेग इवार्णवम् ||१||` | "The bird forcefully entered, like a torrent of water into the ocean. ||1||" |
| `Line 4038: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 4039: स चक्रं क्षुरपर्यन्तमपश्यदमृतान्तिके |` | "Near the amṛta [immortality nectar], he saw a wheel with razor-sharp edges," |
| `Line 4040: परिभ्रमन्तमनिशं तीक्ष्णधारमयस्मयम् ||२||` | "Revolving continuously, with a keen iron edge. ||2||" |
| `Line 4041: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 4042: ज्वलनार्कप्रभं घोरं छेदनं सोमहारिणाम् |` | "Terrible, with the brilliance of fire and sun, a cutter of Soma [nectar] thieves," |
| `Line 4043: घोररूपं तदत्यर्थं यन्त्रं देवैः सुनिर्मितम् ||३||` | "That exceedingly fearsome device was well-constructed by the gods. ||3||" |
| `Line 4044: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 4045: तस्यान्तरं स दृष्ट्वैव पर्यवर्तत खेचरः |` | "Seeing the gap within it, the sky-traveler [bird] circled around," |
| `Line 4046: अरान्तरेणाभ्यपतत्सङ्क्षिप्याङ्गं क्षणेन ह ||४||` | "And in an instant, contracting his body, he darted between the spokes. ||4||" |
| `Line 4047: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 4048: अधश्चक्रस्य चैवात्र दीप्तानलसमद्युती |` | "And below the wheel, with a brilliance like blazing fire," |
| `Line 4049: विद्युज्जिह्वौ महाघोरौ दीप्तास्यौ दीप्तलोचनौ ||५||` | "Were two terrifying beings with lightning-like tongues, blazing mouths, and glowing eyes. ||5||" |
| `Line 4050: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 4051: चक्षुर्विषौ महावीर्यौ नित्यक्रुद्धौ तरस्विनौ |` | "He saw two serpent-lords with poison in their eyes, of great power, perpetually angry, and fierce," |
| `Line 4052: रक्षार्थमेवामृतस्य ददर्श भुजगोत्तमौ ||६||` | "The two excellent serpents [bhujagottamau] stationed there for the protection of the amṛta [nectar of immortality]. ||6||" |
| `Line 4053: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4054: सदा संरब्धनयनौ सदा चानिमिषेक्षणौ |` | "Always with enraged eyes and always with unblinking gaze," |
| `Line 4055: तयोरेकोऽपि यं पश्येत्स तूर्णं भस्मसाद्भवेत् ||७||` | "Whomever even one of them would look at would instantly be reduced to ashes. ||7||" |
| `Line 4056: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4057: तयोश्चक्षूंषि रजसा सुपर्णस्तूर्णमावृणोत् |` | "Suparṇa [Garuḍa] quickly covered their eyes with dust," |
| `Line 4058: अदृष्टरूपस्तौ चापि सर्वतः पर्यकालयत् ||८||` | "And while remaining invisible himself, he observed them from all sides. ||8||" |
| `Line 4059: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4060: तयोरङ्गे समाक्रम्य वैनतेयोऽन्तरिक्षगः |` | "Vainateya [son of Vinatā], the sky-traveler, attacking their bodies," |
| `Line 4061: आच्छिनत्तरसा मध्ये सोममभ्यद्रवत्ततः ||९||` | "Cut through between them swiftly and then rushed toward the Soma [amṛta]. ||9||" |
| `Line 4062: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4063: समुत्पाट्यामृतं तत्तु वैनतेयस्ततो बली |` | "Having snatched that amṛta, the mighty Vainateya [Garuḍa]," |
| `Line 4064: उत्पपात जवेनैव यन्त्रमुन्मथ्य वीर्यवान् ||१०||` | "Flew up with great speed, having destroyed the mechanism [protective device], the powerful one. ||10||" |
| `Line 4065: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4066: अपीत्वैवामृतं पक्षी परिगृह्याशु वीर्यवान् |` | "Without drinking the amṛta, the powerful bird, quickly seizing it," |
| `Line 4067: अगच्छदपरिश्रान्त आवार्यार्कप्रभां खगः ||११||` | "Departed untired, the bird [khaga] warding off the sun's radiance. ||11||" |
| `Line 4068: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4069: विष्णुना तु तदाकाशे वैनतेयः समेयिवान् |` | "Then in the sky, Vainateya [Garuḍa] encountered Viṣṇu [preserver deity]," |
| `Line 4070: तस्य नारायणस्तुष्टस्तेनालौल्येन कर्मणा ||१२||` | "Nārāyaṇa [Viṣṇu] was pleased with him for that steadfast deed. ||12||" |
| `Line 4071: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4072: तमुवाचाव्ययो देवो वरदोऽस्मीति खेचरम् |` | "The imperishable god said to the sky-traveler, 'I am ready to grant you a boon,'" |
| `Line 4073: स वव्रे तव तिष्ठेयमुपरीत्यन्तरिक्षगः ||१३||` | "He chose: 'May I remain above you,' said the sky-traveler. ||13||" |
| `Line 4074: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4075: उवाच चैनं भूयोऽपि नारायणमिदं वचः |` | "And he spoke these words again to Nārāyaṇa [Viṣṇu]:" |
| `Line 4076: अजरश्चामरश्च स्याममृतेन विनाप्यहम् ||१४||` | "I shall be ageless and immortal even without amṛta [nectar of immortality]. ||14||" |
| `Line 4077: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4078: प्रतिगृह्य वरौ तौ च गरुडो विष्णुमब्रवीत् |` | "Having received those two boons, Garuḍa said to Viṣṇu [preserver deity]:" |
| `Line 4079: भवतेऽपि वरं दद्मि वृणीतां भगवानपि ||१५||` | "I also give a boon to you; may the Lord choose one as well. ||15||" |
| `Line 4080: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4081: तं वव्रे वाहनं कृष्णो गरुत्मन्तं महाबलम् |` | "Kṛṣṇa [Viṣṇu] chose him, the mighty Garutmān [Garuḍa], as his vehicle," |
| `Line 4082: ध्वजं च चक्रे भगवानुपरि स्थास्यसीति तम् ||१६||` | "And the Lord made him his emblem, saying, 'You shall remain above me.' ||16||" |
| `Line 4083: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4084: अनुपत्य खगं त्विन्द्रो वज्रेणाङ्गेऽभ्यताडयत् |` | "But Indra [king of gods], pursuing the bird, struck him on his body with the vajra [thunderbolt]," |
| `Line 4085: विहङ्गमं सुरामित्रं हरन्तममृतं बलात् ||१७||` | "The bird who was an enemy of the gods, forcibly carrying away the amṛta [nectar]. ||17||" |
| `Line 4086: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4087: तमुवाचेन्द्रमाक्रन्दे गरुडः पततां वरः |` | "Garuḍa, the best of birds, addressed Indra in his attack," |
| `Line 4088: प्रहसञ्श्लक्ष्णया वाचा तथा वज्रसमाहतः ||१८||` | "Laughing, with smooth speech, even though struck by the vajra [thunderbolt]: ||18||" |
| `Line 4089: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4090: ऋषेर्मानं करिष्यामि वज्रं यस्यास्थिसम्भवम् |` | "I shall honor the sage whose bones became the vajra [thunderbolt]," |
| `Line 4091: वज्रस्य च करिष्यामि तव चैव शतक्रतो ||१९||` | "And I shall honor the vajra [thunderbolt] and you too, O Śatakratu [Indra]. ||19||" |
| `Line 4092: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4093: एष पत्रं त्यजाम्येकं यस्यान्तं नोपलप्स्यसे |` | "I shall drop this one feather, the end of which you will not find," |
| `Line 4094: न हि वज्रनिपातेन रुजा मेऽस्ति कदाचन ||२०||` | "For the strike of the vajra [thunderbolt] causes me no pain whatsoever. ||20||" |
| `Line 4095: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4096: तत्र तं सर्वभूतानि विस्मितान्यब्रुवंस्तदा |` | "Then all beings, astonished, said to him," |
| `Line 4097: सुरूपं पत्रमालक्ष्य सुपर्णोऽयं भवत्विति ||२१||` | "Observing the beautiful feather: 'Let him be called Suparṇa [beautiful-winged].' ||21||" |
| `Line 4098: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4099: दृष्ट्वा तदद्भुतं चापि सहस्राक्षः पुरंदरः |` | "And seeing that wonder, Sahasrākṣa [thousand-eyed] Purandara [Indra]," |
| `Line 4100: खगो महदिदं भूतमिति मत्वाभ्यभाषत ||२२||` | "Thinking 'This bird is a great being,' spoke: ||22||" |
| `Line 4101: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4102: बलं विज्ञातुमिच्छामि यत्ते परमनुत्तमम् |` | "I wish to know your strength, which is supreme and unsurpassed," |
| `Line 4103: सख्यं चानन्तमिच्छामि त्वया सह खगोत्तम ||२३||` | "And I desire eternal friendship with you, O best of birds [Garuḍa]. ||23||" |
| `Line 4104: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4105: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4106: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4107: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4108: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4109: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4110: ३०` | "30" |
| `Line 4111: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4112: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4113: गरुड उवाच||` | "Garuḍa said:" |
| `Line 4114: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4115: सख्यं मेऽस्तु त्वया देव यथेच्छसि पुरंदर |` | "Let there be friendship between us, O god, as you wish, Purandara [Indra, destroyer of cities]," |
| `Line 4116: बलं तु मम जानीहि महच्चासह्यमेव च ||१||` | "But know my strength to be great and indeed irresistible. ||1||" |
| `Line 4117: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4118: कामं नैतत्प्रशंसन्ति सन्तः स्वबलसंस्तवम् |` | "Indeed, the virtuous do not approve of this—praising one's own strength," |
| `Line 4119: गुणसङ्कीर्तनं चापि स्वयमेव शतक्रतो ||२||` | "And also the proclamation of one's own qualities, O Śatakratu [Indra, performer of hundred sacrifices]. ||2||" |
| `Line 4120: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4121: सखेति कृत्वा तु सखे पृष्टो वक्ष्याम्यहं त्वया |` | "But considering you as a friend, O friend, being asked by you, I shall speak," |
| `Line 4122: न ह्यात्मस्तवसंयुक्तं वक्तव्यमनिमित्ततः ||३||` | "For one should not speak words of self-praise without cause. ||3||" |
| `Line 4123: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4124: सपर्वतवनामुर्वीं ससागरवनामिमाम् |` | "This earth with its mountains and forests, with its oceans and woods," |
| `Line 4125: पक्षनाड्यैकया शक्र त्वां चैवात्रावलम्बिनम् ||४||` | "With a single quill of my wing, O Śakra [Indra], I could carry it with you clinging to it. ||4||" |
| `Line 4126: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4127: सर्वान्सम्पिण्डितान्वापि लोकान्सस्थाणुजङ्गमान् |` | "I could carry all the worlds combined, with their stationary and moving beings," |
| `Line 4128: वहेयमपरिश्रान्तो विद्धीदं मे महद्बलम् ||५||` | "I would carry them without fatigue - know this to be my great strength. ||5||" |
| `Line 4129: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4130: सूत उवाच||` | "Sūta [bard/narrator] said:" |
| `Line 4131: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4132: इत्युक्तवचनं वीरं किरीटी श्रीमतां वरः |` | "To the heroic one who spoke these words, Kirīṭī [Indra, crown-wearer], the best among the glorious," |
| `Line 4133: आह शौनक देवेन्द्रः सर्वभूतहितः प्रभुः ||६||` | "Said, O Śaunaka, the lord of gods, the master who is beneficial to all beings: ||6||" |
| `Line 4134: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4135: प्रतिगृह्यतामिदानीं मे सख्यमानन्त्यमुत्तमम् |` | "Accept now my eternal and supreme friendship," |
| `Line 4136: न कार्यं तव सोमेन मम सोमः प्रदीयताम् ||७||` | "You have no need for Soma [sacred elixir], let the Soma be given to me. ||7||" |
| `Line 4137: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4138: अस्मांस्ते हि प्रबाधेयुर्येभ्यो दद्याद्भवानिमम् ||७||` | "Those to whom you would give this would indeed trouble us. ||7||" |
| `Line 4139: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4140: गरुड उवाच||` | "Garuḍa [divine eagle] said:" |
| `Line 4141: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4142: किञ्चित्कारणमुद्दिश्य सोमोऽयं नीयते मया |` | "For a certain purpose this Soma is being carried by me," |
| `Line 4143: न दास्यामि समादातुं सोमं कस्मैचिदप्यहम् ||८||` | "I will not give the Soma to anyone to take away. ||8||" |
| `Line 4144: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4145: यत्रेमं तु सहस्राक्ष निक्षिपेयमहं स्वयम् |` | "But where I myself would place this, O Sahasrākṣa [thousand-eyed Indra]," |
| `Line 4146: त्वमादाय ततस्तूर्णं हरेथास्त्रिदशेश्वर ||९||` | "You may quickly take it from there, O lord of the Tridaśas [thirty gods]. ||9||" |
| `Line 4147: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4148: शक्र उवाच||` | "Śakra [Indra] said:" |
| `Line 4149: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4150: वाक्येनानेन तुष्टोऽहं यत्त्वयोक्तमिहाण्डज |` | "I am pleased with these words that you have spoken here, O Aṇḍaja [egg-born one]," |
| `Line 4151: यदिच्छसि वरं मत्तस्तद्गृहाण खगोत्तम ||१०||` | "If you desire a boon from me, then take it, O best of birds [Garuḍa]. ||10||" |
| `Line 4152: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4153: सूत उवाच||` | "Sūta [bard/narrator] said:" |
| `Line 4154: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4155: इत्युक्तः प्रत्युवाचेदं कद्रूपुत्राननुस्मरन् |` | "Thus addressed, he replied this, remembering the sons of Kadrū [serpents]," |
| `Line 4156: स्मृत्वा चैवोपधिकृतं मातुर्दास्यनिमित्ततः ||११||` | "And recalling the deception that caused his mother's enslavement. ||11||" |
| `Line 4157: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4158: ईशोऽहमपि सर्वस्य करिष्यामि तु तेऽर्थिताम् |` | "Though I am lord of all, I will fulfill your request," |
| `Line 4159: भवेयुर्भुजगाः शक्र मम भक्ष्या महाबलाः ||१२||` | "Let the mighty serpents, O Śakra [Indra], become my food. ||12||" |
| `Line 4160: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4161: तथेत्युक्त्वान्वगच्छत्तं ततो दानवसूदनः |` | "Having said 'so be it,' the slayer of Dānavas [Indra] then followed him," |
| `Line 4162: हरिष्यामि विनिक्षिप्तं सोममित्यनुभाष्य तम् ||१३||` | "After telling him, 'I will take away the Soma [nectar] once it is set down.' ||13||" |
| `Line 4163: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4164: आजगाम ततस्तूर्णं सुपर्णो मातुरन्तिकम् |` | "Then Suparṇa [Garuḍa] swiftly came to his mother's presence," |
| `Line 4165: अथ सर्पानुवाचेदं सर्वान्परमहृष्टवत् ||१४||` | "And then spoke to all the serpents as if extremely delighted. ||14||" |
| `Line 4166: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4167: इदमानीतममृतं निक्षेप्स्यामि कुशेषु वः |` | "I have brought this amṛta [nectar of immortality] and will place it on kuśa grass for you," |
| `Line 4168: स्नाता मङ्गलसंयुक्तास्ततः प्राश्नीत पन्नगाः ||१५||` | "After bathing and performing auspicious rites, then partake of it, O serpents. ||15||" |
| `Line 4169: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4170: अदासी चैव मातेयमद्यप्रभृति चास्तु मे |` | "And let my mother be free from slavery from this day forward," |
| `Line 4171: यथोक्तं भवतामेतद्वचो मे प्रतिपादितम् ||१६||` | "As you had stated, your words have been fulfilled by me. ||16||" |
| `Line 4172: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4173: ततः स्नातुं गताः सर्पाः प्रत्युक्त्वा तं तथेत्युत |` | "Then the serpents went to bathe after replying to him, 'So be it,'" |
| `Line 4174: शक्रोऽप्यमृतमाक्षिप्य जगाम त्रिदिवं पुनः ||१७||` | "And Śakra [Indra], having snatched away the amṛta [nectar], returned to Tridiva [heaven] again. ||17||" |
| `Line 4175: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4176: अथागतास्तमुद्देशं सर्पाः सोमार्थिनस्तदा |` | "Then the serpents, seeking the Soma [sacred elixir], arrived at that place," |
| `Line 4177: स्नाताश्च कृतजप्याश्च प्रहृष्टाः कृतमङ्गलाः ||१८||` | "Bathed, having performed their prayers, delighted, and having completed auspicious rites. ||18||" |
| `Line 4178: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4179: तद्विज्ञाय हृतं सर्पाः प्रतिमायाकृतं च तत् |` | "The serpents, realizing that it had been taken and replaced with an illusion," |
| `Line 4180: सोमस्थानमिदं चेति दर्भांस्ते लिलिहुस्तदा ||१९||` | "Thinking 'this is the place of Soma,' they licked the darbha grass [sacred grass] then. ||19||" |
| `Line 4181: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4182: ततो द्वैधीकृता जिह्वा सर्पाणां तेन कर्मणा |` | "Then by that action, the tongues of the serpents became split in two," |
| `Line 4183: अभवंश्चामृतस्पर्शाद्दर्भास्तेऽथ पवित्रिणः ||२०||` | "And from the touch of the amṛta [immortal nectar], those darbha grasses became purifiers. ||20||" |
| `Line 4184: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4185: ततः सुपर्णः परमप्रहृष्टवा; न्विहृत्य मात्रा सह तत्र कानने |` | "Then Suparṇa [Garuḍa], extremely delighted, having sported with his mother in that forest," |
| `Line 4186: भुजङ्गभक्षः परमार्चितः खगै; रहीनकीर्तिर्विनतामनन्दयत् ||२१||` | "The serpent-eater, highly honored by birds, with undying fame, brought joy to Vinatā. ||21||" |
| `Line 4187: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4188: इमां कथां यः शृणुयान्नरः सदा; पठेत वा द्विजजनमुख्यसंसदि |` | "The man who always listens to this story or recites it in an assembly headed by the twice-born [Brahmins]," |
| `Line 4189: असंशयं त्रिदिवमियात्स पुण्यभा; ङ्महात्मनः पतगपतेः प्रकीर्तनात् ||२२||` | "Without doubt goes to heaven, partaking of merit from glorifying the great-souled king of birds. ||22||" |
| `Line 4190: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4191: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4192: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4193: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4194: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4195: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4196: ३१` | "31" |
| `Line 4197: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4198: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4199: शौनक उवाच||` | "Śaunaka [sage, chief interlocutor] said:" |
| `Line 4200: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4201: भुजङ्गमानां शापस्य मात्रा चैव सुतेन च |` | "The curse of the serpents by the mother and the son," |
| `Line 4202: विनतायास्त्वया प्रोक्तं कारणं सूतनन्दन ||१||` | "The cause of Vinatā's [Garuḍa's mother] situation has been explained by you, O Sūtanandana [son of Sūta]. ||1||" |
| `Line 4203: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4204: वरप्रदानं भर्त्रा च कद्रूविनतयोस्तथा |` | "The granting of boons by the husband to both Kadrū and Vinatā," |
| `Line 4205: नामनी चैव ते प्रोक्ते पक्षिणोर्वैनतेययोः ||२||` | "And you have mentioned the names of the two birds, sons of Vinatā [Garuḍa and Aruṇa]. ||2||" |
| `Line 4206: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4207: पन्नगानां तु नामानि न कीर्तयसि सूतज |` | "But you do not mention the names of the serpents, O son of Sūta," |
| `Line 4208: प्राधान्येनापि नामानि श्रोतुमिच्छामहे वयम् ||३||` | "We wish to hear the names, especially the prominent ones. ||3||" |
| `Line 4209: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4210: सूत उवाच||` | "Sūta [narrator] said:" |
| `Line 4211: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4212: बहुत्वान्नामधेयानि भुजगानां तपोधन |` | "Due to their great number, the names of the serpents, O Tapodhana [ascetic]," |
| `Line 4213: न कीर्तयिष्ये सर्वेषां प्राधान्येन तु मे शृणु ||४||` | "I will not recite all of them, but listen to me as I name the principal ones. ||4||" |
| `Line 4214: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4215: शेषः प्रथमतो जातो वासुकिस्तदनन्तरम् |` | "Śeṣa [cosmic serpent] was born first, then Vāsuki [serpent king]," |
| `Line 4216: ऐरावतस्तक्षकश्च कर्कोटकधनञ्जयौ ||५||` | "Airāvata, Takṣaka, and Karkoṭaka and Dhanañjaya. ||5||" |
| `Line 4217: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4218: कालियो मणिनागश्च नागश्चापूरणस्तथा |` | "Kāliya [poisonous serpent], Maṇināga, and the serpent Āpūraṇa as well," |
| `Line 4219: नागस्तथा पिञ्जरक एलापत्रोऽथ वामनः ||६||` | "And the serpent Piñjaraka, Elāpatra, and Vāmana. ||6||" |
| `Line 4220: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4221: नीलानीलौ तथा नागौ कल्माषशबलौ तथा |` | "The serpents Nīla and Anīla, as well as Kalmāṣa and Śabala," |
| `Line 4222: आर्यकश्चादिकश्चैव नागश्च शलपोतकः ||७||` | "Āryaka and Ādika, and the serpent Śalapotaka. ||7||" |
| `Line 4223: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4224: सुमनोमुखो दधिमुखस्तथा विमलपिण्डकः |` | "Sumanomukha, Dadhimukha, and Vimalapiṇḍaka," |
| `Line 4225: आप्तः कोटनकश्चैव शङ्खो वालशिखस्तथा ||८||` | "Āpta, Koṭanaka, and Śaṅkha and Vālaśikha as well. ||8||" |
| `Line 4226: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4227: निष्ठ्यूनको हेमगुहो नहुषः पिङ्गलस्तथा |` | "Niṣṭhyūnaka, Hemaguha, Nahuṣa [ancient king], and Piṅgala," |
| `Line 4228: बाह्यकर्णो हस्तिपदस्तथा मुद्गरपिण्डकः ||९||` | "Bāhyakarṇa, Hastipada, and Mudgarapiṇḍaka. ||9||" |
| `Line 4229: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4230: कम्बलाश्वतरौ चापि नागः कालीयकस्तथा |` | "Kambala and Aśvatara, and also the serpent Kālīyaka [black serpent]," |
| `Line 4231: वृत्तसंवर्तकौ नागौ द्वौ च पद्माविति श्रुतौ ||१०||` | "The two serpents Vṛtta and Saṃvartaka, and the two known as Padma. ||10||" |
| `Line 4232: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4233: नागः शङ्खनकश्चैव तथा च स्फण्डकोऽपरः |` | "The serpent Śaṅkhanaka, and also another named Sphaṇḍaka," |
| `Line 4234: क्षेमकश्च महानागो नागः पिण्डारकस्तथा ||११||` | "And Kṣemaka the great serpent, and the serpent Piṇḍāraka. ||11||" |
| `Line 4235: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4236: करवीरः पुष्पदंष्ट्र एळको बिल्वपाण्डुकः |` | "Karavīra, Puṣpadaṃṣṭra, Eḷaka, Bilvapāṇḍuka," |
| `Line 4237: मूषकादः शङ्खशिराः पूर्णदंष्ट्रो हरिद्रकः ||१२||` | "Mūṣakāda, Śaṅkaśirāḥ, Pūrṇadaṃṣṭra, and Haridrakā. ||12||" |
| `Line 4238: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4239: अपराजितो ज्योतिकश्च पन्नगः श्रीवहस्तथा |` | "Aparājita [unconquered], Jyotika, the serpent Śrīvaha," |
| `Line 4240: कौरव्यो धृतराष्ट्रश्च पुष्करः शल्यकस्तथा ||१३||` | "Kauravya, Dhṛtarāṣṭra [blind king], Puṣkara, and Śalyaka. ||13||" |
| `Line 4241: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4242: विरजाश्च सुबाहुश्च शालिपिण्डश्च वीर्यवान् |` | "Virajā, Subāhu, and the mighty Śālipiṇḍa," |
| `Line 4243: हस्तिभद्रः पिठरको मुखरः कोणवासनः ||१४||` | "Hastibhadra, Piṭharaka, Mukhara, and Koṇavāsana. ||14||" |
| `Line 4244: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4245: कुञ्जरः कुररश्चैव तथा नागः प्रभाकरः |` | "Kuñjara, Kurara, and also the serpent Prabhākara [light-maker]," |
| `Line 4246: कुमुदः कुमुदाक्षश्च तित्तिरिर्हलिकस्तथा ||१५||` | "Kumuda, Kumudākṣa, Tittiri, and Halika. ||15||" |
| `Line 4247: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4248: कर्कराकर्करौ चोभौ कुण्डोदरमहोदरौ ||१५||` | "Both Karkara and Akarkara, and Kuṇḍodara and Mahodara. ||15||" |
| `Line 4249: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4250: एते प्राधान्यतो नागाः कीर्तिता द्विजसत्तम |` | "These are the principal serpents [nāgas] mentioned, O best of the twice-born [Brahmin]," |
| `Line 4251: बहुत्वान्नामधेयानामितरे न प्रकीर्तिताः ||१६||` | "Due to the multitude of names, the others have not been enumerated. ||16||" |
| `Line 4252: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4253: एतेषां प्रसवो यश्च प्रसवस्य च सन्ततिः |` | "Their offspring and the progeny of that offspring," |
| `Line 4254: असङ्ख्येयेति मत्वा तान्न ब्रवीमि द्विजोत्तम ||१७||` | "Considering them to be innumerable, I do not describe them, O best of the twice-born [Brahmin]. ||17||" |
| `Line 4255: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4256: बहूनीह सहस्राणि प्रयुतान्यर्बुदानि च |` | "Many thousands, millions, and hundreds of millions," |
| `Line 4257: अशक्यान्येव सङ्ख्यातुं भुजगानां तपोधन ||१८||` | "It is impossible to count the serpents, O wealth of austerities [ascetic sage]. ||18||" |
| `Line 4258: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4259: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4260: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4261: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4262: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4263: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4264: ३२` | "32" |
| `Line 4265: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4266: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4267: शौनक उवाच||` | "Śaunaka [sage, listener] said:" |
| `Line 4268: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4269: जाता वै भुजगास्तात वीर्यवन्तो दुरासदाः |` | "Born indeed were the serpents, dear one, powerful and unapproachable," |
| `Line 4270: शापं तं त्वथ विज्ञाय कृतवन्तो नु किं परम् ||१||` | "After knowing that curse, what else did they do? ||1||" |
| `Line 4271: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4272: सूत उवाच||` | "Sūta [bard/narrator] said:" |
| `Line 4273: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4274: तेषां तु भगवाञ्शेषस्त्यक्त्वा कद्रूं महायशाः |` | "Among them, the illustrious lord Śeṣa [cosmic serpent], abandoning Kadrū [serpent mother]," |
| `Line 4275: तपो विपुलमातस्थे वायुभक्षो यतव्रतः ||२||` | "Engaged in intense austerities, subsisting on air, with controlled vows. ||2||" |
| `Line 4276: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4277: गन्धमादनमासाद्य बदर्यां च तपोरतः |` | "Having reached Gandhamādana [fragrant mountain] and engaged in austerities at Badarī [sacred place]," |
| `Line 4278: गोकर्णे पुष्करारण्ये तथा हिमवतस्तटे ||३||` | "At Gokarṇa [cow's ear site], in Puṣkarāraṇya [lotus forest], and on the slopes of Himavat [Himalayas]. ||3||" |
| `Line 4279: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4280: तेषु तेषु च पुण्येषु तीर्थेष्वायतनेषु च |` | "In those various sacred tīrthas [pilgrimage sites] and temples," |
| `Line 4281: एकान्तशीली नियतः सततं विजितेन्द्रियः ||४||` | "Solitary in habit, disciplined, and always with conquered senses. ||4||" |
| `Line 4282: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4283: तप्यमानं तपो घोरं तं ददर्श पितामहः |` | "Pitāmaha [Brahmā] saw him performing terrible austerities," |
| `Line 4284: परिशुष्कमांसत्वक्स्नायुं जटाचीरधरं प्रभुम् ||५||` | "With dried-up flesh, skin and sinews, wearing matted locks and bark garments, the mighty one. ||5||" |
| `Line 4285: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4286: तमब्रवीत्सत्यधृतिं तप्यमानं पितामहः |` | "Pitāmaha [Brahmā] spoke to Satyadhṛti [Śeṣa, truth-steadfast] who was performing austerities," |
| `Line 4287: किमिदं कुरुषे शेष प्रजानां स्वस्ति वै कुरु ||६||` | "Why are you doing this, Śeṣa? Ensure the welfare of all creatures. ||6||" |
| `Line 4288: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4289: त्वं हि तीव्रेण तपसा प्रजास्तापयसेऽनघ |` | "With your intense austerities, you are causing distress to creatures, O sinless one," |
| `Line 4290: ब्रूहि कामं च मे शेष यत्ते हृदि चिरं स्थितम् ||७||` | "Tell me your desire, Śeṣa, that which has long resided in your heart. ||7||" |
| `Line 4291: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4292: शेष उवाच||` | "Śeṣa [serpent king] said:" |
| `Line 4293: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4294: सोदर्या मम सर्वे हि भ्रातरो मन्दचेतसः |` | "All my brothers born of the same womb are dull-witted," |
| `Line 4295: सह तैर्नोत्सहे वस्तुं तद्भवाननुमन्यताम् ||८||` | "I cannot bear to live with them; may you approve of this. ||8||" |
| `Line 4296: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4297: अभ्यसूयन्ति सततं परस्परममित्रवत् |` | "They constantly envy each other like enemies," |
| `Line 4298: ततोऽहं तप आतिष्ठे नैतान्पश्येयमित्युत ||९||` | "Therefore I undertake these austerities so that I may not see them again. ||9||" |
| `Line 4299: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4300: न मर्षयन्ति सततं विनतां ससुतां च ते |` | "They constantly cannot tolerate Vinatā [Garuḍa's mother] and her son," |
| `Line 4301: अस्माकं चापरो भ्राता वैनतेयः पितामह ||१०||` | "And we have another brother, Vainateya [son of Vinatā], O Pitāmaha [grandfather]. ||10||" |
| `Line 4302: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4303: तं च द्विषन्ति तेऽत्यर्थं स चापि सुमहाबलः |` | "They hate him exceedingly, and he too is of tremendous strength," |
| `Line 4304: वरप्रदानात्स पितुः कश्यपस्य महात्मनः ||११||` | "Due to the boon granted by our father, the great-souled Kaśyapa. ||11||" |
| `Line 4305: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4306: सोऽहं तपः समास्थाय मोक्ष्यामीदं कलेवरम् |` | "I, having undertaken austerities, will abandon this body," |
| `Line 4307: कथं मे प्रेत्यभावेऽपि न तैः स्यात्सह सङ्गमः ||१२||` | "How can I avoid association with them even after death? ||12||" |
| `Line 4308: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4309: ब्रह्मोवाच||` | "Brahmā [creator deity] said:" |
| `Line 4310: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4311: जानामि शेष सर्वेषां भ्रातृणां ते विचेष्टितम् |` | "I know, Śeṣa, the conduct of all your brothers," |
| `Line 4312: मातुश्चाप्यपराधाद्वै भ्रातृणां ते महद्भयम् ||१३||` | "And indeed due to your mother's offense, there is great fear from your brothers. ||13||" |
| `Line 4313: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4314: कृतोऽत्र परिहारश्च पूर्वमेव भुजङ्गम |` | "A remedy for this has already been made, O serpent," |
| `Line 4315: भ्रातृणां तव सर्वेषां न शोकं कर्तुमर्हसि ||१४||` | "You should not grieve about all your brothers. ||14||" |
| `Line 4316: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4317: वृणीष्व च वरं मत्तः शेष यत्तेऽभिकाङ्क्षितम् |` | "Choose a boon from me, Śeṣa, whatever you desire," |
| `Line 4318: दित्सामि हि वरं तेऽद्य प्रीतिर्मे परमा त्वयि ||१५||` | "For I wish to give you a boon today, as I am extremely pleased with you. ||15||" |
| `Line 4319: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4320: दिष्ट्या च बुद्धिर्धर्मे ते निविष्टा पन्नगोत्तम |` | "Fortunately, your mind is established in dharma [righteousness], O best of serpents," |
| `Line 4321: अतो भूयश्च ते बुद्धिर्धर्मे भवतु सुस्थिरा ||१६||` | "Therefore, may your mind be even more firmly established in dharma. ||16||" |
| `Line 4322: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4323: शेष उवाच||` | "Śeṣa [serpent king] said:" |
| `Line 4324: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4325: एष एव वरो मेऽद्य काङ्क्षितः प्रपितामह |` | "This indeed is the boon I desire today, O Prapitāmaha [great grandfather]," |
| `Line 4326: धर्मे मे रमतां बुद्धिः शमे तपसि चेश्वर ||१७||` | "May my mind delight in dharma [righteousness], in tranquility, and in austerity, O Lord. ||17||" |
| `Line 4327: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4328: ब्रह्मोवाच||` | "Brahmā [creator deity] said:" |
| `Line 4329: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4330: प्रीतोऽस्म्यनेन ते शेष दमेन प्रशमेन च |` | "I am pleased, O Śeṣa, with your self-control and tranquility," |
| `Line 4331: त्वया त्विदं वचः कार्यं मन्नियोगात्प्रजाहितम् ||१८||` | "But you must fulfill this command from me for the welfare of all creatures. ||18||" |
| `Line 4332: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4333: इमां महीं शैलवनोपपन्नां; ससागरां साकरपत्तनां च |` | "This earth, endowed with mountains and forests, with oceans, mines and cities," |
| `Line 4334: त्वं शेष सम्यक्चलितां यथाव; त्सङ्गृह्य तिष्ठस्व यथाचला स्यात् ||१९||` | "You, Śeṣa, should properly hold it when it moves, so that it becomes stable. ||19||" |
| `Line 4335: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4336: शेष उवाच||` | "Śeṣa [serpent deity] said:" |
| `Line 4337: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4338: यथाह देवो वरदः प्रजापति; र्महीपतिर्भूतपतिर्जगत्पतिः |` | "As commands the boon-giving god, Prajāpati [lord of creatures], lord of the earth, lord of beings, lord of the universe," |
| `Line 4339: तथा महीं धारयितास्मि निश्चलां; प्रयच्छ तां मे शिरसि प्रजापते ||२०||` | "So shall I hold the earth steady; place it upon my head, O Prajāpati. ||20||" |
| `Line 4340: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4341: ब्रह्मोवाच||` | "Brahmā said:" |
| `Line 4342: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4343: अधो महीं गच्छ भुजङ्गमोत्तम; स्वयं तवैषा विवरं प्रदास्यति |` | "Go beneath the earth, O best of serpents; it will itself create an opening for you," |
| `Line 4344: इमां धरां धारयता त्वया हि मे; महत्प्रियं शेष कृतं भविष्यति ||२१||` | "By supporting this earth, O Śeṣa, you will have done me a great favor. ||21||" |
| `Line 4345: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4346: सूत उवाच||` | "Sūta [bard/narrator] said:" |
| `Line 4347: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4348: तथेति कृत्वा विवरं प्रविश्य स; प्रभुर्भुवो भुजगवराग्रजः स्थितः |` | "Having said 'So be it,' he entered through the opening; the lord of the earth, the foremost of serpents, positioned himself," |
| `Line 4349: बिभर्ति देवीं शिरसा महीमिमां; समुद्रनेमिं परिगृह्य सर्वतः ||२२||` | "He bears this divine earth on his head, supporting it completely with its ocean boundaries. ||22||" |
| `Line 4350: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4351: ब्रह्मोवाच॥` | "Brahmā [creator deity] said:" |
| `Line 4352: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4353: शेषोऽसि नागोत्तम धर्मदेवो; महीमिमां धारयसे यदेकः |` | "You are Śeṣa, O best of Nāgas [serpent beings], the god of dharma [righteousness]; you alone support this earth," |
| `Line 4354: अनन्तभोगः परिगृह्य सर्वां; यथाहमेवं बलभिद्यथा वा ॥२३॥` | "With your infinite coils encompassing all of it; just as I do, or as Balabhid [Indra] does. ||23||" |
| `Line 4355: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4356: सूत उवाच॥` | "Sūta [bard/narrator] said:" |
| `Line 4357: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4358: अधो भूमेर्वसत्येवं नागोऽनन्तः प्रतापवान् |` | "Thus below the earth dwells the mighty serpent Ananta [the endless one]," |
| `Line 4359: धारयन्वसुधामेकः शासनाद्ब्रह्मणो विभुः ॥२४॥` | "Supporting the earth alone, by the command of Brahmā, the all-pervading lord. ||24||" |
| `Line 4360: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4361: सुपर्णं च सखायं वै भगवानमरोत्तमः |` | "And the divine lord, foremost among immortals [Brahmā]," |
| `Line 4362: प्रादादनन्ताय तदा वैनतेयं पितामहः ॥२५॥` | "Gave Suparṇa [Garuḍa], the son of Vinatā, as a friend to Ananta then, did the Grandfather [Brahmā]. ||25||" |
| `Line 4363: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4364: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4365: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4366: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4367: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4368: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4369: ३३` | "33" |
| `Line 4370: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4371: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4372: सूत उवाच॥` | "Sūta [bard/narrator] said:" |
| `Line 4373: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4374: मातुः सकाशात्तं शापं श्रुत्वा पन्नगसत्तमः |` | "Having heard that curse from his mother, the foremost of serpents," |
| `Line 4375: वासुकिश्चिन्तयामास शापोऽयं न भवेत्कथम् ॥१॥` | "Vāsuki pondered, 'How might this curse not come to pass?' ||1||" |
| `Line 4376: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4377: ततः स मन्त्रयामास भ्रातृभिः सह सर्वशः |` | "Then he consulted thoroughly with his brothers," |
| `Line 4378: ऐरावतप्रभृतिभिर्ये स्म धर्मपरायणाः ||२||` | "With Airāvata [chief serpent] and others who were devoted to dharma [righteousness]. ||2||" |
| `Line 4379: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4380: वासुकिरुवाच||` | "Vāsuki [serpent king] said:" |
| `Line 4381: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4382: अयं शापो यथोद्दिष्टो विदितं वस्तथानघाः |` | "This curse as proclaimed is known to you all, O sinless ones," |
| `Line 4383: तस्य शापस्य मोक्षार्थं मन्त्रयित्वा यतामहे ||३||` | "Let us consult together and strive for liberation from that curse. ||3||" |
| `Line 4384: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4385: सर्वेषामेव शापानां प्रतिघातो हि विद्यते |` | "For all curses indeed, there exists a counteraction," |
| `Line 4386: न तु मात्राभिशप्तानां मोक्षो विद्येत पन्नगाः ||४||` | "But for those cursed by a mother, O serpents, there may be no release. ||4||" |
| `Line 4387: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4388: अव्ययस्याप्रमेयस्य सत्यस्य च तथाग्रतः |` | "In the presence of the imperishable, immeasurable, and truthful one," |
| `Line 4389: शप्ता इत्येव मे श्रुत्वा जायते हृदि वेपथुः ||५||` | "Hearing that we are cursed, trembling arises in my heart. ||5||" |
| `Line 4390: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4391: नूनं सर्वविनाशोऽयमस्माकं समुदाहृतः |` | "Surely this complete destruction of ours has been pronounced," |
| `Line 4392: न ह्येनां सोऽव्ययो देवः शपन्तीं प्रत्यषेधयत् ||६||` | "For that imperishable god did not restrain her when she was cursing. ||6||" |
| `Line 4393: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4394: तस्मात्संमन्त्रयामोऽत्र भुजगानामनामयम् |` | "Therefore, let us consult here about the welfare of the serpents," |
| `Line 4395: यथा भवेत सर्वेषां मा नः कालोऽत्यगादयम् ||७||` | "So that it may be good for all, lest this time of doom overtake us. ||7||" |
| `Line 4396: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4397: अपि मन्त्रयमाणा हि हेतुं पश्याम मोक्षणे |` | "Perhaps by consulting, we may see a means for liberation," |
| `Line 4398: यथा नष्टं पुरा देवा गूढमग्निं गुहागतम् ||८||` | "Just as the gods once found the lost fire [Agni] hidden in a cave. ||8||" |
| `Line 4399: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4400: यथा स यज्ञो न भवेद्यथा वापि पराभवेत् |` | "So that the sacrifice may not take place, or that it may be defeated," |
| `Line 4401: जनमेजयस्य सर्पाणां विनाशकरणाय हि ||९||` | "For the destruction of the serpents by Janamejaya [Pāṇḍava king]. ||9||" |
| `Line 4402: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4403: सूत उवाच||` | "Sūta [bard/narrator] said:" |
| `Line 4404: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4405: तथेत्युक्त्वा तु ते सर्वे काद्रवेयाः समागताः |` | "Having said 'so be it,' all those Kādraveyās [serpent sons of Kadrū] assembled together," |
| `Line 4406: समयं चक्रिरे तत्र मन्त्रबुद्धिविशारदाः ||१०||` | "And there they made a plan, being skilled in deliberation and counsel. ||10||" |
| `Line 4407: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4408: एके तत्राब्रुवन्नागा वयं भूत्वा द्विजर्षभाः |` | "Some serpents there said, 'We shall become Brāhmaṇas [twice-born bulls]," |
| `Line 4409: जनमेजयं तं भिक्षामो यज्ञस्ते न भवेदिति ||११||` | "And beg Janamejaya saying, 'May your sacrifice not take place.'" ||11||" |
| `Line 4410: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4411: अपरे त्वब्रुवन्नागास्तत्र पण्डितमानिनः |` | "But other serpents there, considering themselves learned, said," |
| `Line 4412: मन्त्रिणोऽस्य वयं सर्वे भविष्यामः सुसंमताः ||१२||` | "'We all shall become his highly respected counselors. ||12||" |
| `Line 4413: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4414: स नः प्रक्ष्यति सर्वेषु कार्येष्वर्थविनिश्चयम् |` | "'He will ask us for decisions on all matters of importance," |
| `Line 4415: तत्र बुद्धिं प्रवक्ष्यामो यथा यज्ञो निवर्तते ||१३||` | "'Then we shall give such advice that the sacrifice will be stopped. ||13||" |
| `Line 4416: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4417: स नो बहुमतान्राजा बुद्ध्वा बुद्धिमतां वरः |` | "'The king, considering us highly esteemed and being the best among the wise," |
| `Line 4418: यज्ञार्थं प्रक्ष्यति व्यक्तं नेति वक्ष्यामहे वयम् ||१४||` | "'Will surely ask us about the sacrifice, and we shall say 'no.' ||14||" |
| `Line 4419: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4420: दर्शयन्तो बहून्दोषान्प्रेत्य चेह च दारुणान् |` | "'Showing many terrible faults both in the afterlife and here," |
| `Line 4421: हेतुभिः कारणैश्चैव यथा यज्ञो भवेन्न सः ||१५||` | "'With reasons and causes so that the sacrifice may not take place.' ||15||" |
| `Line 4422: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4423: अथवा य उपाध्यायः क्रतौ तस्मिन्भविष्यति |` | "'Or else, whoever will be the preceptor [teacher] in that sacrifice," |
| `Line 4424: सर्पसत्रविधानज्ञो राजकार्यहिते रतः ||१६||` | "'Knowledgeable in the rules of the serpent sacrifice and devoted to the king's welfare, ||16||" |
| `Line 4425: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4426: तं गत्वा दशतां कश्चिद्भुजगः स मरिष्यति |` | "Going there, some serpent will bite him and die," |
| `Line 4427: तस्मिन्हते यज्ञकरे क्रतुः स न भविष्यति ||१७||` | "With that sacrificer killed, the sacrifice will not take place. ||17||" |
| `Line 4428: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4429: ये चान्ये सर्पसत्रज्ञा भविष्यन्त्यस्य ऋत्विजः |` | "And those others who are knowledgeable in serpent-sacrifices who will be his priests [ṛtvij]," |
| `Line 4430: तांश्च सर्वान्दशिष्यामः कृतमेवं भविष्यति ||१८||` | "We shall bite all of them too, thus it will be accomplished. ||18||" |
| `Line 4431: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4432: तत्रापरेऽमन्त्रयन्त धर्मात्मानो भुजङ्गमाः |` | "Then other righteous serpents [bhujangama] counseled there," |
| `Line 4433: अबुद्धिरेषा युष्माकं ब्रह्महत्या न शोभना ||१९||` | "This is unwise of you; killing a Brahmin [brahmahatya] is not virtuous. ||19||" |
| `Line 4434: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4435: सम्यक्सद्धर्ममूला हि व्यसने शान्तिरुत्तमा |` | "Indeed, the highest peace in calamity is rooted in proper righteousness [dharma]," |
| `Line 4436: अधर्मोत्तरता नाम कृत्स्नं व्यापादयेज्जगत् ||२०||` | "Predominance of unrighteousness [adharma] would destroy the entire world. ||20||" |
| `Line 4437: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4438: अपरे त्वब्रुवन्नागाः समिद्धं जातवेदसम् |` | "But other serpents [nāga] said, 'The blazing fire [jātavedas]," |
| `Line 4439: वर्षैर्निर्वापयिष्यामो मेघा भूत्वा सविद्युतः ||२१||` | "We shall extinguish with rains, becoming clouds with lightning.' ||21||" |
| `Line 4440: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4441: स्रुग्भाण्डं निशि गत्वा वा अपरे भुजगोत्तमाः |` | "Or other excellent serpents [bhujagottama] said, 'Going at night to the sacrificial vessels [srugbhāṇḍa]," |
| `Line 4442: प्रमत्तानां हरन्त्वाशु विघ्न एवं भविष्यति ||२२||` | "Let them quickly steal them from the careless ones; thus there will be an obstacle.' ||22||" |
| `Line 4443: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4444: यज्ञे वा भुजगास्तस्मिञ्शतशोऽथ सहस्रशः |` | "Or at that sacrifice, let serpents by hundreds and thousands," |
| `Line 4445: जनं दशन्तु वै सर्वमेवं त्रासो भविष्यति ||२३||` | "Bite all the people; thus there will be terror. ||23||" |
| `Line 4446: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4447: अथवा संस्कृतं भोज्यं दूषयन्तु भुजङ्गमाः |` | "Or let the serpents contaminate the prepared food," |
| `Line 4448: स्वेन मूत्रपुरीषेण सर्वभोज्यविनाशिना ||२४||` | "With their urine and feces that destroy all food. ||24||" |
| `Line 4449: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4450: अपरे त्वब्रुवंस्तत्र ऋत्विजोऽस्य भवामहे |` | "But others said there, 'Let us become his priests [ṛtvij]," |
| `Line 4451: यज्ञविघ्नं करिष्यामो दीयतां दक्षिणा इति ||२५||` | "We will create an obstacle to the sacrifice; let the sacrificial fee be given, thus. ||25||" |
| `Line 4452: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4453: वश्यतां च गतोऽसौ नः करिष्यति यथेप्षितम् ||२५||` | "And having come under our control, he will do as we desire. ||25||" |
| `Line 4454: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4455: अपरे त्वब्रुवंस्तत्र जले प्रक्रीडितं नृपम् |` | "But others said there: 'Let us seize the king while he is sporting in water," |
| `Line 4456: गृहमानीय बध्नीमः क्रतुरेवं भवेन्न सः ||२६||` | "Bring him to our abode and bind him; thus the sacrifice will not take place.' ||26||" |
| `Line 4457: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4458: अपरे त्वब्रुवंस्तत्र नागाः सुकृतकारिणः |` | "But other serpents [nāgas], skilled in action, said there:" |
| `Line 4459: दशामैनं प्रगृह्याशु कृतमेवं भविष्यति ||२७||` | "'Let us quickly seize him by his garment's edge; thus it will be accomplished. ||27||" |
| `Line 4460: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4461: छिन्नं मूलमनर्थानां मृते तस्मिन्भविष्यति ||२७||` | "When he is dead, the root of our calamities will be cut off.' ||27||" |
| `Line 4462: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4463: एषा वै नैष्ठिकी बुद्धिः सर्वेषामेव संमता |` | "This indeed is the final decision approved by all," |
| `Line 4464: यथा वा मन्यसे राजंस्तत्क्षिप्रं संविधीयताम् ||२८||` | "Or as you think, O king [serpent king], let that be quickly arranged.' ||28||" |
| `Line 4465: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4466: इत्युक्त्वा समुदैक्षन्त वासुकिं पन्नगेश्वरम् |` | "Having spoken thus, they looked toward Vāsuki, the lord of serpents [pannageśvara]," |
| `Line 4467: वासुकिश्चापि सञ्चिन्त्य तानुवाच भुजङ्गमान् ||२९||` | "And Vāsuki, having reflected, said to those serpents [bhujangama]: ||29||" |
| `Line 4468: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4469: नैषा वो नैष्ठिकी बुद्धिर्मता कर्तुं भुजङ्गमाः |` | "'This final decision of yours is not acceptable to execute, O serpents [bhujangama]," |
| `Line 4470: सर्वेषामेव मे बुद्धिः पन्नगानां न रोचते ||३०||` | "My opinion does not please all the serpents [pannaga]. ||30||" |
| `Line 4471: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4472: किं त्वत्र संविधातव्यं भवतां यद्भवेद्धितम् |` | "However, what should be arranged here that would be beneficial for you?" |
| `Line 4473: अनेनाहं भृशं तप्ये गुणदोषौ मदाश्रयौ ||३१||` | "I am greatly tormented by this, as the merits and faults rest with me.' ||31||" |
| `Line 4474: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4475: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4476: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4477: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4478: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4479: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4480: ३४` | "34" |
| `Line 4481: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4482: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4483: सूत उवाच||` | "Sūta [bard/narrator] said:" |
| `Line 4484: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4485: श्रुत्वा तु वचनं तेषां सर्वेषामिति चेति च |` | "Having heard the words of all of them, thus and thus," |
| `Line 4486: वासुकेश्च वचः श्रुत्वा एलापत्रोऽब्रवीदिदम् ||१||` | "And having heard the words of Vāsuki [serpent king], Elāpatra [serpent sage] spoke this. ||1||" |
| `Line 4487: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4488: न स यज्ञो न भविता न स राजा तथाविधः |` | "That sacrifice will not happen, nor will that king be of such nature," |
| `Line 4489: जनमेजयः पाण्डवेयो यतोऽस्माकं महाभयम् ||२||` | "Janamejaya, the descendant of Pāṇḍu, from whom comes our great fear. ||2||" |
| `Line 4490: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4491: दैवेनोपहतो राजन्यो भवेदिह पूरुषः |` | "A person who is struck down by fate in this world, O king," |
| `Line 4492: स दैवमेवाश्रयते नान्यत्तत्र परायणम् ||३||` | "He takes refuge in fate alone, there is no other recourse there. ||3||" |
| `Line 4493: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4494: तदिदं दैवमस्माकं भयं पन्नगसत्तमाः |` | "This fear of ours is fated, O best of serpents [pannaga-sattamāḥ]," |
| `Line 4495: दैवमेवाश्रयामोऽत्र शृणुध्वं च वचो मम ||४||` | "Let us take refuge in fate alone here, and listen to my words. ||4||" |
| `Line 4496: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4497: अहं शापे समुत्सृष्टे समश्रौषं वचस्तदा |` | "When the curse was pronounced, I heard those words then," |
| `Line 4498: मातुरुत्सङ्गमारूढो भयात्पन्नगसत्तमाः ||५||` | "While sitting on my mother's lap, out of fear, O best of serpents. ||5||" |
| `Line 4499: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4500: देवानां पन्नगश्रेष्ठास्तीक्ष्णास्तीक्ष्णा इति प्रभो |` | "The gods (said), 'O best of serpents, fierce, fierce,' thus, O lord," |
| `Line 4501: पितामहमुपागम्य दुःखार्तानां महाद्युते ||६||` | "Having approached Pitāmaha [Brahmā], O greatly radiant one, in their grief-stricken state. ||6||" |
| `Line 4502: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4503: देवा ऊचुः||` | "The gods said:" |
| `Line 4504: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4505: का हि लब्ध्वा प्रियान्पुत्राञ्शपेदेवं पितामह |` | "Who indeed, after obtaining beloved sons, would curse them thus, O Pitāmaha [Brahmā]," |
| `Line 4506: ऋते कद्रूं तीक्ष्णरूपां देवदेव तवाग्रतः ||७||` | "Except Kadrū of fierce nature, O God of gods, in your presence? ||7||" |
| `Line 4507: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4508: तथेति च वचस्तस्यास्त्वयाप्युक्तं पितामह |` | "And you also said 'so be it' to her words, O Pitāmaha [Brahmā]," |
| `Line 4509: एतदिच्छाम विज्ञातुं कारणं यन्न वारिता ||८||` | "We wish to know the reason why she was not stopped. ||8||" |
| `Line 4510: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4511: ब्रह्मोवाच||` | "Brahmā said:" |
| `Line 4512: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4513: बहवः पन्नगास्तीक्ष्णा भीमवीर्या विषोल्बणाः |` | "Many serpents are fierce, of terrible power, and excessive venom," |
| `Line 4514: प्रजानां हितकामोऽहं न निवारितवांस्तदा ||९||` | "Desiring the welfare of creatures, I did not prevent it then. ||9||" |
| `Line 4515: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4516: ये दन्दशूकाः क्षुद्राश्च पापचारा विषोल्बणाः |` | "Those serpents who are biters, vile, of evil conduct, with excessive venom," |
| `Line 4517: तेषां विनाशो भविता न तु ये धर्मचारिणः ||१०||` | "Their destruction will come about, but not of those who follow dharma [righteousness]. ||10||" |
| `Line 4518: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4519: यन्निमित्तं च भविता मोक्षस्तेषां महाभयात् |` | "And the cause by which there will be liberation for them from this great fear," |
| `Line 4520: पन्नगानां निबोधध्वं तस्मिन्काले तथागते ||११||` | "Of the serpents, understand this when that time comes. ||11||" |
| `Line 4521: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4522: यायावरकुले धीमान्भविष्यति महानृषिः |` | "In the Yāyāvara [wandering ascetic] family, there will be a wise great sage," |
| `Line 4523: जरत्कारुरिति ख्यातस्तेजस्वी नियतेन्द्रियः ||१२||` | "Known as Jaratkāru, radiant and with controlled senses. ||12||" |
| `Line 4524: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4525: तस्य पुत्रो जरत्कारोरुत्पत्स्यति महातपाः |` | "A son of that Jaratkāru will be born, of great austerity," |
| `Line 4526: आस्तीको नाम यज्ञं स प्रतिषेत्स्यति तं तदा ||१३||` | "One named Āstīka will stop that sacrifice then. ||13||" |
| `Line 4527: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4528: तत्र मोक्ष्यन्ति भुजगा ये भविष्यन्ति धार्मिकाः ||१३||` | "There the serpents who will be righteous shall be freed. ||13||" |
| `Line 4529: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4530: देवा ऊचुः||` | "The gods said:" |
| `Line 4531: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4532: स मुनिप्रवरो देव जरत्कारुर्महातपाः |` | "O god, that eminent sage Jaratkāru of great austerity," |
| `Line 4533: कस्यां पुत्रं महात्मानं जनयिष्यति वीर्यवान् ||१४||` | "In which woman will that powerful one beget a noble son? ||14||" |
| `Line 4534: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4535: ब्रह्मोवाच||` | "Brahmā [creator deity] said:" |
| `Line 4536: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4537: सनामायां सनामा स कन्यायां द्विजसत्तमः |` | "That foremost of twice-born [Brahmin], having the same name, in a maiden of the same name," |
| `Line 4538: अपत्यं वीर्यवान्देवा वीर्यवज्जनयिष्यति ||१५||` | "The powerful one will beget, O gods, a powerful offspring. ||15||" |
| `Line 4539: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4540: एलापत्र उवाच||` | "Elāpatra [serpent sage] said:" |
| `Line 4541: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4542: एवमस्त्विति तं देवाः पितामहमथाब्रुवन् |` | "The gods then said to Pitāmaha [Brahmā], 'Let it be so,'" |
| `Line 4543: उक्त्वा चैवं गता देवाः स च देवः पितामहः ||१६||` | "Having spoken thus, the gods departed, and so did the god Pitāmaha [Brahmā]. ||16||" |
| `Line 4544: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4545: सोऽहमेवं प्रपश्यामि वासुके भगिनीं तव |` | "Thus I foresee, O Vāsuki, that your sister," |
| `Line 4546: जरत्कारुरिति ख्यातां तां तस्मै प्रतिपादय ||१७||` | "Known as Jaratkāru, should be given by you to him. ||17||" |
| `Line 4547: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4548: भैक्षवद्भिक्षमाणाय नागानां भयशान्तये |` | "To him who begs like a mendicant, for the pacification of the serpents' fear," |
| `Line 4549: ऋषये सुव्रताय त्वमेष मोक्षः श्रुतो मया ||१८||` | "To the sage of good vows—this is the deliverance that I have heard. ||18||" |
| `Line 4550: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4551: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4552: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4553: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4554: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4555: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4556: ३५` | "35" |
| `Line 4557: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4558: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4559: सूत उवाच||` | "Sūta [bard/narrator] said:" |
| `Line 4560: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4561: एलापत्रस्य तु वचः श्रुत्वा नागा द्विजोत्तम |` | "Having heard the words of Elāpatra [serpent sage], O best of the twice-born [Brahmin]," |
| `Line 4562: सर्वे प्रहृष्टमनसः साधु साध्वित्यपूजयन् ||१||` | "All the Nāgas [serpents], with delighted minds, honored him saying 'well done, well done.' ||1||" |
| `Line 4563: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4564: ततः प्रभृति तां कन्यां वासुकिः पर्यरक्षत |` | "From then on, Vāsuki [serpent king] protected that maiden," |
| `Line 4565: जरत्कारुं स्वसारं वै परं हर्षमवाप च ||२||` | "His sister Jaratkāru, and experienced supreme joy. ||2||" |
| `Line 4566: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4567: ततो नातिमहान्कालः समतीत इवाभवत् |` | "Then, not a very long time seemed to have passed," |
| `Line 4568: अथ देवासुराः सर्वे ममन्थुर्वरुणालयम् ||३||` | "When all the Devas [gods] and Asuras [demons] churned Varuṇālaya [ocean]. ||3||" |
| `Line 4569: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4570: तत्र नेत्रमभून्नागो वासुकिर्बलिनां वरः |` | "There, Vāsuki, the best among the strong ones, became the rope [churning cord]," |
| `Line 4571: समाप्यैव च तत्कर्म पितामहमुपागमन् ||४||` | "And having completed that task, they approached Pitāmaha [Brahmā]. ||4||" |
| `Line 4572: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4573: देवा वासुकिना सार्धं पितामहमथाब्रुवन् |` | "The gods, together with Vāsuki, then said to Pitāmaha [Brahmā]," |
| `Line 4574: भगवञ्शापभीतोऽयं वासुकिस्तप्यते भृशम् ||५||` | "O Lord, this Vāsuki, afraid of the curse, is greatly tormented. ||5||" |
| `Line 4575: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4576: तस्येदं मानसं शल्यं समुद्धर्तुं त्वमर्हसि |` | "You ought to remove this mental anguish [thorn] of his," |
| `Line 4577: जनन्याः शापजं देव ज्ञातीनां हितकाङ्क्षिणः ||६||` | "O god, which arose from his mother's curse, for he desires the welfare of his relatives. ||6||" |
| `Line 4578: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4579: हितो ह्ययं सदास्माकं प्रियकारी च नागराट् |` | "This king of serpents [Nāgarāṭ] is always beneficial to us and acts kindly," |
| `Line 4580: कुरु प्रसादं देवेश शमयास्य मनोज्वरम् ||७||` | "Grant your favor, O lord of gods, and calm his mental fever. ||7||" |
| `Line 4581: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4582: ब्रह्मोवाच||` | "Brahmā [creator deity] said:" |
| `Line 4583: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4584: मयैवैतद्वितीर्णं वै वचनं मनसामराः |` | "O gods, this promise was indeed given by me," |
| `Line 4585: एलापत्रेण नागेन यदस्याभिहितं पुरा ||८||` | "What was declared earlier by the serpent Elāpatra. ||8||" |
| `Line 4586: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4587: तत्करोत्वेष नागेन्द्रः प्राप्तकालं वचस्तथा |` | "Let this lord of serpents fulfill that promise when the time comes," |
| `Line 4588: विनशिष्यन्ति ये पापा न तु ये धर्मचारिणः ||९||` | "Those who are sinful will perish, but not those who follow dharma [righteousness]. ||9||" |
| `Line 4589: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4590: उत्पन्नः स जरत्कारुस्तपस्युग्रे रतो द्विजः |` | "That Jaratkarū, a twice-born [Brahmin] devoted to severe austerities, has been born," |
| `Line 4591: तस्यैष भगिनीं काले जरत्कारुं प्रयच्छतु ||१०||` | "Let him give his sister Jaratkarū to him at the proper time. ||10||" |
| `Line 4592: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4593: यदेलापत्रेण वचस्तदोक्तं भुजगेन ह |` | "What was said by the serpent Elāpatra," |
| `Line 4594: पन्नगानां हितं देवास्तत्तथा न तदन्यथा ||११||` | "O gods, is for the welfare of the serpents; it shall be so and not otherwise. ||11||" |
| `Line 4595: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4596: सूत उवाच||` | "Sūta [bard/narrator] said:" |
| `Line 4597: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4598: एतच्छ्रुत्वा स नागेन्द्रः पितामहवचस्तदा |` | "Having heard these words of Pitāmaha [Brahmā], that lord of serpents then," |
| `Line 4599: सर्पान्बहूञ्जरत्कारौ नित्ययुक्तान्समादधत् ||१२||` | "Appointed many serpents to constantly keep watch for Jaratkarū. ||12||" |
| `Line 4600: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4601: जरत्कारुर्यदा भार्यामिच्छेद्वरयितुं प्रभुः |` | "When the master Jaratkarū would wish to choose a wife," |
| `Line 4602: शीघ्रमेत्य ममाख्येयं तन्नः श्रेयो भविष्यति ||१३||` | "Coming quickly, he should inform me—that will be beneficial for us. ||13||" |
| `Line 4603: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4604: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4605: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4606: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4607: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4608: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4609: ३६` | "36" |
| `Line 4610: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4611: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4612: शौनक उवाच||` | "Śaunaka [sage, ritual expert] said:" |
| `Line 4613: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4614: जरत्कारुरिति प्रोक्तं यत्त्वया सूतनन्दन |` | "O Sūtanandana [son of Sūta], what you have mentioned about Jaratkarū," |
| `Line 4615: इच्छाम्येतदहं तस्य ऋषेः श्रोतुं महात्मनः ||१||` | "I wish to hear about that great-souled sage. ||1||" |
| `Line 4616: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4617: किं कारणं जरत्कारोर्नामैतत्प्रथितं भुवि |` | "What is the reason this name Jaratkarū became famous on earth?" |
| `Line 4618: जरत्कारुनिरुक्तं त्वं यथावद्वक्तुमर्हसि ||२||` | "You should properly explain the etymology of Jaratkarū. ||2||" |
| `Line 4619: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4620: सूत उवाच||` | "Sūta [bard/narrator] said:" |
| `Line 4621: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4622: जरेति क्षयमाहुर्वै दारुणं कारुसञ्ज्ञितम् |` | "Indeed, 'Jara' means decay, and 'kāru' is known as terrible," |
| `Line 4623: शरीरं कारु तस्यासीत्तत्स धीमाञ्शनैः शनैः ||३||` | "His body was 'kāru' [instrument], and that wise one gradually ||3||" |
| `Line 4624: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4625: क्षपयामास तीव्रेण तपसेत्यत उच्यते |` | "Wasted it away through intense austerities—hence he is called thus." |
| `Line 4626: जरत्कारुरिति ब्रह्मन्वासुकेर्भगिनी तथा ||४||` | "Jaratkarū is her name, O Brahman [learned sage], and she is the sister of Vāsuki [serpent king]. ||4||" |
| `Line 4627: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4628: एवमुक्तस्तु धर्मात्मा शौनकः प्राहसत्तदा |` | "Thus addressed, the righteous Śaunaka [sage] then smiled," |
| `Line 4629: उग्रश्रवसमामन्त्र्य उपपन्नमिति ब्रुवन् ||५||` | "Addressing Ugraśravas [Sūta's name], saying, 'This is appropriate.' ||5||" |
| `Line 4630: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4631: सूत उवाच||` | "Sūta [bard/narrator] said:" |
| `Line 4632: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4633: अथ कालस्य महतः स मुनिः संशितव्रतः |` | "Then, after a long time, that sage of strict vows," |
| `Line 4634: तपस्यभिरतो धीमान्न दारानभ्यकाङ्क्षत ||६||` | "The wise one, devoted to austerities, did not desire a wife. ||6||" |
| `Line 4635: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4636: स ऊर्ध्वरेतास्तपसि प्रसक्तः; स्वाध्यायवान्वीतभयक्लमः सन् |` | "He, practicing celibacy [semen retention], engaged in austerities, devoted to self-study, free from fear and fatigue," |
| `Line 4637: चचार सर्वां पृथिवीं महात्मा; न चापि दारान्मनसाप्यकाङ्क्षत् ||७||` | "The great soul wandered over the entire earth; and did not desire a wife even in his mind. ||7||" |
| `Line 4638: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4639: ततोऽपरस्मिन्सम्प्राप्ते काले कस्मिंश्चिदेव तु |` | "Then, at some later time," |
| `Line 4640: परिक्षिदिति विख्यातो राजा कौरववंशभृत् ||८||` | "A king named Parikṣit [encircler], renowned as the bearer of the Kuru lineage. ||8||" |
| `Line 4641: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4642: यथा पाण्डुर्महाबाहुर्धनुर्धरवरो भुवि |` | "Just as Pāṇḍu [pale one], the mighty-armed, the best archer on earth," |
| `Line 4643: बभूव मृगयाशीलः पुरास्य प्रपितामहः ||९||` | "Was fond of hunting, so was his great-grandfather before him. ||9||" |
| `Line 4644: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4645: मृगान्विध्यन्वराहांश्च तरक्षून्महिषांस्तथा |` | "Piercing deer, boars, hyenas, and buffaloes," |
| `Line 4646: अन्यांश्च विविधान्वन्यांश्चचार पृथिवीपतिः ||१०||` | "And various other wild animals, the lord of the earth roamed about. ||10||" |
| `Line 4647: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4648: स कदाचिन्मृगं विद्ध्वा बाणेन नतपर्वणा |` | "Once, having pierced a deer with an arrow of curved joints," |
| `Line 4649: पृष्ठतो धनुरादाय ससार गहने वने ||११||` | "Taking his bow, he pursued it from behind into the dense forest. ||11||" |
| `Line 4650: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4651: यथा हि भगवान्रुद्रो विद्ध्वा यज्ञमृगं दिवि |` | "Just as the venerable Rudra [Śiva], having pierced the sacrificial deer in heaven," |
| `Line 4652: अन्वगच्छद्धनुष्पाणिः पर्यन्वेषंस्ततस्ततः ||१२||` | "Followed it with bow in hand, searching here and there. ||12||" |
| `Line 4653: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4654: न हि तेन मृगो विद्धो जीवन्गच्छति वै वनम् |` | "For indeed, the deer pierced by him does not go living to the forest," |
| `Line 4655: पूर्वरूपं तु तन्नूनमासीत्स्वर्गगतिं प्रति ||१३||` | "But surely that was a foretoken regarding the path to heaven. ||13||" |
| `Line 4656: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4657: परिक्षितस्तस्य राज्ञो विद्धो यन्नष्टवान्मृगः ||१३||` | "For King Parikshit, the deer that was shot had disappeared. ||13||" |
| `Line 4658: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4659: दूरं चापहृतस्तेन मृगेण स महीपतिः |` | "And that ruler of the earth was led far away by that deer," |
| `Line 4660: परिश्रान्तः पिपासार्त आससाद मुनिं वने ||१४||` | "Exhausted and afflicted with thirst, he came upon a sage in the forest. ||14||" |
| `Line 4661: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4662: गवां प्रचारेष्वासीनं वत्सानां मुखनिःसृतम् |` | "The sage was sitting in the pastures of cows, drinking the foam," |
| `Line 4663: भूयिष्ठमुपयुञ्जानं फेनमापिबतां पयः ||१५||` | "Abundantly consuming the foam of milk flowing from the mouths of calves. ||15||" |
| `Line 4664: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4665: तमभिद्रुत्य वेगेन स राजा संशितव्रतम् |` | "Rushing quickly toward him, that king approached the sage of strict vows," |
| `Line 4666: अपृच्छद्धनुरुद्यम्य तं मुनिं क्षुच्छ्रमान्वितः ||१६||` | "And raising his bow, asked the sage, being afflicted with hunger and fatigue. ||16||" |
| `Line 4667: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4668: भो भो ब्रह्मन्नहं राजा परिक्षिदभिमन्युजः |` | "O Brahmin, I am King Parikshit, son of Abhimanyu," |
| `Line 4669: मया विद्धो मृगो नष्टः कच्चित्त्वं दृष्टवानसि ||१७||` | "A deer pierced by me has disappeared; have you perhaps seen it? ||17||" |
| `Line 4670: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4671: स मुनिस्तस्य नोवाच किञ्चिन्मौनव्रते स्थितः |` | "That sage did not say anything to him, being established in a vow of silence," |
| `Line 4672: तस्य स्कन्धे मृतं सर्पं क्रुद्धो राजा समासजत् ||१८||` | "The angry king placed a dead snake on his shoulder. ||18||" |
| `Line 4673: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4674: धनुष्कोट्या समुत्क्षिप्य स चैनं समुदैक्षत |` | "Having lifted it with the end of his bow, and the sage looked at him," |
| `Line 4675: न च किञ्चिदुवाचैनं शुभं वा यदि वाशुभम् ||१९||` | "But did not say anything to him, whether good or bad. ||19||" |
| `Line 4676: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 4677: स राजा क्रोधमुत्सृज्य व्यथितस्तं तथागतम् |` | "That king, abandoning his anger, distressed upon seeing him in such a condition," |
| `Line 4678: दृष्ट्वा जगाम नगरमृषिस्त्वास्ते तथैव सः ||२०||` | "Went back to his city, while the sage remained there in the same state. ||20||" |
| `Line 4679: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 4680: तरुणस्तस्य पुत्रोऽभूत्तिग्मतेजा महातपाः |` | "That sage had a young son of fierce energy and great austerity," |
| `Line 4681: शृङ्गी नाम महाक्रोधो दुष्प्रसादो महाव्रतः ||२१||` | "Named Śṛṅgī, who was extremely wrathful, difficult to please, and of great vows. ||21||" |
| `Line 4682: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 4683: स देवं परमीशानं सर्वभूतहिते रतम् |` | "He worshipped the supreme lord [Brahma], who is devoted to the welfare of all beings," |
| `Line 4684: ब्रह्माणमुपतस्थे वै काले काले सुसंयतः ||२२||` | "He approached Brahmā at regular intervals, with great self-control. ||22||" |
| `Line 4685: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 4686: स तेन समनुज्ञातो ब्रह्मणा गृहमेयिवान् ||२२||` | "Having been permitted by Brahmā, he returned home. ||22||" |
| `Line 4687: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 4688: सख्योक्तः क्रीडमानेन स तत्र हसता किल |` | "There, he was told by a playful, laughing friend," |
| `Line 4689: संरम्भी कोपनोऽतीव विषकल्प ऋषेः सुतः ||२३||` | "That sage's son who was impetuous, extremely irascible, and venomous in nature. ||23||" |
| `Line 4690: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 4691: ऋषिपुत्रेण नर्मार्थं कृशेन द्विजसत्तम ||२३||` | "By a thin sage's son named Kṛśa [emaciated one], in jest, O best of the twice-born. ||23||" |
| `Line 4692: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 4693: तेजस्विनस्तव पिता तथैव च तपस्विनः |` | "'Your father, though powerful and austere," |
| `Line 4694: शवं स्कन्धेन वहति मा शृङ्गिन्गर्वितो भव ||२४||` | "Is carrying a dead snake on his shoulders. O Śṛṅgī, do not be proud! ||24||'" |
| `Line 4695: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 4696: व्याहरत्स्वृषिपुत्रेषु मा स्म किञ्चिद्वचो वदीः |` | "'Do not speak any words among the sons of sages," |
| `Line 4697: अस्मद्विधेषु सिद्धेषु ब्रह्मवित्सु तपस्विषु ||२५||` | "Among accomplished ones like us, who are knowers of Brahman and ascetics. ||25||'" |
| `Line 4698: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 4699: क्व ते पुरुषमानित्वं क्व ते वाचस्तथाविधाः |` | "'Where is your manly pride, where are those boastful words of yours," |
| `Line 4700: दर्पजाः पितरं यस्त्वं द्रष्टा शवधरं तथा ||२६||` | "Born of arrogance, when you will see your father bearing a corpse thus? ||26||'" |
| `Line 4701: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4702: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4703: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4704: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4705: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4706: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4707: ३७` | "37" |
| `Line 4708: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4709: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4710: सूत उवाच||` | "Sūta [bard/narrator] said:" |
| `Line 4711: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4712: एवमुक्तः स तेजस्वी शृङ्गी कोपसमन्वितः |` | "Thus addressed, the radiant Śṛṅgī [sage's son], filled with anger," |
| `Line 4713: मृतधारं गुरुं श्रुत्वा पर्यतप्यत मन्युना ||१||` | "Having heard that his guru [teacher] bore a dead snake, was consumed by wrath. ||1||" |
| `Line 4714: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4715: स तं कृशमभिप्रेष्क्य सूनृतां वाचमुत्सृजन् |` | "He, looking at Kṛśa [thin one], speaking gentle words," |
| `Line 4716: अपृच्छत कथं तातः स मेऽद्य मृतधारकः ||२||` | "Asked, 'How is it that my father today bears a dead snake?' ||2||" |
| `Line 4717: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4718: कृश उवाच||` | "Kṛśa said:" |
| `Line 4719: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4720: राज्ञा परिक्षिता तात मृगयां परिधावता |` | "King Parīkṣit [Parikshit], O dear one, while running about hunting," |
| `Line 4721: अवसक्तः पितुस्तेऽद्य मृतः स्कन्धे भुजङ्गमः ||३||` | "Placed a dead serpent [snake] today on your father's shoulders. ||3||" |
| `Line 4722: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4723: शृङ्ग्युवाच||` | "Śṛṅgī said:" |
| `Line 4724: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4725: किं मे पित्रा कृतं तस्य राज्ञोऽनिष्टं दुरात्मनः |` | "What harm did my father do to that evil-minded king?" |
| `Line 4726: ब्रूहि त्वं कृश तत्त्वेन पश्य मे तपसो बलम् ||४||` | "Tell me the truth, O Kṛśa, behold the power of my austerities. ||4||" |
| `Line 4727: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4728: कृश उवाच||` | "Kṛśa [the thin one] said:" |
| `Line 4729: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4730: स राजा मृगयां यातः परिक्षिदभिमन्युजः |` | "That king, Parikṣit [son of Abhimanyu], went hunting," |
| `Line 4731: ससार मृगमेकाकी विद्ध्वा बाणेन पत्रिणा ||५||` | "He pursued a deer alone, having pierced it with a feathered arrow. ||5||" |
| `Line 4732: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4733: न चापश्यन्मृगं राजा चरंस्तस्मिन्महावने |` | "And the king did not see the deer while wandering in that great forest," |
| `Line 4734: पितरं ते स दृष्ट्वैव पप्रच्छानभिभाषिणम् ||६||` | "Seeing your father, he questioned him who was not speaking. ||6||" |
| `Line 4735: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4736: तं स्थाणुभूतं तिष्ठन्तं क्षुत्पिपासाश्रमातुरः |` | "To him who was standing motionless like a pillar, the king, afflicted by hunger, thirst, and fatigue," |
| `Line 4737: पुनः पुनर्मृगं नष्टं पप्रच्छ पितरं तव ||७||` | "Again and again asked your father about the lost deer. ||7||" |
| `Line 4738: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4739: स च मौनव्रतोपेतो नैव तं प्रत्यभाषत |` | "And he, observing a vow of silence, did not reply to him," |
| `Line 4740: तस्य राजा धनुष्कोट्या सर्पं स्कन्धे समासृजत् ||८||` | "The king placed a dead snake on his shoulders with the tip of his bow. ||8||" |
| `Line 4741: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4742: शृङ्गिंस्तव पिताद्यासौ तथैवास्ते यतव्रतः |` | "O Śṛṅgin [horned one], your father even now sits there, steadfast in his vow," |
| `Line 4743: सोऽपि राजा स्वनगरं प्रतियातो गजाह्वयम् ||९||` | "And that king has returned to his own city, Gajāhvaya [Hastināpura]. ||9||" |
| `Line 4744: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4745: सूत उवाच||` | "Sūta [bard/narrator] said:" |
| `Line 4746: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4747: श्रुत्वैवमृषिपुत्रस्तु दिवं स्तब्ध्वेव विष्ठितः |` | "Hearing this, the sage's son stood as if freezing the sky," |
| `Line 4748: कोपसंरक्तनयनः प्रज्वलन्निव मन्युना ||१०||` | "With eyes reddened by anger, as if blazing with wrath. ||10||" |
| `Line 4749: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4750: आविष्टः स तु कोपेन शशाप नृपतिं तदा |` | "Possessed by anger, he then cursed the king," |
| `Line 4751: वार्युपस्पृश्य तेजस्वी क्रोधवेगबलात्कृतः ||११||` | "Having touched water [ritual purification], the radiant one was overcome by the force of his anger. ||11||" |
| `Line 4752: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4753: शृङ्ग्युवाच||` | "Śṛṅgī [young sage] said:" |
| `Line 4754: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4755: योऽसौ वृद्धस्य तातस्य तथा कृच्छ्रगतस्य च |` | "That one who, when my elderly father was in such a difficult situation," |
| `Line 4756: स्कन्धे मृतमवास्राक्षीत्पन्नगं राजकिल्बिषी ||१२||` | "Placed a dead snake on his shoulders, that sinful king, ||12||" |
| `Line 4757: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4758: तं पापमतिसङ्क्रुद्धस्तक्षकः पन्नगोत्तमः |` | "That sinful one, Takṣaka [serpent king], the foremost among serpents, extremely enraged," |
| `Line 4759: आशीविषस्तिग्मतेजा मद्वाक्यबलचोदितः ||१३||` | "The venomous one with fierce power, impelled by the force of my words, ||13||" |
| `Line 4760: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4761: सप्तरात्रादितो नेता यमस्य सदनं प्रति |` | "Will lead from today, after seven nights, to the abode of Yama [death god]," |
| `Line 4762: द्विजानामवमन्तारं कुरूणामयशस्करम् ||१४||` | "This insulter of twice-born [Brahmins] who brings disgrace to the Kurus. ||14||" |
| `Line 4763: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4764: सूत उवाच||` | "Sūta [bard/narrator] said:" |
| `Line 4765: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4766: इति शप्त्वा नृपं क्रुद्धः शृङ्गी पितरमभ्ययात् |` | "Having thus cursed the king in anger, Śṛṅgī approached his father," |
| `Line 4767: आसीनं गोचरे तस्मिन्वहन्तं शवपन्नगम् ||१५||` | "Who was sitting in that pasture, bearing the dead snake. ||15||" |
| `Line 4768: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4769: स तमालक्ष्य पितरं शृङ्गी स्कन्धगतेन वै |` | "Seeing his father with the snake placed on his shoulders," |
| `Line 4770: शवेन भुजगेनासीद्भूयः क्रोधसमन्वितः ||१६||` | "Śṛṅgī was again filled with anger. ||16||" |
| `Line 4771: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4772: दुःखाच्चाश्रूणि मुमुचे पितरं चेदमब्रवीत् |` | "And from sorrow he shed tears and said this to his father:" |
| `Line 4773: श्रुत्वेमां धर्षणां तात तव तेन दुरात्मना ||१७||` | "Having heard of this insult to you, father, by that evil-minded one, ||17||" |
| `Line 4774: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4775: राज्ञा परिक्षिता कोपादशपं तमहं नृपम् |` | "In anger I have cursed that king Parikṣit [Kuru ruler]," |
| `Line 4776: यथार्हति स एवोग्रं शापं कुरुकुलाधमः ||१८||` | "That very lowest of the Kuru family [Parikshit] deserves this terrible curse. ||18||" |
| `Line 4777: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4778: सप्तमेऽहनि तं पापं तक्षकः पन्नगोत्तमः |` | "On the seventh day, Takshaka, the best of serpents [nāga chief]," |
| `Line 4779: वैवस्वतस्य भवनं नेता परमदारुणम् ||१९||` | "Will lead that sinful one to the abode of Vaivasvata [Yama, death god], most terribly. ||19||" |
| `Line 4780: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4781: तमब्रवीत्पिता ब्रह्मंस्तथा कोपसमन्वितम् |` | "His father said to him, O Brahman [sage], who was thus filled with anger," |
| `Line 4782: न मे प्रियं कृतं तात नैष धर्मस्तपस्विनाम् ||२०||` | "You have not done what pleases me, my son; this is not the dharma [righteous duty] of ascetics. ||20||" |
| `Line 4783: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4784: वयं तस्य नरेन्द्रस्य विषये निवसामहे |` | "We live in the kingdom of that lord of men [king]," |
| `Line 4785: न्यायतो रक्षितास्तेन तस्य पापं न रोचये ||२१||` | "Justly protected by him; I do not approve of his being cursed. ||21||" |
| `Line 4786: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4787: सर्वथा वर्तमानस्य राज्ञो ह्यस्मद्विधैः सदा |` | "The king who always conducts himself properly toward people like us," |
| `Line 4788: क्षन्तव्यं पुत्र धर्मो हि हतो हन्ति न संशयः ||२२||` | "Should be forgiven, my son, for dharma [righteousness] destroyed destroys in return, without doubt. ||22||" |
| `Line 4789: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4790: यदि राजा न रक्षेत पीडा वै नः परा भवेत् |` | "If the king did not protect us, great suffering would befall us," |
| `Line 4791: न शक्नुयाम चरितुं धर्मं पुत्र यथासुखम् ||२३||` | "We would not be able to practice dharma [religious duties] comfortably, my son. ||23||" |
| `Line 4792: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4793: रक्ष्यमाणा वयं तात राजभिः शास्त्रदृष्टिभिः |` | "Being protected, my dear son, by kings who follow the scriptures," |
| `Line 4794: चरामो विपुलं धर्मं तेषां चांशोऽस्ति धर्मतः ||२४||` | "We practice extensive dharma [religious duties], and they have a share in that dharma. ||24||" |
| `Line 4795: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4796: परिक्षित्तु विशेषेण यथास्य प्रपितामहः |` | "Parikshit especially, just like his great-grandfather [Yudhishthira]," |
| `Line 4797: रक्षत्यस्मान्यथा राज्ञा रक्षितव्याः प्रजास्तथा ||२५||` | "Protects us as subjects should be protected by a king. ||25||" |
| `Line 4798: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4799: तेनेह क्षुधितेनाद्य श्रान्तेन च तपस्विना |` | "By him today, hungry and tired, an ascetic [king]," |
| `Line 4800: अजानता व्रतमिदं कृतमेतदसंशयम् ||२६||` | "This was done unknowingly of our vow, without doubt. ||26||" |
| `Line 4801: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4802: तस्मादिदं त्वया बाल्यात्सहसा दुष्कृतं कृतम् |` | "Therefore, this evil deed has been done by you hastily out of childishness," |
| `Line 4803: न ह्यर्हति नृपः शापमस्मत्तः पुत्र सर्वथा ||२७||` | "For the king does not deserve a curse from us in any way, O son. ||27||" |
| `Line 4804: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4805: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4806: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4807: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4808: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4809: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4810: ३८` | "38" |
| `Line 4811: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4812: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4813: शृङ्ग्युवाच||` | "Śṛṅgī [sage's son] said:" |
| `Line 4814: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4815: यद्येतत्साहसं तात यदि वा दुष्कृतं कृतम् |` | "Whether this was rashness, father, or whether an evil deed was done," |
| `Line 4816: प्रियं वाप्यप्रियं वा ते वागुक्ता न मृषा मया ||१||` | "Whether pleasing or displeasing to you, the words spoken by me are not false. ||1||" |
| `Line 4817: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4818: नैवान्यथेदं भविता पितरेष ब्रवीमि ते |` | "This will not be otherwise, father, I tell you this," |
| `Line 4819: नाहं मृषा प्रब्रवीमि स्वैरेष्वपि कुतः शपन् ||२||` | "I do not speak falsely even in casual matters, how much less when pronouncing a curse? ||2||" |
| `Line 4820: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4821: शमीक उवाच||` | "Śamīka [sage father] said:" |
| `Line 4822: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4823: जानाम्युग्रप्रभावं त्वां पुत्र सत्यगिरं तथा |` | "I know your terrible power, O son, and that you speak the truth," |
| `Line 4824: नानृतं ह्युक्तपूर्वं ते नैतन्मिथ्या भविष्यति ||३||` | "You have never spoken falsehood before, and this will not prove false. ||3||" |
| `Line 4825: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4826: पित्रा पुत्रो वयःस्थोऽपि सततं वाच्य एव तु |` | "A son, even when grown up [of mature age], should always be instructed by his father," |
| `Line 4827: यथा स्याद्गुणसंयुक्तः प्राप्नुयाच्च महद्यशः ||४||` | "So that he may be endowed with virtues and attain great fame. ||4||" |
| `Line 4828: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4829: किं पुनर्बाल एव त्वं तपसा भावितः प्रभो |` | "How much more so when you are but a child, though empowered by austerities, O lord," |
| `Line 4830: वर्धते च प्रभवतां कोपोऽतीव महात्मनाम् ||५||` | "And the anger of powerful great souls increases exceedingly. ||5||" |
| `Line 4831: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4832: सोऽहं पश्यामि वक्तव्यं त्वयि धर्मभृतां वर |` | "I see what must be said to you, O best of the upholders of dharma [righteousness]," |
| `Line 4833: पुत्रत्वं बालतां चैव तवावेक्ष्य च साहसम् ||६||` | "Considering your status as my son, your childhood, and your rashness. ||6||" |
| `Line 4834: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4835: स त्वं शमयुतो भूत्वा वन्यमाहारमाहरन् |` | "You should be filled with tranquility, subsisting on forest food," |
| `Line 4836: चर क्रोधमिमं त्यक्त्वा नैवं धर्मं प्रहास्यसि ||७||` | "Live abandoning this anger, and thus you will not forsake dharma [righteousness]. ||7||" |
| `Line 4837: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4838: क्रोधो हि धर्मं हरति यतीनां दुःखसञ्चितम् |` | "For anger steals away the dharma of ascetics [renunciates] accumulated through hardship," |
| `Line 4839: ततो धर्मविहीनानां गतिरिष्टा न विद्यते ||८||` | "And for those bereft of dharma, the desired destination does not exist. ||8||" |
| `Line 4840: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4841: शम एव यतीनां हि क्षमिणां सिद्धिकारकः |` | "Tranquility alone is the cause of perfection for ascetics who are forgiving," |
| `Line 4842: क्षमावतामयं लोकः परश्चैव क्षमावताम् ||९||` | "This world and the next belong to those who are forgiving. ||9||" |
| `Line 4843: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4844: तस्माच्चरेथाः सततं क्षमाशीलो जितेन्द्रियः |` | "Therefore, you should always live with a forgiving nature, with controlled senses," |
| `Line 4845: क्षमया प्राप्स्यसे लोकान्ब्रह्मणः समनन्तरान् ||१०||` | "Through forgiveness, you will attain worlds equal to those of Brahma [creator deity]. ||10||" |
| `Line 4846: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4847: मया तु शममास्थाय यच्छक्यं कर्तुमद्य वै |` | "But I, having resorted to tranquility, will do what can be done today," |
| `Line 4848: तत्करिष्येऽद्य ताताहं प्रेषयिष्ये नृपाय वै ||११||` | "I will do that today, my child, I will send a message to the king. ||11||" |
| `Line 4849: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4850: मम पुत्रेण शप्तोऽसि बालेनाकृतबुद्धिना |` | "You have been cursed by my son, a child of undeveloped intellect," |
| `Line 4851: ममेमां धर्षणां त्वत्तः प्रेक्ष्य राजन्नमर्षिणा ||१२||` | "Seeing this insult to me from you, O king, I could not tolerate it. ||12||" |
| `Line 4852: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4853: सूत उवाच||` | "Sūta [bard/narrator] said:" |
| `Line 4854: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4855: एवमादिश्य शिष्यं स प्रेषयामास सुव्रतः |` | "Having thus instructed his disciple, that virtuous one [sage] of great austerity sent him," |
| `Line 4856: परिक्षिते नृपतये दयापन्नो महातपाः ||१३||` | "To King Parikshit, out of compassion, that great ascetic. ||13||" |
| `Line 4857: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4858: संदिश्य कुशलप्रश्नं कार्यवृत्तान्तमेव च |` | "Having instructed him to inquire about the king's welfare and to relate the entire matter," |
| `Line 4859: शिष्यं गौरमुखं नाम शीलवन्तं समाहितम् ||१४||` | "His disciple named Gauramukha, who was virtuous and composed. ||14||" |
| `Line 4860: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4861: सोऽभिगम्य ततः शीघ्रं नरेन्द्रं कुरुवर्धनम् |` | "He then quickly approached the king, the enhancer of the Kuru race," |
| `Line 4862: विवेश भवनं राज्ञः पूर्वं द्वाःस्थैर्निवेदितः ||१५||` | "And entered the king's palace, having been first announced by the doorkeepers. ||15||" |
| `Line 4863: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4864: पूजितश्च नरेन्द्रेण द्विजो गौरमुखस्ततः |` | "And having been honored by the king, the Brahmin Gauramukha then," |
| `Line 4865: आचख्यौ परिविश्रान्तो राज्ञे सर्वमशेषतः ||१६||` | "After resting, related everything in full to the king. ||16||" |
| `Line 4866: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4867: शमीकवचनं घोरं यथोक्तं मन्त्रिसंनिधौ ||१६||` | "The terrible words of Shamika, as spoken in the presence of ministers. ||16||" |
| `Line 4868: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4869: शमीको नाम राजेन्द्र विषये वर्तते तव |` | "O king of kings, in your domain lives one named Shamika," |
| `Line 4870: ऋषिः परमधर्मात्मा दान्तः शान्तो महातपाः ||१७||` | "A sage of supreme righteousness, self-controlled, peaceful, and of great austerity. ||17||" |
| `Line 4871: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4872: तस्य त्वया नरव्याघ्र सर्पः प्राणैर्वियोजितः |` | "O tiger among men [mighty king], you deprived a serpent of its life," |
| `Line 4873: अवसक्तो धनुष्कोट्या स्कन्धे भरतसत्तम ||१८||` | "By hanging it with the tip of your bow on his shoulder, O best of the Bharatas. ||18||" |
| `Line 4874: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4875: क्षान्तवांस्तव तत्कर्म पुत्रस्तस्य न चक्षमे ||१८||` | "Though he forgave your deed, his son did not forgive it. ||18||" |
| `Line 4876: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4877: तेन शप्तोऽसि राजेन्द्र पितुरज्ञातमद्य वै |` | "By him you have been cursed, O Rājendra [king of kings], today indeed without your father's knowledge," |
| `Line 4878: तक्षकः सप्तरात्रेण मृत्युस्ते वै भविष्यति ||१९||` | "Takṣaka [serpent king] will be your death within seven nights. ||19||" |
| `Line 4879: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4880: तत्र रक्षां कुरुष्वेति पुनः पुनरथाब्रवीत् |` | "'Take precautions against this,' he said again and again," |
| `Line 4881: तदन्यथा न शक्यं च कर्तुं केनचिदप्युत ||२०||` | "And that cannot be altered by anyone whatsoever. ||20||" |
| `Line 4882: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4883: न हि शक्नोति संयन्तुं पुत्रं कोपसमन्वितम् |` | "For he is unable to restrain his son who is filled with anger," |
| `Line 4884: ततोऽहं प्रेषितस्तेन तव राजन्हितार्थिना ||२१||` | "Therefore I have been sent by him, O king, who desires your welfare. ||21||" |
| `Line 4885: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4886: इति श्रुत्वा वचो घोरं स राजा कुरुनन्दनः |` | "Having heard these terrible words, that king, the descendant of Kuru," |
| `Line 4887: पर्यतप्यत तत्पापं कृत्वा राजा महातपाः ||२२||` | "The king of great austerity was tormented by that sin he had committed. ||22||" |
| `Line 4888: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4889: तं च मौनव्रतधरं श्रुत्वा मुनिवरं तदा |` | "And hearing then that the excellent sage had taken a vow of silence," |
| `Line 4890: भूय एवाभवद्राजा शोकसन्तप्तमानसः ||२३||` | "The king became even more afflicted with grief in his mind. ||23||" |
| `Line 4891: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4892: अनुक्रोशात्मतां तस्य शमीकस्यावधार्य तु |` | "Understanding the compassionate nature of that Śamīka [sage's name]," |
| `Line 4893: पर्यतप्यत भूयोऽपि कृत्वा तत्किल्बिषं मुनेः ||२४||` | "He was tormented even more for having committed that offense against the sage. ||24||" |
| `Line 4894: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4895: न हि मृत्युं तथा राजा श्रुत्वा वै सोऽन्वतप्यत |` | "For the king was not so much tormented after hearing about his death," |
| `Line 4896: अशोचदमरप्रख्यो यथा कृत्वेह कर्म तत् ||२५||` | "The godlike one grieved more for having committed that deed here. ||25||" |
| `Line 4897: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4898: ततस्तं प्रेषयामास राजा गौरमुखं तदा |` | "Then the king sent Gauramukha [minister's name] there," |
| `Line 4899: भूयः प्रसादं भगवान्करोत्विति ममेति वै ||२६||` | "Saying, 'May the venerable one show favor to me again.' ||26||" |
| `Line 4900: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4901: तस्मिंश्च गतमात्रे वै राजा गौरमुखे तदा |` | "And as soon as he had gone to Gauramukha [a place], the king then," |
| `Line 4902: मन्त्रिभिर्मन्त्रयामास सह संविग्नमानसः ||२७||` | "Consulted with his ministers together, with an anxious mind. ||27||" |
| `Line 4903: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4904: निश्चित्य मन्त्रिभिश्चैव सहितो मन्त्रतत्त्ववित् |` | "Having decided together with his ministers, he who knew the essence of counsel," |
| `Line 4905: प्रासादं कारयामास एकस्तम्भं सुरक्षितम् ||२८||` | "Had a palace built with a single pillar, well-protected. ||28||" |
| `Line 4906: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4907: रक्षां च विदधे तत्र भिषजश्चौषधानि च |` | "And he arranged protection there, physicians and medicines too," |
| `Line 4908: ब्राह्मणान्सिद्धमन्त्रांश्च सर्वतो वै न्यवेशयत् ||२९||` | "And he stationed Brahmins with powerful mantras [sacred chants] all around. ||29||" |
| `Line 4909: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4910: राजकार्याणि तत्रस्थः सर्वाण्येवाकरोच्च सः |` | "Stationed there, he performed all his royal duties," |
| `Line 4911: मन्त्रिभिः सह धर्मज्ञः समन्तात्परिरक्षितः ||३०||` | "Together with his ministers, the righteous one, protected from all sides. ||30||" |
| `Line 4912: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4913: प्राप्ते तु दिवसे तस्मिन्सप्तमे द्विजसत्तम |` | "When the seventh day arrived, O best of the twice-born [Brahmin]," |
| `Line 4914: काश्यपोऽभ्यागमद्विद्वांस्तं राजानं चिकित्सितुम् ||३१||` | "The learned Kāśyapa [sage] came to heal that king. ||31||" |
| `Line 4915: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4916: श्रुतं हि तेन तदभूदद्य तं राजसत्तमम् |` | "For he had heard that today that excellent king," |
| `Line 4917: तक्षकः पन्नगश्रेष्ठो नेष्यते यमसादनम् ||३२||` | "Takṣaka [serpent king], the foremost of serpents, would take to Yama's abode [realm of death]. ||32||" |
| `Line 4918: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4919: तं दष्टं पन्नगेन्द्रेण करिष्येऽहमपज्वरम् |` | "'I will make him, bitten by the lord of serpents, free from fever," |
| `Line 4920: तत्र मेऽर्थश्च धर्मश्च भवितेति विचिन्तयन् ||३३||` | "In this, I will gain both wealth and righteousness'—thinking thus. ||33||" |
| `Line 4921: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4922: तं ददर्श स नागेन्द्रस्तक्षकः काश्यपं पथि |` | "That lord of serpents, Takṣaka, saw Kāśyapa on the way," |
| `Line 4923: गच्छन्तमेकमनसं द्विजो भूत्वा वयोतिगः ||३४||` | "Going with single-minded purpose, having taken the form of an aged Brahmin. ||34||" |
| `Line 4924: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4925: तमब्रवीत्पन्नगेन्द्रः काश्यपं मुनिपुङ्गवम् |` | "The lord of serpents spoke to Kāśyapa, the foremost of sages:" |
| `Line 4926: क्व भवांस्त्वरितो याति किं च कार्यं चिकीर्षति ||३५||` | "Where are you going in such haste, and what task do you wish to accomplish? ||35||" |
| `Line 4927: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4928: काश्यप उवाच||` | "Kāśyapa [sage, son of Marīci] said:" |
| `Line 4929: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4930: नृपं कुरुकुलोत्पन्नं परिक्षितमरिंदमम् |` | "The king born in the Kuru lineage, Parikṣit [Pāṇḍava grandson], the destroyer of enemies," |
| `Line 4931: तक्षकः पन्नगश्रेष्ठस्तेजसाद्य प्रधक्ष्यति ||३६||` | "Takṣaka [serpent king], the foremost among serpents, will burn him today with his power. ||36||" |
| `Line 4932: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4933: तं दष्टं पन्नगेन्द्रेण तेनाग्निसमतेजसा |` | "Him, bitten by that lord of serpents whose power equals fire," |
| `Line 4934: पाण्डवानां कुलकरं राजानममितौजसम् ||३७||` | "The king of immeasurable strength, who continues the lineage of the Pāṇḍavas, ||37||" |
| `Line 4935: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4936: गच्छामि सौम्य त्वरितं सद्यः कर्तुमपज्वरम् ||३७||` | "I go quickly, O gentle one, to immediately make him free from fever. ||37||" |
| `Line 4937: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4938: तक्षक उवाच||` | "Takṣaka [serpent king] said:" |
| `Line 4939: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4940: अहं स तक्षको ब्रह्मंस्तं धक्ष्यामि महीपतिम् |` | "I am that Takṣaka, O Brahmin, who will burn that king," |
| `Line 4941: निवर्तस्व न शक्तस्त्वं मया दष्टं चिकित्सितुम् ||३८||` | "Turn back, you are not able to heal one who has been bitten by me. ||38||" |
| `Line 4942: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4943: काश्यप उवाच||` | "Kāśyapa [sage] said:" |
| `Line 4944: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4945: अहं तं नृपतिं नाग त्वया दष्टमपज्वरम् |` | "I, O serpent, will make that king bitten by you free from fever," |
| `Line 4946: करिष्य इति मे बुद्धिर्विद्याबलमुपाश्रितः ||३९||` | "This is my intention, relying on the power of my knowledge. ||39||" |
| `Line 4947: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4948: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4949: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4950: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4951: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4952: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4953: ३९` | "39" |
| `Line 4954: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4955: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4956: तक्षक उवाच||` | "Takṣaka [serpent king] said:" |
| `Line 4957: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4958: दष्टं यदि मयेह त्वं शक्तः किञ्चिच्चिकित्सितुम् |` | "If you are able to heal anything that has been bitten by me here," |
| `Line 4959: ततो वृक्षं मया दष्टमिमं जीवय काश्यप ||१||` | "Then revive this tree that has been bitten by me, O Kāśyapa. ||1||" |
| `Line 4960: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4961: परं मन्त्रबलं यत्ते तद्दर्शय यतस्व च |` | "Show the supreme power of your mantras and make an effort," |
| `Line 4962: न्यग्रोधमेनं धक्ष्यामि पश्यतस्ते द्विजोत्तम ||२||` | "I will burn this banyan tree before your eyes, O best of the twice-born [Brahmin]. ||2||" |
| `Line 4963: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4964: काश्यप उवाच||` | "Kāśyapa [sage] said:" |
| `Line 4965: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4966: दश नागेन्द्र वृक्षं त्वं यमेनमभिमन्यसे |` | "Bite this tree, O lord of serpents, whichever one you choose," |
| `Line 4967: अहमेनं त्वया दष्टं जीवयिष्ये भुजङ्गम ||३||` | "I will revive it after it has been bitten by you, O serpent. ||3||" |
| `Line 4968: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4969: सूत उवाच||` | "Sūta [bard/narrator] said:" |
| `Line 4970: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4971: एवमुक्तः स नागेन्द्रः काश्यपेन महात्मना |` | "Thus addressed by the great-souled Kāśyapa, that lord of serpents," |
| `Line 4972: अदशद्वृक्षमभ्येत्य न्यग्रोधं पन्नगोत्तमः ||४||` | "The foremost of serpents approached and bit the banyan tree. ||4||" |
| `Line 4973: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4974: स वृक्षस्तेन दष्टः सन्सद्य एव महाद्युते |` | "That tree, having been bitten by him, O greatly radiant one," |
| `Line 4975: आशीविषविषोपेतः प्रजज्वाल समन्ततः ||५||` | "Filled with the poison of the venomous snake, burst into flames on all sides. ||5||" |
| `Line 4976: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4977: तं दग्ध्वा स नगं नागः काश्यपं पुनरब्रवीत् |` | "Having burnt that tree, the nāga [serpent king] spoke again to Kāśyapa," |
| `Line 4978: कुरु यत्नं द्विजश्रेष्ठ जीवयैनं वनस्पतिम् ||६||` | "Make an effort, O best of the twice-born [Brahmin], revive this forest lord [tree]. ||6||" |
| `Line 4979: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4980: भस्मीभूतं ततो वृक्षं पन्नगेन्द्रस्य तेजसा |` | "Then, the tree reduced to ashes by the serpent lord's power," |
| `Line 4981: भस्म सर्वं समाहृत्य काश्यपो वाक्यमब्रवीत् ||७||` | "Gathering all the ashes, Kāśyapa spoke these words: ||7||" |
| `Line 4982: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4983: विद्याबलं पन्नगेन्द्र पश्य मेऽस्मिन्वनस्पतौ |` | "O lord of serpents, behold the power of my knowledge on this forest lord [tree]," |
| `Line 4984: अहं सञ्जीवयाम्येनं पश्यतस्ते भुजङ्गम ||८||` | "I shall revive it before your eyes, O serpent. ||8||" |
| `Line 4985: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4986: ततः स भगवान्विद्वान्काश्यपो द्विजसत्तमः |` | "Then that venerable learned Kāśyapa, best of the twice-born [Brahmin]," |
| `Line 4987: भस्मराशीकृतं वृक्षं विद्यया समजीवयत् ||९||` | "Revived the tree reduced to a heap of ashes through his knowledge. ||9||" |
| `Line 4988: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4989: अङ्कुरं तं स कृतवांस्ततः पर्णद्वयान्वितम् |` | "He made it first a sprout, then with two leaves," |
| `Line 4990: पलाशिनं शाखिनं च तथा विटपिनं पुनः ||१०||` | "Then with foliage, branches, and finally a complete tree again. ||10||" |
| `Line 4991: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4992: तं दृष्ट्वा जीवितं वृक्षं काश्यपेन महात्मना |` | "Seeing the tree brought back to life by the great-souled Kāśyapa," |
| `Line 4993: उवाच तक्षको ब्रह्मन्नेतदत्यद्भुतं त्वयि ||११||` | "Takṣaka said, 'O Brahmin, this is not surprising in you. ||11||'" |
| `Line 4994: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4995: विप्रेन्द्र यद्विषं हन्या मम वा मद्विधस्य वा |` | "O foremost of sages, you can neutralize the poison of mine or those like me," |
| `Line 4996: कं त्वमर्थमभिप्रेप्सुर्यासि तत्र तपोधन ||१२||` | "What purpose do you seek to fulfill by going there, O wealth of austerities [ascetic]? ||12||" |
| `Line 4997: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 4998: यत्तेऽभिलषितं प्राप्तुं फलं तस्मान्नृपोत्तमात् |` | "Whatever reward you desire to obtain from that best of kings," |
| `Line 4999: अहमेव प्रदास्यामि तत्ते यद्यपि दुर्लभम् ||१३||` | "I myself shall give it to you, even if it is difficult to obtain. ||13||" |
| `Line 5000: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5001: विप्रशापाभिभूते च क्षीणायुषि नराधिपे |` | "And when the king [ruler of men] is overwhelmed by a Brahmin's curse and his life-span is diminished," |
| `Line 5002: घटमानस्य ते विप्र सिद्धिः संशयिता भवेत् ||१४||` | "Your efforts, O Brahmin, would yield doubtful success. ||14||" |
| `Line 5003: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5004: ततो यशः प्रदीप्तं ते त्रिषु लोकेषु विश्रुतम् |` | "Then your blazing fame, renowned in the three worlds [cosmic realms]," |
| `Line 5005: विरश्मिरिव घर्मांशुरन्तर्धानमितो व्रजेत् ||१५||` | "Would vanish from here like the sun [hot-rayed one] without its rays. ||15||" |
| `Line 5006: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5007: काश्यप उवाच||` | "Kāśyapa said:" |
| `Line 5008: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5009: धनार्थी याम्यहं तत्र तन्मे दित्स भुजङ्गम |` | "I am going there seeking wealth, so give it to me, O serpent [snake-being]," |
| `Line 5010: ततोऽहं विनिवर्तिष्ये गृहायोरगसत्तम ||१६||` | "Then I shall return home, O best of serpents [snake-lord]. ||16||" |
| `Line 5011: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5012: तक्षक उवाच||` | "Takṣaka said:" |
| `Line 5013: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5014: यावद्धनं प्रार्थयसे तस्माद्राज्ञस्ततोऽधिकम् |` | "Whatever wealth you desire from that king, I shall give you even more," |
| `Line 5015: अहं तेऽद्य प्रदास्यामि निवर्तस्व द्विजोत्तम ||१७||` | "I shall give it to you today, turn back, O best of the twice-born [Brahmin]. ||17||" |
| `Line 5016: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5017: सूत उवाच||` | "Sūta [bard/narrator] said:" |
| `Line 5018: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5019: तक्षकस्य वचः श्रुत्वा काश्यपो द्विजसत्तमः |` | "Hearing Takṣaka's words, Kāśyapa, the best of Brahmins [twice-born]," |
| `Line 5020: प्रदध्यौ सुमहातेजा राजानं प्रति बुद्धिमान् ||१८||` | "The highly splendid and wise one pondered about the king. ||18||" |
| `Line 5021: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5022: दिव्यज्ञानः स तेजस्वी ज्ञात्वा तं नृपतिं तदा |` | "That radiant one with divine knowledge, having then understood that the king [ruler]," |
| `Line 5023: क्षीणायुषं पाण्डवेयमपावर्तत काश्यपः ||१९||` | "The Pāṇḍava descendant, was of diminished lifespan, Kāśyapa turned back. ||19||" |
| `Line 5024: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5025: लब्ध्वा वित्तं मुनिवरस्तक्षकाद्यावदीप्सितम् ||१९||` | "The excellent sage having received from Takṣaka as much wealth as he desired. ||19||" |
| `Line 5026: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5027: निवृत्ते काश्यपे तस्मिन्समयेन महात्मनि |` | "When Kāśyapa [sage], that great soul, had departed according to the agreement," |
| `Line 5028: जगाम तक्षकस्तूर्णं नगरं नागसाह्वयम् ||२०||` | "Takṣaka quickly went to the city named Nāgasāhvaya [Hastināpura]. ||20||" |
| `Line 5029: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5030: अथ शुश्राव गच्छन्स तक्षको जगतीपतिम् |` | "Then Takṣaka, while going, heard that the lord of the earth [king]" |
| `Line 5031: मन्त्रागदैर्विषहरै रक्ष्यमाणं प्रयत्नतः ||२१||` | "Was being carefully protected by mantras and antidotes that neutralize poison. ||21||" |
| `Line 5032: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5033: स चिन्तयामास तदा मायायोगेन पार्थिवः |` | "Then he thought, 'By means of illusion, the king" |
| `Line 5034: मया वञ्चयितव्योऽसौ क उपायो भवेदिति ||२२||` | "Must be deceived by me. What method would work for this?' ||22||" |
| `Line 5035: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5036: ततस्तापसरूपेण प्राहिणोत्स भुजङ्गमान् |` | "Then Takṣaka, the serpent, sent some snakes in the guise of ascetics," |
| `Line 5037: फलपत्रोदकं गृह्य राज्ञे नागोऽथ तक्षकः ||२३||` | "Carrying fruits, leaves, and water to the king. ||23||" |
| `Line 5038: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5039: तक्षक उवाच||` | "Takṣaka said:" |
| `Line 5040: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5041: गच्छध्वं यूयमव्यग्रा राजानं कार्यवत्तया |` | "Go, all of you, without anxiety, to the king with purpose," |
| `Line 5042: फलपत्रोदकं नाम प्रतिग्राहयितुं नृपम् ||२४||` | "To make the king accept these fruits, leaves, and water as offerings. ||24||" |
| `Line 5043: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5044: सूत उवाच||` | "Sūta [bard/narrator] said:" |
| `Line 5045: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5046: ते तक्षकसमादिष्टास्तथा चक्रुर्भुजङ्गमाः |` | "Those serpents, instructed by Takṣaka, did exactly that," |
| `Line 5047: उपनिन्युस्तथा राज्ञे दर्भानापः फलानि च ||२५||` | "They brought to the king sacred grass, water, and fruits. ||25||" |
| `Line 5048: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5049: तच्च सर्वं स राजेन्द्रः प्रतिजग्राह वीर्यवान् |` | "And the powerful king accepted all of that," |
| `Line 5050: कृत्वा च तेषां कार्याणि गम्यतामित्युवाच तान् ||२६||` | "And after fulfilling their purpose, he said to them, 'You may go.' ||26||" |
| `Line 5051: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5052: गतेषु तेषु नागेषु तापसच्छद्मरूपिषु |` | "When those serpents [nāgas] disguised as ascetics had gone," |
| `Line 5053: अमात्यान्सुहृदश्चैव प्रोवाच स नराधिपः ||२७||` | "That king [ruler of men] spoke to his ministers and friends. ||27||" |
| `Line 5054: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5055: भक्षयन्तु भवन्तो वै स्वादूनीमानि सर्वशः |` | "Let your honors eat these delicious fruits completely," |
| `Line 5056: तापसैरुपनीतानि फलानि सहिता मया ||२८||` | "These fruits brought by the ascetics, together with me. ||28||" |
| `Line 5057: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5058: ततो राजा ससचिवः फलान्यादातुमैच्छत |` | "Then the king with his ministers desired to take the fruits," |
| `Line 5059: यद्गृहीतं फलं राज्ञा तत्र कृमिरभूदणुः ||२९||` | "In the fruit that was taken by the king, there was a tiny worm. ||29||" |
| `Line 5060: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5061: ह्रस्वकः कृष्णनयनस्ताम्रो वर्णेन शौनक ||२९||` | "Small, black-eyed, and copper-colored, O Śaunaka. ||29||" |
| `Line 5062: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5063: स तं गृह्य नृपश्रेष्ठः सचिवानिदमब्रवीत् |` | "Taking it, that best of kings said this to his ministers:" |
| `Line 5064: अस्तमभ्येति सविता विषादद्य न मे भयम् ||३०||` | "The sun [Savitā] is setting, but today I have no fear of poison. ||30||" |
| `Line 5065: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5066: सत्यवागस्तु स मुनिः कृमिको मां दशत्वयम् |` | "Let this little worm bite me, for that sage's words are true," |
| `Line 5067: तक्षको नाम भूत्वा वै तथा परिहृतं भवेत् ||३१||` | "Having become Takṣaka [serpent king] by name, thus it shall be fulfilled. ||31||" |
| `Line 5068: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5069: ते चैनमन्ववर्तन्त मन्त्रिणः कालचोदिताः |` | "Those ministers, impelled by fate, followed him," |
| `Line 5070: एवमुक्त्वा स राजेन्द्रो ग्रीवायां संनिवेश्य ह ||३२||` | "Having spoken thus, that king of kings placed it on his neck. ||32||" |
| `Line 5071: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5072: कृमिकं प्राहसत्तूर्णं मुमूर्षुर्नष्टचेतनः ||३२||` | "He laughed quickly at the little worm, about to die, losing consciousness. ||32||" |
| `Line 5073: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5074: हसन्नेव च भोगेन तक्षकेणाभिवेष्टितः |` | "And even as he laughed, he was enveloped by the coils of Takṣaka," |
| `Line 5075: तस्मात्फलाद्विनिष्क्रम्य यत्तद्राज्ञे निवेदितम् ||३३||` | "Who, having emerged from that fruit, was presented to the king. ||33||" |
| `Line 5076: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5077: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5078: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5079: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5080: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5081: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5082: ४०` | "40" |
| `Line 5083: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5084: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5085: सूत उवाच||` | "Sūta [bard/narrator] said:" |
| `Line 5086: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5087: तं तथा मन्त्रिणो दृष्ट्वा भोगेन परिवेष्टितम् |` | "Seeing him thus, the ministers saw him entwined by the serpent's coils," |
| `Line 5088: विवर्णवदनाः सर्वे रुरुदुर्भृशदुःखिताः ||१||` | "All with pale faces, they wept, deeply grieved. ||1||" |
| `Line 5089: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5090: तं तु नादं ततः श्रुत्वा मन्त्रिणस्ते प्रदुद्रुवुः |` | "Hearing that sound, those ministers ran forth," |
| `Line 5091: अपश्यंश्चैव ते यान्तमाकाशे नागमद्भुतम् ||२||` | "And they saw the wondrous serpent departing through the sky. ||2||" |
| `Line 5092: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5093: सीमन्तमिव कुर्वाणं नभसः पद्मवर्चसम् |` | "Creating what seemed like a parting in the sky, radiant like a lotus," |
| `Line 5094: तक्षकं पन्नगश्रेष्ठं भृशं शोकपरायणाः ||३||` | "Takṣaka [serpent king], the foremost of serpents, while they were overcome with grief. ||3||" |
| `Line 5095: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5096: ततस्तु ते तद्गृहमग्निना वृतं; प्रदीप्यमानं विषजेन भोगिनः |` | "Then that palace, engulfed in flames, burning from the serpent's poison," |
| `Line 5097: भयात्परित्यज्य दिशः प्रपेदिरे; पपात तच्चाशनिताडितं यथा ||४||` | "They abandoned in fear and fled in all directions; and it fell as if struck by lightning. ||4||" |
| `Line 5098: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5099: ततो नृपे तक्षकतेजसा हते; प्रयुज्य सर्वाः परलोकसत्क्रियाः |` | "Then, when the king was slain by Takṣaka's power, having performed all the funeral rites," |
| `Line 5100: शुचिर्द्विजो राजपुरोहितस्तदा; तथैव ते तस्य नृपस्य मन्त्रिणः ||५||` | "The pure twice-born [Brahmin] royal priest and those ministers of the king ||5||" |
| `Line 5101: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5102: नृपं शिशुं तस्य सुतं प्रचक्रिरे; समेत्य सर्वे पुरवासिनो जनाः |` | "All the city-dwelling people, having assembled, made his son, though a child, the king;" |
| `Line 5103: नृपं यमाहुस्तममित्रघातिनं; कुरुप्रवीरं जनमेजयं जनाः ||६||` | "The people called him Janamejaya [destroyer of enemies], the slayer of foes, the foremost hero of the Kurus. ||6||" |
| `Line 5104: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5105: स बाल एवार्यमतिर्नृपोत्तमः; सहैव तैर्मन्त्रिपुरोहितैस्तदा |` | "That excellent king, though a child, with noble intellect, along with those ministers and priests," |
| `Line 5106: शशास राज्यं कुरुपुङ्गवाग्रजो; यथास्य वीरः प्रपितामहस्तथा ||७||` | "Ruled the kingdom as the foremost of the Kuru bulls, just as his valiant great-grandfather had done. ||7||" |
| `Line 5107: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5108: ततस्तु राजानममित्रतापनं; समीक्ष्य ते तस्य नृपस्य मन्त्रिणः |` | "Then, observing the king, the scorcher of enemies, those ministers of the king," |
| `Line 5109: सुवर्णवर्माणमुपेत्य काशिपं; वपुष्टमार्थं वरयां प्रचक्रमुः ||८||` | "Approached Suvarṇavarmā [golden-armored], the king of Kāśi, and sought Vapuṣṭamā [beautiful-bodied] for marriage. ||8||" |
| `Line 5110: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5111: ततः स राजा प्रददौ वपुष्टमां; कुरुप्रवीराय परीक्ष्य धर्मतः |` | "Then that king, having examined according to dharma, gave Vapuṣṭamā to the Kuru hero," |
| `Line 5112: स चापि तां प्राप्य मुदा युतोऽभव; न्न चान्यनारीषु मनो दधे क्वचित् ||९||` | "And he too, having obtained her, was filled with joy, and never set his mind on any other woman. ||9||" |
| `Line 5113: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5114: सरःसु फुल्लेषु वनेषु चैव ह; प्रसन्नचेता विजहार वीर्यवान् |` | "In blooming lakes and forests indeed, the mighty one, with a cheerful heart, sported," |
| `Line 5115: तथा स राजन्यवरो विजह्रिवा; न्यथोर्वशीं प्राप्य पुरा पुरूरवाः ||१०||` | "Thus that excellent king enjoyed himself, just as Purūravas [ancient king] had done after obtaining Urvaśī [celestial nymph] in ancient times. ||10||" |
| `Line 5116: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5117: वपुष्टमा चापि वरं पतिं तदा; प्रतीतरूपं समवाप्य भूमिपम् |` | "And Vapuṣṭamā too, having obtained the excellent husband, the renowned king of the earth," |
| `Line 5118: भावेन रामा रमयां बभूव वै; विहारकालेष्ववरोधसुन्दरी ||११||` | "The beautiful lady of the inner chambers truly delighted him with her love during times of recreation. ||11||" |
| `Line 5119: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5120: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5121: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5122: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5123: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5124: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5125: ४१` | "41" |
| `Line 5126: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5127: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5128: सूत उवाच||` | "Sūta [bard/narrator] said:" |
| `Line 5129: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5130: एतस्मिन्नेव काले तु जरत्कारुर्महातपाः |` | "At this very time, Jaratkarū [sage's name], of great austerity," |
| `Line 5131: चचार पृथिवीं कृत्स्नां यत्रसायङ्गृहो मुनिः ||१||` | "Wandered over the entire earth, the sage who had no home for the night. ||1||" |
| `Line 5132: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5133: चरन्दीक्षां महातेजा दुश्चरामकृतात्मभिः |` | "Practicing vows difficult to perform for those of undisciplined minds, the highly radiant one," |
| `Line 5134: तीर्थेष्वाप्लवनं कुर्वन्पुण्येषु विचचार ह ||२||` | "Bathing in sacred waters, he wandered through holy places. ||2||" |
| `Line 5135: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5136: वायुभक्षो निराहारः शुष्यन्नहरहर्मुनिः |` | "Subsisting on air, without food, the sage growing drier day by day," |
| `Line 5137: स ददर्श पितृन्गर्ते लम्बमानानधोमुखान् ||३||` | "He saw his ancestors hanging in a pit, head downward. ||3||" |
| `Line 5138: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5139: एकतन्त्ववशिष्टं वै वीरणस्तम्बमाश्रितान् |` | "Hanging by a single remaining thread, clinging to a clump of kusa grass [vīraṇa plant]," |
| `Line 5140: तं च तन्तुं शनैराखुमाददानं बिलाश्रयम् ||४||` | "And that thread was slowly being gnawed by a rat dwelling in a hole. ||4||" |
| `Line 5141: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5142: निराहारान्कृशान्दीनान्गर्तेऽऽर्तांस्त्राणमिच्छतः |` | "Famished, emaciated, miserable, distressed in the pit, seeking protection," |
| `Line 5143: उपसृत्य स तान्दीनान्दीनरूपोऽभ्यभाषत ||५||` | "Approaching those wretched ones, he, with a sorrowful appearance, spoke to them. ||5||" |
| `Line 5144: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5145: के भवन्तोऽवलम्बन्ते वीरणस्तम्बमाश्रिताः |` | "Who are you who hang clinging to this clump of kusa grass," |
| `Line 5146: दुर्बलं खादितैर्मूलैराखुना बिलवासिना ||६||` | "Weakened by its roots being eaten by the hole-dwelling rat? ||6||" |
| `Line 5147: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5148: वीरणस्तम्बके मूलं यदप्येकमिह स्थितम् |` | "Even the single root that remains here in this clump of kusa grass," |
| `Line 5149: तदप्ययं शनैराखुरादत्ते दशनैः शितैः ||७||` | "Even that this rat is slowly gnawing away with its sharp teeth. ||7||" |
| `Line 5150: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5151: छेत्स्यतेऽल्पावशिष्टत्वादेतदप्यचिरादिव |` | "It will be cut off soon, as very little of it remains," |
| `Line 5152: ततः स्थ पतितारोऽत्र गर्ते अस्मिन्नधोमुखाः ||८||` | "Then you will fall headlong into this pit. ||8||" |
| `Line 5153: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5154: ततो मे दुःखमुत्पन्नं दृष्ट्वा युष्मानधोमुखान् |` | "Therefore, grief has arisen in me seeing you hanging head-downward," |
| `Line 5155: कृच्छ्रामापदमापन्नान्प्रियं किं करवाणि वः ||९||` | "Having fallen into dire calamity. What service may I do for you? ||9||" |
| `Line 5156: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5157: तपसोऽस्य चतुर्थेन तृतीयेनापि वा पुनः |` | "With a fourth of my ascetic merit, or even a third," |
| `Line 5158: अर्धेन वापि निस्तर्तुमापदं ब्रूत माचिरम् ||१०||` | "Or even half, to rescue you from this calamity—tell me quickly. ||10||" |
| `Line 5159: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5160: अथवापि समग्रेण तरन्तु तपसा मम |` | "Or even with all of my ascetic merit, may you be rescued," |
| `Line 5161: भवन्तः सर्व एवास्मात्काममेवं विधीयताम् ||११||` | "All of you from this—let it be done according to your wish. ||11||" |
| `Line 5162: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5163: पितर ऊचुः||` | "The Pitṛs [ancestors] said:" |
| `Line 5164: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5165: ऋद्धो भवान्ब्रह्मचारी यो नस्त्रातुमिहेच्छति |` | "Prosperous are you, O celibate one, who wishes to rescue us here," |
| `Line 5166: न तु विप्राग्र्य तपसा शक्यमेतद्व्यपोहितुम् ||१२||` | "But O foremost of Brahmins, this cannot be removed by ascetic merit. ||12||" |
| `Line 5167: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5168: अस्ति नस्तात तपसः फलं प्रवदतां वर |` | "We have, dear child, the fruit of austerities, O best of speakers," |
| `Line 5169: सन्तानप्रक्षयाद्ब्रह्मन्पतामो निरयेऽशुचौ ||१३||` | "But due to the extinction of our lineage, O Brahmin, we are falling into an impure hell. ||13||" |
| `Line 5170: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5171: लम्बतामिह नस्तात न ज्ञानं प्रतिभाति वै |` | "As we hang here, dear child, our knowledge does not shine forth," |
| `Line 5172: येन त्वां नाभिजानीमो लोके विख्यातपौरुषम् ||१४||` | "By which we do not recognize you, who is renowned for prowess in the world. ||14||" |
| `Line 5173: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5174: ऋद्धो भवान्महाभागो यो नः शोच्यान्सुदुःखितान् |` | "Prosperous are you, O fortunate one, who out of compassion," |
| `Line 5175: शोचस्युपेत्य कारुण्याच्छृणु ये वै वयं द्विज ||१५||` | "Laments for us who are pitiable and deeply distressed. Listen to who we are, O twice-born [Brahmin]. ||15||" |
| `Line 5176: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5177: यायावरा नाम वयमृषयः संशितव्रताः |` | "We are the Yāyāvara [wandering] sages, of strict vows," |
| `Line 5178: लोकात्पुण्यादिह भ्रष्टाः सन्तानप्रक्षयाद्विभो ||१६||` | "Fallen here from the virtuous world due to the extinction of our lineage, O mighty one. ||16||" |
| `Line 5179: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5180: प्रनष्टं नस्तपः पुण्यं न हि नस्तन्तुरस्ति वै |` | "Our ascetic merit is lost, for we truly have no lineage continuation," |
| `Line 5181: अस्ति त्वेकोऽद्य नस्तन्तुः सोऽपि नास्ति यथा तथा ||१७||` | "There is today only one thread of our lineage, but he too is as good as non-existent. ||17||" |
| `Line 5182: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5183: मन्दभाग्योऽल्पभाग्यानां बन्धुः स किल नः कुले |` | "That unfortunate relative in our family of ill-fated ones," |
| `Line 5184: जरत्कारुरिति ख्यातो वेदवेदाङ्गपारगः ||१८||` | "Is known as Jaratkāru, a master of the Vedas and Vedāṅgas [Vedic auxiliaries]. ||18||" |
| `Line 5185: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5186: नियतात्मा महात्मा च सुव्रतः सुमहातपाः ||१८||` | "Self-controlled, noble-souled, of excellent vows, and of great austerity. ||18||" |
| `Line 5187: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5188: तेन स्म तपसो लोभात्कृच्छ्रमापादिता वयम् |` | "Due to his greed for austerities, we have been brought to this miserable state," |
| `Line 5189: न तस्य भार्या पुत्रो वा बान्धवो वास्ति कश्चन ||१९||` | "He has neither wife, nor son, nor any relative whatsoever. ||19||" |
| `Line 5190: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5191: तस्माल्लम्बामहे गर्ते नष्टसञ्ज्ञा ह्यनाथवत् |` | "Therefore we hang in this pit, unconscious like orphans," |
| `Line 5192: स वक्तव्यस्त्वया दृष्ट्वा अस्माकं नाथवत्तया ||२०||` | "He should be told by you upon seeing him, as our protector. ||20||" |
| `Line 5193: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5194: पितरस्तेऽवलम्बन्ते गर्ते दीना अधोमुखाः |` | "Your forefathers hang in a pit, wretched, with faces downward," |
| `Line 5195: साधु दारान्कुरुष्वेति प्रजायस्वेति चाभिभो ||२१||` | "'Please take a wife and beget children,' O powerful one. ||21||" |
| `Line 5196: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5197: कुलतन्तुर्हि नः शिष्टस्त्वमेवैकस्तपोधन ||२१||` | "For you alone remain as the thread of our family, O wealth of austerities. ||21||" |
| `Line 5198: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5199: यं तु पश्यसि नो ब्रह्मन्वीरणस्तम्बमाश्रितान् |` | "The reed grass clump that you see us clinging to, O Brahmin," |
| `Line 5200: एषोऽस्माकं कुलस्तम्ब आसीत्स्वकुलवर्धनः ||२२||` | "This was the pillar of our family, the propagator of our lineage. ||22||" |
| `Line 5201: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5202: यानि पश्यसि वै ब्रह्मन्मूलानीहास्य वीरुधः |` | "O Brahman [learned sage], the roots of this creeper that you see here," |
| `Line 5203: एते नस्तन्तवस्तात कालेन परिभक्षिताः ||२३||` | "These are our lineage threads, dear one, being devoured by Time [personified]. ||23||" |
| `Line 5204: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5205: यत्त्वेतत्पश्यसि ब्रह्मन्मूलमस्यार्धभक्षितम् |` | "And this root that you see, O Brahman, half-eaten," |
| `Line 5206: तत्र लम्बामहे सर्वे सोऽप्येकस्तप आस्थितः ||२४||` | "On it we all hang, while that one [Jaratāru] is engaged in austerities alone. ||24||" |
| `Line 5207: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5208: यमाखुं पश्यसि ब्रह्मन्काल एष महाबलः |` | "The rat that you see, O Brahman, is mighty Time itself," |
| `Line 5209: स तं तपोरतं मन्दं शनैः क्षपयते तुदन् ||२५||` | "It slowly consumes that slow-witted one absorbed in austerities, gnawing away. ||25||" |
| `Line 5210: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5211: जरत्कारुं तपोलुब्धं मन्दात्मानमचेतसम् ||२५||` | "Jaratāru, greedy for austerities, slow-minded and thoughtless. ||25||" |
| `Line 5212: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5213: न हि नस्तत्तपस्तस्य तारयिष्यति सत्तम |` | "Indeed, his austerities will not save us, O excellent one," |
| `Line 5214: छिन्नमूलान्परिभ्रष्टान्कालोपहतचेतसः ||२६||` | "With our roots cut, fallen away, our minds destroyed by Time. ||26||" |
| `Line 5215: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5216: नरकप्रतिष्ठान्पश्यास्मान्यथा दुष्कृतिनस्तथा ||२६||` | "See us destined for hell, like evildoers. ||26||" |
| `Line 5217: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5218: अस्मासु पतितेष्वत्र सह पूर्वैः पितामहैः |` | "When we fall here along with our forefathers," |
| `Line 5219: छिन्नः कालेन सोऽप्यत्र गन्ता वै नरकं ततः ||२७||` | "Cut off by Time, he too will then go to hell. ||27||" |
| `Line 5220: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5221: तपो वाप्यथवा यज्ञो यच्चान्यत्पावनं महत् |` | "Austerities, sacrifices, or any other great purifying act," |
| `Line 5222: तत्सर्वं न समं तात सन्तत्येति सतां मतम् ||२८||` | "None of these equals progeny, dear one - this is the opinion of the virtuous. ||28||" |
| `Line 5223: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5224: स तात दृष्ट्वा ब्रूयास्त्वं जरत्कारुं तपस्विनम् |` | "Having seen this, dear one, you should tell the ascetic Jaratāru," |
| `Line 5225: यथादृष्टमिदं चास्मै त्वयाख्येयमशेषतः ||२९||` | "And you should relate to him completely everything as you have seen it. ||29||" |
| `Line 5226: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5227: यथा दारान्प्रकुर्यात्स पुत्रांश्चोत्पादयेद्यथा |` | "How he should take a wife and how he should beget sons," |
| `Line 5228: तथा ब्रह्मंस्त्वया वाच्यः सोऽस्माकं नाथवत्तया ||३०||` | "Thus, O Brahman [sage], you should instruct him, who is like a protector to us. ||30||" |
| `Line 5229: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5230: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5231: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5232: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5233: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5234: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5235: ४२` | "42" |
| `Line 5236: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5237: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5238: सूत उवाच||` | "Sūta [bard/narrator] said:" |
| `Line 5239: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5240: एतच्छ्रुत्वा जरत्कारुर्दुःखशोकपरायणः |` | "Hearing this, Jaratkāru, overwhelmed with grief and sorrow," |
| `Line 5241: उवाच स्वान्पितृन्दुःखाद्बाष्पसंदिग्धया गिरा ||१||` | "Spoke to his forefathers with a voice choked with tears due to sorrow. ||1||" |
| `Line 5242: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5243: अहमेव जरत्कारुः किल्बिषी भवतां सुतः |` | "I am indeed Jaratkāru, your sinful son," |
| `Line 5244: तद्दण्डं धारयत मे दुष्कृतेरकृतात्मनः ||२||` | "Therefore, impose punishment on me, the evil-doer with an undisciplined self. ||2||" |
| `Line 5245: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5246: पितर ऊचुः||` | "The forefathers said:" |
| `Line 5247: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5248: पुत्र दिष्ट्यासि सम्प्राप्त इमं देशं यदृच्छया |` | "Son, fortunately you have arrived at this place by chance," |
| `Line 5249: किमर्थं च त्वया ब्रह्मन्न कृतो दारसङ्ग्रहः ||३||` | "But why, O Brahman [ascetic], have you not taken a wife? ||3||" |
| `Line 5250: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5251: जरत्कारुरुवाच॥` | "Jaratkāru said:" |
| `Line 5252: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5253: ममायं पितरो नित्यं हृद्यर्थः परिवर्तते |` | "O fathers, this thought constantly revolves in my heart:" |
| `Line 5254: ऊर्ध्वरेताः शरीरं वै प्रापयेयममुत्र वै ॥४॥` | "As a celibate [ūrdhvaretās], I would indeed carry my body to the other world. ||4||" |
| `Line 5255: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5256: एवं दृष्ट्वा तु भवतः शकुन्तानिव लम्बतः |` | "But having seen you hanging like birds," |
| `Line 5257: मया निवर्तिता बुद्धिर्ब्रह्मचर्यात्पितामहाः ॥५॥` | "My mind has turned away from celibacy, O grandfathers. ||5||" |
| `Line 5258: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5259: करिष्ये वः प्रियं कामं निवेक्ष्ये नात्र संशयः |` | "I will fulfill your dear wish and marry, there is no doubt about this," |
| `Line 5260: सनाम्नीं यद्यहं कन्यामुपलप्स्ये कदाचन ॥६॥` | "If I ever find a maiden who bears the same name as mine. ||6||" |
| `Line 5261: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5262: भविष्यति च या काचिद्भैक्षवत्स्वयमुद्यता |` | "And she should be one who comes forward herself like a beggar," |
| `Line 5263: प्रतिग्रहीता तामस्मि न भरेयं च यामहम् ॥७॥` | "I will accept her, but not one whom I would have to maintain. ||7||" |
| `Line 5264: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5265: एवंविधमहं कुर्यां निवेशं प्राप्नुयां यदि |` | "I would marry in this manner if I find such a bride," |
| `Line 5266: अन्यथा न करिष्ये तु सत्यमेतत्पितामहाः ॥८॥` | "Otherwise I will not do so - this is the truth, O grandfathers. ||8||" |
| `Line 5267: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5268: सूत उवाच॥` | "Sūta [bard/narrator] said:" |
| `Line 5269: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5270: एवमुक्त्वा तु स पितृंश्चचार पृथिवीं मुनिः |` | "Having spoken thus to his ancestors, the sage wandered over the earth," |
| `Line 5271: न च स्म लभते भार्यां वृद्धोऽयमिति शौनक ॥९॥` | "But he did not find a wife, as people thought, 'He is old,' O Śaunaka. ||9||" |
| `Line 5272: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5273: यदा निर्वेदमापन्नः पितृभिश्चोदितस्तथा |` | "When he became despondent, and was thus urged by his ancestors," |
| `Line 5274: तदारण्यं स गत्वोच्चैश्चुक्रोश भृशदुःखितः ॥१०॥` | "Then, going to the forest, he cried out loudly, deeply distressed. ||10||" |
| `Line 5275: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5276: यानि भूतानि सन्तीह स्थावराणि चराणि च |` | "Whatever beings exist here, both immovable and movable," |
| `Line 5277: अन्तर्हितानि वा यानि तानि शृण्वन्तु मे वचः ||११||` | "Or those that are invisible, let them all hear my words. ||11||" |
| `Line 5278: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5279: उग्रे तपसि वर्तन्तं पितरश्चोदयन्ति माम् |` | "Engaged in severe austerities, my ancestors [forefathers] urge me," |
| `Line 5280: निविशस्वेति दुःखार्तास्तेषां प्रियचिकीर्षया ||१२||` | "'Settle down,' they say, afflicted with sorrow; desiring to please them ||12||" |
| `Line 5281: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5282: निवेशार्थ्यखिलां भूमिं कन्याभैक्षं चरामि भोः |` | "For the purpose of settling down, I wander the entire earth begging for a maiden, oh!" |
| `Line 5283: दरिद्रो दुःखशीलश्च पितृभिः संनियोजितः ||१३||` | "Poor and accustomed to suffering, commissioned by my ancestors. ||13||" |
| `Line 5284: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5285: यस्य कन्यास्ति भूतस्य ये मयेह प्रकीर्तिताः |` | "Whichever being has a daughter among those I have addressed here," |
| `Line 5286: ते मे कन्यां प्रयच्छन्तु चरतः सर्वतोदिशम् ||१४||` | "Let them give me a maiden as I wander in all directions. ||14||" |
| `Line 5287: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5288: मम कन्या सनाम्नी या भैक्षवच्चोद्यता भवेत् |` | "A maiden who has the same name as mine and who would be offered like alms," |
| `Line 5289: भरेयं चैव यां नाहं तां मे कन्यां प्रयच्छत ||१५||` | "And whom I would not have to support—give me such a maiden. ||15||" |
| `Line 5290: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5291: ततस्ते पन्नगा ये वै जरत्कारौ समाहिताः |` | "Then those serpents [nāgas] who were attentive to Jaratkāru," |
| `Line 5292: तामादाय प्रवृत्तिं ते वासुकेः प्रत्यवेदयन् ||१६||` | "Taking that information, reported it to Vāsuki [serpent king]. ||16||" |
| `Line 5293: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5294: तेषां श्रुत्वा स नागेन्द्रः कन्यां तां समलङ्कृताम् |` | "Hearing them, that lord of serpents, taking his well-adorned daughter," |
| `Line 5295: प्रगृह्यारण्यमगमत्समीपं तस्य पन्नगः ||१७||` | "The serpent went to the forest near him. ||17||" |
| `Line 5296: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5297: तत्र तां भैक्षवत्कन्यां प्रादात्तस्मै महात्मने |` | "There, he offered that maiden like alms to that great soul," |
| `Line 5298: नागेन्द्रो वासुकिर्ब्रह्मन्न स तां प्रत्यगृह्णत ||१८||` | "Vāsuki, the lord of serpents, O Brahman [sage], but he did not accept her. ||18||" |
| `Line 5299: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5300: असनामेति वै मत्वा भरणे चाविचारिते |` | "Thinking 'she is not of the same name,' and without considering her maintenance," |
| `Line 5301: मोक्षभावे स्थितश्चापि द्वन्द्वीभूतः परिग्रहे ||१९||` | "Though established in the state of liberation [mokṣa], he became conflicted regarding acceptance [of a wife]. ||19||" |
| `Line 5302: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5303: ततो नाम स कन्यायाः पप्रच्छ भृगुनन्दन |` | "Then, O Bhṛgunandana [descendant of Bhṛgu], he asked the name of the maiden," |
| `Line 5304: वासुके भरणं चास्या न कुर्यामित्युवाच ह ||२०||` | "And said to Vāsuki, 'I shall not maintain her.' ||20||" |
| `Line 5305: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5306: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5307: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5308: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5309: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5310: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5311: ४३` | "43" |
| `Line 5312: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5313: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5314: सूत उवाच||` | "Sūta [bard/narrator] said:" |
| `Line 5315: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5316: वासुकिस्त्वब्रवीद्वाक्यं जरत्कारुमृषिं तदा |` | "Then Vāsuki spoke these words to the sage Jaratkarū," |
| `Line 5317: सनामा तव कन्येयं स्वसा मे तपसान्विता ||१||` | "This maiden, my sister, bearing your name, is endowed with austerity [tapas]. ||1||" |
| `Line 5318: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5319: भरिष्यामि च ते भार्यां प्रतीच्छेमां द्विजोत्तम |` | "I shall maintain your wife; accept her, O best of the twice-born [Brahmin]," |
| `Line 5320: रक्षणं च करिष्येऽस्याः सर्वशक्त्या तपोधन ||२||` | "And I shall protect her with all my power, O wealthy in austerities [tapas]. ||2||" |
| `Line 5321: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5322: प्रतिश्रुते तु नागेन भरिष्ये भगिनीमिति |` | "When the serpent [nāga] promised, 'I shall maintain my sister,'" |
| `Line 5323: जरत्कारुस्तदा वेश्म भुजगस्य जगाम ह ||३||` | "Jaratkarū then went to the dwelling of the serpent. ||3||" |
| `Line 5324: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5325: तत्र मन्त्रविदां श्रेष्ठस्तपोवृद्धो महाव्रतः |` | "There, the foremost among knowers of mantras [sacred formulas], grown in austerity, of great vows," |
| `Line 5326: जग्राह पाणिं धर्मात्मा विधिमन्त्रपुरस्कृतम् ||४||` | "The righteous one [Jaratakāru] took her hand with proper mantras and rituals. ||4||" |
| `Line 5327: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5328: ततो वासगृहं शुभ्रं पन्नगेन्द्रस्य संमतम् |` | "Then to a splendid dwelling place, approved by the serpent lord [Vāsuki]," |
| `Line 5329: जगाम भार्यामादाय स्तूयमानो महर्षिभिः ||५||` | "He went, taking his wife, being praised by the great sages. ||5||" |
| `Line 5330: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5331: शयनं तत्र वै कॢप्तं स्पर्ध्यास्तरणसंवृतम् |` | "A bed was arranged there, covered with enviable bedding," |
| `Line 5332: तत्र भार्यासहायः स जरत्कारुरुवास ह ||६||` | "There Jaratakāru dwelt with his wife as companion. ||6||" |
| `Line 5333: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5334: स तत्र समयं चक्रे भार्यया सह सत्तमः |` | "That excellent one made an agreement there with his wife," |
| `Line 5335: विप्रियं मे न कर्तव्यं न च वाच्यं कदाचन ||७||` | "'Nothing unpleasant should be done to me, nor should anything disagreeable ever be said. ||7||'" |
| `Line 5336: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5337: त्यजेयमप्रिये हि त्वां कृते वासं च ते गृहे |` | "'I would abandon you if anything unpleasant is done, and also my residence in your house,'" |
| `Line 5338: एतद्गृहाण वचनं मया यत्समुदीरितम् ||८||` | "'Accept these words that have been uttered by me.' ||8||" |
| `Line 5339: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5340: ततः परमसंविग्ना स्वसा नागपतेस्तु सा |` | "Then, extremely agitated, that sister of the serpent lord [Vāsuki]," |
| `Line 5341: अतिदुःखान्विता वाचं तमुवाचैवमस्त्विति ||९||` | "Filled with great distress, said to him, 'Let it be so.' ||9||" |
| `Line 5342: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5343: तथैव सा च भर्तारं दुःखशीलमुपाचरत् |` | "And she served her husband, who was of a melancholy disposition," |
| `Line 5344: उपायैः श्वेतकाकीयैः प्रियकामा यशस्विनी ||१०||` | "With rare and extraordinary [white-crow-like] methods, the illustrious one desiring to please him. ||10||" |
| `Line 5345: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5346: ऋतुकाले ततः स्नाता कदाचिद्वासुकेः स्वसा |` | "Then once, having bathed at the proper time [for conception], Vāsuki's sister," |
| `Line 5347: भर्तारं तं यथान्यायमुपतस्थे महामुनिम् ||११||` | "Approached her husband, the great sage, according to proper custom. ||11||" |
| `Line 5348: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5349: तत्र तस्याः समभवद्गर्भो ज्वलनसंनिभः |` | "There in her was conceived an embryo resembling fire," |
| `Line 5350: अतीव तपसा युक्तो वैश्वानरसमद्युतिः ||१२||` | "Endowed with extreme ascetic power, with radiance equal to Vaiśvānara [fire deity]. ||12||" |
| `Line 5351: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5352: शुक्लपक्षे यथा सोमो व्यवर्धत तथैव सः ||१२||` | "Just as the Soma [moon] waxes in the bright fortnight, so did he grow. ||12||" |
| `Line 5353: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5354: ततः कतिपयाहस्य जरत्कारुर्महातपाः |` | "Then after a few days, Jaratkarū [sage], of great austerity," |
| `Line 5355: उत्सङ्गेऽस्याः शिरः कृत्वा सुष्वाप परिखिन्नवत् ||१३||` | "Placing his head on her lap, fell asleep as if exhausted. ||13||" |
| `Line 5356: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5357: तस्मिंश्च सुप्ते विप्रेन्द्रे सवितास्तमियाद्गिरिम् |` | "And while that foremost of Brahmins was asleep, the Savitā [sun] set behind the mountain," |
| `Line 5358: अह्नः परिक्षये ब्रह्मंस्ततः साचिन्तयत्तदा ||१४||` | "At the end of the day, O Brahman [sage], then she began to think. ||14||" |
| `Line 5359: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5360: वासुकेर्भगिनी भीता धर्मलोपान्मनस्विनी ||१४||` | "Vāsuki's sister [Jaratkāru], thoughtful and afraid of violating dharma [religious duty]. ||14||" |
| `Line 5361: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5362: किं नु मे सुकृतं भूयाद्भर्तुरुत्थापनं न वा |` | "What would be the right thing for me to do—to wake my husband or not?" |
| `Line 5363: दुःखशीलो हि धर्मात्मा कथं नास्यापराध्नुयाम् ||१५||` | "For he is righteous but easily distressed—how might I not offend him? ||15||" |
| `Line 5364: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5365: कोपो वा धर्मशीलस्य धर्मलोपोऽथ वा पुनः |` | "Either the anger of the righteous one, or the violation of dharma again," |
| `Line 5366: धर्मलोपो गरीयान्वै स्यादत्रेत्यकरोन्मनः ||१६||` | "The violation of dharma would be more serious here—thus she made up her mind. ||16||" |
| `Line 5367: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5368: उत्थापयिष्ये यद्येनं ध्रुवं कोपं करिष्यति |` | "If I wake him, he will surely become angry," |
| `Line 5369: धर्मलोपो भवेदस्य सन्ध्यातिक्रमणे ध्रुवम् ||१७||` | "But there will certainly be a violation of dharma if he misses the twilight prayers. ||17||" |
| `Line 5370: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5371: इति निश्चित्य मनसा जरत्कारुर्भुजङ्गमा |` | "Having thus decided in her mind, Jaratkāru of the serpent race," |
| `Line 5372: तमृषिं दीप्ततपसं शयानमनलोपमम् ||१८||` | "To that sage of blazing austerity, who was sleeping, resembling fire, ||18||" |
| `Line 5373: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5374: उवाचेदं वचः श्लक्ष्णं ततो मधुरभाषिणी ||१८||` | "Spoke these gentle words, she of the sweet speech. ||18||" |
| `Line 5375: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5376: उत्तिष्ठ त्वं महाभाग सूर्योऽस्तमुपगच्छति |` | "Rise up, O fortunate one [great-blessed], the sun is setting," |
| `Line 5377: सन्ध्यामुपास्स्व भगवन्नपः स्पृष्ट्वा यतव्रतः ||१९||` | "Worship the twilight [sandhyā], O lord, after touching water, with controlled vows. ||19||" |
| `Line 5378: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5379: प्रादुष्कृताग्निहोत्रोऽयं मुहूर्तो रम्यदारुणः |` | "This is the time for performing Agnihotra [fire sacrifice], a beautiful reddish moment," |
| `Line 5380: सन्ध्या प्रवर्तते चेयं पश्चिमायां दिशि प्रभो ||२०||` | "And this twilight proceeds in the western direction, O master. ||20||" |
| `Line 5381: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5382: एवमुक्तः स भगवाञ्जरत्कारुर्महातपाः |` | "Thus addressed, the venerable Jaratkāru [sage] of great austerity," |
| `Line 5383: भार्यां प्रस्फुरमाणोष्ठ इदं वचनमब्रवीत् ||२१||` | "With quivering lips, spoke these words to his wife: ||21||" |
| `Line 5384: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5385: अवमानः प्रयुक्तोऽयं त्वया मम भुजङ्गमे |` | "This insult has been inflicted by you upon me, O serpent woman," |
| `Line 5386: समीपे ते न वत्स्यामि गमिष्यामि यथागतम् ||२२||` | "I shall not dwell near you; I shall depart as I came. ||22||" |
| `Line 5387: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5388: न हि तेजोऽस्ति वामोरु मयि सुप्ते विभावसोः |` | "There is no power, O beautiful-thighed one, for the sun [fire-lord] to set while I sleep," |
| `Line 5389: अस्तं गन्तुं यथाकालमिति मे हृदि वर्तते ||२३||` | "To go to setting at its proper time - this dwells in my heart. ||23||" |
| `Line 5390: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5391: न चाप्यवमतस्येह वस्तुं रोचेत कस्यचित् |` | "And no one who is insulted would like to stay here," |
| `Line 5392: किं पुनर्धर्मशीलस्य मम वा मद्विधस्य वा ||२४||` | "How much less for one devoted to dharma [righteousness] like me or those like me? ||24||" |
| `Line 5393: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5394: एवमुक्ता जरत्कारुर्भर्त्रा हृदयकम्पनम् |` | "Thus addressed by her husband, Jaratkāru [female form], with a trembling heart," |
| `Line 5395: अब्रवीद्भगिनी तत्र वासुकेः संनिवेशने ||२५||` | "The sister of Vāsuki spoke there in Vāsuki's dwelling: ||25||" |
| `Line 5396: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5397: नावमानात्कृतवती तवाहं प्रतिबोधनम् |` | "I did not awaken you out of disrespect," |
| `Line 5398: धर्मलोपो न ते विप्र स्यादित्येतत्कृतं मया ||२६||` | "I did this so that you, O Brahmin, would not neglect dharma [religious duty]. ||26||" |
| `Line 5399: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5400: उवाच भार्यामित्युक्तो जरत्कारुर्महातपाः |` | "Having been thus addressed, Jaratkāru of great austerity said to his wife:" |
| `Line 5401: ऋषिः कोपसमाविष्टस्त्यक्तुकामो भुजङ्गमाम् ||२७||` | "The sage, filled with anger, desired to leave the serpent woman. ||27||" |
| `Line 5402: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5403: न मे वागनृतं प्राह गमिष्येऽहं भुजङ्गमे |` | "My word has never spoken falsehood. I shall depart, O serpent woman," |
| `Line 5404: समयो ह्येष मे पूर्वं त्वया सह मिथः कृतः ||२८||` | "For this was the agreement previously made between you and me. ||28||" |
| `Line 5405: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5406: सुखमस्म्युषितो भद्रे ब्रूयास्त्वं भ्रातरं शुभे |` | "I have dwelt happily here, O blessed one. Tell your brother, O auspicious lady," |
| `Line 5407: इतो मयि गते भीरु गतः स भगवानिति ||२९||` | "'When I departed from here, O timid one, that venerable one also departed.' ||29||" |
| `Line 5408: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5409: त्वं चापि मयि निष्क्रान्ते न शोकं कर्तुमर्हसि ||२९||` | "And you too, when I have gone, should not grieve. ||29||" |
| `Line 5410: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5411: इत्युक्ता सानवद्याङ्गी प्रत्युवाच पतिं तदा |` | "Thus addressed, she of faultless limbs then replied to her husband," |
| `Line 5412: जरत्कारुं जरत्कारुश्चिन्ताशोकपरायणा ||३०||` | "Jaratkāru to Jaratkāru, overwhelmed with anxiety and sorrow. ||30||" |
| `Line 5413: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5414: बाष्पगद्गदया वाचा मुखेन परिशुष्यता |` | "With a voice choked with tears and with a parched mouth," |
| `Line 5415: कृताञ्जलिर्वरारोहा पर्यश्रुनयना ततः ||३१||` | "With folded hands, the beautiful woman with eyes full of tears, ||31||" |
| `Line 5416: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5417: धैर्यमालम्ब्य वामोरूर्हृदयेन प्रवेपता ||३१||` | "Summoning courage, the fair-thighed one, with a trembling heart, ||31||" |
| `Line 5418: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5419: न मामर्हसि धर्मज्ञ परित्यक्तुमनागसम् |` | "You should not, O knower of dharma, abandon me who am innocent," |
| `Line 5420: धर्मे स्थितां स्थितो धर्मे सदा प्रियहिते रताम् ||३२||` | "Me who stands firm in dharma, as you stand in dharma, always devoted to your welfare and happiness. ||32||" |
| `Line 5421: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5422: प्रदाने कारणं यच्च मम तुभ्यं द्विजोत्तम |` | "The purpose for which I was given to you, O best of the twice-born [Brahmin]," |
| `Line 5423: तदलब्धवतीं मन्दां किं मां वक्ष्यति वासुखिः ||३३||` | "Not having achieved that, what will the unhappy one [Vāsuki] say to me, unfortunate as I am? ||33||" |
| `Line 5424: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5425: मातृशापाभिभूतानां ज्ञातीनां मम सत्तम |` | "For my kinsmen who are afflicted by their mother's curse, O excellent one," |
| `Line 5426: अपत्यमीप्षितं त्वत्तस्तच्च तावन्न दृश्यते ||३४||` | "The desired offspring from you is not yet seen. ||34||" |
| `Line 5427: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5428: त्वत्तो ह्यपत्यलाभेन ज्ञातीनां मे शिवं भवेत् |` | "By obtaining offspring from you, there would be welfare for my relatives," |
| `Line 5429: सम्प्रयोगो भवेन्नायं मम मोघस्त्वया द्विज ||३५||` | "Let this union with you not be fruitless, O twice-born [Brahmin]. ||35||" |
| `Line 5430: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5431: ज्ञातीनां हितमिच्छन्ती भगवंस्त्वां प्रसादये |` | "Desiring the welfare of my relatives, O lord, I beseech you," |
| `Line 5432: इममव्यक्तरूपं मे गर्भमाधाय सत्तम ||३६||` | "Place in me this unmanifested form of a child, O excellent one. ||36||" |
| `Line 5433: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5434: कथं त्यक्त्वा महात्मा सन्गन्तुमिच्छस्यनागसम् ||३६||` | "How can you, being a great soul, wish to depart leaving me who is innocent? ||36||" |
| `Line 5435: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5436: एवमुक्तस्तु स मुनिर्भार्यां वचनमब्रवीत् |` | "Thus addressed, that sage spoke these words to his wife," |
| `Line 5437: यद्युक्तमनुरूपं च जरत्कारुस्तपोधनः ||३७||` | "Words that were proper and appropriate, Jaratkāru, the wealth of austerities [ascetic sage]. ||37||" |
| `Line 5438: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5439: अस्त्येष गर्भः सुभगे तव वैश्वानरोपमः |` | "This child exists in you, O fortunate one, comparable to Vaiśvānara [fire deity]," |
| `Line 5440: ऋषिः परमधर्मात्मा वेदवेदाङ्गपारगः ||३८||` | "A sage of supreme righteousness, master of the Vedas and Vedāṅgas [auxiliary texts]. ||38||" |
| `Line 5441: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5442: एवमुक्त्वा स धर्मात्मा जरत्कारुर्महानृषिः |` | "Having spoken thus, that righteous-souled Jaratkāru, the great sage," |
| `Line 5443: उग्राय तपसे भूयो जगाम कृतनिश्चयः ||३९||` | "Went again for severe austerities, having made his decision. ||39||" |
| `Line 5444: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5445: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5446: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5447: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5448: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5449: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5450: ४४` | "44" |
| `Line 5451: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5452: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5453: सूत उवाच||` | "Sūta [bard-narrator] said:" |
| `Line 5454: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5455: गतमात्रं तु भर्तारं जरत्कारुरवेदयत् |` | "As soon as her husband had departed, Jaratkāru [female sage] informed" |
| `Line 5456: भ्रातुस्त्वरितमागम्य यथातथ्यं तपोधन ||१||` | "Her brother, quickly approaching him, the truth exactly as it happened, O wealth of austerities [sage]. ||1||" |
| `Line 5457: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5458: ततः स भुजगश्रेष्ठः श्रुत्वा सुमहदप्रियम् |` | "Then that foremost of serpents [Vāsuki], hearing this greatly unpleasant news," |
| `Line 5459: उवाच भगिनीं दीनां तदा दीनतरः स्वयम् ||२||` | "Spoke to his distressed sister, himself even more distressed then. ||2||" |
| `Line 5460: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5461: जानासि भद्रे यत्कार्यं प्रदाने कारणं च यत् |` | "You know, O auspicious one, what purpose and reason there was in giving you away," |
| `Line 5462: पन्नगानां हितार्थाय पुत्रस्ते स्यात्ततो यदि ||३||` | "For the welfare of the serpents [nāgas], if a son would be born to you from him. ||3||" |
| `Line 5463: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5464: स सर्पसत्रात्किल नो मोक्षयिष्यति वीर्यवान् |` | "That mighty one will indeed liberate us from the serpent sacrifice [Sarpa-satra]," |
| `Line 5465: एवं पितामहः पूर्वमुक्तवान्मां सुरैः सह ||४||` | "Thus had the Grandfather [Brahmā] previously told me along with the gods. ||4||" |
| `Line 5466: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5467: अप्यस्ति गर्भः सुभगे तस्मात्ते मुनिसत्तमात् |` | "Is there a child, O fortunate one, from that best of sages in you?" |
| `Line 5468: न चेच्छाम्यफलं तस्य दारकर्म मनीषिणः ||५||` | "I do not wish the marriage ceremony of that wise one to be fruitless. ||5||" |
| `Line 5469: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5470: कामं च मम न न्याय्यं प्रष्टुं त्वां कार्यमीदृशम् |` | "Indeed, it is not proper for me to ask you about such a matter," |
| `Line 5471: किं तु कार्यगरीयस्त्वात्ततस्त्वाहमचूचुदम् ||६||` | "But due to the importance of the task, therefore I urged you. ||6||" |
| `Line 5472: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5473: दुर्वासतां विदित्वा च भर्तुस्तेऽतितपस्विनः |` | "And knowing the irritable nature of your husband, that great ascetic," |
| `Line 5474: नैनमन्वागमिष्यामि कदाचिद्धि शपेत्स माम् ||७||` | "I will not follow after him, for he might indeed curse me. ||7||" |
| `Line 5475: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5476: आचक्ष्व भद्रे भर्तुस्त्वं सर्वमेव विचेष्टितम् |` | "Tell me, auspicious one, all about your husband's actions," |
| `Line 5477: शल्यमुद्धर मे घोरं भद्रे हृदि चिरस्थितम् ||८||` | "Remove, O blessed one, the terrible arrow [of worry] that has long been lodged in my heart. ||8||" |
| `Line 5478: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5479: जरत्कारुस्ततो वाक्यमित्युक्ता प्रत्यभाषत |` | "Jaratkāru, thus addressed, replied with these words," |
| `Line 5480: आश्वासयन्ती सन्तप्तं वासुकिं पन्नगेश्वरम् ||९||` | "Consoling the distressed Vāsuki, the lord of serpents [nāga king]. ||9||" |
| `Line 5481: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5482: पृष्टो मयापत्यहेतोः स महात्मा महातपाः |` | "When asked by me about offspring, that great-souled one of great austerities," |
| `Line 5483: अस्तीत्युदरमुद्दिश्य ममेदं गतवांश्च सः ||१०||` | "Said 'It exists,' pointing to my womb, and then he departed. ||10||" |
| `Line 5484: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5485: स्वैरेष्वपि न तेनाहं स्मरामि वितथं क्वचित् |` | "Even in personal matters, I do not remember him ever speaking falsely," |
| `Line 5486: उक्तपूर्वं कुतो राजन्साम्पराये स वक्ष्यति ||११||` | "How then, O king [of serpents], would he speak falsely about the future? ||11||" |
| `Line 5487: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5488: न सन्तापस्त्वया कार्यः कार्यं प्रति भुजङ्गमे |` | "You should not grieve about this matter, O serpent," |
| `Line 5489: उत्पत्स्यति हि ते पुत्रो ज्वलनार्कसमद्युतिः ||१२||` | "For a son will be born to you with radiance equal to fire and the sun. ||12||" |
| `Line 5490: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5491: इत्युक्त्वा हि स मां भ्रातर्गतो भर्ता तपोवनम् |` | "Having said this to me, O brother, my husband departed for the forest of austerities," |
| `Line 5492: तस्माद्व्येतु परं दुःखं तवेदं मनसि स्थितम् ||१३||` | "Therefore, let this extreme sorrow that dwells in your mind depart. ||13||" |
| `Line 5493: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5494: एतच्छ्रुत्वा स नागेन्द्रो वासुकिः परया मुदा |` | "Hearing this, that king of serpents, Vāsuki, with great joy," |
| `Line 5495: एवमस्त्विति तद्वाक्यं भगिन्याः प्रत्यगृह्णत ||१४||` | "Accepted those words of his sister, saying, 'Let it be so.' ||14||" |
| `Line 5496: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5497: सान्त्वमानार्थदानैश्च पूजया चानुरूपया |` | "With consolations, gifts of wealth, and appropriate honors," |
| `Line 5498: सोदर्यां पूजयामास स्वसारं पन्नगोत्तमः ||१५||` | "That best of serpents honored his own sister. ||15||" |
| `Line 5499: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5500: ततः स ववृधे गर्भो महातेजा रविप्रभः |` | "Then that embryo grew, full of great splendor, radiant like the sun," |
| `Line 5501: यथा सोमो द्विजश्रेष्ठ शुक्लपक्षोदितो दिवि ||१६||` | "Like the moon, O best of the twice-born [eminent Brahmin], rising in the sky during the bright fortnight. ||16||" |
| `Line 5502: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5503: यथाकालं तु सा ब्रह्मन्प्रजज्ञे भुजगस्वसा |` | "In due time, O Brahmin, that sister of the serpents gave birth" |
| `Line 5504: कुमारं देवगर्भाभं पितृमातृभयापहम् ||१७||` | "To a boy radiant like a divine embryo, who would remove the fear of his father and mother. ||17||" |
| `Line 5505: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5506: ववृधे स च तत्रैव नागराजनिवेशने |` | "And he grew up there in the abode of the serpent king," |
| `Line 5507: वेदांश्चाधिजगे साङ्गान्भार्गवाच्च्यवनात्मजात् ||१८||` | "And he mastered the Vedas with their auxiliary texts [Vedangas] from Bhargava, the son of Chyavana. ||18||" |
| `Line 5508: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5509: चरितव्रतो बाल एव बुद्धिसत्त्वगुणान्वितः |` | "Even as a child, he observed his vows, endowed with intelligence, purity, and good qualities," |
| `Line 5510: नाम चास्याभवत्ख्यातं लोकेष्वास्तीक इत्युत ||१९||` | "And his name became renowned in the worlds as Astika. ||19||" |
| `Line 5511: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5512: अस्तीत्युक्त्वा गतो यस्मात्पिता गर्भस्थमेव तम् |` | "Since his father had departed saying 'asti' [he exists] when he was still in the womb," |
| `Line 5513: वनं तस्मादिदं तस्य नामास्तीकेति विश्रुतम् ||२०||` | "Therefore his name became famous as Astika. ||20||" |
| `Line 5514: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5515: स बाल एव तत्रस्थश्चरन्नमितबुद्धिमान् |` | "Even as a child, living there, moving about, with immeasurable intelligence," |
| `Line 5516: गृहे पन्नगराजस्य प्रयत्नात्पर्यरक्ष्यत ||२१||` | "He was carefully protected in the house of the serpent king. ||21||" |
| `Line 5517: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5518: भगवानिव देवेशः शूलपाणिर्हिरण्यदः |` | "Like the lord of gods, the trident-bearer [Shiva], the giver of gold," |
| `Line 5519: विवर्धमानः सर्वांस्तान्पन्नगानभ्यहर्षयत् ||२२||` | "As he grew, he delighted all those serpents. ||22||" |
| `Line 5520: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5521: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5522: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5523: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5524: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5525: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5526: ४५` | "45" |
| `Line 5527: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5528: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5529: शौनक उवाच||` | "Śaunaka said:" |
| `Line 5530: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5531: यदपृच्छत्तदा राजा मन्त्रिणो जनमेजयः |` | "What King Janamejaya then asked his ministers," |
| `Line 5532: पितुः स्वर्गगतिं तन्मे विस्तरेण पुनर्वद ||१||` | "About his father's journey to heaven, tell me that again in detail. ||1||" |
| `Line 5533: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5534: सूत उवाच||` | "Sūta [bard-narrator] said:" |
| `Line 5535: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5536: शृणु ब्रह्मन्यथा पृष्टा मन्त्रिणो नृपतेस्तदा |` | "Listen, O Brahmin, how the ministers were questioned by the king then," |
| `Line 5537: आख्यातवन्तस्ते सर्वे निधनं तत्परिक्षितः ||२||` | "And how they all narrated the death of that Parikshit. ||2||" |
| `Line 5538: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5539: जनमेजय उवाच||` | "Janamejaya said:" |
| `Line 5540: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5541: जानन्ति तु भवन्तस्तद्यथावृत्तः पिता मम |` | "You all know how my father conducted himself," |
| `Line 5542: आसीद्यथा च निधनं गतः काले महायशाः ||३||` | "And how that highly renowned one met his death in due time. ||3||" |
| `Line 5543: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5544: श्रुत्वा भवत्सकाशाद्धि पितुर्वृत्तमशेषतः |` | "Having heard from you completely about my father's conduct," |
| `Line 5545: कल्याणं प्रतिपत्स्यामि विपरीतं न जातु चित् ||४||` | "I shall follow the righteous path and never the contrary. ||4||" |
| `Line 5546: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5547: सूत उवाच||` | "Sūta [bard-narrator] said:" |
| `Line 5548: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5549: मन्त्रिणोऽथाब्रुवन्वाक्यं पृष्टास्तेन महात्मना |` | "Then the ministers, when questioned by that great-souled one," |
| `Line 5550: सर्वधर्मविदः प्राज्ञा राजानं जनमेजयम् ||५||` | "Those knowers of all dharma [righteousness], wise ones, spoke to King Janamejaya. ||5||" |
| `Line 5551: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5552: धर्मात्मा च महात्मा च प्रजापालः पिता तव |` | "Righteous-souled and great-souled, a protector of subjects was your father," |
| `Line 5553: आसीदिह यथावृत्तः स महात्मा शृणुष्व तत् ||६||` | "He was here as described, that great soul - listen to that. ||6||" |
| `Line 5554: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5555: चातुर्वर्ण्यं स्वधर्मस्थं स कृत्वा पर्यरक्षत |` | "Having established the four varnas [social orders] in their respective duties, he protected them," |
| `Line 5556: धर्मतो धर्मविद्राजा धर्मो विग्रहवानिव ||७||` | "Righteously did that king, knower of dharma, like dharma personified. ||7||" |
| `Line 5557: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5558: ररक्ष पृथिवीं देवीं श्रीमानतुलविक्रमः |` | "He protected the divine Earth, that glorious one of matchless valor," |
| `Line 5559: द्वेष्टारस्तस्य नैवासन्स च न द्वेष्टि कञ्चन ||८||` | "He had no enemies, nor did he hate anyone. ||8||" |
| `Line 5560: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5561: समः सर्वेषु भूतेषु प्रजापतिरिवाभवत् ||८||` | "Equal toward all beings, he was like Prajapati [creator deity]. ||8||" |
| `Line 5562: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5563: ब्राह्मणाः क्षत्रिया वैश्याः शूद्राश्चैव स्वकर्मसु |` | "Brahmins, Kshatriyas, Vaishyas, and Shudras in their respective duties," |
| `Line 5564: स्थिताः सुमनसो राजंस्तेन राज्ञा स्वनुष्ठिताः ||९||` | "Were established contentedly, O king, by that king's proper governance. ||9||" |
| `Line 5565: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5566: विधवानाथकृपणान्विकलांश्च बभार सः |` | "He supported widows, orphans, the poor, and the disabled," |
| `Line 5567: सुदर्शः सर्वभूतानामासीत्सोम इवापरः ||१०||` | "Pleasing to behold by all beings, he was like another Soma [moon deity]. ||10||" |
| `Line 5568: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5569: तुष्टपुष्टजनः श्रीमान्सत्यवाग्दृढविक्रमः |` | "With satisfied and nourished subjects, glorious, truthful in speech, of firm valor," |
| `Line 5570: धनुर्वेदे च शिष्योऽभून्नृपः शारद्वतस्य सः ||११||` | "In archery, that king was a disciple of Sharadwata [sage teacher]. ||11||" |
| `Line 5571: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5572: गोविन्दस्य प्रियश्चासीत्पिता ते जनमेजय |` | "Dear to Govinda [Krishna] was your father, O Janamejaya," |
| `Line 5573: लोकस्य चैव सर्वस्य प्रिय आसीन्महायशाः ||१२||` | "And dear to all the world was that highly renowned one. ||12||" |
| `Line 5574: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5575: परिक्षीणेषु कुरुषु उत्तरायामजायत |` | "When the Kurus were nearly extinct, he was born to Uttara [princess]," |
| `Line 5576: परिक्षिदभवत्तेन सौभद्रस्यात्मजो बली ||१३||` | "From him was born Parikshit, the mighty son of Subhadra's son [Abhimanyu]. ||13||" |
| `Line 5577: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5578: राजधर्मार्थकुशलो युक्तः सर्वगुणैर्नृपः |` | "The king was skilled in royal duty and wealth, endowed with all virtues," |
| `Line 5579: जितेन्द्रियश्चात्मवांश्च मेधावी वृद्धसेवितः ||१४||` | "With conquered senses, self-controlled, intelligent, and attended by the elders. ||14||" |
| `Line 5580: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5581: षड्वर्गविन्महाबुद्धिर्नीतिधर्मविदुत्तमः |` | "Knower of the six enemies [sensory passions], of great intellect, supreme knower of ethics and righteousness," |
| `Line 5582: प्रजा इमास्तव पिता षष्टिं वर्षाण्यपालयत् ||१५||` | "Your father protected these subjects for sixty years. ||15||" |
| `Line 5583: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5584: ततो दिष्टान्तमापन्नः सर्पेणानतिवर्तितम् ||१५||` | "Then he met his destined end, unavoidable, by a serpent. ||15||" |
| `Line 5585: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5586: ततस्त्वं पुरुषश्रेष्ठ धर्मेण प्रतिपेदिवान् |` | "Then you, O best of men, righteously obtained," |
| `Line 5587: इदं वर्षसहस्राय राज्यं कुरुकुलागतम् ||१६||` | "This kingdom descended from the Kuru lineage, for a thousand years. ||16||" |
| `Line 5588: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5589: बाल एवाभिजातोऽसि सर्वभूतानुपालकः ||१६||` | "Even as a youth, you were born noble, a protector of all beings. ||16||" |
| `Line 5590: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5591: जनमेजय उवाच||` | "Janamejaya said:" |
| `Line 5592: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5593: नास्मिन्कुले जातु बभूव राजा; यो न प्रजानां हितकृत्प्रियश्च |` | "Never in this family was there a king who was not a benefactor and beloved of his subjects," |
| `Line 5594: विशेषतः प्रेक्ष्य पितामहानां; वृत्तं महद्वृत्तपरायणानाम् ||१७||` | "Especially considering the conduct of my ancestors, who were devoted to noble behavior. ||17||" |
| `Line 5595: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5596: कथं निधनमापन्नः पिता मम तथाविधः |` | "How did my father, being of such nature, meet his death?" |
| `Line 5597: आचक्षध्वं यथावन्मे श्रोतुमिच्छामि तत्त्वतः ||१८||` | "Tell me properly, I wish to hear the truth. ||18||" |
| `Line 5598: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5599: सूत उवाच||` | "Suta said:" |
| `Line 5600: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5601: एवं सञ्चोदिता राज्ञा मन्त्रिणस्ते नराधिपम् |` | "Thus urged by the king, those ministers addressed the ruler," |
| `Line 5602: ऊचुः सर्वे यथावृत्तं राज्ञः प्रियहिते रताः ||१९||` | "All of them narrated the events as they occurred, devoted to the welfare and good of the king. ||19||" |
| `Line 5603: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5604: बभूव मृगयाशीलस्तव राजन्पिता सदा |` | "Your father, O king, was always fond of hunting," |
| `Line 5605: यथा पाण्डुर्महाभागो धनुर्धरवरो युधि ||२०||` | "Just like the illustrious Pandu [Pandava father], the foremost archer in battle. ||20||" |
| `Line 5606: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5607: अस्मास्वासज्य सर्वाणि राजकार्याण्यशेषतः ||२०||` | "Having entrusted to us all royal duties completely. ||20||" |
| `Line 5608: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5609: स कदाचिद्वनचरो मृगं विव्याध पत्रिणा |` | "Once while roaming in the forest, he pierced a deer with an arrow," |
| `Line 5610: विद्ध्वा चान्वसरत्तूर्णं तं मृगं गहने वने ||२१||` | "And after shooting it, he quickly pursued that deer in the dense forest. ||21||" |
| `Line 5611: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5612: पदातिर्बद्धनिस्त्रिंशस्ततायुधकलापवान् |` | "On foot, with sword fastened and quiver of arrows strapped," |
| `Line 5613: न चाससाद गहने मृगं नष्टं पिता तव ||२२||` | "Your father could not find the lost deer in the dense forest. ||22||" |
| `Line 5614: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5615: परिश्रान्तो वयःस्थश्च षष्टिवर्षो जरान्वितः |` | "Exhausted, advanced in age, sixty years old and affected by old age," |
| `Line 5616: क्षुधितः स महारण्ये ददर्श मुनिमन्तिके ||२३||` | "Hungry, he saw a sage nearby in the great forest. ||23||" |
| `Line 5617: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5618: स तं पप्रच्छ राजेन्द्रो मुनिं मौनव्रतान्वितम् |` | "That king [your father] asked the sage who was observing a vow of silence," |
| `Line 5619: न च किञ्चिदुवाचैनं स मुनिः पृच्छतोऽपि सन् ||२४||` | "But that sage did not say anything to him, even though he was being questioned. ||24||" |
| `Line 5620: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5621: ततो राजा क्षुच्छ्रमार्तस्तं मुनिं स्थाणुवत्स्थितम् |` | "Then the king, afflicted by hunger and fatigue, seeing that sage standing still like a post [sthāṇu]," |
| `Line 5622: मौनव्रतधरं शान्तं सद्यो मन्युवशं ययौ ||२५||` | "Who was observing a vow of silence and was peaceful, immediately came under the influence of anger. ||25||" |
| `Line 5623: ` | [Blank line] |
| `Line 5624: न बुबोध हि तं राजा मौनव्रतधरं मुनिम् |` | "The king did not understand that sage who was observing a vow of silence," |
| `Line 5625: स तं मन्युसमाविष्टो धर्षयामास ते पिता ||२६||` | "Your father, overcome with anger, insulted him. ||26||" |
| `Line 5626: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5627: मृतं सर्पं धनुष्कोट्या समुत्क्षिप्य धरातलात् |` | "Having lifted a dead serpent from the ground with the end of his bow," |
| `Line 5628: तस्य शुद्धात्मनः प्रादात्स्कन्धे भरतसत्तम ||२७||` | "He placed it on the shoulders of that pure-souled one, O best of Bharatas [noble lineage]. ||27||" |
| `Line 5629: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5630: न चोवाच स मेधावी तमथो साध्वसाधु वा |` | "And that wise one neither said to him whether it was good or bad," |
| `Line 5631: तस्थौ तथैव चाक्रुध्यन्सर्पं स्कन्धेन धारयन् ||२८||` | "He stood just as he was, without anger, bearing the serpent on his shoulder. ||28||" |
| `Line 5632: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5633: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5634: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5635: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5636: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5637: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5638: ४६` | "46 [chapter number]" |
| `Line 5639: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5640: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5641: मन्त्रिण ऊचुः||` | "The ministers said:" |
| `Line 5642: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5643: ततः स राजा राजेन्द्र स्कन्धे तस्य भुजङ्गमम् |` | "Then that king, O lord of kings, having placed the serpent on the shoulder," |
| `Line 5644: मुनेः क्षुत्क्षाम आसज्य स्वपुरं पुनराययौ ||१||` | "Of the sage who was emaciated from hunger, returned again to his city. ||1||" |
| `Line 5645: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5646: ऋषेस्तस्य तु पुत्रोऽभूद्गवि जातो महायशाः |` | "But that sage had a son, born of a cow [miraculous birth], of great fame," |
| `Line 5647: शृङ्गी नाम महातेजास्तिग्मवीर्योऽतिकोपनः ||२||` | "Shringi by name, of great splendor, of fierce power and extremely wrathful. ||2||" |
| `Line 5648: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5649: ब्रह्माणं सोऽभ्युपागम्य मुनिः पूजां चकार ह |` | "That sage, having approached Brahman [creator deity], performed worship," |
| `Line 5650: अनुज्ञातो गतस्तत्र शृङ्गी शुश्राव तं तदा ||३||` | "Having been permitted, Shringi went there and then heard about it. ||3||" |
| `Line 5651: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5652: सख्युः सकाशात्पितरं पित्रा ते धर्षितं तथा ||३||` | "From his friend about his father being thus insulted by your father. ||3||" |
| `Line 5653: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5654: मृतं सर्पं समासक्तं पित्रा ते जनमेजय |` | "A dead serpent was placed by your father, O Janamejaya [king, Parikshit's son]," |
| `Line 5655: वहन्तं कुरुशार्दूल स्कन्धेनानपकारिणम् ||४||` | "On the shoulder of the innocent one who carried it, O tiger among Kurus [royal epithet]. ||4||" |
| `Line 5656: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5657: तपस्विनमतीवाथ तं मुनिप्रवरं नृप |` | "That ascetic who was exceedingly the foremost among sages, O king," |
| `Line 5658: जितेन्द्रियं विशुद्धं च स्थितं कर्मण्यथाद्भुते ||५||` | "Self-controlled, pure, and engaged in wonderful austerities. ||5||" |
| `Line 5659: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5660: तपसा द्योतितात्मानं स्वेष्वङ्गेषु यतं तथा |` | "His self illumined by austerities, disciplined in all his limbs," |
| `Line 5661: शुभाचारं शुभकथं सुस्थिरं तमलोलुपम् ||६||` | "Of virtuous conduct, pleasant speech, steadfast and free from desires. ||6||" |
| `Line 5662: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5663: अक्षुद्रमनसूयं च वृद्धं मौनव्रते स्थितम् |` | "Not mean-minded, free from envy, aged, observing the vow of silence," |
| `Line 5664: शरण्यं सर्वभूतानां पित्रा विप्रकृतं तव ||७||` | "A refuge for all beings - was insulted by your father. ||7||" |
| `Line 5665: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5666: शशापाथ स तच्छ्रुत्वा पितरं ते रुषान्वितः |` | "Having heard that, he cursed your father, filled with anger," |
| `Line 5667: ऋषेः पुत्रो महातेजा बालोऽपि स्थविरैर्वरः ||८||` | "The sage's son of great splendor, though a child, superior to elders. ||8||" |
| `Line 5668: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5669: स क्षिप्रमुदकं स्पृष्ट्वा रोषादिदमुवाच ह |` | "He quickly touched water [purification ritual] and in anger said this," |
| `Line 5670: पितरं तेऽभिसन्धाय तेजसा प्रज्वलन्निव ||९||` | "Addressing your father, blazing as it were with energy. ||9||" |
| `Line 5671: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5672: अनागसि गुरौ यो मे मृतं सर्पमवासृजत् |` | "He who placed a dead serpent on my innocent father [guru]," |
| `Line 5673: तं नागस्तक्षकः क्रुद्धस्तेजसा सादयिष्यति ||१०||` | "Him shall the angry serpent Takshaka [serpent king] destroy with his power. ||10||" |
| `Line 5674: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5675: सप्तरात्रादितः पापं पश्य मे तपसो बलम् ||१०||` | "Within seven nights from now, O sinner, behold the power of my austerities. ||10||" |
| `Line 5676: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5677: इत्युक्त्वा प्रययौ तत्र पिता यत्रास्य सोऽभवत् |` | "Having said this, he went there where his father was," |
| `Line 5678: दृष्ट्वा च पितरं तस्मै शापं तं प्रत्यवेदयत् ||११||` | "And having seen his father, he informed him about that curse. ||11||" |
| `Line 5679: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5680: स चापि मुनिशार्दूलः प्रेषयामास ते पितुः |` | "And that tiger among sages [eminent sage] sent a message to your father:" |
| `Line 5681: शप्तोऽसि मम पुत्रेण यत्तो भव महीपते ||१२||` | "'You have been cursed by my son, be prepared, O king. ||12||'" |
| `Line 5682: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5683: तक्षकस्त्वां महाराज तेजसा सादयिष्यति ||१२||` | "'Takshaka [serpent king] will destroy you with his power, O great king.' ||12||" |
| `Line 5684: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5685: श्रुत्वा तु तद्वचो घोरं पिता ते जनमेजय |` | "Having heard those terrible words, your father, O Janamejaya," |
| `Line 5686: यत्तोऽभवत्परित्रस्तस्तक्षकात्पन्नगोत्तमात् ||१३||` | "Became vigilant and terrified of Takshaka, the foremost among serpents. ||13||" |
| `Line 5687: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5688: ततस्तस्मिंस्तु दिवसे सप्तमे समुपस्थिते |` | "Then, when the seventh day approached," |
| `Line 5689: राज्ञः समीपं ब्रह्मर्षिः काश्यपो गन्तुमैच्छत ||१४||` | "The brahmin sage Kashyapa wished to go to the king. ||14||" |
| `Line 5690: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5691: तं ददर्शाथ नागेन्द्रः काश्यपं तक्षकस्तदा |` | "Then Takshaka, the lord of serpents [naga king], saw Kashyapa," |
| `Line 5692: तमब्रवीत्पन्नगेन्द्रः काश्यपं त्वरितं व्रजन् ||१५||` | "The lord of serpents spoke to Kashyapa, who was going hurriedly. ||15||" |
| `Line 5693: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5694: क्व भवांस्त्वरितो याति किं च कार्यं चिकीर्षति ||१५||` | "'Where are you going in such haste, and what task do you wish to accomplish?' ||15||" |
| `Line 5695: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5696: काश्यप उवाच||` | "Kashyapa said:" |
| `Line 5697: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5698: यत्र राजा कुरुश्रेष्ठः परिक्षिन्नाम वै द्विज |` | "'Where the best of Kurus [Kuru dynasty], King Parikshit, is, O twice-born [brahmin]," |
| `Line 5699: तक्षकेण भुजङ्गेन धक्ष्यते किल तत्र वै ||१६||` | "'He will indeed be burned by the serpent Takshaka there. ||16||'" |
| `Line 5700: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5701: गच्छाम्यहं तं त्वरितः सद्यः कर्तुमपज्वरम् |` | "I will go to him quickly to immediately make him free from fever," |
| `Line 5702: मयाभिपन्नं तं चापि न सर्पो धर्षयिष्यति ||१७||` | "And the serpent will not harm him who is protected by me. ||17||" |
| `Line 5703: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5704: तक्षक उवाच||` | "Takshaka [serpent king] said:" |
| `Line 5705: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5706: किमर्थं तं मया दष्टं सञ्जीवयितुमिच्छसि |` | "Why do you wish to revive him who has been bitten by me?" |
| `Line 5707: ब्रूहि काममहं तेऽद्य दद्मि स्वं वेश्म गम्यताम् ||१८||` | "Tell me your desire, I shall grant it to you today. Return to your own home. ||18||" |
| `Line 5708: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5709: मन्त्रिण ऊचुः||` | "The ministers said:" |
| `Line 5710: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5711: धनलिप्सुरहं तत्र यामीत्युक्तश्च तेन सः |` | "He (Kashyapa) said, 'I go there desiring wealth,' and that one (Takshaka)" |
| `Line 5712: तमुवाच महात्मानं मानयञ्श्लक्ष्णया गिरा ||१९||` | "Addressed that great soul, honoring him with gentle words: ||19||" |
| `Line 5713: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5714: यावद्धनं प्रार्थयसे तस्माद्राज्ञस्ततोऽधिकम् |` | "Whatever wealth you desire from that king, even more than that," |
| `Line 5715: गृहाण मत्त एव त्वं संनिवर्तस्व चानघ ||२०||` | "Take from me instead, and turn back, O sinless one. ||20||" |
| `Line 5716: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5717: स एवमुक्तो नागेन काश्यपो द्विपदां वरः |` | "Thus addressed by the serpent, Kashyapa [sage], the best among the twice-born [Brahmins]," |
| `Line 5718: लब्ध्वा वित्तं निववृते तक्षकाद्यावदीप्सितम् ||२१||` | "Having received from Takshaka as much wealth as he desired, turned back. ||21||" |
| `Line 5719: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5720: तस्मिन्प्रतिगते विप्रे छद्मनोपेत्य तक्षकः |` | "When that Brahmin had returned, Takshaka, approaching in disguise," |
| `Line 5721: तं नृपं नृपतिश्रेष्ठ पितरं धार्मिकं तव ||२२||` | "That king, O best of kings, your righteous father, ||22||" |
| `Line 5722: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5723: प्रासादस्थं यत्तमपि दग्धवान्विषवह्निना |` | "Though he was vigilant in his palace, (Takshaka) burned him with his poison-fire," |
| `Line 5724: ततस्त्वं पुरुषव्याघ्र विजयायाभिषेचितः ||२३||` | "Thereafter you, O tiger among men [heroic king], were crowned for victory. ||23||" |
| `Line 5725: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5726: एतद्दृष्टं श्रुतं चापि यथावन्नृपसत्तम |` | "This has been seen and heard exactly as it happened, O best of kings [royal epithet]," |
| `Line 5727: अस्माभिर्निखिलं सर्वं कथितं ते सुदारुणम् ||२४||` | "Everything has been told to you by us in full, this most terrible event. ||24||" |
| `Line 5728: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5729: श्रुत्वा चैतं नृपश्रेष्ठ पार्थिवस्य पराभवम् |` | "Having heard this, O foremost of kings [royal epithet], about the defeat of the king [your father]," |
| `Line 5730: अस्य चर्षेरुत्तङ्कस्य विधत्स्व यदनन्तरम् ||२५||` | "And of this sage Uttanka, decide what should be done next. ||25||" |
| `Line 5731: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5732: जनमेजय उवाच||` | "Janamejaya said:" |
| `Line 5733: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5734: एतत्तु श्रोतुमिच्छामि अटव्यां निर्जने वने |` | "But I wish to hear about this, in the desolate forest in the wilderness," |
| `Line 5735: संवादं पन्नगेन्द्रस्य काश्यपस्य च यत्तदा ||२६||` | "The conversation between the lord of serpents [Takshaka] and Kashyapa [sage] that took place then. ||26||" |
| `Line 5736: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5737: केन दृष्टं श्रुतं चापि भवतां श्रोत्रमागतम् |` | "By whom was it seen and heard, and how did it come to your ears?" |
| `Line 5738: श्रुत्वा चाथ विधास्यामि पन्नगान्तकरीं मतिम् ||२७||` | "After hearing it, I shall then form a resolution to destroy the serpents [snake sacrifice]. ||27||" |
| `Line 5739: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5740: मन्त्रिण ऊचुः||` | "The ministers said:" |
| `Line 5741: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5742: शृणु राजन्यथास्माकं येनैतत्कथितं पुरा |` | "Listen, O king, how this was told to us before," |
| `Line 5743: समागमं द्विजेन्द्रस्य पन्नगेन्द्रस्य चाध्वनि ||२८||` | "About the meeting of the foremost Brahmin [Kashyapa] and the lord of serpents on the way. ||28||" |
| `Line 5744: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5745: तस्मिन्वृक्षे नरः कश्चिदिन्धनार्थाय पार्थिव |` | "In that tree, O ruler [Janamejaya], a certain man in search of firewood," |
| `Line 5746: विचिन्वन्पूर्वमारूढः शुष्कशाखं वनस्पतिम् ||२९||` | "Had previously climbed that forest tree with dry branches. ||29||" |
| `Line 5747: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5748: अबुध्यमानौ तं तत्र वृक्षस्थं पन्नगद्विजौ ||२९||` | "The serpent and the twice-born [Brahmin] were unaware of him there in the tree. ||29||" |
| `Line 5749: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5750: स तु तेनैव वृक्षेण भस्मीभूतोऽभवत्तदा |` | "But he, along with that very tree, was reduced to ashes then," |
| `Line 5751: द्विजप्रभावाद्राजेन्द्र जीवितः सवनस्पतिः ||३०||` | "Due to the Brahmin's [twice-born] power, O lord of kings, the tree with its forest was revived. ||30||" |
| `Line 5752: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5753: तेन गत्वा नृपश्रेष्ठ नगरेऽस्मिन्निवेदितम् |` | "Having gone there, O best of kings, he reported everything in this city," |
| `Line 5754: यथावृत्तं तु तत्सर्वं तक्षकस्य द्विजस्य च ||३१||` | "All that had happened between Takshaka [serpent king] and the Brahmin, exactly as it occurred. ||31||" |
| `Line 5755: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5756: एतत्ते कथितं राजन्यथावृत्तं यथाश्रुतम् |` | "This has been told to you, O king, exactly as it happened, exactly as we heard it," |
| `Line 5757: श्रुत्वा तु नृपशार्दूल प्रकुरुष्व यथेप्सितम् ||३२||` | "Having heard this, O tiger among kings [mighty ruler], do as you desire. ||32||" |
| `Line 5758: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5759: सूत उवाच||` | "Suta [bard-narrator] said:" |
| `Line 5760: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5761: मन्त्रिणां तु वचः श्रुत्वा स राजा जनमेजयः |` | "Having heard the words of the ministers, that King Janamejaya," |
| `Line 5762: पर्यतप्यत दुःखार्तः प्रत्यपिंषत्करे करम् ||३३||` | "Was consumed with grief, afflicted with sorrow, and rubbed one hand against the other. ||33||" |
| `Line 5763: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5764: निःश्वासमुष्णमसकृद्दीर्घं राजीवलोचनः |` | "The lotus-eyed [beautiful-eyed] king repeatedly heaved hot, long sighs," |
| `Line 5765: मुमोचाश्रूणि च तदा नेत्राभ्यां प्रततं नृपः ||३४||` | "And then the king shed continuous tears from his eyes. ||34||" |
| `Line 5766: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5767: उवाच च महीपालो दुःखशोकसमन्वितः ||३४||` | "And the ruler of the earth spoke, overcome with grief and sorrow. ||34||" |
| `Line 5768: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5769: श्रुत्वैतद्भवतां वाक्यं पितुर्मे स्वर्गतिं प्रति |` | "Having heard your words regarding my father's journey to heaven [death]," |
| `Line 5770: निश्चितेयं मम मतिर्या वै तां मे निबोधत ||३५||` | "My mind is now made up; know this decision of mine. ||35||" |
| `Line 5771: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5772: अनन्तरमहं मन्ये तक्षकाय दुरात्मने |` | "I think I must immediately retaliate against the wicked Takshaka," |
| `Line 5773: प्रतिकर्तव्यमित्येव येन मे हिंसितः पिता ||३६||` | "Indeed, I must take revenge on him by whom my father was killed. ||36||" |
| `Line 5774: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5775: ऋषेर्हि शृङ्गेर्वचनं कृत्वा दग्ध्वा च पार्थिवम् |` | "Having fulfilled the words of sage Shringi and having burnt the king [Parikshit]," |
| `Line 5776: यदि गच्छेदसौ पापो ननु जीवेत्पिता मम ||३७||` | "If that sinful one [Takshaka] had gone away, would not my father still be alive? ||37||" |
| `Line 5777: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5778: परिहीयेत किं तस्य यदि जीवेत्स पार्थिवः |` | "What would have been lost to him if that king [Parikshit] had lived," |
| `Line 5779: काश्यपस्य प्रसादेन मन्त्रिणां सुनयेन च ||३८||` | "By the grace of Kashyapa [snake-charming sage] and through the good policy of the ministers? ||38||" |
| `Line 5780: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5781: स तु वारितवान्मोहात्काश्यपं द्विजसत्तमम् |` | "But he [Takshaka], out of delusion, stopped Kashyapa, the best of the twice-born [Brahmin]," |
| `Line 5782: सञ्जिजीवयिषुं प्राप्तं राजानमपराजितम् ||३९||` | "Who had arrived to revive the unconquered king. ||39||" |
| `Line 5783: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5784: महानतिक्रमो ह्येष तक्षकस्य दुरात्मनः |` | "This is indeed a great transgression of the wicked Takshaka," |
| `Line 5785: द्विजस्य योऽददद्द्रव्यं मा नृपं जीवयेदिति ||४०||` | "Who gave wealth to the twice-born [Kashyapa] so that he would not revive the king. ||40||" |
| `Line 5786: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5787: उत्तङ्कस्य प्रियं कुर्वन्नात्मनश्च महत्प्रियम् |` | "Doing what is pleasing to Uttanka [sage who cursed] and what is greatly pleasing to myself," |
| `Line 5788: भवतां चैव सर्वेषां यास्याम्यपचितिं पितुः ||४१||` | "And to all of you as well, I shall seek retribution for my father. ||41||" |
| `Line 5789: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5790: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5791: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5792: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5793: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5794: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5795: ४७` | "47" |
| `Line 5796: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5797: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5798: सूत उवाच||` | "Suta [bard narrator] said:" |
| `Line 5799: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5800: एवमुक्त्वा ततः श्रीमान्मन्त्रिभिश्चानुमोदितः |` | "Having spoken thus, then the illustrious one [Janamejaya], approved by his ministers," |
| `Line 5801: आरुरोह प्रतिज्ञां स सर्पसत्राय पार्थिवः ||१||` | "That king ascended to the vow for the serpent sacrifice. ||1||" |
| `Line 5802: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5803: ब्रह्मन्भरतशार्दूलो राजा पारिक्षितस्तदा ||१||` | "O Brahmin, that tiger among the Bharatas [heroic descendant], King Parikshit, then ||1||" |
| `Line 5804: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5805: पुरोहितमथाहूय ऋत्विजं वसुधाधिपः |` | "The lord of the earth, having summoned the family priest and the officiating priests," |
| `Line 5806: अब्रवीद्वाक्यसम्पन्नः सम्पदर्थकरं वचः ||२||` | "Spoke, endowed with eloquence, words conducive to prosperity and purpose: ||2||" |
| `Line 5807: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5808: यो मे हिंसितवांस्तातं तक्षकः स दुरात्मवान् |` | "That evil-souled Takshaka who killed my father," |
| `Line 5809: प्रतिकुर्यां यथा तस्य तद्भवन्तो ब्रुवन्तु मे ||३||` | "How I may retaliate against him, let your honors tell me. ||3||" |
| `Line 5810: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5811: अपि तत्कर्म विदितं भवतां येन पन्नगम् |` | "Is there any ritual known to you by which the serpent," |
| `Line 5812: तक्षकं सम्प्रदीप्तेऽग्नौ प्राप्स्येऽहं सहबान्धवम् ||४||` | "Takshaka, along with his relatives, I might obtain in the blazing fire? ||4||" |
| `Line 5813: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5814: यथा तेन पिता मह्यं पूर्वं दग्धो विषाग्निना |` | "Just as my father was previously burned by him with poison-fire," |
| `Line 5815: तथाहमपि तं पापं दग्धुमिच्छामि पन्नगम् ||५||` | "So I too wish to burn that sinful serpent. ||5||" |
| `Line 5816: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5817: ऋत्विज ऊचुः||` | "The priests [ritual officiants] said:" |
| `Line 5818: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5819: अस्ति राजन्महत्सत्रं त्वदर्थं देवनिर्मितम् |` | "There exists, O king, a great sacrifice designed by the gods for your purpose," |
| `Line 5820: सर्पसत्रमिति ख्यातं पुराणे कथ्यते नृप ||६||` | "Known as the Serpent Sacrifice, it is described in the Puranas [ancient texts], O ruler. ||6||" |
| `Line 5821: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5822: आहर्ता तस्य सत्रस्य त्वन्नान्योऽस्ति नराधिप |` | "The performer of that sacrifice is none other than you, O lord of men," |
| `Line 5823: इति पौराणिकाः प्राहुरस्माकं चास्ति स क्रतुः ||७||` | "Thus the knowers of Puranas have declared, and we possess knowledge of that ritual. ||7||" |
| `Line 5824: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5825: सूत उवाच||` | "Suta [bard/narrator] said:" |
| `Line 5826: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5827: एवमुक्तः स राजर्षिर्मेने सर्पं हि तक्षकम् |` | "Thus addressed, that royal sage [king-seer] believed that the serpent Takshaka" |
| `Line 5828: हुताशनमुखं दीप्तं प्रविष्टमिति सत्तम ||८||` | "Had entered the blazing mouth of the fire [Hutashana], O excellent one. ||8||" |
| `Line 5829: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5830: ततोऽब्रवीन्मन्त्रविदस्तान्राजा ब्राह्मणांस्तदा |` | "Then the king addressed those Brahmins [twice-born], who were knowers of mantras, saying:" |
| `Line 5831: आहरिष्यामि तत्सत्रं सम्भाराः सम्भ्रियन्तु मे ||९||` | "I shall perform that sacrificial session [snake sacrifice]; let the materials be gathered for me. ||9||" |
| `Line 5832: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5833: ततस्ते ऋत्विजस्तस्य शास्त्रतो द्विजसत्तम |` | "Then those priests [ritual performers] of his, according to the scriptures, O best of the twice-born," |
| `Line 5834: देशं तं मापयामासुर्यज्ञायतनकारणात् ||१०||` | "Measured that place for the purpose of constructing the sacrificial altar. ||10||" |
| `Line 5835: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5836: यथावज्ज्ञानविदुषः सर्वे बुद्ध्या परं गताः ||१०||` | "All those knowledgeable ones, with proper understanding, reached the highest level of wisdom. ||10||" |
| `Line 5837: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5838: ऋद्ध्या परमया युक्तमिष्टं द्विजगणायुतम् |` | "Endowed with supreme prosperity, desired, filled with groups of Brahmins," |
| `Line 5839: प्रभूतधनधान्याढ्यमृत्विग्भिः सुनिवेशितम् ||११||` | "Abundant in wealth and grain, well-arranged by the priests. ||11||" |
| `Line 5840: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5841: निर्माय चापि विधिवद्यज्ञायतनमीप्सितम् |` | "And having constructed according to the rules the desired sacrificial altar," |
| `Line 5842: राजानं दीक्षयामासुः सर्पसत्राप्तये तदा ||१२||` | "They initiated the king then for the accomplishment of the snake sacrifice [serpent ritual]. ||12||" |
| `Line 5843: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5844: इदं चासीत्तत्र पूर्वं सर्पसत्रे भविष्यति |` | "And this happened there before the snake sacrifice was to take place," |
| `Line 5845: निमित्तं महदुत्पन्नं यज्ञविघ्नकरं तदा ||१३||` | "A great omen arose then, creating an obstacle to the sacrifice. ||13||" |
| `Line 5846: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5847: यज्ञस्यायतने तस्मिन्क्रियमाणे वचोऽब्रवीत् |` | "While that sacrificial altar was being constructed, these words were spoken" |
| `Line 5848: स्थपतिर्बुद्धिसम्पन्नो वास्तुविद्याविशारदः ||१४||` | "By the architect [master builder], endowed with intelligence, expert in the science of construction. ||14||" |
| `Line 5849: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5850: इत्यब्रवीत्सूत्रधारः सूतः पौराणिकस्तदा |` | "Thus spoke the master architect [string-holder], the Suta [bard], the reciter of Puranas at that time." |
| `Line 5851: यस्मिन्देशे च काले च मापनेयं प्रवर्तिता ||१५||` | "In which place and at which time this measurement [ritual procedure] was established. ||15||" |
| `Line 5852: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5853: ब्राह्मणं कारणं कृत्वा नायं संस्थास्यते क्रतुः ||१५||` | "Making a Brahmin the cause [instrument], this sacrifice will not be completed. ||15||" |
| `Line 5854: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5855: एतच्छ्रुत्वा तु राजा स प्राग्दीक्षाकालमब्रवीत् |` | "Having heard this, the king, before the time of initiation [consecration ceremony], said," |
| `Line 5856: क्षत्तारं नेह मे कश्चिदज्ञातः प्रविशेदिति ||१६||` | "To the chamberlain [doorkeeper]: 'Let no unknown person enter here.' ||16||" |
| `Line 5857: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5858: ततः कर्म प्रववृते सर्पसत्रे विधानतः |` | "Then the ritual procedures of the snake sacrifice [serpent offering] began according to the prescribed rules," |
| `Line 5859: पर्यक्रामंश्च विधिवत्स्वे स्वे कर्मणि याजकाः ||१७||` | "And the priests moved about properly in their respective duties. ||17||" |
| `Line 5860: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5861: परिधाय कृष्णवासांसि धूमसंरक्तलोचनाः |` | "Wearing black garments, with eyes reddened by smoke," |
| `Line 5862: जुहुवुर्मन्त्रवच्चैव समिद्धं जातवेदसम् ||१८||` | "They made offerings with mantras into the blazing Jatavedas [fire deity]. ||18||" |
| `Line 5863: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5864: कम्पयन्तश्च सर्वेषामुरगाणां मनांसि ते |` | "They caused the minds of all the serpents [snake beings] to tremble," |
| `Line 5865: सर्पानाजुहुवुस्तत्र सर्वानग्निमुखे तदा ||१९||` | "And offered all the serpents there into the mouth of fire [sacrificial flame] then. ||19||" |
| `Line 5866: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5867: ततः सर्पाः समापेतुः प्रदीप्ते हव्यवाहने |` | "Then the serpents fell into the blazing Havyavahana [fire carrier]," |
| `Line 5868: विवेष्टमानाः कृपणा आह्वयन्तः परस्परम् ||२०||` | "Writhing pitifully, calling out to one another. ||20||" |
| `Line 5869: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5870: विस्फुरन्तः श्वसन्तश्च वेष्टयन्तस्तथा परे |` | "Hissing, gasping, and coiling, others," |
| `Line 5871: पुच्छैः शिरोभिश्च भृशं चित्रभानुं प्रपेदिरे ||२१||` | "With their tails and heads violently entered Chitrabhaanu [fire deity]. ||21||" |
| `Line 5872: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5873: श्वेताः कृष्णाश्च नीलाश्च स्थविराः शिशवस्तथा |` | "White, black, and blue ones, the old and the young alike," |
| `Line 5874: रुवन्तो भैरवान्नादान्पेतुर्दीप्ते विभावसौ ||२२||` | "Uttering terrible cries, fell into the blazing Vibhaavasu [fire deity]. ||22||" |
| `Line 5875: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5876: एवं शतसहस्राणि प्रयुतान्यर्बुदानि च |` | "Thus hundreds of thousands, millions, and tens of millions" |
| `Line 5877: अवशानि विनष्टानि पन्नगानां द्विजोत्तम ||२३||` | "Of helpless serpents [snake beings] were destroyed, O best of the twice-born [Brahmin]. ||23||" |
| `Line 5878: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5879: इन्दुरा इव तत्रान्ये हस्तिहस्ता इवापरे |` | "Some there were like large rats, others like elephant trunks," |
| `Line 5880: मत्ता इव च मातङ्गा महाकाया महाबलाः ||२४||` | "And some like intoxicated elephants, with massive bodies and great strength. ||24||" |
| `Line 5881: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5882: उच्चावचाश्च बहवो नानावर्णा विषोल्बणाः |` | "Many were of various sizes, diverse colors, swollen with poison," |
| `Line 5883: घोराश्च परिघप्रख्या दन्दशूका महाबलाः ||२५||` | "Terrible and resembling iron clubs, these mighty biters [venomous serpents]. ||25||" |
| `Line 5884: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5885: प्रपेतुरग्नावुरगा मातृवाग्दण्डपीडिताः ||२५||` | "The serpents fell into the fire, tormented by the mother's curse [Kadru's words]. ||25||" |
| `Line 5886: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5887: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5888: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5889: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5890: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5891: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5892: ४८` | "48 [chapter number]" |
| `Line 5893: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5894: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5895: शौनक उवाच||` | "Shaunaka [sage-interlocutor] said:" |
| `Line 5896: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5897: सर्पसत्रे तदा राज्ञः पाण्डवेयस्य धीमतः |` | "In that serpent sacrifice [snake ritual] of the wise king, descendant of the Pandavas [Pandava lineage]," |
| `Line 5898: जनमेजयस्य के त्वासन्नृत्विजः परमर्षयः ||१||` | "Janamejaya, who were the priests and great sages? ||1||" |
| `Line 5899: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5900: के सदस्या बभूवुश्च सर्पसत्रे सुदारुणे |` | "Who were the assembly members at that terrifying serpent sacrifice," |
| `Line 5901: विषादजननेऽत्यर्थं पन्नगानां महाभये ||२||` | "In causing extreme dejection and great fear among the serpents [snake beings]. ||2||" |
| `Line 5902: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5903: सर्वं विस्तरतस्तात भवाञ्शंसितुमर्हति |` | "O dear one [term of respect], you should narrate everything in detail," |
| `Line 5904: सर्पसत्रविधानज्ञा विज्ञेयास्ते हि सूतज ||३||` | "For you are known to be knowledgeable in the procedures of the serpent sacrifice, O son of Suta [bard lineage]. ||3||" |
| `Line 5905: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5906: सूत उवाच||` | "Suta [bard/narrator] said:" |
| `Line 5907: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5908: हन्त ते कथयिष्यामि नामानीह मनीषिणाम् |` | "Well then, I shall tell you the names of the wise men," |
| `Line 5909: ये ऋत्विजः सदस्याश्च तस्यासन्नृपतेस्तदा ||४||` | "Who were the priests [ritual officiants] and assembly members of that king at that time. ||4||" |
| `Line 5910: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5911: तत्र होता बभूवाथ ब्राह्मणश्चण्डभार्गवः |` | "There, the Hota [chief priest] was the Brahmin Chanda Bhargava," |
| `Line 5912: च्यवनस्यान्वये जातः ख्यातो वेदविदां वरः ||५||` | "Born in the lineage of Chyavana, renowned as the best among the knowers of the Vedas. ||5||" |
| `Line 5913: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5914: उद्गाता ब्राह्मणो वृद्धो विद्वान्कौत्सार्यजैमिनिः |` | "The Udgata [chanting priest] was the learned elderly Brahmin Kautsarya Jaimini," |
| `Line 5915: ब्रह्माभवच्छार्ङ्गरवो अध्वर्युर्बोधपिङ्गलः ||६||` | "Sharngrava became the Brahma [supervising priest], and Bodha Pingala was the Adhvaryu [procedural priest]. ||6||" |
| `Line 5916: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5917: सदस्यश्चाभवद्व्यासः पुत्रशिष्यसहायवान् |` | "And Vyasa became a Sadasya [assembly member], accompanied by his sons and disciples," |
| `Line 5918: उद्दालकः शमठकः श्वेतकेतुश्च पञ्चमः ||७||` | "Uddalaka, Shamathaka, and Shvetaketu the fifth. ||7||" |
| `Line 5919: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5920: असितो देवलश्चैव नारदः पर्वतस्तथा |` | "Asita, Devala, and also Narada, Parvata likewise," |
| `Line 5921: आत्रेयः कुण्डजठरो द्विजः कुटिघटस्तथा ||८||` | "Atreya, Kundajathara, the twice-born [Brahmin] Kutighata likewise. ||8||" |
| `Line 5922: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5923: वात्स्यः श्रुतश्रवा वृद्धस्तपःस्वाध्यायशीलवान् |` | "The elderly Vatsya Shrutashrava, devoted to austerities and Vedic study," |
| `Line 5924: कहोडो देवशर्मा च मौद्गल्यः शमसौभरः ||९||` | "Kahoda, Devasharma, and Maudgalya Shamasaubhara. ||9||" |
| `Line 5925: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5926: एते चान्ये च बहवो ब्राह्मणाः संशितव्रताः |` | "These and many other Brahmins of strict vows [disciplined practitioners]," |
| `Line 5927: सदस्या अभवंस्तत्र सत्रे पारिक्षितस्य ह ||१०||` | "Became assembly members there at the sacrificial session of Parikshita [Janamejaya's father], indeed. ||10||" |
| `Line 5928: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5929: जुह्वत्स्वृत्विक्ष्वथ तदा सर्पसत्रे महाक्रतौ |` | "When the priests were making offerings in that great snake sacrifice [sarpa-satra]," |
| `Line 5930: अहयः प्रापतंस्तत्र घोराः प्राणिभयावहाः ||११||` | "Terrible snakes fell there, causing fear to living beings. ||11||" |
| `Line 5931: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5932: वसामेदोवहाः कुल्या नागानां सम्प्रवर्तिताः |` | "Streams carrying fat and marrow of the serpents [nagas] flowed forth," |
| `Line 5933: ववौ गन्धश्च तुमुलो दह्यतामनिशं तदा ||१२||` | "And a tumultuous smell wafted from those being continuously burned then. ||12||" |
| `Line 5934: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5935: पततां चैव नागानां धिष्ठितानां तथाम्बरे |` | "Of the falling serpents and those stationed likewise in the sky," |
| `Line 5936: अश्रूयतानिशं शब्दः पच्यतां चाग्निना भृशम् ||१३||` | "Incessantly was heard the sound of those being intensely burned by fire. ||13||" |
| `Line 5937: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5938: तक्षकस्तु स नागेन्द्रः पुरंदरनिवेशनम् |` | "But that Takshaka, the lord of serpents [naga king], to Purandara's [Indra's] abode" |
| `Line 5939: गतः श्रुत्वैव राजानं दीक्षितं जनमेजयम् ||१४||` | "Went, having heard that King Janamejaya had been initiated [for the ritual]. ||14||" |
| `Line 5940: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5941: ततः सर्वं यथावृत्तमाख्याय भुजगोत्तमः |` | "Then, having related everything as it happened, that foremost of serpents [Takshaka]," |
| `Line 5942: अगच्छच्छरणं भीत आगस्कृत्वा पुरंदरम् ||१५||` | "Frightened, sought refuge with Purandara [Indra], having committed an offense. ||15||" |
| `Line 5943: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5944: तमिन्द्रः प्राह सुप्रीतो न तवास्तीह तक्षक |` | "To him Indra [king of gods] said, well-pleased: 'There is no reason for you, Takshaka," |
| `Line 5945: भयं नागेन्द्र तस्माद्वै सर्पसत्रात्कथञ्चन ||१६||` | "O lord of serpents [naga king], to fear from that snake sacrifice [sarpa-satra] in any way.' ||16||" |
| `Line 5946: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5947: प्रसादितो मया पूर्वं तवार्थाय पितामहः |` | "Pitamaha [Brahma, grandfather] has been propitiated by me earlier for your sake." |
| `Line 5948: तस्मात्तव भयं नास्ति व्येतु ते मानसो ज्वरः ||१७||` | "Therefore, you have no fear; let your mental fever [anxiety] depart. ||17||" |
| `Line 5949: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5950: एवमाश्वासितस्तेन ततः स भुजगोत्तमः |` | "Thus reassured by him, then that foremost of serpents [naga lord]," |
| `Line 5951: उवास भवने तत्र शक्रस्य मुदितः सुखी ||१८||` | "Dwelt there in the abode of Shakra [Indra], happy and content. ||18||" |
| `Line 5952: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5953: अजस्रं निपतत्स्वग्नौ नागेषु भृशदुःखितः |` | "As the serpents [nagas] fell incessantly into the fire, deeply distressed," |
| `Line 5954: अल्पशेषपरीवारो वासुकिः पर्यतप्यत ||१९||` | "Vasuki [naga king], with few attendants remaining, suffered greatly. ||19||" |
| `Line 5955: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5956: कश्मलं चाविशद्घोरं वासुकिं पन्नगेश्वरम् |` | "And a terrible swoon [unconsciousness] overtook Vasuki, the lord of serpents [naga king]." |
| `Line 5957: स घूर्णमानहृदयो भगिनीमिदमब्रवीत् ||२०||` | "He, with his heart reeling [dizzy], said this to his sister. ||20||" |
| `Line 5958: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5959: दह्यन्तेऽङ्गानि मे भद्रे दिशो न प्रतिभान्ति च |` | "My limbs are burning, O auspicious one [sister], and the directions do not appear clear to me." |
| `Line 5960: सीदामीव च संमोहाद्घूर्णतीव च मे मनः ||२१||` | "I seem to be sinking from confusion, and my mind seems to be whirling. ||21||" |
| `Line 5961: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5962: दृष्टिर्भ्रमति मेऽतीव हृदयं दीर्यतीव च |` | "My vision wanders excessively, and my heart seems to be breaking." |
| `Line 5963: पतिष्याम्यवशोऽद्याहं तस्मिन्दीप्ते विभावसौ ||२२||` | "Helpless, today I shall fall into that blazing fire [Agni]. ||22||" |
| `Line 5964: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5965: पारिक्षितस्य यज्ञोऽसौ वर्ततेऽस्मज्जिघांसया |` | "That sacrifice of Parikshita's son [Janamejaya] proceeds with the desire to kill us." |
| `Line 5966: व्यक्तं मयापि गन्तव्यं पितृराजनिवेशनम् ||२३||` | "Surely I too must go to the abode of the king of ancestors [Yama's realm]. ||23||" |
| `Line 5967: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5968: अयं स कालः सम्प्राप्तो यदर्थमसि मे स्वसः |` | "This is that time which has arrived, for which purpose you are my sister," |
| `Line 5969: जरत्कारोः पुरा दत्ता सा त्राह्यस्मान्सबान्धवान् ||२४||` | "Given earlier to Jaratkaru. May she save us along with our relatives. ||24||" |
| `Line 5970: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5971: आस्तीकः किल यज्ञं तं वर्तन्तं भुजगोत्तमे |` | "Astika [sage son] will indeed stop that sacrifice proceeding against the best of serpents [nagas]," |
| `Line 5972: प्रतिषेत्स्यति मां पूर्वं स्वयमाह पितामहः ||२५||` | "Pitamaha [Brahma] himself told me earlier. ||25||" |
| `Line 5973: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5974: तद्वत्से ब्रूहि वत्सं स्वं कुमारं वृद्धसंमतम् |` | "Therefore, dear one [daughter], tell your son, the youth respected by the elders," |
| `Line 5975: ममाद्य त्वं सभृत्यस्य मोक्षार्थं वेदवित्तमम् ||२६||` | "For the liberation of me and my servants today, O most knowledgeable in the Vedas. ||26||" |
| `Line 5976: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5977: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5978: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5979: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5980: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5981: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5982: ४९` | "49 [chapter number]" |
| `Line 5983: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5984: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5985: सूत उवाच||` | "Suta [bard/narrator] said:" |
| `Line 5986: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5987: तत आहूय पुत्रं स्वं जरत्कारुर्भुजङ्गमा |` | "Then Jaratkaaru [serpent woman], the serpent, having called her son," |
| `Line 5988: वासुकेर्नागराजस्य वचनादिदमब्रवीत् ||१||` | "Spoke these words at the command of Vaasuki [serpent king], the king of serpents. ||1||" |
| `Line 5989: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5990: अहं तव पितुः पुत्र भ्रात्रा दत्ता निमित्ततः |` | "O son, I was given to your father by my brother for a specific purpose," |
| `Line 5991: कालः स चायं सम्प्राप्तस्तत्कुरुष्व यथातथम् ||२||` | "And that time has now arrived; therefore, do what must be done. ||2||" |
| `Line 5992: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5993: आस्तीक उवाच||` | "Aastika [sage's name] said:" |
| `Line 5994: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5995: किंनिमित्तं मम पितुर्दत्ता त्वं मातुलेन मे |` | "For what purpose were you given to my father by my maternal uncle?" |
| `Line 5996: तन्ममाचक्ष्व तत्त्वेन श्रुत्वा कर्तास्मि तत्तथा ||३||` | "Tell me this truthfully; after hearing it, I shall act accordingly. ||3||" |
| `Line 5997: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 5998: सूत उवाच||` | "Suta [bard/narrator] said:" |
| `Line 5999: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 6000: तत आचष्ट सा तस्मै बान्धवानां हितैषिणी |` | "Then she, who desired the welfare of her relatives, told him," |
| `Line 6001: भगिनी नागराजस्य जरत्कारुरविक्लवा ||४||` | "The sister of the Nāga-king [serpent ruler], the steadfast Jaratkāru. ||4||" |
| `Line 6002: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 6003: भुजगानामशेषाणां माता कद्रूरिति श्रुतिः |` | "Kadrū is known as the mother of all the serpents [snake beings]," |
| `Line 6004: तया शप्ता रुषितया सुता यस्मान्निबोध तत् ||५||` | "By her, enraged, her sons were cursed - hear the reason why. ||5||" |
| `Line 6005: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 6006: उच्छैःश्रवाः सोऽश्वराजो यन्मिथ्या न कृतो मम |` | "Because Uchchaihshravas, that king of horses [divine steed], was not falsely represented for me," |
| `Line 6007: विनतानिमित्तं पणिते दासभावाय पुत्रकाः ||६||` | "In the wager with Vinatā, you, my sons, were reduced to slavery. ||6||" |
| `Line 6008: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 6009: जनमेजयस्य वो यज्ञे धक्ष्यत्यनिलसारथिः |` | "In Janamejaya's sacrifice, the fire [wind-charioteer] shall consume you," |
| `Line 6010: तत्र पञ्चत्वमापन्नाः प्रेतलोकं गमिष्यथ ||७||` | "There, meeting your end, you shall go to the world of the dead [afterlife realm]. ||7||" |
| `Line 6011: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 6012: तां च शप्तवतीमेवं साक्षाल्लोकपितामहः |` | "And to her who had pronounced this curse, the Grandfather of the worlds [Brahmā] himself," |
| `Line 6013: एवमस्त्विति तद्वाक्यं प्रोवाचानुमुमोद च ||८||` | "Said 'So be it,' confirming her words with his approval. ||8||" |
| `Line 6014: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 6015: वासुकिश्चापि तच्छ्रुत्वा पितामहवचस्तदा |` | "And Vāsuki, having heard these words of the Grandfather [Brahmā]," |
| `Line 6016: अमृते मथिते तात देवाञ्शरणमीयिवान् ||९||` | "When the nectar [immortality elixir] was churned, O dear one, sought refuge with the gods. ||9||" |
| `Line 6017: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 6018: सिद्धार्थाश्च सुराः सर्वे प्राप्यामृतमनुत्तमम् |` | "And all the gods, having achieved their purpose by obtaining the supreme nectar," |
| `Line 6019: भ्रातरं मे पुरस्कृत्य प्रजापतिमुपागमन् ||१०||` | "Placing my brother at their head, approached Prajāpati [creation lord]. ||10||" |
| `Line 6020: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 6021: ते तं प्रसादयामासुर्देवाः सर्वे पितामहम् |` | "All those gods propitiated the Grandfather [Brahmā]," |
| `Line 6022: राज्ञा वासुकिना सार्धं स शापो न भवेदिति ||११||` | "Along with King Vāsuki, (praying) that the curse might not come to pass. ||11||" |
| `Line 6023: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 6024: वासुकिर्नागराजोऽयं दुःखितो ज्ञातिकारणात् |` | "This Vāsuki, king of serpents [Nāga ruler], distressed for the sake of his kinsmen," |
| `Line 6025: अभिशापः स मात्रास्य भगवन्न भवेदिति ||१२||` | "(Pleaded) 'O Lord, may the curse of his mother not come to pass.' ||12||" |
| `Line 6026: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 6027: ब्रह्मोवाच॥` | "Brahma [creator deity] said:" |
| `Line 6028: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 6029: जरत्कारुर्जरत्कारुं यां भार्यां समवाप्स्यति |` | "The Jaratkaru [sage's name] who will obtain Jaratkaru [female counterpart] as his wife," |
| `Line 6030: तत्र जातो द्विजः शापाद्भुजगान्मोक्षयिष्यति ॥१३॥` | "The twice-born [brahmin] born from that union will free the serpents from the curse. ||13||" |
| `Line 6031: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 6032: जरत्कारुरुवाच॥` | "Jaratkaru [mother] said:" |
| `Line 6033: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 6034: एतच्छ्रुत्वा तु वचनं वासुकिः पन्नगेश्वरः |` | "Having heard these words, Vasuki [serpent king], the lord of serpents," |
| `Line 6035: प्रादान्माममरप्रख्य तव पित्रे महात्मने ॥१४॥` | "Gave me to your noble father, who was like an immortal. ||14||" |
| `Line 6036: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 6037: प्रागेवानागते काले तत्र त्वं मय्यजायथाः ॥१४॥` | "Before the appointed time arrived, you were born to me. ||14||" |
| `Line 6038: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 6039: अयं स कालः सम्प्राप्तो भयान्नस्त्रातुमर्हसि |` | "Now that time has arrived; you should save us from this fear," |
| `Line 6040: भ्रातरं चैव मे तस्मात्त्रातुमर्हसि पावकात् ॥१५॥` | "And you should save my brother from that fire [sacrificial fire]. ||15||" |
| `Line 6041: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 6042: अमोघं नः कृतं तत्स्याद्यदहं तव धीमते |` | "Let our efforts not be in vain, that I was given to your wise," |
| `Line 6043: पित्रे दत्ता विमोक्षार्थं कथं वा पुत्र मन्यसे ॥१६॥` | "Father for the purpose of liberation. What do you think, my son? ||16||" |
| `Line 6044: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 6045: सूत उवाच॥` | "Suta [bard/narrator] said:" |
| `Line 6046: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 6047: एवमुक्तस्तथेत्युक्त्वा सोऽस्तीको मातरं तदा |` | "Having been thus addressed, Astika [sage's name] said 'So be it' to his mother then," |
| `Line 6048: अब्रवीद्दुःखसन्तप्तं वासुकिं जीवयन्निव ॥१७॥` | "And spoke to the grief-stricken Vasuki, as if giving him new life. ||17||" |
| `Line 6049: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 6050: अहं त्वां मोक्षयिष्यामि वासुके पन्नगोत्तम |` | "I will free you, O Vasuki, best of serpents," |
| `Line 6051: तस्माच्छापान्महासत्त्व सत्यमेतद्ब्रवीमि ते ||१८||` | "Therefore, O mighty one [great-souled being], I tell you truly about this curse. ||18||" |
| `Line 6052: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 6053: भव स्वस्थमना नाग न हि ते विद्यते भयम् |` | "Be at ease in your mind, O Nāga [serpent lord], for you have nothing to fear." |
| `Line 6054: प्रयतिष्ये तथा सौम्य यथा श्रेयो भविष्यति ||१९||` | "I shall strive, O gentle one, so that good will come of it. ||19||" |
| `Line 6055: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 6056: न मे वागनृतं प्राह स्वैरेष्वपि कुतोऽन्यथा ||१९||` | "My words have never spoken falsehood, even in jest, how then otherwise? ||19||" |
| `Line 6057: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 6058: तं वै नृपवरं गत्वा दीक्षितं जनमेजयम् |` | "Going to that excellent king, the initiated Janamejaya [snake-sacrifice performer]," |
| `Line 6059: वाग्भिर्मङ्गलयुक्ताभिस्तोषयिष्येऽद्य मातुल ||२०||` | "I shall please him today with auspicious words, O maternal uncle. ||20||" |
| `Line 6060: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 6061: यथा स यज्ञो नृपतेर्निर्वर्तिष्यति सत्तम ||२०||` | "So that the sacrifice of the king will be completed, O best of beings. ||20||" |
| `Line 6062: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 6063: स सम्भावय नागेन्द्र मयि सर्वं महामते |` | "Therefore, O lord of serpents [Nāga-king], trust everything in me, O great-minded one." |
| `Line 6064: न ते मयि मनो जातु मिथ्या भवितुमर्हति ||२१||` | "Your trust in me should never prove false. ||21||" |
| `Line 6065: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 6066: वासुकिरुवाच||` | "Vāsuki said:" |
| `Line 6067: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 6068: आस्तीक परिघूर्णामि हृदयं मे विदीर्यते |` | "Āstīka, I am reeling, my heart is breaking," |
| `Line 6069: दिशश्च न प्रजानामि ब्रह्मदण्डनिपीडितः ||२२||` | "I cannot discern the directions, oppressed by Brahmā's punishment [divine curse]. ||22||" |
| `Line 6070: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 6071: आस्तीक उवाच||` | "Āstīka said:" |
| `Line 6072: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 6073: न सन्तापस्त्वया कार्यः कथञ्चित्पन्नगोत्तम |` | "You should not grieve in any way, O best of serpents [snake-lord]," |
| `Line 6074: दीप्तादग्नेः समुत्पन्नं नाशयिष्यामि ते भयम् ||२३||` | "I shall destroy your fear arising from the blazing fire [sacrificial flames]. ||23||" |
| `Line 6075: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 6076: ब्रह्मदण्डं महाघोरं कालाग्निसमतेजसम् |` | "The terrifying Brahmā's punishment [divine curse], with radiance equal to the fire of cosmic dissolution [world-ending flame]," |
| `Line 6077: नाशयिष्यामि मात्र त्वं भयं कार्षीः कथञ्चन ||२४||` | "I shall destroy it; do not fear in any way whatsoever. ||24||" |
| `Line 6078: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 6079: सूत उवाच||` | "Sūta [bard-narrator] said:" |
| `Line 6080: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 6081: ततः स वासुकेर्घोरमपनीय मनोज्वरम् |` | "Then, having removed the terrible mental anguish of Vāsuki [serpent king]," |
| `Line 6082: आधाय चात्मनोऽङ्गेषु जगाम त्वरितो भृशम् ||२५||` | "And taking (the burden) upon his own limbs, he departed in great haste. ||25||" |
| `Line 6083: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 6084: जनमेजयस्य तं यज्ञं सर्वैः समुदितं गुणैः |` | "To Janamejaya's sacrifice, complete with all excellent qualities," |
| `Line 6085: मोक्षाय भुजगेन्द्राणामास्तीको द्विजसत्तमः ||२६||` | "For the liberation of the serpent lords [nāga chiefs], went Āstīka, best of the twice-born [brahmin sage]. ||26||" |
| `Line 6086: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 6087: स गत्वापश्यदास्तीको यज्ञायतनमुत्तमम् |` | "Going there, Āstīka beheld the excellent sacrificial arena," |
| `Line 6088: वृतं सदस्यैर्बहुभिः सूर्यवह्निसमप्रभैः ||२७||` | "Surrounded by many priests [ritual experts] with radiance equal to the sun and fire. ||27||" |
| `Line 6089: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 6090: स तत्र वारितो द्वाःस्थैः प्रविशन्द्विजसत्तमः |` | "There, though stopped by the doorkeepers, the best of the twice-born [brahmin sage] entered," |
| `Line 6091: अभितुष्टाव तं यज्ञं प्रवेशार्थी द्विजोत्तमः ||२८||` | "And began to praise that sacrifice, the excellent brahmin desiring entry. ||28||" |
| `Line 6092: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 6093: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 6094: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 6095: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 6096: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 6097: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 6098: ५०` | "50 [chapter number]" |
| `Line 6099: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 6100: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 6101: आस्तीक उवाच||` | "Āstīka said:" |
| `Line 6102: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 6103: सोमस्य यज्ञो वरुणस्य यज्ञः; प्रजापतेर्यज्ञ आसीत्प्रयागे |` | "The sacrifice of Soma [moon deity], the sacrifice of Varuṇa [water deity]; the sacrifice of Prajāpati [creation lord] was at Prayāga [sacred confluence]." |
| `Line 6104: तथा यज्ञोऽयं तव भारताग्र्य; पारिक्षित स्वस्ति नोऽस्तु प्रियेभ्यः ||१||` | "So is this sacrifice of yours, O foremost of Bharatas [Kuru dynasty]; O Pārīkṣita [Parikshit's son], may there be well-being for our dear ones. ||1||" |
| `Line 6105: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 6106: शक्रस्य यज्ञः शतसङ्ख्य उक्त; स्तथापरस्तुल्यसङ्ख्यः शतं वै |` | "The sacrifices of Śakra [Indra] are said to number a hundred; likewise another hundred of equal number indeed." |
| `Line 6107: तथा यज्ञोऽयं तव भारताग्र्य; पारिक्षित स्वस्ति नोऽस्तु प्रियेभ्यः ||२||` | "So is this sacrifice of yours, O foremost of Bharatas [Kuru dynasty]; O Pārīkṣita [Parikshit's son], may there be well-being for our dear ones. ||2||" |
| `Line 6108: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 6109: यमस्य यज्ञो हरिमेधसश्च; यथा यज्ञो रन्तिदेवस्य राज्ञः |` | "The sacrifice of Yama [death deity] and of Harimedhasa [sage]; like the sacrifice of King Rantideva [legendary king]." |
| `Line 6110: तथा यज्ञोऽयं तव भारताग्र्य; पारिक्षित स्वस्ति नोऽस्तु प्रियेभ्यः ||३||` | "So is this sacrifice of yours, O foremost of Bharatas [Kuru dynasty]; O Pārīkṣita [Parikshit's son], may there be well-being for our dear ones. ||3||" |
| `Line 6111: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 6112: गयस्य यज्ञः शशबिन्दोश्च राज्ञो; यज्ञस्तथा वैश्रवणस्य राज्ञः |` | "The sacrifice of Gaya [royal sage] and of King Śaśabindu [ancient king]; likewise the sacrifice of King Vaiśravaṇa [Kubera]." |
| `Line 6113: तथा यज्ञोऽयं तव भारताग्र्य; पारिक्षित स्वस्ति नोऽस्तु प्रियेभ्यः ||४||` | "So is this sacrifice of yours, O foremost of Bharatas [Kuru dynasty]; O Pārīkṣita [Parikshit's son], may there be well-being for our dear ones. ||4||" |
| `Line 6114: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 6115: नृगस्य यज्ञस्त्वजमीढस्य चासी; द्यथा यज्ञो दाशरथेश्च राज्ञः |` | "The sacrifice of Nṛga [ancient king] and of Ajamīḍha [Kuru ancestor] was; like the sacrifice of King Dāśaratha [Rama's father]." |
| `Line 6116: तथा यज्ञोऽयं तव भारताग्र्य; पारिक्षित स्वस्ति नोऽस्तु प्रियेभ्यः ||५||` | "Likewise is this sacrifice of yours, O foremost of Bharatas [Kuru dynasty]; O Pārīkṣita [Janamejaya], may there be well-being for our loved ones. ||5||" |
| `Line 6117: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 6118: यज्ञः श्रुतो नो दिवि देवसूनो; र्युधिष्ठिरस्याजमीढस्य राज्ञः |` | "We have heard of the sacrifice in heaven of the son of gods [Yudhiṣṭhira], the king of Ajamīḍha's line [Kuru dynasty]," |
| `Line 6119: तथा यज्ञोऽयं तव भारताग्र्य; पारिक्षित स्वस्ति नोऽस्तु प्रियेभ्यः ||६||` | "Likewise is this sacrifice of yours, O foremost of Bharatas [Kuru dynasty]; O Pārīkṣita [Janamejaya], may there be well-being for our loved ones. ||6||" |
| `Line 6120: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 6121: कृष्णस्य यज्ञः सत्यवत्याः सुतस्य; स्वयं च कर्म प्रचकार यत्र |` | "The sacrifice of Krishna [Vyāsa], the son of Satyavatī, where he himself performed the rituals," |
| `Line 6122: तथा यज्ञोऽयं तव भारताग्र्य; पारिक्षित स्वस्ति नोऽस्तु प्रियेभ्यः ||७||` | "Likewise is this sacrifice of yours, O foremost of Bharatas [Kuru dynasty]; O Pārīkṣita [Janamejaya], may there be well-being for our loved ones. ||7||" |
| `Line 6123: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 6124: इमे हि ते सूर्यहुताशवर्चसः; समासते वृत्रहणः क्रतुं यथा |` | "These priests with radiance like the sun and fire are seated here, as at the sacrifice of Vṛtrahana [Indra, slayer of Vṛtra]," |
| `Line 6125: नैषां ज्ञानं विद्यते ज्ञातुमद्य; दत्तं येभ्यो न प्रणश्येत्कथञ्चित् ||८||` | "Their knowledge cannot be fully comprehended today; what is given to them would never perish in any way. ||8||" |
| `Line 6126: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 6127: ऋत्विक्समो नास्ति लोकेषु चैव; द्वैपायनेनेति विनिश्चितं मे |` | "There is none in the worlds equal to the priest [ritual officiant] Dvaipāyana [Vyāsa]; this is my firm conviction," |
| `Line 6128: एतस्य शिष्या हि क्षितिं चरन्ति; सर्वर्त्विजः कर्मसु स्वेषु दक्षाः ||९||` | "His disciples indeed walk the earth; all priests [ritual officiants] are skilled in their respective duties. ||9||" |
| `Line 6129: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 6130: विभावसुश्चित्रभानुर्महात्मा; हिरण्यरेता विश्वभुक्कृष्णवर्त्मा |` | "Vibhāvasu [fire deity], the brilliantly radiant great soul, Hiraṇyaretā [golden-seed fire], the all-consuming one with the dark path," |
| `Line 6131: प्रदक्षिणावर्तशिखः प्रदीप्तो; हव्यं तवेदं हुतभुग्वष्टि देवः ||१०||` | "With flames spiraling clockwise, blazing brightly; this god Hutabhug [fire deity] desires your oblation. ||10||" |
| `Line 6132: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 6133: नेह त्वदन्यो विद्यते जीवलोके; समो नृपः पालयिता प्रजानाम् |` | "There exists no king in this world of the living equal to you as a protector of subjects," |
| `Line 6134: धृत्या च ते प्रीतमनाः सदाहं; त्वं वा राजा धर्मराजो यमो वा ||११||` | "I am always pleased with your steadfastness; you are either a king, Dharmarāja [Yudhiṣṭhira], or Yama [death god] himself. ||11||" |
| `Line 6135: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 6136: शक्रः साक्षाद्वज्रपाणिर्यथेह; त्राता लोकेऽस्मिंस्त्वं तथेह प्रजानाम् |` | "As Śakra [Indra] himself, the wielder of the thunderbolt, is here; so are you the protector of the people in this world." |
| `Line 6137: मतस्त्वं नः पुरुषेन्द्रेह लोके; न च त्वदन्यो गृहपतिरस्ति यज्ञे ||१२||` | "You are regarded by us as the foremost among men in this world; and there is no host of the sacrifice other than you. ||12||" |
| `Line 6138: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 6139: खट्वाङ्गनाभागदिलीपकल्पो; ययातिमान्धातृसमप्रभावः |` | "You are equal to Khaṭvāṅga [royal sage], Nābhāga [virtuous king], and Dilīpa [legendary king]; with power comparable to Yayāti [ancient king] and Māndhātṛ [sovereign king]." |
| `Line 6140: आदित्यतेजःप्रतिमानतेजा; भीष्मो यथा भ्राजसि सुव्रतस्त्वम् ||१३||` | "With radiance equal to the splendor of the sun; you shine like Bhīṣma [Kuru elder], steadfast in your vows. ||13||" |
| `Line 6141: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 6142: वाल्मीकिवत्ते निभृतं सुधैर्यं; वसिष्ठवत्ते नियतश्च कोपः |` | "Your composure and steadfastness are like Vālmīki's [sage poet]; your anger is controlled like Vasiṣṭha's [royal priest]." |
| `Line 6143: प्रभुत्वमिन्द्रेण समं मतं मे; द्युतिश्च नारायणवद्विभाति ||१४||` | "Your lordship is, I believe, equal to Indra's [king of gods]; and your splendor shines like Nārāyaṇa's [Vishnu]. ||14||" |
| `Line 6144: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 6145: यमो यथा धर्मविनिश्चयज्ञः; कृष्णो यथा सर्वगुणोपपन्नः |` | "Like Yama [death deity], you are knowledgeable in determining dharma [righteousness]; like Kṛṣṇa [divine hero], you are endowed with all virtues." |
| `Line 6146: श्रियां निवासोऽसि यथा वसूनां; निधानभूतोऽसि तथा क्रतूनाम् ||१५||` | "You are the abode of wealth like the Vasus [wealth deities]; you are the repository of sacrificial rites. ||15||" |
| `Line 6147: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 6148: दम्भोद्भवेनासि समो बलेन; रामो यथा शस्त्रविदस्त्रविच्च |` | "In strength, you are equal to Dambhodbhava [mighty king]; like Rāma [warrior prince], you are skilled in weapons and missiles." |
| `Line 6149: और्वत्रिताभ्यामसि तुल्यतेजा; दुष्प्रेक्षणीयोऽसि भगीरथो वा ||१६||` | "You have radiance equal to Aurva [fire-sage] and Trita [Vedic deity]; you are as magnificent to behold as Bhagīratha [Ganga-bringer]. ||16||" |
| `Line 6150: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 6151: सूत उवाच||` | "Sūta [bard-sage] said:" |
| `Line 6152: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 6153: एवं स्तुताः सर्व एव प्रसन्ना; राजा सदस्या ऋत्विजो हव्यवाहः |` | "Thus praised, all became pleased - the king, the assembly members, the priests, and Havyavāha [fire deity]." |
| `Line 6154: तेषां दृष्ट्वा भावितानीङ्गितानि; प्रोवाच राजा जनमेजयोऽथ ||१७||` | "Seeing their pleased expressions, King Janamejaya [snake-sacrifice performer] then spoke. ||17||" |
| `Line 6155: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 6156: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 6157: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 6158: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 6159: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 6160: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 6161: ५१` | "51 [chapter number]" |
| `Line 6162: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 6163: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 6164: जनमेजय उवाच||` | "Janamejaya [snake-sacrifice king] said:" |
| `Line 6165: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 6166: बालो वाक्यं स्थविर इव प्रभाषते; नायं बालः स्थविरोऽयं मतो मे |` | "This youth speaks words like an elder; I do not consider him a child but an elder." |
| `Line 6167: इच्छाम्यहं वरमस्मै प्रदातुं; तन्मे विप्रा वितरध्वं समेताः ||१||` | "I wish to grant him a boon; O assembled Brahmins [priests], allow me to bestow it. ||1||" |
| `Line 6168: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 6169: सदस्या ऊचुः||` | "The assembly members said:" |
| `Line 6170: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 6171: बालोऽपि विप्रो मान्य एवेह राज्ञां; यश्चाविद्वान्यश्च विद्वान्यथावत् |` | "Even a young Brahmin [priest] is worthy of respect from kings; whether he is unlearned or learned as he should be." |
| `Line 6172: सर्वान्कामांस्त्वत्त एषोऽर्हतेऽद्य; यथा च नस्तक्षक एति शीघ्रम् ||२||` | "He deserves all desires from you today; and may Takshaka [serpent king] come to us quickly. ||2||" |
| `Line 6173: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 6174: सूत उवाच||` | "Sūta [bard-sage] said:" |
| `Line 6175: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 6176: व्याहर्तुकामे वरदे नृपे द्विजं; वरं वृणीष्वेति ततोऽभ्युवाच |` | "As the king, the bestower of boons, was about to speak to the Brahmin, saying 'Choose a boon,' then..." |
| `Line 6177: होता वाक्यं नातिहृष्टान्तरात्मा; कर्मण्यस्मिंस्तक्षको नैति तावत् ||३||` | "The hotā [chief priest] spoke these words, with a not-too-pleased heart: 'In this sacrifice, Takṣaka [serpent king] has not yet come.' ||3||" |
| `Line 6178: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 6179: जनमेजय उवाच||` | "Janamejaya [snake-sacrifice performer] said:" |
| `Line 6180: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 6181: यथा चेदं कर्म समाप्यते मे; यथा च नस्तक्षक एति शीघ्रम् |` | "So that this sacrifice of mine may be completed; and so that Takṣaka may come to us quickly," |
| `Line 6182: तथा भवन्तः प्रयतन्तु सर्वे; परं शक्त्या स हि मे विद्विषाणः ||४||` | "Let all of you strive with your utmost power; for he is my bitter enemy. ||4||" |
| `Line 6183: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 6184: ऋत्विज ऊचुः||` | "The priests said:" |
| `Line 6185: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 6186: यथा शास्त्राणि नः प्राहुर्यथा शंसति पावकः |` | "According to what the scriptures tell us, and as the fire [Agni] proclaims," |
| `Line 6187: इन्द्रस्य भवने राजंस्तक्षको भयपीडितः ||५||` | "Takṣaka, stricken with fear, is in Indra's [king of gods] abode, O king. ||5||" |
| `Line 6188: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 6189: सूत उवाच||` | "Sūta [bard-sage] said:" |
| `Line 6190: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 6191: यथा सूतो लोहिताक्षो महात्मा; पौराणिको वेदितवान्पुरस्तात् |` | "As the noble red-eyed Sūta [royal chronicler], the knower of ancient lore, had known beforehand," |
| `Line 6192: स राजानं प्राह पृष्टस्तदानीं; यथाहुर्विप्रास्तद्वदेतन्नृदेव ||६||` | "He, when asked, then told the king: 'What the Brahmins say is true, O lord of men. ||6||'" |
| `Line 6193: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 6194: पुराणमागम्य ततो ब्रवीम्यहं; दत्तं तस्मै वरमिन्द्रेण राजन् |` | "Based on the Purāṇas [ancient texts], I tell you this: Indra has given him a boon, O king," |
| `Line 6195: वसेह त्वं मत्सकाशे सुगुप्तो; न पावकस्त्वां प्रदहिष्यतीति ||७||` | "'Stay here with me, well-protected; the fire shall not burn you.' ||7||" |
| `Line 6196: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 6197: एतच्छ्रुत्वा दीक्षितस्तप्यमान; आस्ते होतारं चोदयन्कर्मकाले |` | "Hearing this, the consecrated one [king], burning with anticipation, sat urging the hotā [chief priest] at the time of ritual." |
| `Line 6198: होता च यत्तः स जुहाव मन्त्रै; रथो इन्द्रः स्वयमेवाजगाम ||८||` | "And the attentive hotā [chief priest] made offerings with mantras; then Indra [king of gods] himself came in his chariot. ||8||" |
| `Line 6199: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 6200: विमानमारुह्य महानुभावः; सर्वैर्देवैः परिसंस्तूयमानः |` | "The mighty one [Indra], mounted on his celestial vehicle, being praised by all the gods," |
| `Line 6201: बलाहकैश्चाप्यनुगम्यमानो; विद्याधरैरप्सरसां गणैश्च ||९||` | "And followed by clouds, Vidyādharas [knowledge-bearers], and groups of Apsarās [celestial nymphs]. ||9||" |
| `Line 6202: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 6203: तस्योत्तरीये निहितः स नागो; भयोद्विग्नः शर्म नैवाभ्यगच्छत् |` | "That serpent [Takshaka], hidden in his [Indra's] upper garment, terrified with fear, found no peace." |
| `Line 6204: ततो राजा मन्त्रविदोऽब्रवीत्पुनः; क्रुद्धो वाक्यं तक्षकस्यान्तमिच्छन् ||१०||` | "Then the king, desiring Takshaka's end, spoke again angrily to the mantra-knowers [priests]. ||10||" |
| `Line 6205: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 6206: इन्द्रस्य भवने विप्रा यदि नागः स तक्षकः |` | "O Brahmins [priests], if that serpent Takshaka is in Indra's abode," |
| `Line 6207: तमिन्द्रेणैव सहितं पातयध्वं विभावसौ ||११||` | "Make him fall into the fire [sacrificial flame] together with Indra himself. ||11||" |
| `Line 6208: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 6209: ऋत्विज ऊचुः||` | "The priests said:" |
| `Line 6210: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 6211: अयमायाति वै तूर्णं तक्षकस्ते वशं नृप |` | "O king, Takshaka is quickly coming under your control." |
| `Line 6212: श्रूयतेऽस्य महान्नादो रुवतो भैरवं भयात् ||१२||` | "His loud, terrifying cry can be heard as he roars from fear. ||12||" |
| `Line 6213: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 6214: नूनं मुक्तो वज्रभृता स नागो; भ्रष्टश्चाङ्कान्मन्त्रविस्रस्तकायः |` | "Surely that serpent has been released by the thunderbolt-bearer [Indra], falling from his lap, his body loosened by the mantras." |
| `Line 6215: घूर्णन्नाकाशे नष्टसञ्ज्ञोऽभ्युपैति; तीव्रान्निःश्वासान्निःश्वसन्पन्नगेन्द्रः ||१३||` | "The lord of serpents approaches, whirling in the sky, unconscious, breathing heavy breaths. ||13||" |
| `Line 6216: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 6217: वर्तते तव राजेन्द्र कर्मैतद्विधिवत्प्रभो |` | "This sacrifice of yours, O Rājendra [king of kings], is proceeding according to the proper rituals, O lord." |
| `Line 6218: अस्मै तु द्विजमुख्याय वरं त्वं दातुमर्हसि ||१४||` | "But to this foremost of Brahmins [dvija-mukhya], you should grant a boon. ||14||" |
| `Line 6219: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 6220: जनमेजय उवाच||` | "Janamejaya [snake-sacrifice performer] said:" |
| `Line 6221: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 6222: बालाभिरूपस्य तवाप्रमेय; वरं प्रयच्छामि यथानुरूपम् |` | "To you, who are young and handsome, O immeasurable one, I shall grant a suitable boon." |
| `Line 6223: वृणीष्व यत्तेऽभिमतं हृदि स्थितं; तत्ते प्रदास्याम्यपि चेददेयम् ||१५||` | "Choose whatever you desire, that which is in your heart; I shall grant it to you, even if it is something that should not be given. ||15||" |
| `Line 6224: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 6225: सूत उवाच||` | "Sūta [bard-sage] said:" |
| `Line 6226: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 6227: पतिष्यमाणे नागेन्द्रे तक्षके जातवेदसि |` | "As Takṣaka, the lord of serpents [nāgendra], was about to fall into the fire [jātavedas]," |
| `Line 6228: इदमन्तरमित्येवं तदास्तीकोऽभ्यचोदयत् ||१६||` | "Thinking 'This is the opportunity,' Āstīka then urged (the king). ||16||" |
| `Line 6229: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 6230: वरं ददासि चेन्मह्यं वृणोमि जनमेजय |` | "If you grant me a boon, I choose this, O Janamejaya:" |
| `Line 6231: सत्रं ते विरमत्वेतन्न पतेयुरिहोरगाः ||१७||` | "Let this sacrifice of yours cease; let no more serpents [uragas] fall into it. ||17||" |
| `Line 6232: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 6233: एवमुक्तस्ततो राजा ब्रह्मन्पारिक्षितस्तदा |` | "Having been thus addressed, King Pārikṣita [Janamejaya], O Brahmin," |
| `Line 6234: नातिहृष्टमना वाक्यमास्तीकमिदमब्रवीत् ||१८||` | "With a not-too-pleased mind, spoke these words to Āstīka. ||18||" |
| `Line 6235: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 6236: सुवर्णं रजतं गाश्च यच्चान्यन्मन्यसे विभो |` | "Gold, silver, cows, and whatever else you desire, O mighty one [brahmin]," |
| `Line 6237: तत्ते दद्यां वरं विप्र न निवर्तेत्क्रतुर्मम ||१९||` | "I shall give you that boon, O brahmin, but my sacrifice should not cease. ||19||" |
| `Line 6238: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 6239: आस्तीक उवाच||` | "Āstīka said:" |
| `Line 6240: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 6241: सुवर्णं रजतं गाश्च न त्वां राजन्वृणोम्यहम् |` | "Gold, silver, and cows I do not choose from you, O king," |
| `Line 6242: सत्रं ते विरमत्वेतत्स्वस्ति मातृकुलस्य नः ||२०||` | "Let this sacrifice of yours cease, for the welfare of our maternal lineage [snake clan]. ||20||" |
| `Line 6243: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 6244: सूत उवाच||` | "Sūta said:" |
| `Line 6245: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 6246: आस्तीकेनैवमुक्तस्तु राजा पारिक्षितस्तदा |` | "When thus addressed by Āstīka, King Parikshit [Janamejaya's father] then," |
| `Line 6247: पुनः पुनरुवाचेदमास्तीकं वदतां वरम् ||२१||` | "Again and again said this to Āstīka, the best among speakers: ||21||" |
| `Line 6248: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 6249: अन्यं वरय भद्रं ते वरं द्विजवरोत्तम |` | "Choose another boon, good fortune to you, O best of the excellent twice-born [brahmin]," |
| `Line 6250: अयाचत न चाप्यन्यं वरं स भृगुनन्दन ||२२||` | "But he, O descendant of Bhrigu [Shaunaka], did not ask for any other boon. ||22||" |
| `Line 6251: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 6252: ततो वेदविदस्तत्र सदस्याः सर्व एव तम् |` | "Then all the Veda-knowers [priests] there, the assembly members," |
| `Line 6253: राजानमूचुः सहिता लभतां ब्राह्मणो वरम् ||२३||` | "Together said to the king: 'Let the brahmin obtain his boon.' ||23||" |
| `Line 6254: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 6255: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 6256: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 6257: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 6258: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 6259: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 6260: ५२` | "52 [chapter number]" |
| `Line 6261: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 6262: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 6263: शौनक उवाच||` | "Śaunaka [sage-questioner] said:" |
| `Line 6264: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 6265: ये सर्पाः सर्पसत्रेऽस्मिन्पतिता हव्यवाहने |` | "Those serpents [sarpas] who fell into the fire [havyavāhana] during this serpent sacrifice," |
| `Line 6266: तेषां नामानि सर्वेषां श्रोतुमिच्छामि सूतज ||१||` | "I wish to hear the names of all of them, O son of Sūta [sūtaja]. ||1||" |
| `Line 6267: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 6268: सूत उवाच||` | "Sūta [bard-sage] said:" |
| `Line 6269: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 6270: सहस्राणि बहून्यस्मिन्प्रयुतान्यर्बुदानि च |` | "Many thousands, tens of millions [prayuta], and hundreds of millions [arbuda] (of serpents)" |
| `Line 6271: न शक्यं परिसङ्ख्यातुं बहुत्वाद्वेदवित्तम ||२||` | "Cannot be counted due to their great number, O best knower of Vedas [vedavittama]. ||2||" |
| `Line 6272: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 6273: यथास्मृति तु नामानि पन्नगानां निबोध मे |` | "But listen to me as I recall the names of the serpents [pannagas]," |
| `Line 6274: उच्यमानानि मुख्यानां हुतानां जातवेदसि ||३||` | "As I recite (the names) of the chief ones who were offered into the fire [jātavedas]. ||3||" |
| `Line 6275: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 7596: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 7597: धरो ध्रुवश्च सोमश्च अहश्चैवानिलोऽनलः |` | "Dhara [earth-bearer], Dhruva [steadfast one], Soma [moon deity], Aha [day], and also Anila [wind] and Anala [fire]," |
| `Line 7598: प्रत्यूषश्च प्रभासश्च वसवोऽष्टाविति स्मृताः ||१७||` | "Pratyūṣa [dawn] and Prabhāsa [radiance] - these are remembered as the eight Vasus [divine beings]. ||17||" |
| `Line 7599: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 7600: धूम्रायाश्च धरः पुत्रो ब्रह्मविद्यो ध्रुवस्तथा |` | "Dhara is the son of Dhūmrā [smoke-colored], and similarly Dhruva is (the son) of Brahmavidyā [Vedic knowledge]," |
| `Line 7601: चन्द्रमास्तु मनस्विन्याः श्वसायाः श्वसनस्तथा ||१८||` | "Chandramās [moon] is (the son) of Manasvinī [thoughtful one], and similarly Śvasana [breath] is (the son) of Śvasā. ||18||" |
| `Line 7602: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 7603: रतायाश्चाप्यहः पुत्रः शाण्डिल्याश्च हुताशनः |` | "Aha [day] is the son of Ratā [beloved], and Hutāśana [fire-consumer] is (the son) of Śāṇḍilyā," |
| `Line 7604: प्रत्यूषश्च प्रभासश्च प्रभातायाः सुतौ स्मृतौ ||१९||` | "Pratyūṣa and Prabhāsa are remembered as the two sons of Prabhātā [dawn]. ||19||" |
| `Line 7605: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 7606: धरस्य पुत्रो द्रविणो हुतहव्यवहस्तथा |` | "Dhara's son is Draviṇa, and also Hutahavyavaha [fire-offering carrier]," |
| `Line 7607: ध्रुवस्य पुत्रो भगवान्कालो लोकप्रकालनः ||२०||` | "Dhruva's son is the illustrious Kāla [Time deity], the illuminator of worlds. ||20||" |
| `Line 7608: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 7609: सोमस्य तु सुतो वर्चा वर्चस्वी येन जायते |` | "Soma's [Moon god] son is Varchā, through whom one becomes radiant [varchasvī]," |
| `Line 7610: मनोहरायाः शिशिरः प्राणोऽथ रमणस्तथा ||२१||` | "From Manoharā [mind-captivating goddess] were born Śiśira [cool season], Prāṇa [life-breath], and Ramaṇa [delighter]. ||21||" |
| `Line 7611: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 7612: अह्नः सुतो स्मृतो ज्योतिः श्रमः शान्तस्तथा मुनिः |` | "The son of Ahan [Day] is remembered as Jyotis [light], Śrama [exertion], Śānta [peace], and Muni [sage]," |
| `Line 7613: अग्नेः पुत्रः कुमारस्तु श्रीमाञ्शरवणालयः ||२२||` | "Agni's [fire god] son is Kumāra [youth-deity], the illustrious one who dwells in reed-beds [Śaravaṇālaya]. ||22||" |
| `Line 7614: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 7615: तस्य शाखो विशाखश्च नैगमेशश्च पृष्ठजः |` | "His (Kumāra's) sons are Śākha, Viśākha, Naigameśa, and Pṛṣṭhaja [born from the back]," |
| `Line 7616: कृत्तिकाभ्युपपत्तेश्च कार्त्तिकेय इति स्मृतः ||२३||` | "And due to his association with the Kṛttikās [Pleiades stars], he is remembered as Kārttikeya [son of Kṛttikās]. ||23||" |
| `Line 7617: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 7618: अनिलस्य शिवा भार्या तस्याः पुत्रः पुरोजवः |` | "Anila's [wind god] wife is Śivā, and her son is Purojava [swift-moving]," |
| `Line 7619: अविज्ञातगतिश्चैव द्वौ पुत्रावनिलस्य तु ||२४||` | "And Avijñātagati [of unknown course] - these two are the sons of Anila. ||24||" |
| `Line 7620: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 7621: प्रत्यूषस्य विदुः पुत्रमृषिं नाम्नाथ देवलम् |` | "They know Pratyūṣa's [dawn] son as the sage named Devala [divine one]," |
| `Line 7622: द्वौ पुत्रौ देवलस्यापि क्षमावन्तौ मनीषिणौ ||२५||` | "And Devala also has two sons, both patient and wise. ||25||" |
| `Line 7623: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 7624: बृहस्पतेस्तु भगिनी वरस्त्री ब्रह्मचारिणी |` | "Bṛhaspati's [preceptor of gods] sister is an excellent woman, a celibate [brahmacharini]," |
| `Line 7625: योगसिद्धा जगत्सर्वमसक्तं विचरत्युत ||२६||` | "Accomplished in yoga, she wanders throughout the entire world, unattached. ||26||" |
| `Line 7626: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 7627: प्रभासस्य तु भार्या सा वसूनामष्टमस्य ह ||२६||` | "She is the wife of Prabhāsa [radiance], the eighth of the Vasus. ||26||" |
| `Line 7628: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 7629: विश्वकर्मा महाभागो जज्ञे शिल्पप्रजापतिः |` | "Viśvakarmā [universal architect], the illustrious one, was born as the lord of crafts [śilpa-prajāpati]," |
| `Line 7630: कर्ता शिल्पसहस्राणां त्रिदशानां च वर्धकिः ||२७||` | "The creator of thousands of crafts and the carpenter of the thirty [tridaśa] gods. ||27||" |
| `Line 7631: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 7632: भूषणानां च सर्वेषां कर्ता शिल्पवतां वरः |` | "The maker of all ornaments, the best among craftsmen," |
| `Line 7633: यो दिव्यानि विमानानि देवतानां चकार ह ||२८||` | "Who created the divine aerial chariots [vimāna] for the deities. ||28||" |
| `Line 7634: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 7635: मनुष्याश्चोपजीवन्ति यस्य शिल्पं महात्मनः |` | "Humans also live by the craft of that great-souled one," |
| `Line 7636: पूजयन्ति च यं नित्यं विश्वकर्माणमव्ययम् ||२९||` | "And they worship daily that imperishable Viśvakarmā. ||29||" |
| `Line 7637: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 7638: स्तनं तु दक्षिणं भित्त्वा ब्रह्मणो नरविग्रहः |` | "Breaking through the right breast of Brahmā [creator god], in human form," |
| `Line 7639: निःसृतो भगवान्धर्मः सर्वलोकसुखावहः ||३०||` | "Emerged the divine Dharma [righteousness], who brings happiness to all worlds. ||30||" |
| `Line 7640: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 7641: त्रयस्तस्य वराः पुत्राः सर्वभूतमनोहराः |` | "He has three excellent sons who captivate the minds of all beings:" |
| `Line 7642: शमः कामश्च हर्षश्च तेजसा लोकधारिणः ||३१||` | "Śama [tranquility], Kāma [desire], and Harṣa [joy], who sustain the worlds with their splendor. ||31||" |
| `Line 7643: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 7644: कामस्य तु रतिर्भार्या शमस्य प्राप्तिरङ्गना |` | "Kāma's wife is Rati [pleasure], Śama's wife is Prāpti [attainment]," |
| `Line 7645: नन्दी तु भार्या हर्षस्य यत्र लोकाः प्रतिष्ठिताः ||३२||` | "And Harṣa's wife is Nandī [delight], in whom the worlds are established. ||32||" |
| `Line 7646: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 7647: मरीचेः कश्यपः पुत्रः कश्यपस्य सुरासुराः |` | "Kaśyapa is the son of Marīci [light ray], and from Kaśyapa were born the gods and demons," |
| `Line 7648: जज्ञिरे नृपशार्दूल लोकानां प्रभवस्तु सः ||३३||` | "O tiger among kings [nṛpa-śārdūla], he is the progenitor of the worlds. ||33||" |
| `Line 7649: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 7650: त्वाष्ट्री तु सवितुर्भार्या वडवारूपधारिणी |` | "Tvāṣṭrī [daughter of Tvaṣṭṛ], the wife of Savitṛ [sun deity], who took the form of a mare [vaḍavā]," |
| `Line 7651: असूयत महाभागा सान्तरिक्षेऽश्विनावुभौ ||३४||` | "The illustrious one gave birth to both the Aśvins [divine twins] in the sky. ||34||" |
| `Line 7652: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 7653: द्वादशैवादितेः पुत्राः शक्रमुख्या नराधिप |` | "Aditi has twelve sons with Śakra [Indra] as their chief, O lord of men," |
| `Line 7654: तेषामवरजो विष्णुर्यत्र लोकाः प्रतिष्ठिताः ||३५||` | "The youngest among them is Viṣṇu [preserver deity], in whom the worlds are established. ||35||" |
| `Line 7655: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 7656: त्रयस्त्रिंशत इत्येते देवास्तेषामहं तव |` | "These are the thirty-three gods, and I shall now," |
| `Line 7657: अन्वयं सम्प्रवक्ष्यामि पक्षैश्च कुलतो गणान् ||३६||` | "Describe to you their lineage and groups according to their families and divisions. ||36||" |
| `Line 7658: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 7659: रुद्राणामपरः पक्षः साध्यानां मरुतां तथा |` | "There is another division of the Rudras [storm deities], as well as of the Sādhyas [celestial beings] and the Maruts [wind gods]," |
| `Line 7660: वसूनां भार्गवं विद्याद्विश्वेदेवांस्तथैव च ||३७||` | "Know the Bhārgava [descendant of Bhṛgu] to be of the Vasus [elemental deities], and likewise the Viśvedevas [universal gods]. ||37||" |
| `Line 7661: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 7662: वैनतेयस्तु गरुडो बलवानरुणस्तथा |` | "Garuḍa [divine eagle], the son of Vinatā, is mighty, and so is Aruṇa [dawn]," |
| `Line 7663: बृहस्पतिश्च भगवानादित्येष्वेव गण्यते ||३८||` | "And the divine Bṛhaspati [preceptor of gods] is counted among the Ādityas [solar deities]. ||38||" |
| `Line 7664: ` | "[Blank line]" |
| `Line 7665: अश्विभ्यां गुह्यकान्विद्धि सर्वौषध्यस्तथा पशून् |` | "Know the Guhyakas [hidden beings] to be from the Aśvins, as well as all medicinal herbs and animals." |
